63  bool force_cast;

262 /* pt_combine_compatible_info () - combine two cinfo into cinfo1
263  * return: true if compatible, else false
264  * cinfo1(in);
265  * cinfo2(in):
266  * att1(in):
267  * att2(in):
268  * index(in): for update the idx of cinfo1
269  */
270 static bool
271 pt_combine_compatible_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo1, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo2,
272  PT_NODE * att1, PT_NODE * att2, int index)
273 {
274  PT_TYPE_ENUM common_type;
275  bool is_compatible = false;
276 
277  assert (parser != NULL && cinfo1 != NULL && cinfo2 != NULL);
278  assert (att1 != NULL && att2 != NULL);
279 
280  /* init cinfo before combine */
281  if (cinfo1->idx == -1 && cinfo2->idx == -1)
282  {
283  return true;
284  }
285 
286  if (cinfo1->idx == -1)
287  {
288  cinfo1->idx = index;
289  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (att1, cinfo1);
290  }
291 
292  if (cinfo2->idx == -1)
293  {
294  cinfo2->idx = index;
295  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (att2, cinfo2);
296  }
297 
298  common_type = pt_common_type (cinfo1->type_enum, cinfo2->type_enum);
299  is_compatible = pt_update_compatible_info (parser, cinfo1, common_type, cinfo1, cinfo2);
300 
301  return is_compatible;
302 }
303 
304 /* pt_update_compatible_info () - update cinfo after get common type for cast
305  * return: true if compatible, else false
306  * cinfo(in);
307  * common_type(in):
308  * int p1, s1, p2, s2: prec1,scale1,prec2 and scale2
309  */
310 static bool
311 pt_update_compatible_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo, PT_TYPE_ENUM common_type,
312  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * att1_info, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * att2_info)
313 {
314  bool is_compatible = false;
315 
316  assert (parser != NULL && cinfo != NULL);
317  assert (att1_info != NULL && att2_info != NULL);
318 
319  switch (common_type)
320  {
321  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
322  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
323  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
324  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
325  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
326  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
327  is_compatible = true;
328 
329  if (common_type == PT_TYPE_CHAR || common_type == PT_TYPE_VARCHAR)
330  {
331  cinfo->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARCHAR;
332  }
333  else if (common_type == PT_TYPE_NCHAR || common_type == PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR)
334  {
335  cinfo->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR;
336  }
337  else
338  {
339  cinfo->type_enum = PT_TYPE_VARBIT;
340  }
341 
342  if (att1_info->prec == DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION || att2_info->prec == DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION)
343  {
344  cinfo->prec = DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION;
345  }
346  else
347  {
348  cinfo->prec = MAX (att1_info->prec, att2_info->prec);
349  if (cinfo->prec == 0)
350  {
351  cinfo->prec = DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION;
352  }
353  }
354  break;
355 
356  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
357  is_compatible = true;
358 
359  cinfo->type_enum = common_type;
360 
361  cinfo->scale = MAX (att1_info->scale, att2_info->scale);
362  cinfo->prec = MAX ((att1_info->prec - att1_info->scale), (att2_info->prec - att2_info->scale)) + cinfo->scale;
363 
364  if (cinfo->prec > DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION)
365  { /* overflow */
366  cinfo->scale -= (cinfo->prec - DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION);
367  if (cinfo->scale < 0)
368  {
369  cinfo->scale = 0;
370  }
371  cinfo->prec = DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION;
372  }
373  break;
374 
375  case PT_TYPE_SET:
376  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
377  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
378  /* NEVER try to fix set types */
379  is_compatible = true;
380  break;
381  case PT_TYPE_NONE:
382  is_compatible = false;
383  break;
384 
385  default:
386  is_compatible = true;
387  cinfo->type_enum = common_type;
388  break;
389  }
390 
391  return is_compatible;
392 }
393 
394 /* pt_values_query_to_compatible_cast () - cast select list with cinfo
395  * return:
396  * parser(in):
397  * node(in):
398  * cinfo(in):
399  */
400 static PT_NODE *
401 pt_values_query_to_compatible_cast (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo,
402  int num_cinfo)
403 {
404  PT_NODE *node_list, *result = node;
405  int i;
406  PT_NODE *attrs, *att;
407  PT_NODE *prev_att, *next_att, *new_att = NULL;
408  bool new_cast_added;
409  bool need_to_cast;
410  PT_NODE_LIST_INFO *cur_node_list_info;
411  bool is_select_data_type_set = false;
412 
413  assert (parser != NULL && node != NULL && cinfo != NULL);
414  assert (node->node_type == PT_SELECT && PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (node));
415 
416  node_list = node->info.query.q.select.list;
417  assert (node_list);
418 
419  for (; node_list; node_list = node_list->next)
420  {
421  cur_node_list_info = &node_list->info.node_list;
422  attrs = cur_node_list_info->list;
423 
424  prev_att = NULL;
425  for (att = attrs, i = 0; i < num_cinfo && att != NULL; ++i, att = next_att)
426  {
427  bool is_cast_allowed = true;
428 
429  new_cast_added = false;
430  next_att = att->next;
431  need_to_cast = false;
432  if (cinfo[i].idx == i)
433  {
434  if (!pt_is_compatible_without_cast (parser, &(cinfo[i]), att, &is_cast_allowed))
435  {
436  need_to_cast = true;
437  if ((PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (att->type_enum) || att->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC)
438  && att->data_type == NULL)
439  {
440  result = NULL;
441  goto end;
442  }
443  }
444  }
445 
446  if (need_to_cast)
447  {
448  if (!is_cast_allowed)
449  {
450  result = NULL;
451  goto end;
452  }
453 
454  new_att = pt_make_cast_with_compatible_info (parser, att, next_att, cinfo + i, &new_cast_added);
455  if (new_att == NULL)
456  {
457  goto out_of_mem;
458  }
459 
460  if (new_cast_added)
461  {
462  att = new_att;
463  }
464 
465  if (prev_att == NULL)
466  {
467  cur_node_list_info->list = att;
468  if (is_select_data_type_set == false)
469  {
470  node->type_enum = att->type_enum;
471  if (node->data_type)
472  {
473  parser_free_tree (parser, node->data_type);
474  }
475  node->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, att->data_type);
476  is_select_data_type_set = true;
477  }
478  }
479  else
480  {
481  prev_att->next = att;
482  }
483  }
484  prev_att = att;
485  }
486  }
487 
488 end:
489  return result;
490 
491 out_of_mem:
492  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
493  return NULL;
494 }
495 
496 /*
497  * pt_get_compatible_info () -
498  * return: return a pointer of SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO array or null on error
499  * parser(in): parser context
500  * node(in): values query node or union
501  * select_list1(in):
502  * select_list2(in):
503  * need_cast(in/out):
504  * current_row(in): for value query error info
505  * note: the return pointer must be freed by free_and_init
506  */
507 static SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *
508 pt_get_compatible_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_NODE * select_list1, PT_NODE * select_list2,
509  bool * need_cast)
510 {
511  PT_NODE *att1, *att2, *p, *q;
512  PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE compatible;
513  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo = NULL, *result = NULL;
514  bool is_object_type;
515  int i, k;
516  int cnt1, cnt2;
517  bool need_cast_tmp = false;
518 
519  assert (parser != NULL && node != NULL && select_list1 != NULL && select_list2 != NULL && need_cast != NULL);
520 
521  *need_cast = false;
522 
523  p = select_list1;
524  q = select_list2;
525 
526  if (p->node_type == PT_NODE_LIST)
527  {
528  assert (q->node_type == PT_NODE_LIST);
529 
530  select_list1 = p->info.node_list.list;
531  select_list2 = q->info.node_list.list;
532  }
533 
534  cnt1 = pt_length_of_select_list (select_list1, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
535  cnt2 = pt_length_of_select_list (select_list2, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
536 
537  if (cnt1 != cnt2)
538  {
539  if (select_list1->node_type == PT_NODE_LIST)
540  {
541  PT_ERRORmf4 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ARITY_OF_VALUES_CLAUSE_MISMATCH, cnt1,
542  pt_short_print (parser, p), cnt2, pt_short_print (parser, q));
543  }
544  else
545  {
546  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, select_list1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ARITY_MISMATCH, cnt1, cnt2);
547  }
548  goto end;
549  }
550 
551  /* compare the columns */
552  for (i = 0, att1 = select_list1, att2 = select_list2; i < cnt1; ++i, att1 = att1->next, att2 = att2->next)
553  {
554  compatible = pt_union_compatible (parser, att1, att2, false, &is_object_type);
555  if (compatible == PT_UNION_INCOMP)
556  {
557  /* alloc compatible info array */
558  if (cinfo == NULL)
559  {
560  cinfo = (SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *) malloc (cnt1 * sizeof (SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO));
561  if (cinfo == NULL)
562  {
563  goto out_of_mem;
564  }
565 
566  for (k = 0; k < cnt1; ++k)
567  {
568  cinfo[k].idx = -1;
569  cinfo[k].type_enum = PT_TYPE_NONE;
570  cinfo[k].prec = DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION;
571  cinfo[k].scale = DB_DEFAULT_SCALE;
572  cinfo[k].force_cast = false;
573  cinfo[k].coll_infer.coll_id = LANG_SYS_COLLATION;
574  cinfo[k].coll_infer.codeset = LANG_SYS_CODESET;
575  cinfo[k].coll_infer.coerc_level = PT_COLLATION_NOT_COERC;
576  cinfo[k].coll_infer.can_force_cs = false;
577  cinfo[k].ref_att = NULL;
578  }
579  }
580 
581  if (pt_get_common_type_for_union (parser, att1, att2, &cinfo[i], i, &need_cast_tmp) == NULL)
582  {
583  goto end;
584  }
585  *need_cast |= need_cast_tmp;
586  }
587  else if (compatible == PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX || compatible == PT_UNION_ERROR)
588  {
589  if (!is_object_type)
590  {
591  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNION_INCOMPATIBLE,
592  pt_short_print (parser, att1), pt_short_print (parser, att2));
593  goto end;
594  }
595  }
596  }
597 
598  result = cinfo;
599 
600 end:
601  if (result != cinfo && cinfo != NULL)
602  {
603  free_and_init (cinfo);
604  }
605  return result;
606 
607 out_of_mem:
608  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
609  return NULL;
610 }
611 
612 /*
613  * pt_make_cast_with_compatible_info () -
614  * return: return a pointer to PT_EXPR node (cast)
615  * parser(in): parser context
616  * att(in): current attribute
617  * next_att(in): next attribute
618  * cinfo(in): compatible info
619  * new_cast_added(out): true if a new PT_EXPR node for cast if allocated, else false
620  */
621 static PT_NODE *
622 pt_make_cast_with_compatible_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * att, PT_NODE * next_att,
623  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo, bool * new_cast_added)
624 {
625  PT_EXPR_INFO *temp_expr;
626  PT_DATA_TYPE_INFO *temp_data_type;
627  PT_NODE *new_att = NULL, *new_dt = NULL;
628 
629  assert (parser != NULL && att != NULL && cinfo != NULL && new_cast_added != NULL);
630 
631  *new_cast_added = false;
632  if (att->node_type == PT_EXPR && att->info.expr.op == PT_CAST && att->etc != NULL)
633  {
634  /* system added cast operator */
635  temp_expr = &att->info.expr;
636  temp_expr->cast_type->type_enum = cinfo->type_enum;
637 
638  temp_data_type = &temp_expr->cast_type->info.data_type;
639  temp_data_type->precision = cinfo->prec;
640  temp_data_type->dec_precision = cinfo->scale;
641  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (cinfo->type_enum))
642  {
643  temp_data_type->collation_id = cinfo->coll_infer.coll_id;
644  temp_data_type->units = (int) cinfo->coll_infer.codeset;
645  }
646 
647  att->type_enum = att->info.expr.cast_type->type_enum;
648  att->data_type->type_enum = cinfo->type_enum;
649  temp_data_type = &att->data_type->info.data_type;
650  temp_data_type->precision = cinfo->prec;
651  temp_data_type->dec_precision = cinfo->scale;
652  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (cinfo->type_enum))
653  {
654  temp_data_type->collation_id = cinfo->coll_infer.coll_id;
655  temp_data_type->units = (int) cinfo->coll_infer.codeset;
656  }
657 
658  new_att = att;
659  }
660  else
661  {
662  /* create new cast node */
663  att->next = NULL;
664 
665  new_att = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
666  new_dt = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
667  if (new_att == NULL || new_dt == NULL)
668  {
669  if (new_att)
670  {
671  parser_free_tree (parser, new_att);
672  new_att = NULL;
673  }
674  if (new_dt)
675  {
676  parser_free_tree (parser, new_dt);
677  new_dt = NULL;
678  }
679 
680  goto out_of_mem;
681  }
682 
683  /* move alias */
684  new_att->line_number = att->line_number;
685  new_att->column_number = att->column_number;
686  if (att->alias_print == NULL && att->node_type == PT_NAME)
687  {
688  new_att->alias_print = att->info.name.original;
689  }
690  else
691  {
692  new_att->alias_print = att->alias_print;
693  }
694  att->alias_print = NULL;
695 
696  new_dt->type_enum = cinfo->type_enum;
697  temp_data_type = &new_dt->info.data_type;
698  temp_data_type->precision = cinfo->prec;
699  temp_data_type->dec_precision = cinfo->scale;
700  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (cinfo->type_enum))
701  {
702  temp_data_type->collation_id = cinfo->coll_infer.coll_id;
703  temp_data_type->units = (int) cinfo->coll_infer.codeset;
704  }
705 
706  new_att->type_enum = new_dt->type_enum;
707  temp_expr = &new_att->info.expr;
708  temp_expr->op = PT_CAST;
709  temp_expr->cast_type = new_dt;
710  temp_expr->arg1 = att;
711  new_att->next = next_att;
712  new_att->etc = cinfo; /* to make this as system added */
713  new_att->is_value_query = att->is_value_query;
714 
715  new_att->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, new_dt);
716  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (new_att, PT_EXPR_INFO_CAST_SHOULD_FOLD);
717 
718  *new_cast_added = true;
719  }
720 
721  return new_att;
722 
723 out_of_mem:
724  /* the error msg will be set in the caller */
725  return NULL;
726 }
727 
728 /*
729  * pt_get_values_query_compatible_info () -
730  * return: return a pointer of SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO array or null on error
731  * parser(in): parser context
732  * node(in): values query node
733  * need_cast(in/out):
734  *
735  * note: the return pointer must be freed by free_and_init
736  */
737 static SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *
738 pt_get_values_query_compatible_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, bool * need_cast)
739 {
740  PT_NODE *attrs1, *attrs2, *att1, *att2, *node_list, *next_node_list;
741  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo = NULL, *cinfo_cur = NULL, *result = NULL;
742  int i, count;
743  bool is_compatible, need_cast_cond = false;
744 
745  assert (parser);
746 
747  *need_cast = false;
748 
749  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_SELECT || !PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (node))
750  {
751  return NULL;
752  }
753 
754  node_list = node->info.query.q.select.list;
755  if (node_list == NULL)
756  {
757  return NULL;
758  }
759  attrs1 = node_list->info.node_list.list;
760 
761  next_node_list = node_list->next;
762  /* only one row */
763  if (next_node_list == NULL)
764  {
765  return NULL;
766  }
767  attrs2 = next_node_list->info.node_list.list;
768 
769  count = pt_length_of_select_list (attrs1, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
770 
771  /* get compatible_info for cast */
772  while (next_node_list != NULL)
773  {
774  cinfo_cur = pt_get_compatible_info (parser, node, node_list, next_node_list, &need_cast_cond);
775  if (cinfo_cur == NULL && need_cast_cond)
776  {
777  goto end;
778  }
779 
780  if (cinfo == NULL)
781  {
782  cinfo = cinfo_cur;
783  *need_cast = need_cast_cond;
784  cinfo_cur = NULL; /* do not free */
785  }
786  else
787  {
788  /* compare cinfo[i].type_enum and cinfo_cur[i].type_enum and save the compatible type_enum in cinfo[i] */
789  if (need_cast_cond)
790  {
791  is_compatible = true;
792  for (i = 0, att1 = attrs1, att2 = attrs2; i < count; ++i, att1 = att1->next, att2 = att2->next)
793  {
794  if (cinfo_cur[i].idx == -1)
795  {
796  continue;
797  }
798 
799  if (cinfo[i].idx == -1)
800  {
801  cinfo[i] = cinfo_cur[i];
802  *need_cast = true;
803  continue;
804  }
805 
806  /* if equal, skip the following steps */
807  if (cinfo[i].type_enum == cinfo_cur[i].type_enum && cinfo[i].prec == cinfo_cur[i].prec
808  && cinfo[i].scale == cinfo_cur[i].scale
809  && cinfo[i].coll_infer.coll_id == cinfo_cur[i].coll_infer.coll_id)
810  {
811  assert (cinfo[i].idx == cinfo_cur[i].idx);
812  continue;
813  }
814 
815  /* combine the two cinfos */
816  is_compatible = pt_combine_compatible_info (parser, cinfo + i, cinfo_cur + i, att1, att2, i);
817  if (!is_compatible)
818  {
819  break;
820  }
821 
822  *need_cast = true;
823  }
824 
825  if (!is_compatible)
826  {
827  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNION_INCOMPATIBLE,
828  pt_short_print (parser, att1), pt_short_print (parser, att2));
829  goto end;
830  }
831  }
832  }
833 
834  attrs1 = attrs2;
835  node_list = next_node_list;
836  next_node_list = next_node_list->next;
837  if (next_node_list != NULL)
838  {
839  attrs2 = next_node_list->info.node_list.list;
840  }
841 
842  /* free cinfo_cur */
843  free_and_init (cinfo_cur);
844  }
845 
846  /* assign cinfo to return value */
847  result = cinfo;
848 
849 end:
850  if (cinfo_cur != NULL)
851  {
852  free_and_init (cinfo_cur);
853  }
854  if (result != cinfo && cinfo != NULL)
855  {
856  free_and_init (cinfo);
857  }
858  return result;
859 }
860 
861 /*
862  * pt_check_compatible_node_for_orderby ()
863  */
864 bool
865 pt_check_compatible_node_for_orderby (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * order, PT_NODE * column)
866 {
867  PT_NODE *arg1, *cast_type;
868  PT_TYPE_ENUM type1, type2;
869 
870  if (order == NULL || column == NULL || order->node_type != PT_EXPR || order->info.expr.op != PT_CAST)
871  {
872  return false;
873  }
874 
875  arg1 = order->info.expr.arg1;
876  if (arg1->node_type != column->node_type)
877  {
878  return false;
879  }
880 
881  if (arg1->node_type != PT_NAME && arg1->node_type != PT_DOT_)
882  {
883  return false;
884  }
885 
886  if (pt_check_path_eq (parser, arg1, column) != 0)
887  {
888  return false;
889  }
890 
891  cast_type = order->info.expr.cast_type;
892  assert (cast_type != NULL);
893 
894  type1 = arg1->type_enum;
895  type2 = cast_type->type_enum;
896 
897  if (PT_IS_NUMERIC_TYPE (type1) && PT_IS_NUMERIC_TYPE (type2))
898  {
899  return true;
900  }
901 
902  /* Only string type : Do not consider 'CAST (enum_col as VARCHAR)' equal to 'enum_col' */
903  if (PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (type1) && PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (type2))
904  {
905  int c1, c2;
906 
907  c1 = arg1->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id;
908  c2 = cast_type->info.data_type.collation_id;
909  return c1 == c2;
910  }
911 
912  if (PT_IS_DATE_TIME_TYPE (type1) && PT_IS_DATE_TIME_TYPE (type2))
913  {
914  if ((type1 == PT_TYPE_TIME && type2 != PT_TYPE_TIME) || (type1 != PT_TYPE_TIME && type2 == PT_TYPE_TIME))
915  {
916  return false;
917  }
918  return true;
919  }
920 
921  return false;
922 }
923 
924 /*
925  * pt_check_cast_op () - Checks to see if the cast operator is well-formed
926  * return: none
927  * parser(in):
928  * node(in): the node to check
929  */
930 bool
931 pt_check_cast_op (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
932 {
933  PT_NODE *arg1;
934  PT_TYPE_ENUM cast_type = PT_TYPE_NONE, arg_type;
935  PT_CAST_VAL cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_VALID;
936 
937  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_EXPR || node->info.expr.op != PT_CAST)
938  {
939  /* this should not happen, but don't crash and burn if it does */
940  assert (false);
941  return false;
942  }
943 
944  /* check special CAST : COLLATE modifier */
945  if (PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_CAST_COLL_MODIFIER))
946  {
947  LANG_COLLATION *lc;
948  PT_NODE *arg_dt = NULL;
949 
950  if (node->info.expr.arg1 != NULL && node->info.expr.arg1->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NONE
951  && !PT_HAS_COLLATION (node->info.expr.arg1->type_enum))
952  {
953  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_COLLATE_NOT_ALLOWED);
954  return false;
955  }
956  /* arg1 may have been set NULL due to previous semantic errors */
957  arg_dt = (node->info.expr.arg1 != NULL) ? node->info.expr.arg1->data_type : NULL;
958 
959  lc = lang_get_collation (PT_GET_COLLATION_MODIFIER (node));
960  if (arg_dt != NULL && lc->codeset != arg_dt->info.data_type.units)
961  {
962  /* cannot change codeset with COLLATE */
963  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CS_MATCH_COLLATE,
964  lang_get_codeset_name (arg_dt->info.data_type.units), lang_get_codeset_name (lc->codeset));
965  return false;
966  }
967  }
968 
969  /* get cast type */
970  if (node->info.expr.cast_type != NULL)
971  {
972  cast_type = node->info.expr.cast_type->type_enum;
973  }
974  else
975  {
976  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && !PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_CAST_COLL_MODIFIER))
977  {
978  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "null cast type");
979  }
980  return false;
981  }
982 
983  /* get argument */
984  arg1 = node->info.expr.arg1;
985  if (arg1 == NULL)
986  {
987  /* a parse error might have occurred lower in the parse tree of arg1; don't register another error unless no
988  * error has been set */
989 
990  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
991  {
992  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CANT_COERCE_TO, "(null)",
993  pt_show_type_enum (cast_type));
994  }
995  return false;
996  }
997 
998  /* CAST (arg_type AS cast_type) */
999  if (arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR && arg1->info.expr.op == PT_CAST)
1000  {
1001  /* arg1 is a cast, so arg1.type_enum is not yet set; pull type from expression's cast type */
1002  arg_type = arg1->info.expr.cast_type->type_enum;
1003  }
1004  else
1005  {
1006  /* arg1 is not a cast */
1007  arg_type = arg1->type_enum;
1008  }
1009 
1010  switch (arg_type)
1011  {
1012  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1013  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
1014  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
1015  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1016  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1017  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
1018  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1019  switch (cast_type)
1020  {
1021  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1022  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1023  case PT_TYPE_DATE:
1024  /* allow numeric to TIME and TIMESTAMP conversions */
1025  case PT_TYPE_DATETIME:
1026  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
1027  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
1028  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1029  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1030  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1031  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1032  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1033  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1034  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1035  break;
1036  default:
1037  break;
1038  }
1039  break;
1040  case PT_TYPE_DATE:
1041  switch (cast_type)
1042  {
1043  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1044  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
1045  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
1046  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1047  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1048  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
1049  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1050  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1051  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1052  case PT_TYPE_TIME:
1053  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1054  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1055  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1056  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1057  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1058  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1059  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1060  break;
1061  default:
1062  break;
1063  }
1064  break;
1065  case PT_TYPE_TIME:
1066  switch (cast_type)
1067  {
1068  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1069  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
1070  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
1071  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1072  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1073  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
1074  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1075  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1076  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1077  case PT_TYPE_DATE:
1078  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1079  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1080  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1081  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1082  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1083  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1084  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1085  break;
1086  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
1087  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
1088  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
1089  case PT_TYPE_DATETIME:
1090  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
1091  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
1092  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED;
1093  break;
1094  default:
1095  break;
1096  }
1097  break;
1098  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
1099  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
1100  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
1101  switch (cast_type)
1102  {
1103  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1104  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
1105  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
1106  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1107  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1108  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
1109  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1110  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1111  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1112  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1113  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1114  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1115  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1116  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1117  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1118  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1119  break;
1120  default:
1121  break;
1122  }
1123  break;
1124  case PT_TYPE_DATETIME:
1125  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
1126  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
1127  switch (cast_type)
1128  {
1129  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1130  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
1131  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1132  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1133  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
1134  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1135  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1136  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1137  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1138  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1139  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1140  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1141  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1142  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1143  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1144  break;
1145  default:
1146  break;
1147  }
1148  break;
1149  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
1150  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
1151  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
1152  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
1153  if ((PT_IS_NATIONAL_CHAR_STRING_TYPE (arg_type) && PT_IS_SIMPLE_CHAR_STRING_TYPE (cast_type))
1154  || (PT_IS_SIMPLE_CHAR_STRING_TYPE (arg_type) && PT_IS_NATIONAL_CHAR_STRING_TYPE (cast_type)))
1155  {
1156  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1157  break;
1158  }
1159 
1160  switch (cast_type)
1161  {
1162  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1163  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1164  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1165  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED;
1166  break;
1167  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1168  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1169  break;
1170  default:
1171  break;
1172  }
1173  break;
1174  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1175  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1176  switch (cast_type)
1177  {
1178  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1179  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
1180  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
1181  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1182  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1183  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
1184  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1185  case PT_TYPE_DATE:
1186  case PT_TYPE_TIME:
1187  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
1188  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
1189  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
1190  case PT_TYPE_DATETIME:
1191  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
1192  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
1193  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1194  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1195  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1196  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1197  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1198  break;
1199  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1200  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED;
1201  break;
1202  default:
1203  break;
1204  }
1205  break;
1206  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1207  /* some functions like DECODE, CASE perform wrap with CAST, allow it */
1208  if (!PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_CAST_SHOULD_FOLD))
1209  {
1210  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED;
1211  }
1212  break;
1213  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1214  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1215  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1216  switch (cast_type)
1217  {
1218  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
1219  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
1220  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
1221  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
1222  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
1223  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
1224  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
1225  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1226  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1227  case PT_TYPE_DATE:
1228  case PT_TYPE_TIME:
1229  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
1230  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
1231  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
1232  case PT_TYPE_DATETIME:
1233  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
1234  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
1235  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1236  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1237  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1238  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1239  break;
1240  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
1241  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
1242  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
1243  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
1244  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED;
1245  break;
1246  default:
1247  break;
1248  }
1249  break;
1250  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1251  switch (cast_type)
1252  {
1253  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
1254  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
1255  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1256  case PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION:
1257  break;
1258  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1259  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED;
1260  break;
1261  default:
1262  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1263  break;
1264  }
1265  break;
1266  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1267  switch (cast_type)
1268  {
1269  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
1270  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
1271  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
1272  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
1273  case PT_TYPE_CLOB:
1274  case PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION:
1275  break;
1276  case PT_TYPE_BLOB:
1277  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED;
1278  break;
1279  default:
1280  cast_is_valid = PT_CAST_INVALID;
1281  break;
1282  }
1283  break;
1284  default:
1285  break;
1286  }
1287 
1288  switch (cast_is_valid)
1289  {
1290  case PT_CAST_VALID:
1291  break;
1292  case PT_CAST_INVALID:
1293  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CANT_COERCE_TO,
1294  pt_short_print (parser, node->info.expr.arg1), pt_show_type_enum (cast_type));
1295  break;
1296  case PT_CAST_UNSUPPORTED:
1297  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_COERCE_UNSUPPORTED,
1298  pt_short_print (parser, node->info.expr.arg1), pt_show_type_enum (cast_type));
1299  break;
1300  }
1301 
1302  return (cast_is_valid == PT_CAST_VALID) ? true : false;
1303 }
1304 
1305 /*
1306  * pt_check_user_exists () - given 'user.class', check that 'user' exists
1307  * return: db_user instance if user exists, NULL otherwise.
1308  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive cls_ref
1309  * cls_ref(in): a PT_NAME node
1310  *
1311  * Note :
1312  * this routine is needed only in the context of checking create stmts,
1313  * ie, in checking 'create vclass usr.cls ...'.
1314  * Otherwise, pt_check_user_owns_class should be used.
1315  */
1316 static DB_OBJECT *
1317 pt_check_user_exists (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * cls_ref)
1318 {
1319  const char *usr;
1320  DB_OBJECT *result;
1321 
1322  assert (parser != NULL);
1323 
1324  if (!cls_ref || cls_ref->node_type != PT_NAME || (usr = cls_ref->info.name.resolved) == NULL || usr[0] == '\0')
1325  {
1326  return NULL;
1327  }
1328 
1329  result = db_find_user (usr);
1330  if (!result)
1331  {
1332  PT_ERRORmf (parser, cls_ref, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USER_IS_NOT_IN_DB, usr);
1333  }
1334 
1335  return result;
1336 }
1337 
1338 /*
1339  * pt_check_user_owns_class () - given user.class, check that user owns class
1340  * return: db_user instance if 'user' exists & owns 'class', NULL otherwise
1341  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive cls_ref
1342  * cls_ref(in): a PT_NAME node
1343  */
1344 DB_OBJECT *
1345 pt_check_user_owns_class (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * cls_ref)
1346 {
1347  DB_OBJECT *result, *cls, *owner;
1348 
1349  if ((result = pt_check_user_exists (parser, cls_ref)) == NULL || (cls = cls_ref->info.name.db_object) == NULL)
1350  {
1351  return NULL;
1352  }
1353 
1354  owner = db_get_owner (cls);
1355  result = (ws_is_same_object (owner, result) ? result : NULL);
1356  if (!result)
1357  {
1358  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, cls_ref, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USER_DOESNT_OWN_CLS,
1359  cls_ref->info.name.resolved, cls_ref->info.name.original);
1360  }
1361 
1362  return result;
1363 }
1364 
1365 /*
1366  * pt_derive_attribute () - derive a new ATTR_DEF node from a query_spec
1367  * column
1368  * return: a new ATTR_DEF node derived from c if all OK, NULL otherwise.
1369  * parser(in): the parser context to use for creating the ATTR_DEF node
1370  * c(in): a query_spec column
1371  */
1372 static PT_NODE *
1373 pt_derive_attribute (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * c)
1374 {
1375  PT_NODE *attr = NULL;
1376  PT_NODE *cname = NULL;
1377 
1378  assert (parser != NULL);
1379 
1380  if (c == NULL)
1381  {
1382  return NULL;
1383  }
1384 
1385  if (c->alias_print != NULL)
1386  {
1387  cname = pt_name (parser, c->alias_print);
1388  }
1389  else if (c->node_type == PT_NAME)
1390  {
1391  if (c->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT && c->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR
1392  && (c->info.name.original == NULL || strlen (c->info.name.original) == 0))
1393  {
1394  cname = pt_name (parser, c->info.name.resolved);
1395  }
1396  else
1397  {
1398  cname = pt_name (parser, c->info.name.original);
1399  }
1400  }
1401  else
1402  {
1403  return NULL;
1404  }
1405 
1406  if (cname == NULL)
1407  {
1408  return NULL;
1409  }
1410 
1411  attr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_ATTR_DEF);
1412  if (attr == NULL)
1413  {
1414  return NULL;
1415  }
1416 
1417  attr->data_type = NULL;
1418  attr->info.attr_def.attr_name = cname;
1419  attr->info.attr_def.attr_type = PT_NORMAL;
1420 
1421  return attr;
1422 }
1423 
1424 /*
1425  * pt_get_attributes () - get & return the attribute list of
1426  * a {class|vclass|view}
1427  * return: c's attribute list if successful, NULL otherwise.
1428  * parser(in): the parser context to use for creating the list
1429  * c(in): a {class|vclass|view} object
1430  */
1431 /* TODO modify the function so that we can distinguish between a class having
1432  * no attributes and an execution error.
1433  */
1434 static PT_NODE *
1435 pt_get_attributes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const DB_OBJECT * c)
1436 {
1437  DB_ATTRIBUTE *attributes;
1438  const char *class_name;
1439  PT_NODE *i_attr, *name, *typ, *types, *list = NULL;
1440  DB_OBJECT *cls;
1441  DB_DOMAIN *dom;
1442 
1443  assert (parser != NULL);
1444 
1445  if (!c || !(class_name = db_get_class_name ((DB_OBJECT *) c)))
1446  {
1447  return list;
1448  }
1449 
1450  attributes = db_get_attributes ((DB_OBJECT *) c);
1451  while (attributes)
1452  {
1453  /* create a new attribute node */
1454  i_attr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_ATTR_DEF);
1455  if (i_attr == NULL)
1456  {
1457  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
1458  return NULL;
1459  }
1460 
1461  /* its name is class_name.attribute_name */
1462  i_attr->info.attr_def.attr_name = name = pt_name (parser, db_attribute_name (attributes));
1463  name->info.name.resolved = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, class_name);
1464  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (name, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE);
1465  name->info.name.meta_class = (db_attribute_is_shared (attributes) ? PT_SHARED : PT_NORMAL);
1466 
1467  /* set its data type */
1468  i_attr->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (db_attribute_type (attributes));
1469  switch (i_attr->type_enum)
1470  {
1471  case PT_TYPE_OBJECT:
1472  cls = db_domain_class (db_attribute_domain (attributes));
1473  if (cls)
1474  {
1475  name = pt_name (parser, db_get_class_name (cls));
1476  name->info.name.meta_class = PT_CLASS;
1477  name->info.name.db_object = cls;
1478  name->info.name.spec_id = (UINTPTR) name;
1479  i_attr->data_type = typ = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
1480  if (typ)
1481  {
1482  typ->info.data_type.entity = name;
1483  }
1484  }
1485  break;
1486 
1487  case PT_TYPE_SET:
1488  case PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE:
1489  case PT_TYPE_MULTISET:
1490  types = NULL;
1491  dom = db_domain_set (db_attribute_domain (attributes));
1492  while (dom)
1493  {
1494  typ = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, dom);
1495  if (typ)
1496  {
1497  typ->next = types;
1498  }
1499  types = typ;
1500  dom = db_domain_next (dom);
1501  }
1502  i_attr->data_type = types;
1503  break;
1504 
1505  default:
1506  dom = attributes->domain;
1507  typ = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, dom);
1508  i_attr->data_type = typ;
1509  break;
1510  }
1511 
1512  list = parser_append_node (i_attr, list);
1513 
1514  /* advance to next attribute */
1515  attributes = db_attribute_next (attributes);
1516  }
1517  return list;
1518 }
1519 
1520 /*
1521  * pt_get_class_type () - return a class instance's type
1522  * return: PT_CLASS, PT_VCLASS, or PT_MISC_DUMMY
1523  * cls(in): a class instance
1524  */
1525 static PT_MISC_TYPE
1526 pt_get_class_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const DB_OBJECT * cls)
1527 {
1528  if (!cls)
1529  {
1530  return PT_MISC_DUMMY;
1531  }
1532 
1533  if (db_is_vclass ((DB_OBJECT *) cls) > 0)
1534  {
1535  return PT_VCLASS;
1536  }
1537 
1538  if (db_is_class ((DB_OBJECT *) cls) > 0)
1539  {
1540  return PT_CLASS;
1541  }
1542 
1543  return PT_MISC_DUMMY;
1544 }
1545 
1546 /*
1547  * pt_number_of_attributes () - determine the number of attributes
1548  * of the new class to be created by a create_vclass statement,
1549  * or the number of attributes of the new definition of a view
1550  * in the case of "ALTER VIEW xxx AS SELECT ...".
1551  * return: number of attributes of the new class to be created by stmt
1552  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive stmt
1553  * stmt(in): a create_vclass statement
1554  * attrs(out): the attributes of the new class to be created by stmt
1555  *
1556  * Note :
1557  * non-inherited class_attributes are excluded from the attribute count.
1558  */
1559 static int
1560 pt_number_of_attributes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt, PT_NODE ** attrs)
1561 {
1562  int count = 0;
1563  PT_NODE *crt_attr = NULL;
1564  PT_NODE *crt_parent = NULL;
1565  PT_NODE *t_attr = NULL;
1566  PT_NODE *inherited_attrs = NULL;
1567  PT_NODE *r = NULL;
1568  PT_NODE *i_attr = NULL;
1569  PT_NODE *next_node = NULL;
1570 
1571  if (stmt == NULL || attrs == NULL)
1572  {
1573  return count;
1574  }
1575 
1576  if ((stmt->node_type == PT_ALTER) && (stmt->info.alter.code == PT_RESET_QUERY))
1577  {
1578  *attrs = stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.query.attr_def_list;
1579  count = pt_length_of_list (*attrs);
1580  return count;
1581  }
1582 
1583  assert (stmt->node_type == PT_CREATE_ENTITY);
1584  if (stmt->node_type != PT_CREATE_ENTITY)
1585  {
1586  return count;
1587  }
1588 
1589  *attrs = stmt->info.create_entity.attr_def_list;
1590  count = pt_length_of_list (*attrs);
1591 
1592  /* Exclude class_attributes from count but keep them in the attrs list. */
1593  for (crt_attr = *attrs; crt_attr != NULL; crt_attr = crt_attr->next)
1594  {
1595  if (crt_attr->info.attr_def.attr_type == PT_META_ATTR)
1596  {
1597  count--;
1598  }
1599  }
1600 
1601  /* collect into one list all inherited attributes from all parents */
1602  inherited_attrs = NULL;
1603  for (crt_parent = stmt->info.create_entity.supclass_list; crt_parent != NULL; crt_parent = crt_parent->next)
1604  {
1605  /* get this parent's attributes & append them to the list */
1606  PT_NODE *const parent_attrs = pt_get_attributes (parser, crt_parent->info.name.db_object);
1607 
1608  inherited_attrs = parser_append_node (parent_attrs, inherited_attrs);
1609  }
1610 
1611  /* Rule 2: If two or more superclasses have attributes with the same name and domain but different origins, the class
1612  * may inherit one or more of the attributes, but the user needs to specify inheritance. Implementation: scan through
1613  * the inheritance list and do any attribute renaming specified by the user. */
1614  for (r = stmt->info.create_entity.resolution_list; r != NULL; r = r->next)
1615  {
1616  PT_NODE *const new_name = r->info.resolution.as_attr_mthd_name;
1617  PT_NODE *const resolv_class = r->info.resolution.of_sup_class_name;
1618  PT_NODE *const resolv_attr = r->info.resolution.attr_mthd_name;
1619 
1620  if (new_name == NULL)
1621  {
1622  continue;
1623  }
1624 
1625  for (i_attr = inherited_attrs; i_attr != NULL; t_attr = i_attr, i_attr = i_attr->next)
1626  {
1627  PT_NODE *const name = i_attr->info.attr_def.attr_name;
1628 
1629  if (pt_str_compare (resolv_attr->info.name.original, name->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0
1630  && pt_str_compare (resolv_class->info.name.original, name->info.name.resolved, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
1631  {
1632  name->info.name.original = new_name->info.name.original;
1633  }
1634  }
1635  }
1636 
1637  /* Rule 2 implementation continued: remove from inherited_attrs all inherited attributes that conflict with any
1638  * user-specified inheritance. */
1639  for (r = stmt->info.create_entity.resolution_list; r != NULL; r = r->next)
1640  {
1641  PT_NODE *const resolv_class = r->info.resolution.of_sup_class_name;
1642  PT_NODE *const resolv_attr = r->info.resolution.attr_mthd_name;
1643 
1644  if (r->info.resolution.as_attr_mthd_name != NULL)
1645  {
1646  continue;
1647  }
1648 
1649  /* user wants class to inherit this attribute without renaming */
1650  for (i_attr = inherited_attrs; i_attr != NULL; i_attr = i_attr->next)
1651  {
1652  PT_NODE *const name = i_attr->info.attr_def.attr_name;
1653 
1654  if (pt_str_compare (resolv_attr->info.name.original, name->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) != 0)
1655  {
1656  /* i_attr is a keeper so advance t_attr. */
1657  t_attr = i_attr;
1658  }
1659  else
1660  {
1661  if (pt_str_compare (resolv_class->info.name.original, name->info.name.resolved, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
1662  {
1663  /* i_attr is a keeper. keep the user-specified inherited attribute */
1664  t_attr = i_attr;
1665  continue;
1666  }
1667  /* delete inherited attribute that conflicts with resolv_attr */
1668  if (i_attr == inherited_attrs)
1669  {
1670  inherited_attrs = i_attr->next;
1671  }
1672  else
1673  {
1674  t_attr->next = i_attr->next;
1675  }
1676  /* i_attr is a goner. do NOT advance t_attr! */
1677  }
1678  }
1679  }
1680 
1681  /*
1682  * At this point, the conflicting attributes that the user wants us to keep have been safely preserved and renamed in
1683  * inherited_attrs. It is now safe to start weeding out remaining attribute conflicts. */
1684 
1685  /*
1686  * Rule 1: If the name of an attribute in a class C conflicts (i.e., is the same as) with that of an attribute in a
1687  * superclass S, the name in class C is used; that is, the attribute is not inherited. Implementation: remove from
1688  * inherited_attrs each attribute whose name matches some non-inherited attribute name. */
1689  for (crt_attr = stmt->info.create_entity.attr_def_list; crt_attr != NULL; crt_attr = crt_attr->next)
1690  {
1691  for (i_attr = inherited_attrs; i_attr; i_attr = i_attr->next)
1692  {
1693  if (pt_str_compare (crt_attr->info.attr_def.attr_name->info.name.original,
1694  i_attr->info.attr_def.attr_name->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) != 0)
1695  {
1696  /* i_attr is a keeper. */
1697  t_attr = i_attr;
1698  }
1699  else
1700  {
1701  /* delete it from inherited_attrs */
1702  if (i_attr == inherited_attrs)
1703  {
1704  inherited_attrs = i_attr->next;
1705  }
1706  else
1707  {
1708  t_attr->next = i_attr->next;
1709  }
1710  /* i_attr is a goner. do NOT advance t_attr! */
1711  }
1712  }
1713  }
1714 
1715  /*
1716  * Rule 2 continued: If the user does not specify the attributes (to be inherited), the system will pick one
1717  * arbitrarily, and notify the user. Jeff probably knows how to 'pick one arbitrarily', but until we learn how, the
1718  * following will do for TPR. We lump together Rules 2 & 3 and implement them as: given a group of attributes with
1719  * the same name, keep the first and toss the rest. */
1720  for (i_attr = inherited_attrs, next_node = i_attr ? i_attr->next : NULL; i_attr != NULL;
1721  i_attr = next_node, next_node = i_attr ? i_attr->next : NULL)
1722  {
1723  for (r = i_attr->next; r != NULL; r = r->next)
1724  {
1725  if (pt_str_compare (i_attr->info.attr_def.attr_name->info.name.original,
1726  r->info.attr_def.attr_name->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) != 0)
1727  {
1728  /* r is a keeper so advance t_attr. */
1729  t_attr = r;
1730  }
1731  else
1732  {
1733  if (r == i_attr->next)
1734  {
1735  i_attr->next = r->next;
1736  }
1737  else
1738  {
1739  t_attr->next = r->next;
1740  }
1741  /* r is a goner. do NOT advance t_attr! */
1742  }
1743  }
1744  }
1745 
1746  /* Append the non-inherited attributes to the inherited attributes. */
1747  if (inherited_attrs != NULL)
1748  {
1749  count += pt_length_of_list (inherited_attrs);
1750  *attrs = parser_append_node (*attrs, inherited_attrs);
1751  }
1752 
1753  return count;
1754 }
1755 
1756 /*
1757  * pt_is_real_class_of_vclass () - determine if s_class is a
1758  * real class of d_class
1759  * return: 1 if s_class is a real class of the view d_class
1760  * parser(in): the parser context
1761  * s_class(in): a PT_DATA_TYPE node whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1762  * d_class(in): a PT_DATA_TYPE node whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1763  */
1764 static int
1765 pt_is_real_class_of_vclass (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * s_class, const PT_NODE * d_class)
1766 {
1767  if (!d_class || d_class->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE || !s_class || s_class->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE)
1768  {
1769  return 0;
1770  }
1771 
1772  return mq_is_real_class_of_vclass (parser, s_class->info.data_type.entity, d_class->info.data_type.entity);
1773 }
1774 
1775 /*
1776  * pt_objects_assignable () - determine if src is assignable to data_type dest
1777  * return: 1 iff src is assignable to dest, 0 otherwise
1778  * parser(in): the parser context
1779  * d_class_dt(in): data_type of target attribute
1780  * s_class(in): source PT_NODE
1781  */
1782 static int
1783 pt_objects_assignable (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * d_class_dt, const PT_NODE * s_class)
1784 {
1785  PT_NODE *s_class_type, *d_class_dt_type = NULL;
1786 
1787  if (!s_class || s_class->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
1788  {
1789  return 0;
1790  }
1791 
1792  if (!d_class_dt || (d_class_dt->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE && !(d_class_dt_type = d_class_dt->info.data_type.entity)))
1793  {
1794  /* a wildcard destination object matches any other object type */
1795  return 1;
1796  }
1797 
1798  else if ((d_class_dt && d_class_dt->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE) || !s_class->data_type
1799  || s_class->data_type->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE)
1800  {
1801  /* weed out structural errors as failures */
1802  return 0;
1803  }
1804  else
1805  {
1806  /* s_class is assignable to d_class_dt if s_class is a subclass of d_class_dt this is what it should be: return
1807  * pt_is_subset_of(parser, s_class_type, d_class_dt_type); but d_class_dt->info.data_type.entity does not have
1808  * ALL the subclasses of the type, ie, if d_class_dt's type is "glo", it shows only "glo" instead of: "glo,
1809  * audio, etc." so we do this instead: */
1810  if (!(s_class_type = s_class->data_type->info.data_type.entity))
1811  {
1812  return 1; /* general object type */
1813  }
1814  else
1815  {
1816  return ((s_class_type->info.name.db_object == d_class_dt_type->info.name.db_object)
1817  || (db_is_subclass (s_class_type->info.name.db_object, d_class_dt_type->info.name.db_object) > 0));
1818  }
1819  }
1820 }
1821 
1822 /*
1823  * pt_class_assignable () - determine if s_class is assignable to d_class_dt
1824  * return: 1 if s_class is assignable to d_class
1825  * parser(in): the parser context
1826  * d_class_dt(in): a PT_DATA_TYPE node whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1827  * s_class(in): a PT_NODE whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1828  */
1829 int
1830 pt_class_assignable (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * d_class_dt, const PT_NODE * s_class)
1831 {
1832 
1833  /* a wildcard destination object accepts any other object type */
1834  if (!d_class_dt || (d_class_dt->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE && !d_class_dt->info.data_type.entity))
1835  {
1836  return 1;
1837  }
1838 
1839  /* weed out structural errors as failures */
1840  if (!s_class || (d_class_dt && d_class_dt->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE))
1841  {
1842  return 0;
1843  }
1844 
1845  /* NULL is assignable to any class type */
1846  if (s_class->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NA || s_class->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
1847  {
1848  return 1;
1849  }
1850 
1851  /* make sure we are dealing only with object types */
1852  if (s_class->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
1853  {
1854  return 0;
1855  }
1856 
1857  return (pt_objects_assignable (parser, d_class_dt, s_class)
1858  || pt_is_real_class_of_vclass (parser, s_class->data_type, d_class_dt)
1859  || pt_is_real_class_of_vclass (parser, d_class_dt, s_class->data_type));
1860 }
1861 
1862 /*
1863  * pt_class_compatible () - determine if two classes have compatible domains
1864  * return: 1 if class1 and class2 have compatible domains
1865  * parser(in): the parser context
1866  * class1(in): a PT_NODE whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1867  * class2(in): a PT_NODE whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1868  * view_definition_context(in):
1869  */
1870 static int
1871 pt_class_compatible (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * class1, const PT_NODE * class2,
1872  bool view_definition_context)
1873 {
1874  if (!class1 || class1->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT || !class2 || class2->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
1875  {
1876  return 0;
1877  }
1878 
1879  if (view_definition_context)
1880  {
1881  return pt_class_assignable (parser, class1->data_type, class2);
1882  }
1883  else
1884  {
1885  return (pt_class_assignable (parser, class1->data_type, class2)
1886  || pt_class_assignable (parser, class2->data_type, class1));
1887  }
1888 }
1889 
1890 /*
1891  * pt_vclass_compatible () - determine if att is vclass compatible with qcol
1892  * return: true if att is vclass compatible with qcol
1893  * parser(in): the parser context
1894  * att(in): PT_DATA_TYPE node of a vclass attribute def
1895  * qcol(in): a query spec column
1896  */
1897 static bool
1898 pt_vclass_compatible (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * att, const PT_NODE * qcol)
1899 {
1900  PT_NODE *entity, *qcol_entity, *qcol_typ;
1901  DB_OBJECT *vcls = NULL;
1902  const char *clsnam = NULL, *qcol_typnam = NULL, *spec, *qs_clsnam;
1903  DB_QUERY_SPEC *specs;
1904 
1905  /* a wildcard object accepts any other object type but is not vclass_compatible with any other object */
1906  if (!att || (att->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE && !att->info.data_type.entity))
1907  {
1908  return false;
1909  }
1910 
1911  /* weed out structural errors as failures */
1912  if (!qcol || (att && att->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE) || (entity = att->info.data_type.entity) == NULL
1913  || entity->node_type != PT_NAME || ((vcls = entity->info.name.db_object) == NULL
1914  && (clsnam = entity->info.name.original) == NULL))
1915  {
1916  return false;
1917  }
1918 
1919  /* make sure we are dealing only with object types that can be union vclass_compatible with vcls. */
1920  if (qcol->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT || (qcol_typ = qcol->data_type) == NULL || qcol_typ->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE
1921  || (qcol_entity = qcol_typ->info.data_type.entity) == NULL || qcol_entity->node_type != PT_NAME
1922  || (qcol_typnam = qcol_entity->info.name.original) == NULL)
1923  {
1924  return false;
1925  }
1926 
1927  /* make sure we have the vclass */
1928  if (!vcls)
1929  {
1930  vcls = db_find_class (clsnam);
1931  }
1932  if (!vcls)
1933  {
1934  return false;
1935  }
1936 
1937  /* return true iff att is a vclass & qcol is in att's query_spec list */
1938  for (specs = db_get_query_specs (vcls); specs && (spec = db_query_spec_string (specs));
1939  specs = db_query_spec_next (specs))
1940  {
1941  qs_clsnam = pt_get_proxy_spec_name (spec);
1942  if (qs_clsnam && intl_identifier_casecmp (qs_clsnam, qcol_typnam) == 0)
1943  {
1944  return true; /* att is vclass_compatible with qcol */
1945  }
1946  }
1947 
1948  return false; /* att is not vclass_compatible with qcol */
1949 }
1950 
1951 /*
1952  * pt_type_assignable () - determine if s_type is assignable to d_type
1953  * return: 1 if s_type is assignable to d_type
1954  * parser(in): the parser context
1955  * d_type(in): a PT_DATA_TYPE node whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1956  * s_type(in): a PT_DATA_TYPE node whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
1957  */
1958 static int
1959 pt_type_assignable (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * d_type, const PT_NODE * s_type)
1960 {
1961  PT_NODE *src_type, *dest_type = NULL;
1962 
1963  /* a wildcard destination object accepts any other object type */
1964  if (!d_type || (d_type->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE && !d_type->info.data_type.entity))
1965  {
1966  return 1;
1967  }
1968 
1969  /* weed out structural errors as failures */
1970  if (!s_type || (d_type && d_type->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE))
1971  {
1972  return 0;
1973  }
1974 
1975  /* make sure we are dealing only with object types */
1976  if (s_type->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
1977  {
1978  return 0;
1979  }
1980 
1981  dest_type = d_type->info.data_type.entity;
1982  src_type = s_type->info.data_type.entity;
1983  if (!dest_type || !src_type)
1984  {
1985  return 0;
1986  }
1987 
1988  /* If the destination isn't resolved, resolve it. */
1989  if (!dest_type->info.name.db_object)
1990  {
1991  dest_type->info.name.db_object = db_find_class (dest_type->info.name.original);
1992  dest_type->info.name.meta_class = PT_CLASS;
1993  }
1994 
1995  return (src_type->info.name.db_object == dest_type->info.name.db_object
1996  || (db_is_subclass (src_type->info.name.db_object, dest_type->info.name.db_object) > 0)
1997  || mq_is_real_class_of_vclass (parser, src_type, dest_type));
1998 }
1999 
2000 /*
2001  * pt_collection_assignable () - determine if s_col is assignable to d_col
2002  * return: 1 if s_col is assignable to d_col
2003  * parser(in): the parser context
2004  * d_col(in): a PT_NODE whose type_enum is a PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE
2005  * s_col(in): a PT_NODE whose type_enum is a PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE
2006  */
2007 static int
2008 pt_collection_assignable (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * d_col, const PT_NODE * s_col)
2009 {
2010  int assignable = 1; /* innocent until proven guilty */
2011 
2012  if (!d_col || !s_col || !PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (d_col->type_enum))
2013  {
2014  return 0;
2015  }
2016 
2017  /* NULL is assignable to any class type */
2018  if (s_col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NA || s_col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
2019  {
2020  return 1;
2021  }
2022 
2023  /* make sure we are dealing only with collection types */
2024  if (!PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (s_col->type_enum))
2025  {
2026  return 0;
2027  }
2028 
2029  /* can't assign a multiset or a sequence to a set, or a multiset to a sequence */
2030  if (((d_col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SET)
2031  && ((s_col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MULTISET) || (s_col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE)))
2032  || ((d_col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_SEQUENCE) && (s_col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MULTISET)))
2033  {
2034  assignable = 0;
2035  }
2036  else if (!d_col->data_type)
2037  {
2038  /* the wildcard set (set of anything) can be assigned a set of any type. */
2039  assignable = 1;
2040  }
2041  else if (!s_col->data_type)
2042  {
2043  /* in this case, we have a wild card set being assigned to a non-wildcard set. */
2044  assignable = 0;
2045  }
2046  else
2047  {
2048  /* Check to see that every type in the source collection is in the destination collection. That is, the source
2049  * types must be a subset of the destination types. There is no coercion allowed. */
2050  PT_NODE *st, *dt;
2051  int found;
2052 
2053  for (st = s_col->data_type; st != NULL; st = st->next)
2054  {
2055  found = 0;
2056  for (dt = d_col->data_type; dt != NULL; dt = dt->next)
2057  {
2058  if (st->type_enum == dt->type_enum)
2059  {
2060  if ((st->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT) || (pt_type_assignable (parser, dt, st)))
2061  {
2062  found = 1;
2063  break;
2064  }
2065  }
2066  }
2067 
2068  if (!found)
2069  {
2070  assignable = 0;
2071  break;
2072  }
2073  }
2074  }
2075 
2076  return assignable;
2077 } /* pt_collection_assignable */
2078 
2079 /*
2080  * pt_collection_compatible () - determine if two collections
2081  * have compatible domains
2082  * return: 1 if c1 and c2 have compatible domains
2083  * parser(in): the parser context
2084  * col1(in): a PT_NODE whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
2085  * col2(in): a PT_NODE whose type_enum is PT_TYPE_OBJECT
2086  * view_definition_context(in):
2087  */
2088 static int
2089 pt_collection_compatible (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * col1, const PT_NODE * col2,
2090  bool view_definition_context)
2091 {
2092  if (!col1 || !PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (col1->type_enum) || !col2 || !PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (col2->type_enum))
2093  {
2094  return 0;
2095  }
2096 
2097  if (view_definition_context)
2098  {
2099  return pt_collection_assignable (parser, col1, col2);
2100  }
2101  else
2102  {
2103  return (col1->type_enum == col2->type_enum
2104  && (pt_collection_assignable (parser, col1, col2) || pt_collection_assignable (parser, col2, col1)));
2105  }
2106 }
2107 
2108 /*
2109  * pt_union_compatible () - determine if two select_list items are
2110  * union compatible
2111  * return: 1 if item1 and item2 are union compatible.
2112  * parser(in): the parser context
2113  * item1(in): an element of a select_list or attribute_list
2114  * item2(in): an element of a select_list or attribute_list
2115  * view_definition_context(in):
2116  * is_object_type(in):
2117  *
2118  * Note :
2119  * return 1 if:
2120  * - item1 or item2 is "NA", or
2121  * - item1 and item2 have identical types, or
2122  * - item1 is a literal that can be coerced to item2's type, or
2123  * - item2 is a literal that can be coerced to item1's type.
2124  */
2125 
2126 static PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE
2127 pt_union_compatible (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * item1, PT_NODE * item2, bool view_definition_context,
2128  bool * is_object_type)
2129 {
2130  PT_TYPE_ENUM typ1, typ2, common_type;
2131  PT_NODE *dt1, *dt2, *data_type;
2132  int r;
2133 
2134  typ1 = item1->type_enum;
2135  typ2 = item2->type_enum;
2136  *is_object_type = false;
2137 
2138  if (typ1 == typ2 && typ1 != PT_TYPE_OBJECT && !PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (typ1))
2139  {
2140  if (typ1 == PT_TYPE_NONE) /* is not compatible with anything */
2141  {
2142  return PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX;
2143  }
2144 
2145  if (typ1 == PT_TYPE_MAYBE)
2146  {
2147  /* assume hostvars are compatible */
2148  return PT_UNION_COMP;
2149  }
2150 
2151  if (!view_definition_context)
2152  {
2153  dt1 = item1->data_type;
2154  dt2 = item2->data_type;
2155  common_type = typ1;
2156 
2157  if (dt1 && dt2)
2158  {
2159  /* numeric type, fixed size string type */
2160  if (common_type == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC || PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (common_type))
2161  {
2162  if ((dt1->info.data_type.precision != dt2->info.data_type.precision)
2163  || (dt1->info.data_type.dec_precision != dt2->info.data_type.dec_precision)
2164  || (dt1->info.data_type.units != dt2->info.data_type.units))
2165  {
2166  /* different numeric and fixed size string types are incompatible */
2167  return PT_UNION_INCOMP;
2168  }
2169  }
2170  }
2171  else
2172  {
2173  return PT_UNION_INCOMP;
2174  }
2175  }
2176  return PT_UNION_COMP;
2177  }
2178 
2179  if (typ2 == PT_TYPE_NA || typ2 == PT_TYPE_NULL)
2180  {
2181  /* NA is compatible with any type except PT_TYPE_NONE */
2182  return ((typ1 != PT_TYPE_NONE) ? PT_UNION_COMP : PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX);
2183  }
2184 
2185  if (typ1 == PT_TYPE_NA || typ1 == PT_TYPE_NULL)
2186  {
2187  /* NA is compatible with any type except PT_TYPE_NONE */
2188  return ((typ2 != PT_TYPE_NONE) ? PT_UNION_COMP : PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX);
2189  }
2190 
2191  if (view_definition_context)
2192  {
2193  common_type = typ1;
2194  }
2195  else
2196  {
2197  common_type = pt_common_type (typ1, typ2);
2198  }
2199 
2200  if (common_type == PT_TYPE_NONE) /* not union compatible */
2201  {
2202  return PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX;
2203  }
2204 
2205  if (item1->node_type == PT_VALUE || item2->node_type == PT_VALUE)
2206  {
2207  data_type = NULL;
2208  if (common_type == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC)
2209  {
2210  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO ci1, ci2;
2211 
2212  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (item1, &ci1);
2213  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (item2, &ci2);
2214 
2215  data_type = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
2216  if (data_type == NULL)
2217  {
2218  return PT_UNION_ERROR;
2219  }
2220  data_type->info.data_type.precision =
2221  MAX ((ci1.prec - ci1.scale), (ci2.prec - ci2.scale)) + MAX (ci1.scale, ci2.scale);
2222  data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision = MAX (ci1.scale, ci2.scale);
2223 
2224  if (data_type->info.data_type.precision > DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION)
2225  {
2226  data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision =
2227  (DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION - data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision);
2228  if (data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision < 0)
2229  {
2230  data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision = 0;
2231  }
2232  data_type->info.data_type.precision = DB_MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION;
2233  }
2234  }
2235 
2236  if (item1->type_enum == common_type && item2->type_enum == common_type)
2237  {
2238  return PT_UNION_COMP;
2239  }
2240  else
2241  {
2242  return PT_UNION_INCOMP;
2243  }
2244  }
2245  else if (common_type == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
2246  {
2247  *is_object_type = true;
2248  if ((item1->node_type == PT_NAME && item1->info.name.meta_class == PT_VID_ATTR)
2249  || (item2->node_type == PT_NAME && item2->info.name.meta_class == PT_VID_ATTR))
2250  {
2251  /* system-added OID */
2252  return PT_UNION_COMP;
2253  }
2254  else
2255  {
2256  r = pt_class_compatible (parser, item1, item2, view_definition_context);
2257  return ((r == 1) ? PT_UNION_COMP : PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX);
2258  }
2259  }
2260  else if (PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (common_type))
2261  {
2262  r = pt_collection_compatible (parser, item1, item2, view_definition_context);
2263  return ((r == 1) ? PT_UNION_COMP : PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX);
2264  }
2265 
2266  return PT_UNION_INCOMP; /* not union compatible */
2267 }
2268 
2269 /*
2270  * pt_is_compatible_without_cast () -
2271  * return: true/false
2272  * parser(in):
2273  * dest_type_enum(in):
2274  * dest_prec(in):
2275  * dest_scale(in):
2276  * src(in):
2277  */
2278 static bool
2279 pt_is_compatible_without_cast (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * dest_sci, PT_NODE * src,
2280  bool * is_cast_allowed)
2281 {
2282  assert (dest_sci != NULL);
2283  assert (src != NULL);
2284  assert (is_cast_allowed != NULL);
2285 
2286  *is_cast_allowed = true;
2287 
2288  if (dest_sci->force_cast && dest_sci->type_enum == PT_TYPE_JSON)
2289  {
2290  return false;
2291  }
2292 
2293  if (dest_sci->type_enum != src->type_enum)
2294  {
2295  return false;
2296  }
2297 
2298  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (src->type_enum))
2299  {
2300  if (src->data_type != NULL && src->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id != dest_sci->coll_infer.coll_id)
2301  {
2302  INTL_CODESET att_cs;
2303 
2304  att_cs = (INTL_CODESET) src->data_type->info.data_type.units;
2305 
2306  if (!INTL_CAN_COERCE_CS (att_cs, dest_sci->coll_infer.codeset))
2307  {
2308  *is_cast_allowed = false;
2309  }
2310 
2311  return false;
2312  }
2313  }
2314 
2315  if (PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (dest_sci->type_enum))
2316  {
2317  assert_release (dest_sci->prec != 0);
2318  if (src->data_type && dest_sci->prec == src->data_type->info.data_type.precision)
2319  {
2320  return true;
2321  }
2322  else
2323  {
2324  return false;
2325  }
2326  }
2327  else if (dest_sci->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC)
2328  {
2329  assert_release (dest_sci->prec != 0);
2330  if (src->data_type && dest_sci->prec == src->data_type->info.data_type.precision
2331  && dest_sci->scale == src->data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision)
2332  {
2333  return true;
2334  }
2335  else
2336  {
2337  return false;
2338  }
2339  }
2340  else if (dest_sci->type_enum == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
2341  {
2342  /* enumerations might not have the same domain */
2343  return false;
2344  }
2345  else if (PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (dest_sci->type_enum))
2346  {
2347  /* collections might not have the same domain */
2348  return false;
2349  }
2350 
2351  return true; /* is compatible, no need to cast */
2352 }
2353 
2354 /*
2355  * pt_to_compatible_cast () -
2356  * return:
2357  * parser(in):
2358  * node(in):
2359  * cinfo(in):
2360  */
2361 static PT_NODE *
2362 pt_to_compatible_cast (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo, int num_cinfo)
2363 {
2364  PT_NODE *attrs, *att;
2365  PT_NODE *prev_att, *next_att, *new_att = NULL, *new_dt = NULL;
2366  int i;
2367  bool new_cast_added;
2368  bool need_to_cast;
2369 
2370  assert (parser != NULL);
2371 
2372  if (!node || !pt_is_query (node))
2373  {
2374  return NULL;
2375  }
2376 
2377  if (pt_is_select (node))
2378  {
2379  if (PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (node))
2380  {
2381  node = pt_values_query_to_compatible_cast (parser, node, cinfo, num_cinfo);
2382  }
2383  else
2384  {
2385  attrs = pt_get_select_list (parser, node);
2386  if (attrs == NULL)
2387  {
2388  return NULL;
2389  }
2390 
2391  prev_att = NULL;
2392  for (att = attrs, i = 0; i < num_cinfo && att; att = next_att, i++)
2393  {
2394  bool is_cast_allowed = true;
2395 
2396  new_cast_added = false;
2397 
2398  next_att = att->next; /* save next link */
2399 
2400  need_to_cast = false;
2401  /* find incompatible attr */
2402  if (cinfo[i].idx == i)
2403  {
2404  if (!pt_is_compatible_without_cast (parser, &(cinfo[i]), att, &is_cast_allowed))
2405  {
2406  need_to_cast = true;
2407 
2408  /* assertion check */
2409  if (need_to_cast)
2410  {
2411  if (PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (att->type_enum) || att->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC)
2412  {
2413  if (att->data_type == NULL)
2414  {
2415  assert_release (att->data_type != NULL);
2416  return NULL;
2417  }
2418  }
2419  }
2420  }
2421  }
2422 
2423  if (need_to_cast)
2424  {
2425  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO att_cinfo;
2426 
2427  if (!is_cast_allowed)
2428  {
2429  return NULL;
2430  }
2431 
2432  memcpy (&att_cinfo, &(cinfo[i]), sizeof (att_cinfo));
2433 
2434  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (att->type_enum) && att->data_type != NULL)
2435  {
2436  /* use collation and codeset of original attribute the values from cinfo are not usable */
2437  att_cinfo.coll_infer.coll_id = att->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id;
2438  att_cinfo.coll_infer.codeset = (INTL_CODESET) att->data_type->info.data_type.units;
2439  }
2440 
2441  new_att = pt_make_cast_with_compatible_info (parser, att, next_att, &att_cinfo, &new_cast_added);
2442  if (new_att == NULL)
2443  {
2444  goto out_of_mem;
2445  }
2446 
2447  if (new_cast_added)
2448  {
2449  att = new_att;
2450  }
2451 
2452  if (prev_att == NULL)
2453  {
2454  node->info.query.q.select.list = att;
2455  node->type_enum = att->type_enum;
2456  if (node->data_type)
2457  {
2458  parser_free_tree (parser, node->data_type);
2459  }
2460  node->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, att->data_type);
2461  }
2462  else
2463  {
2464  prev_att->next = att;
2465  }
2466  }
2467 
2468  prev_att = att;
2469  }
2470  }
2471  }
2472  else
2473  { /* PT_UNION, PT_DIFFERENCE, PT_INTERSECTION */
2474  if (!pt_to_compatible_cast (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg1, cinfo, num_cinfo)
2475  || !pt_to_compatible_cast (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg2, cinfo, num_cinfo))
2476  {
2477  return NULL;
2478  }
2479 
2480  if (node->data_type)
2481  {
2482  parser_free_tree (parser, node->data_type);
2483  }
2484  node->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg1->data_type);
2485  }
2486 
2487  return node;
2488 
2489 out_of_mem:
2490  if (new_att)
2491  {
2492  parser_free_tree (parser, new_att);
2493  }
2494 
2495  if (new_dt)
2496  {
2497  parser_free_tree (parser, new_dt);
2498  }
2499 
2500  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
2501  return NULL;
2502 }
2503 
2504 /*
2505  * pt_get_compatible_info_from_node () -
2506  * return:
2507  * att(in):
2508  * cinfo(out):
2509  */
2510 static void
2511 pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (const PT_NODE * att, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo)
2512 {
2513  assert (cinfo != NULL);
2514 
2515  cinfo->coll_infer.coll_id = -1;
2516  cinfo->coll_infer.codeset = INTL_CODESET_NONE;
2517  cinfo->coll_infer.coerc_level = PT_COLLATION_NOT_COERC;
2518  cinfo->coll_infer.can_force_cs = false;
2519  cinfo->prec = cinfo->scale = 0;
2520  cinfo->ref_att = att;
2521  cinfo->force_cast = false;
2522 
2523  cinfo->type_enum = att->type_enum;
2524 
2525  switch (att->type_enum)
2526  {
2527  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
2528  cinfo->prec = 6;
2529  cinfo->scale = 0;
2530  break;
2531  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
2532  cinfo->prec = 10;
2533  cinfo->scale = 0;
2534  break;
2535  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
2536  cinfo->prec = 19;
2537  cinfo->scale = 0;
2538  break;
2539  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
2540  cinfo->prec = (att->data_type) ? att->data_type->info.data_type.precision : 0;
2541  cinfo->scale = (att->data_type) ? att->data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision : 0;
2542  break;
2543  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
2544  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
2545  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
2546  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
2547  cinfo->prec = (att->data_type) ? att->data_type->info.data_type.precision : 0;
2548  cinfo->scale = 0;
2549  break;
2550  default:
2551  break;
2552  }
2553 
2554  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (att->type_enum))
2555  {
2556  (void) pt_get_collation_info ((PT_NODE *) att, &(cinfo->coll_infer));
2557  }
2558 }
2559 
2560 /*
2561  * pt_get_common_type_for_union () -
2562  * return:
2563  * parser(in):
2564  * att1(in):
2565  * att2(in):
2566  * cinfo(out):
2567  * idx(in):
2568  * need_cast(out):
2569  */
2570 static PT_NODE *
2571 pt_get_common_type_for_union (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * att1, PT_NODE * att2, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo,
2572  int idx, bool * need_cast)
2573 {
2574  PT_NODE *dt1, *dt2;
2575  PT_TYPE_ENUM common_type;
2576  bool is_compatible = false;
2577 
2578  dt1 = att1->data_type;
2579  dt2 = att2->data_type;
2580 
2581  if ((PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (att1->type_enum) && att2->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MAYBE)
2582  || (PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (att2->type_enum) && att1->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MAYBE))
2583  {
2584  common_type = (att1->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MAYBE ? att2->type_enum : att1->type_enum);
2585  }
2586  else
2587  {
2588  common_type = pt_common_type (att1->type_enum, att2->type_enum);
2589  }
2590 
2591  if (common_type != PT_TYPE_NONE)
2592  {
2593  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO att1_info, att2_info;
2594  /* save attr idx and compatible type */
2595  cinfo->idx = idx;
2596 
2597  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (att1, &att1_info);
2598  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (att2, &att2_info);
2599 
2600  is_compatible = pt_update_compatible_info (parser, cinfo, common_type, &att1_info, &att2_info);
2601 
2602  if (is_compatible)
2603  {
2604  *need_cast = true;
2605  }
2606  }
2607 
2608  if (!is_compatible)
2609  {
2610  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNION_INCOMPATIBLE,
2611  pt_short_print (parser, att1), pt_short_print (parser, att2));
2612  return NULL;
2613  }
2614 
2615  return att1;
2616 }
2617 
2618 /*
2619  * pt_check_union_compatibility () - check two query_specs for
2620  * union compatibility
2621  * return: node on success, NULL otherwise.
2622  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive qry1 and qry2
2623  * node(in): a query node
2624  *
2625  * Note :
2626  * the definition of union compatible is: same number of pairwise
2627  * union-compatible attributes from the two query_specs.
2628  * two vclass compatible attributes are considered union-compatible.
2629  */
2630 
2631 PT_NODE *
2632 pt_check_union_compatibility (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
2633 {
2634  PT_NODE *attrs1, *attrs2, *result = node;
2635  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2;
2636  int cnt1, cnt2;
2637  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo = NULL;
2638  bool need_cast;
2639 
2640  assert (parser != NULL);
2641 
2642  if (node == NULL
2643  || (node->node_type != PT_UNION && node->node_type != PT_INTERSECTION && node->node_type != PT_DIFFERENCE
2644  && node->node_type != PT_CTE))
2645  {
2646  return NULL;
2647  }
2648 
2649  if (node->node_type == PT_CTE)
2650  {
2651  arg1 = node->info.cte.non_recursive_part;
2652  arg2 = node->info.cte.recursive_part;
2653  }
2654  else
2655  {
2656  arg1 = node->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
2657  arg2 = node->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
2658  }
2659 
2660  attrs1 = pt_get_select_list (parser, arg1);
2661  if (attrs1 == NULL)
2662  {
2663  return NULL;
2664  }
2665  attrs2 = pt_get_select_list (parser, arg2);
2666  if (attrs2 == NULL)
2667  {
2668  return NULL;
2669  }
2670 
2671  cnt1 = pt_length_of_select_list (attrs1, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
2672  cnt2 = pt_length_of_select_list (attrs2, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
2673 
2674  if (cnt1 != cnt2)
2675  {
2676  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, attrs1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ARITY_MISMATCH, cnt1, cnt2);
2677  return NULL;
2678  }
2679 
2680  /* get compatible info */
2681  cinfo = pt_get_compatible_info (parser, node, attrs1, attrs2, &need_cast);
2682  if (cinfo == NULL && need_cast)
2683  {
2684  result = NULL;
2685  }
2686 
2687  /* convert attrs type to compatible type */
2688  if (result && need_cast == true)
2689  {
2690  if (!pt_to_compatible_cast (parser, arg1, cinfo, cnt1) || !pt_to_compatible_cast (parser, arg2, cinfo, cnt1))
2691  {
2692  result = NULL;
2693  }
2694  else
2695  {
2696  /* copy the new data_type to the actual UNION node */
2697  if (node->data_type != NULL)
2698  {
2699  parser_free_tree (parser, node->data_type);
2700  }
2701 
2702  node->data_type = parser_copy_tree (parser, arg1->data_type);
2703  }
2704  }
2705 
2706  if (cinfo)
2707  {
2708  free_and_init (cinfo);
2709  }
2710 
2711  return result;
2712 }
2713 
2714 /*
2715  * pt_check_type_compatibility_of_values_query () - check rows for
2716  * values query compatibility
2717  * return: node on success, NULL otherwise.
2718  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive qry1 and qry2
2719  * node(in): a query node
2720  *
2721  * Note :
2722  * the definition of values query compatible is: same number of
2723  * attributes from rows.
2724  * every two rows' compatible attributes are considered union-compatible.
2725  */
2726 PT_NODE *
2727 pt_check_type_compatibility_of_values_query (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
2728 {
2729  PT_NODE *node_list, *result = node;
2730  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo = NULL;
2731  bool need_cast = false;
2732  PT_NODE *attrs;
2733  int count;
2734 
2735  assert (parser);
2736 
2737  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_SELECT || !PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (node))
2738  {
2739  return NULL;
2740  }
2741 
2742  node_list = node->info.query.q.select.list;
2743  if (node_list == NULL)
2744  {
2745  return NULL;
2746  }
2747  attrs = node_list->info.node_list.list;
2748 
2749  node_list = node_list->next;
2750  /* only one row */
2751  if (node_list == NULL)
2752  {
2753  return result;
2754  }
2755 
2756  count = pt_length_of_select_list (attrs, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
2757 
2758  /* get compatible_info for cast */
2759  cinfo = pt_get_values_query_compatible_info (parser, node, &need_cast);
2760 
2761  if (cinfo == NULL && need_cast)
2762  {
2763  result = NULL;
2764  goto end;
2765  }
2766 
2767  /* convert attrs type to compatible type */
2768  if (need_cast && cinfo != NULL)
2769  {
2770  result = pt_values_query_to_compatible_cast (parser, node, cinfo, count);
2771  }
2772 
2773 end:
2774  if (cinfo)
2775  {
2776  free_and_init (cinfo);
2777  }
2778 
2779  return result;
2780 }
2781 
2782 /*
2783  * pt_check_union_values_query_compatibility () - check compatibility
2784  * when union values query
2785  * return: node on success, NULL otherwise.
2786  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive qry1 and qry2
2787  * node(in): a query node
2788  *
2789  * Note :
2790  * please see pt_check_union_compatibility
2791  * and pt_check_type_compatibility_of_values_query
2792  */
2793 PT_NODE *
2794 pt_check_union_type_compatibility_of_values_query (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
2795 {
2796  PT_NODE *attrs1, *attrs2, *att1, *att2, *result = node;
2797  int cnt1, cnt2, i;
2798  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo = NULL;
2799  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo_arg1 = NULL;
2800  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo_arg2 = NULL;
2801  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo_arg3 = NULL;
2802  bool need_cast;
2803  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2, *tmp;
2804  bool is_compatible;
2805 
2806  assert (parser != NULL);
2807 
2808  if (!node
2809  || !(node->node_type == PT_UNION || node->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION || node->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE
2810  || node->node_type == PT_CTE))
2811  {
2812  return NULL;
2813  }
2814 
2815  if (node->node_type == PT_CTE)
2816  {
2817  arg1 = node->info.cte.non_recursive_part;
2818  arg2 = node->info.cte.recursive_part;
2819  }
2820  else
2821  {
2822  arg1 = node->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
2823  arg2 = node->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
2824  }
2825 
2826  if (!arg1 || !arg2 || !(attrs1 = pt_get_select_list (parser, arg1)) || !(attrs2 = pt_get_select_list (parser, arg2)))
2827  {
2828  return NULL;
2829  }
2830 
2831  cnt1 = pt_length_of_select_list (attrs1, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
2832  cnt2 = pt_length_of_select_list (attrs2, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
2833  if (cnt1 != cnt2)
2834  {
2835  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, attrs1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ARITY_MISMATCH, cnt1, cnt2);
2836  return NULL;
2837  }
2838 
2839  if (PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (arg1) && PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (arg2)) /* two values query */
2840  {
2841  need_cast = false;
2842  cinfo_arg1 = pt_get_values_query_compatible_info (parser, arg1, &need_cast);
2843  if (cinfo_arg1 == NULL && need_cast)
2844  {
2845  result = NULL;
2846  goto end;
2847  }
2848 
2849  need_cast = false;
2850  cinfo_arg2 = pt_get_values_query_compatible_info (parser, arg2, &need_cast);
2851  if (cinfo_arg2 == NULL && need_cast)
2852  {
2853  result = NULL;
2854  goto end;
2855  }
2856 
2857  /* compare cinfo_arg1 and cinfo_arg2 save the compatible cinfo in cinfo_arg1 */
2858  if (cinfo_arg1 != NULL && cinfo_arg2 != NULL)
2859  {
2860  is_compatible = true;
2861 
2862  for (i = 0, att1 = attrs1, att2 = attrs2; i < cnt1; ++i, att1 = att1->next, att2 = att2->next)
2863  {
2864  is_compatible = pt_combine_compatible_info (parser, cinfo_arg1 + i, cinfo_arg2 + i, att1, att2, i);
2865  if (!is_compatible)
2866  {
2867  result = NULL;
2868  goto end;
2869  }
2870  }
2871  }
2872  else if (cinfo_arg2 != NULL)
2873  {
2874  cinfo_arg1 = cinfo_arg2;
2875  cinfo_arg2 = NULL;
2876  }
2877 
2878  /* compare the select list */
2879  cinfo_arg3 = pt_get_compatible_info (parser, node, attrs1, attrs2, &need_cast);
2880  if (cinfo_arg3 == NULL && need_cast)
2881  {
2882  result = NULL;
2883  goto end;
2884  }
2885 
2886  if (need_cast)
2887  {
2888  if (cinfo_arg1 != NULL)
2889  {
2890  is_compatible = true;
2891  for (i = 0, att1 = attrs1, att2 = attrs2; i < cnt1; ++i, att1 = att1->next, att2 = att2->next)
2892  {
2893  is_compatible = pt_combine_compatible_info (parser, cinfo_arg1 + i, cinfo_arg3 + i, att1, att2, i);
2894  if (!is_compatible)
2895  {
2896  result = NULL;
2897  goto end;
2898  }
2899  }
2900  }
2901  else
2902  {
2903  cinfo_arg1 = cinfo_arg3;
2904  cinfo_arg3 = NULL;
2905  }
2906  }
2907 
2908  cinfo = cinfo_arg1;
2909  }
2910  else if (PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (arg1) || PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (arg2)) /* one values query, one select */
2911  {
2912  /* make arg1->is_value_query==1 */
2913  if (PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (arg2))
2914  {
2915  tmp = arg1;
2916  arg1 = arg2;
2917  arg2 = tmp;
2918  }
2919 
2920  /* arg1 is the values query */
2921  need_cast = false;
2922  cinfo_arg1 = pt_get_values_query_compatible_info (parser, arg1, &need_cast);
2923  if (cinfo_arg1 == NULL && need_cast)
2924  {
2925  result = NULL;
2926  goto end;
2927  }
2928 
2929  /* get the cinfo of select */
2930  attrs1 = pt_get_select_list (parser, arg1);
2931  attrs2 = pt_get_select_list (parser, arg2);
2932  cinfo_arg2 = pt_get_compatible_info (parser, node, attrs1, attrs2, &need_cast);
2933  if (cinfo_arg2 == NULL && need_cast)
2934  {
2935  result = NULL;
2936  goto end;
2937  }
2938 
2939  if (need_cast)
2940  {
2941  /* compare cinfo_arg1 and cinfo_arg2 save the compatible cinfo in cinfo_arg1 */
2942  if (cinfo_arg1 != NULL)
2943  {
2944  is_compatible = true;
2945  for (i = 0, att1 = attrs1, att2 = attrs2; i < cnt1; ++i, att1 = att1->next, att2 = att2->next)
2946  {
2947  is_compatible = pt_combine_compatible_info (parser, cinfo_arg1 + i, cinfo_arg2 + i, att1, att2, i);
2948  if (!is_compatible)
2949  {
2950  result = NULL;
2951  goto end;
2952  }
2953  }
2954  }
2955  else
2956  {
2957  cinfo_arg1 = cinfo_arg2;
2958  cinfo_arg2 = NULL;
2959  }
2960  cinfo = cinfo_arg1;
2961  }
2962  }
2963  else
2964  {
2965  /* should not be here */
2966  assert (false);
2967  }
2968 
2969  /* make the cast */
2970  if (cinfo != NULL)
2971  {
2972  if (pt_to_compatible_cast (parser, arg1, cinfo, cnt1) == NULL
2973  || pt_to_compatible_cast (parser, arg2, cinfo, cnt1) == NULL)
2974  {
2975  result = NULL;
2976  }
2977  }
2978 
2979 end:
2980  if (cinfo_arg1)
2981  {
2982  free_and_init (cinfo_arg1);
2983  }
2984  if (cinfo_arg2)
2985  {
2986  free_and_init (cinfo_arg2);
2987  }
2988  if (cinfo_arg3)
2989  {
2990  free_and_init (cinfo_arg3);
2991  }
2992 
2993  return result;
2994 }
