3057 /*
3058  * pt_append_statements_on_add_attribute () -
3059  * return: return a list of statement string or null on error

3062  * stmt_node(in): parse tree for a create or alter statement

3066  *
3067  * Note :
3068  * rewrite rule is like this.

3102

3263 /*
3264  * pt_append_statements_on_insert () -
3265  * return: return a list of statement string or null on error
3266  * parser(in): parser context
3267  * stmt_node(in): parse tree for a insert statement
3268  * class_name(in): class name to do insert
3269  * attr_name(in): attr name to do insert

3271  * parameter(in): output parameter for the insert statement
3272  *
3273  * Note :
3274  * rewrite rule is like this.
3275  * insert into c (..., a, ...) values (..., v, ...);
3276  * => (main) insert into c (..., a.object, ...) values (..., null, ...)

3281 static PT_NODE *

3299  return NULL;
3300  }
3301 
3302  if (parameter && parameter->info.name.original)
3303  {
3304  sprintf (param1_name, "%s", parameter->info.name.original);
3305  }
3306  else
3307  {
3308  sprintf (param1_name, "%s_%p", "p1", stmt_node);
3309  }
3310  sprintf (param2_name, "%s_%p", "p2", stmt_node);

3374 /*
3375  * pt_append_statements_on_update () -
3376  * return: return a list of statement string or null on error
3377  * parser(in): parser context
3378  * stmt_node(in): parse tree for a update statement
3379  * class_name(in): class name to do update
3380  * attr_name(in): attr name to do update

3383  * where_ptr(in/out): pointer of a parse tree for the where clause of

3385  *
3386  * Note :
3387  * rewrite rule is like this.
3388  * update c set ..., a = v, ... where condtion
3389  * => (pre) select (select sum(set{a.object}) from c where condition)
3390  * into :obj1 from db_root
3391  * => (pre) update c_text_a_ set tdata = v where tid in

3396 static PT_NODE *
3397 pt_append_statements_on_update (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt_node, const char *class_name,
3398  const char *attr_name, const char *alias_name, PT_NODE * value, PT_NODE ** where_ptr)
3399 {
3400  PT_NODE *s1, *s2, *list;
3401  PT_NODE *save_next;
3402  DB_VALUE *param1_dbvalp;

3404  char param1_name[256];
3405  char alias1_name[256];
3406  unsigned int save_custom;
3407 
3408  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, class_name);
3409  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, text_class_name, "_text_");
3410  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, text_class_name, attr_name);
3411

3413  {
3414  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_EXIST, text_class_name);
3415  return NULL;
3416  }

3418  sprintf (param1_name, "%s_%p", "p1", attr_name);
3419  sprintf (alias1_name, "%s_%p", "c1", attr_name);

3422  parser->custom_print = parser->custom_print | PT_INTERNAL_PRINT;

3427  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, class_name);

3464  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, alias1_name);

3467  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " ");
3468  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, alias1_name);
3469  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " WHERE [");
3470  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, attr_name);
3471  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, "].OBJECT IN :");
3472  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, param1_name);
3473  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, ")");
3474  s2 = pt_make_string_value (parser, stmt);
3475 
3476  parser->custom_print = save_custom;
3477 
3478  /* redefine where clause if the clause is redefined at first */
3479  if ((*where_ptr) == NULL || (*where_ptr)->etc != (*where_ptr))
3480  {
3481  if (*where_ptr)
3482  {
3483  parser_free_tree (parser, *where_ptr);
3484  }
3485  *where_ptr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
3486  if (*where_ptr == NULL)
3487  {
3488  return NULL;
3489  }
3490  (*where_ptr)->info.expr.op = PT_IS_IN;
3491  (*where_ptr)->info.expr.arg1 = pt_name (parser, attr_name);
3492  (*where_ptr)->info.expr.arg2 = pt_make_parameter (parser, param1_name, 0);
3493  (*where_ptr)->etc = (*where_ptr); /* mark to prevent multiple rewrite */
3494  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG ((*where_ptr)->info.expr.arg1, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL);
3495  }
3496 
3497  /* redefine the assignment value */
3498  save_next = value->next;
3499  parser_free_subtrees (parser, value);
3500  parser_init_node (value);
3501  value->node_type = PT_NAME;
3502  value->info.name.original = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, attr_name);
3503  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (value, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL);
3504  value->next = save_next;
3505 
3506  s1->etc = NULL;
3507  s2->etc = NULL;
3508  s1->next = s2;
3509 
3510  list = stmt_node->info.update.internal_stmts;
3511  if (list == NULL)
3512  {
3513  stmt_node->info.insert.internal_stmts = s1;
3514  }
3515  else
3516  {
3517  while (list->next != NULL)
3518  list = list->next;
3519  list->next = s1;
3520  }
3521  list = s1;
3522 
3523  parser->custom_print = save_custom;
3524 
3525  return list;
3526 }
3527 
3528 /*
3529  * pt_append_statements_on_delete () -
3530  * return: return a list of statement string or null on error
3531  * parser(in): parser context
3532  * stmt_node(in): parse tree for a delete statement
3533  * class_name(in): class name to do delete
3534  * attr_name(in): attr name to do delete
3535  * alias_name(in): alias for the class name
3536  * where_ptr(in/out): pointer of a parse tree for the where clause of
3537  * the delete statement
3538  *
3539  * Note :
3540  * rewrite rule is like this.
3541  * delete from c where condition;
3542  * => (pre) select (select sum(set{a.object}) from c where condition)
3543  * into :obj1 from db_root
3544  * => (pre) delete from c_text_a_ where tid in (select c from c where
3545  * a.object in :obj1)
3546  * => (main) delete from c where a.object in :obj1
3547  */
3548 
3549 static PT_NODE *
3550 pt_append_statements_on_delete (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt_node, const char *class_name,
3551  const char *attr_name, const char *alias_name, PT_NODE ** where_ptr)
3552 {
3553  PT_NODE *s1, *s2, *list;
3554  DB_VALUE *param1_dbvalp;
3555  char *text_class_name = NULL, *stmt = NULL;
3556  char param1_name[256];
3557  char alias1_name[256];
3558  unsigned int save_custom;
3559 
3560  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, class_name);
3561  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, text_class_name, "_text_");
3562  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, text_class_name, attr_name);
3563 
3564  if (!db_find_class (text_class_name))
3565  {
3566  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_EXIST, text_class_name);
3567  return NULL;
3568  }
3569 
3570  sprintf (param1_name, "%s_%p", "p1", attr_name);
3571  sprintf (alias1_name, "%s_%p", "c1", attr_name);
3572 
3573  save_custom = parser->custom_print;
3574  parser->custom_print = parser->custom_print | PT_INTERNAL_PRINT;
3575 
3576  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, "SELECT {null}+(SELECT SUM(SET{[");
3577  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, attr_name);
3578  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, "].OBJECT}) FROM ");
3579  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, class_name);
3580  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " ");
3581  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, alias_name);
3582  if (*where_ptr)
3583  {
3584  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " WHERE ");
3585  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, parser_print_tree (parser, *where_ptr));
3586  }
3587  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, ") INTO :");
3588  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, param1_name);
3589  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " FROM db_root;");
3590  s1 = pt_make_string_value (parser, stmt);
3591 
3592  parser->custom_print = save_custom;
3593 
3594  /* To resolve out parameter at compile time, put the parameter into the label table with null value */
3595  param1_dbvalp = db_value_create ();
3596  if (param1_dbvalp == NULL)
3597  {
3598  return NULL;
3599  }
3600  else
3601  {
3602  db_make_set (param1_dbvalp, db_set_create_basic (NULL, NULL));
3603  if (pt_associate_label_with_value (param1_name, param1_dbvalp) != NO_ERROR)
3604  {
3605  return NULL;
3606  }
3607  }
3608  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, "DELETE FROM ");
3609  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, text_class_name);
3610  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " WHERE tid IN (SELECT ");
3611  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, alias1_name);
3612  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " FROM ");
3613  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, class_name);
3614  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " ");
3615  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, alias1_name);
3616  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, " WHERE [");
3617  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, attr_name);
3618  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, "].OBJECT IN :");
3619  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, param1_name);
3620  stmt = pt_append_string (parser, stmt, ")");
3621  s2 = pt_make_string_value (parser, stmt);
3622 
3623  /* redefine where clause if the clause is redefined at first */
3624  if ((*where_ptr) == NULL || (*where_ptr)->etc != (*where_ptr))
3625  {
3626  if (*where_ptr)
3627  {
3628  parser_free_tree (parser, *where_ptr);
3629  }
3630  if ((*where_ptr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR)) == NULL)
3631  {
3632  return NULL;
3633  }
3634  (*where_ptr)->info.expr.op = PT_IS_IN;
3635  (*where_ptr)->info.expr.arg1 = pt_name (parser, attr_name);
3636  (*where_ptr)->info.expr.arg2 = pt_make_parameter (parser, param1_name, 0);
3637  (*where_ptr)->etc = (*where_ptr); /* mark to prevent multiple rewrite */
3638  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG ((*where_ptr)->info.expr.arg1, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL);
3639  }
3640 
3641  s1->etc = NULL;
3642  s2->etc = NULL;
3643  s1->next = s2;
3644 
3645  list = stmt_node->info.delete_.internal_stmts;
3646  if (list == NULL)
3647  {
3648  stmt_node->info.insert.internal_stmts = s1;
3649  }
3650  else
3651  {
3652  while (list->next != NULL)
3653  list = list->next;
3654  list->next = s1;
3655  }
3656  list = s1;
3657 
3658  return list;
3659 }
3660 
3661 /*
3662  * pt_resolve_insert_external () - create internal statements and
3663  * rewrite a value to insert for TEXT typed attrs on into clause
3664  * of a insert statement
3665  * return: none
3666  * parser(in): parser context
3667  * insert(in): parse tree of a insert statement
3668  */
3669 static void
3670 pt_resolve_insert_external (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * insert)
3671 {
3672  PT_NODE *a, *v, *lhs, *rhs, *save_next;
3673  PT_NODE *spec, *entity, *value;
3674  const char *class_name, *attr_name;
3675  char *text_class_name = NULL, param1_name[256];
3676 
3677  spec = insert->info.insert.spec;
3678  entity = (spec ? spec->info.spec.entity_name : NULL);
3679  class_name = (entity ? entity->info.name.original : NULL);
3680  if (class_name == NULL)
3681  {
3682  return;
3683  }
3684 
3685  a = insert->info.insert.attr_list;
3686 
3687  if (insert->info.insert.is_value == PT_IS_SUBQUERY)
3688  {
3689  for (; a != NULL; a = a->next)
3690  {
3691  if (PT_IS_DOT_NODE (a))
3692  {
3693  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, a, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CANT_COERCE_TO, "subquery", "text");
3694  return;
3695  }
3696  }
3697  }
3698  else if (insert->info.insert.is_value == PT_IS_DEFAULT_VALUE)
3699  {
3700  for (; a != NULL; a = a->next)
3701  {
3702  if (PT_IS_DOT_NODE (a))
3703  {
3704  /* replace "attr.tdata" with "attr" */
3705  save_next = a->next;
3706  lhs = a->info.expr.arg1;
3707  rhs = a->info.expr.arg2;
3708  *a = *lhs;
3709  a->next = save_next;
3710  parser_init_node (lhs); /* not to free subtrees */
3711  parser_free_tree (parser, lhs);
3712  parser_free_tree (parser, rhs);
3713 
3714  /* make a default value */
3715  attr_name = a->info.name.original;
3716  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, NULL, class_name);
3717  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, text_class_name, "_text_");
3718  text_class_name = pt_append_string (parser, text_class_name, attr_name);
3719 
3720  if ((value = pt_make_default_value (parser, text_class_name, "tdata")) == NULL)
3721  {
3722  goto exit_on_error;
3723  }
3724 
3725  if (insert->info.insert.into_var == NULL)
3726  {
3727  sprintf (param1_name, "p1_%p", insert);
3728  insert->info.insert.into_var = pt_make_parameter (parser, param1_name, 1);
3729  }
3730  if (pt_append_statements_on_insert (parser, insert, class_name, attr_name, value,
3731  insert->info.insert.into_var) == NULL)
3732  {
3733  goto exit_on_error;
3734  }
3735  }
3736  }
3737  }
3738  else
3739  {
3740  v = insert->info.insert.value_clause;
3741  for (; a != NULL && v != NULL; a = a->next, v = v->next)
3742  {
3743  if (PT_IS_DOT_NODE (a))
3744  {
3745  /* replace "attr.tdata" to "attr" */
3746  save_next = a->next;
3747  lhs = a->info.expr.arg1;
3748  rhs = a->info.expr.arg2;
3749  *a = *lhs;
3750  a->next = save_next;
3751  parser_init_node (lhs); /* not to free subtrees */
3752  parser_free_tree (parser, lhs);
3753  parser_free_tree (parser, rhs);
3754 
3755  /* if (pt_assignment_compatible(parser, attr, v)) */
3756  attr_name = a->info.name.original;
3757  if (a->type_enum != v->type_enum)
3758  {
3759  if (insert->info.insert.into_var == NULL)
3760  {
3761  sprintf (param1_name, "p1_%p", insert);
3762  insert->info.insert.into_var = pt_make_parameter (parser, param1_name, 1);
3763  }
3764  if (pt_append_statements_on_insert (parser, insert, class_name, attr_name, v,
3765  insert->info.insert.into_var) == NULL)
3766  {
3767  goto exit_on_error;
3768  }
3769  }
3770  }
3771  }
3772  }
3773  return;
3774 
3775 exit_on_error:
3776 
3777  PT_ERRORm (parser, insert, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3778  return;
3779 }
3780 
3781 /*
3782  * pt_resolve_update_external () - create internal statements and redefine
3783  * a value to do update for TEXT typed attrs on assignment clause of
3784  * a update statement
3785  * return: none
3786  * parser(in): parser context
3787  * update(in): parse tree of a update statement
3788  */
3789 static void
3790 pt_resolve_update_external (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * update)
3791 {
3792  PT_NODE *a, *lhs, *rhs;
3793  PT_NODE *spec, *entity, *alias;
3794  DB_OBJECT *db_obj;
3795  DB_ATTRIBUTE *db_att;
3796  const char *class_name, *attr_name, *alias_name;
3797 
3798  spec = update->info.update.spec;
3799  entity = (spec ? spec->info.spec.entity_name : NULL);
3800  class_name = (entity ? entity->info.name.original : NULL);
3801  alias = (spec ? spec->info.spec.range_var : NULL);
3802  alias_name = (alias ? alias->info.name.original : NULL);
3803 
3804  if (class_name && (db_obj = db_find_class (class_name)))
3805  {
3806  for (a = update->info.update.assignment; a; a = a->next)
3807  {
3808  if (PT_IS_ASSIGN_NODE (a) && (lhs = a->info.expr.arg1) != NULL && (rhs = a->info.expr.arg2) != NULL)
3809  {
3810  if (PT_IS_NAME_NODE (lhs) && !PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (lhs, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL))
3811  {
3812  attr_name = lhs->info.name.original;
3813  db_att = db_get_attribute (db_obj, attr_name);
3814 
3815  if (db_att && sm_has_text_domain (db_att, 0))
3816  {
3817  PT_NAME_INFO_SET_FLAG (lhs, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL);
3818  if (pt_append_statements_on_update (parser, update, class_name, attr_name, alias_name, rhs,
3819  &update->info.update.search_cond) == NULL)
3820  {
3821  goto exit_on_error;
3822  }
3823  }
3824  }
3825  }
3826  }
3827  }
3828 
3829  return;
3830 
3831 exit_on_error:
3832 
3833  PT_ERRORm (parser, update, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3834  return;
3835 }
3836 
3837 /*
3838  * pt_resolve_delete_external () - create internal statements
3839  * for TEXT typed attrs defined in class to do delete statement
3840  * return: none
3841  * parser(in): parser context
3842  * delete(in): parse tree of a delete statement
3843  */
3844 static void
3845 pt_resolve_delete_external (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * delete)
3846 {
3847  PT_NODE *spec, *entity, *alias;
3848  DB_OBJECT *db_obj;
3849  DB_ATTRIBUTE *db_att;
3850  const char *class_name, *alias_name;
3851 
3852  spec = delete->info.delete_.spec;
3853  entity = (spec ? spec->info.spec.entity_name : NULL);
3854  class_name = (entity ? entity->info.name.original : NULL);
3855  alias = (spec ? spec->info.spec.range_var : NULL);
3856  alias_name = (alias ? alias->info.name.original : NULL);
3857 
3858  if (class_name && (db_obj = db_find_class (class_name)))
3859  {
3860  db_att = db_get_attributes_force (db_obj);
3861  while (db_att)
3862  {
3863  if (sm_has_text_domain (db_att, 0))
3864  {
3865  if (pt_append_statements_on_delete (parser, delete, class_name, db_attribute_name (db_att), alias_name,
3866  &delete->info.delete_.search_cond) == NULL)
3867  {
3868  goto exit_on_error;
3869  }
3870  }
3871  db_att = db_attribute_next (db_att);
3872  }
3873  }
3874 
3875  return;
3876 
3877 exit_on_error:
3878 
3879  PT_ERRORm (parser, delete, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3880  return;
3881 }
3882 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */

3884 /*
3885  * pt_resolve_default_external () - create internal statements
3886  * for a TEXT typed attr to alter the default value
3887  * return: none
3888  * parser(in): parser context
3889  * alter(in): parse tree of a alter statement
3890  */
3891 static void
3892 pt_resolve_default_external (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * alter)
3893 {
3894  PT_NODE *attr_name_list, *data_default_list, *stmt_list;
3895  PT_NODE *a, *v;
3896  PT_NODE *entity_name;
3897  DB_OBJECT *class_;
3898  DB_ATTRIBUTE *attr;
3899  const char *class_name;
3900 
3901  attr_name_list = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.ch_attr_def.attr_name_list;
3902  data_default_list = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.ch_attr_def.data_default_list;
3903 
3904  entity_name = alter->info.alter.entity_name;
3905  class_name = (entity_name ? entity_name->info.name.original : NULL);
3906  if (class_name && (class_ = db_find_class (class_name)) != NULL)
3907  {
3908  stmt_list = alter->info.alter.internal_stmts;
3909  for (a = attr_name_list, v = data_default_list; a != NULL && v != NULL; a = a->next, v = v->next)
3910  {
3911  attr = db_get_attribute (class_, a->info.name.original);
3912 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
3913  if (attr && sm_has_text_domain (attr, 0))
3914  {
3915  stmt_list =
3916  pt_append_statements_on_change_default (parser, stmt_list, alter, class_name, a->info.name.original, v);
3917  if (stmt_list == NULL)
3918  {
3919  PT_ERRORm (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
3920  }
3921  }
3922 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
3923  }
3924  alter->info.alter.internal_stmts = stmt_list;
3925  }
3926 
3927  return;
3928 }
3929 
3930 /*
3931  * pt_check_data_default () - checks data_default for semantic errors
3932  *
3933  * result : modified data_default
3934  * parser(in) : parser context
3935  * data_default_list(in) : data default node
3936  */
3937 static PT_NODE *
3938 pt_check_data_default (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * data_default_list)
3939 {
3940  PT_NODE *result;
3941  PT_NODE *default_value;
3942  PT_NODE *save_next;
3943  PT_NODE *node_ptr;
3944  PT_NODE *data_default;
3945  PT_NODE *prev;
3946  bool has_query;
3947 
3948  if (pt_has_error (parser))
3949  {
3950  /* do nothing */
3951  return data_default_list;
3952  }
3953 
3954  if (data_default_list == NULL || data_default_list->node_type != PT_DATA_DEFAULT)
3955  {
3956  /* do nothing */
3957  return data_default_list;
3958  }
3959 
3960  prev = NULL;
3961  has_query = false;
3962  for (data_default = data_default_list; data_default; data_default = data_default->next)
3963  {
3964  save_next = data_default->next;
3965  data_default->next = NULL;
3966 
3967  default_value = data_default->info.data_default.default_value;
3968 
3969  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, default_value, pt_find_query, &has_query, NULL, NULL);
3970  if (has_query)
3971  {
3972  PT_ERRORm (parser, default_value, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
3973  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SUBQUERY_NOT_ALLOWED_IN_DEFAULT_CLAUSE);
3974  /* skip other checks */
3975  goto end;
3976  }
3977 
3978  result = pt_semantic_type (parser, data_default, NULL);
3979  if (result != NULL)
3980  {
3981  /* change data_default */
3982  if (prev)
3983  {
3984  prev->next = result;
3985  }
3986  else
3987  {
3988  data_default_list = result;
3989  }
3990  data_default = result;
3991  }
3992  else
3993  {
3994  /* an error has occurred, skip other checks */
3995  goto end;
3996  }
3997 
3998  node_ptr = NULL;
3999  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, default_value, pt_find_default_expression, &node_ptr, NULL, NULL);
4000  if (node_ptr != NULL && node_ptr != default_value)
4001  {
4002  /* nested default expressions are not supported */
4003  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node_ptr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DEFAULT_NESTED_EXPR_NOT_ALLOWED,
4004  pt_show_binopcode (node_ptr->info.expr.op));
4005  goto end;
4006  }
4007 
4008  if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (default_value) && default_value->info.expr.op == PT_TO_CHAR
4009  && PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (default_value->info.expr.arg1))
4010  {
4011  int op_type = -1;
4012 
4013  if (PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (default_value->info.expr.arg2))
4014  {
4015  /* nested expressions in arg2 are not supported */
4016  op_type = default_value->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.op;
4017  }
4018  else if (node_ptr == NULL)
4019  {
4020  /* nested expressions in arg1 are not supported except sys date, time and user. */
4021  op_type = default_value->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.op;
4022  }
4023 
4024  if (op_type != -1)
4025  {
4026  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node_ptr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DEFAULT_NESTED_EXPR_NOT_ALLOWED,
4027  pt_show_binopcode ((PT_OP_TYPE) op_type));
4028  goto end;
4029  }
4030  }
4031 
4032  node_ptr = NULL;
4033  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, default_value, pt_find_aggregate_function, &node_ptr, NULL, NULL);
4034  if (node_ptr != NULL)
4035  {
4036  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node_ptr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DEFAULT_EXPR_NOT_ALLOWED,
4037  pt_show_function (node_ptr->info.function.function_type));
4038  goto end;
4039  }
4040  end:
4041  data_default->next = save_next;
4042  prev = data_default;
4043  }
4044 
4045  return data_default_list;
4046 }
4047 
4048 /*
4049  * pt_attr_check_default_cs_coll () - checks attribute's collation and
4050  * codeset. If necessary, they are replaced with the
4051  * ones passed as arguments.
4052  *
4053  * parser(in): parser context
4054  * attr(in/out) : data default node
4055  * default_cs(in): codeset of the attribute's class, or override value
4056  * if special value = -1 is given, then charset implied by
4057  * default_coll argument is used
4058  * default_coll(in): collation of the attribute's class, or override value
4059  */
4060 int
4061 pt_attr_check_default_cs_coll (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * attr, int default_cs, int default_coll)
4062 {
4063  int attr_cs = attr->data_type->info.data_type.units;
4064  int attr_coll = attr->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id;
4065  LANG_COLLATION *lc;
4066  int err = NO_ERROR;
4067 
4068  assert (default_coll >= 0);
4069 
4070  if (attr->data_type->info.data_type.has_cs_spec)
4071  {
4072  if (attr->data_type->info.data_type.has_coll_spec == false)
4073  {
4074  /* use binary collation of attribute's charset specifier */
4075  attr_coll = LANG_GET_BINARY_COLLATION (attr_cs);
4076  }
4077  }
4078  else if (attr->data_type->info.data_type.has_coll_spec)
4079  {
4080  lc = lang_get_collation (attr_coll);
4081  assert (lc != NULL);
4082  attr_cs = lc->codeset;
4083  }
4084  else
4085  {
4086  /* attribute does not have a codeset or collation spec; use defaults */
4087  attr_coll = default_coll;
4088  if (default_cs == -1)
4089  {
4090  lc = lang_get_collation (default_coll);
4091  assert (lc != NULL);
4092  attr_cs = lc->codeset;
4093  }
4094  else
4095  {
4096  attr_cs = default_cs;
4097  }
4098  }
4099 
4100  if (attr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION && attr->data_type != NULL)
4101  {
4102  /* coerce each element of enum to actual attribute codeset */
4103  PT_NODE *elem = NULL;
4104 
4105  elem = attr->data_type->info.data_type.enumeration;
4106  while (elem != NULL)
4107  {
4108  assert (elem->node_type == PT_VALUE);
4109  assert (PT_HAS_COLLATION (elem->type_enum));
4110 
4111  if ((elem->data_type != NULL && elem->data_type->info.data_type.units != attr_cs)
4112  || (elem->data_type == NULL && attr_cs != LANG_SYS_CODESET))
4113  {
4114  PT_NODE *dt;
4115 
4116  if (elem->data_type != NULL)
4117  {
4118  dt = parser_copy_tree (parser, elem->data_type);
4119  }
4120  else
4121  {
4122  dt = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
4123  dt->type_enum = elem->type_enum;
4124  dt->info.data_type.precision = DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION;
4125  }
4126  dt->info.data_type.collation_id = attr_coll;
4127  dt->info.data_type.units = attr_cs;
4128 
4129  if (attr_cs == INTL_CODESET_RAW_BYTES)
4130  {
4131  /* conversion from multi-byte to binary must keep text */
4132  if (elem->info.value.data_value.str != NULL)
4133  {
4134  dt->info.data_type.precision = elem->info.value.data_value.str->length;
4135  }
4136  else if (elem->info.value.db_value_is_initialized)
4137  {
4138  dt->info.data_type.precision = db_get_string_size (&(elem->info.value.db_value));
4139  }
4140  }
4141 
4142  err = pt_coerce_value (parser, elem, elem, elem->type_enum, dt);
4143  if (err != NO_ERROR)
4144  {
4145  return err;
4146  }
4147 
4148  parser_free_tree (parser, dt);
4149  }
4150  elem = elem->next;
4151  }
4152  }
4153 
4154  attr->data_type->info.data_type.units = attr_cs;
4155  attr->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id = attr_coll;
4156 
4157  return err;
4158 }
4159 
4160 /*
4161  * pt_find_query () - search for a query
4162  *
4163  * result : parser tree node
4164  * parser(in) : parser
4165  * tree(in) : parser tree node
4166  * arg(in/out) : true, if the query is found
4167  * continue_walk : Continue walk.
4168  */
4169 static PT_NODE *
4170 pt_find_query (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
4171 {
4172  bool *has_query = (bool *) arg;
4173  assert (has_query != NULL);
4174 
4175  if (PT_IS_QUERY (tree))
4176  {
4177  *has_query = true;
4178  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
4179  }
4180 
4181  return tree;
4182 }
4183 
4184 
4185 /*
4186  * pt_find_default_expression () - find a default expression
4187  *
4188  * result :
4189  * parser(in) :
4190  * tree(in) :
4191  * arg(in) : will point to default expression if any is found
4192  * continue_walk :
4193  */
4194 static PT_NODE *
4195 pt_find_default_expression (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
4196 {
4197  PT_NODE **default_expr = (PT_NODE **) arg, *node = NULL;
4198 
4199  if (tree == NULL || !PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (tree))
4200  {
4201  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
4202  return tree;
4203  }
4204 
4205  if (tree->info.expr.op == PT_TO_CHAR && tree->info.expr.arg1 != NULL && PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (tree->info.expr.arg1))
4206  {
4207  /* The correctness of TO_CHAR expression is done a little bit later after obtaining system time. */
4208  assert (tree->info.expr.arg2 != NULL);
4209  node = tree->info.expr.arg1;
4210  }
4211  else
4212  {
4213  node = tree;
4214  }
4215 
4216  switch (node->info.expr.op)
4217  {
4218  case PT_SYS_TIME:
4219  case PT_SYS_DATE:
4220  case PT_SYS_DATETIME:
4221  case PT_SYS_TIMESTAMP:
4222  case PT_CURRENT_TIME:
4223  case PT_CURRENT_DATE:
4224  case PT_CURRENT_TIMESTAMP:
4225  case PT_CURRENT_DATETIME:
4226  case PT_USER:
4227  case PT_CURRENT_USER:
4228  case PT_UNIX_TIMESTAMP:
4229  *default_expr = tree;
4230  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
4231  break;
4232 
4233  default:
4234  break;
4235  }
4236 
4237  return tree;
4238 }
4239 
4240 /*
4241  * pt_find_aggregate_function () - check if current expression contains an
4242  * aggregate function
4243  *
4244  * result :
4245  * parser(in) :
4246  * tree(in) :
4247  * arg(in) : will point to an aggregate function if any is found
4248  * continue_walk :
4249  */
4250 static PT_NODE *
4251 pt_find_aggregate_function (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
4252 {
4253  PT_NODE **agg_function = (PT_NODE **) arg;
4254 
4255  if (tree == NULL || (!PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (tree) && !PT_IS_FUNCTION (tree)))
4256  {
4257  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
4258  }
4259 
4260  if (pt_is_aggregate_function (parser, tree))
4261  {
4262  *agg_function = tree;
4263  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
4264  }
4265 
4266  return tree;
4267 }
4268 
4269 /*
4270  * pt_find_aggregate_analytic_pre ()
4271  * - check if current expression contains an aggregate or
4272  * analytic function
4273  *
4274  * result :
4275  * parser(in) :
4276  * tree(in) :
4277  * arg(in) : will point to the function if any is found
4278  * continue_walk :
4279  */
4280 static PT_NODE *
4281 pt_find_aggregate_analytic_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
4282 {
4283  PT_NODE **function = (PT_NODE **) arg;
4284 
4285  if (*continue_walk == PT_STOP_WALK)
4286  {
4287  return tree;
4288  }
4289 
4290  assert (*function == NULL);
4291 
4292  if (tree && PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (tree->node_type))
4293  {
4294  PT_NODE *find = NULL;
4295 
4296  /* For sub-queries, searching is limited to range of WHERE clause */
4297  find = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, tree);
4298  if (find)
4299  {
4300  *function = find;
4301  }
4302 
4303  /*
4304  * Don't search children nodes of this query node, since
4305  * pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where already did it.
4306  * We may continue walking to search in the rest parts,
4307  * See pt_find_aggregate_analytic_post.
4308  */
4309  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
4310  }
4311  else if (PT_IS_FUNCTION (tree))
4312  {
4313  if (pt_is_aggregate_function (parser, tree) || pt_is_analytic_function (parser, tree))
4314  {
4315  *function = tree;
4316  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
4317  }
4318  }
4319 
4320  return tree;
4321 }
4322 
4323 /*
4324  * pt_find_aggregate_analytic_post ()
4325  *
4326  * result :
4327  * parser(in) :
4328  * tree(in) :
4329  * arg(in) :
4330  * continue_walk :
4331  */
4332 static PT_NODE *
4333 pt_find_aggregate_analytic_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * tree, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
4334 {
4335  PT_NODE **function = (PT_NODE **) arg;
4336 
4337  if (tree && PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (tree->node_type) && *function == NULL)
4338  {
4339  /* Need to search the rest part of tree */
4340  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
4341  }
4342  return tree;
4343 }
4344 
4345 /*
4346  * pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where ()
4347  * - find an aggregate or analytic function in where clause
4348  *
4349  * result : point to the found function if any; NULL otherwise
4350  * parser(in) :
4351  * node(in) :
4352  * continue_walk :
4353  *
4354  * [Note]
4355  * This function will search whether an aggregate or analytic function exists
4356  * in WHERE clause of below statements:
4357  * INSERT, DO, SET, DELETE, SELECT, UNION, DIFFERENCE, INTERSECTION, and
4358  * MERGE.
4359  * It stops searching when meets the first aggregate or analytic function.
4360  *
4361  * 1) For below node types, searching is limited to child node who containing
4362  * WHERE clause:
4363  * PT_DO, PT_DELETE, PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES, PT_SELECT
4364  *
4365  * 2) For below node types, searching is executed on its args:
4366  * PT_UNION, PT_DIFFERENCE, PT_INTERSECTION
4367  *
4368  * 3) For below node types, searching is executed on its all nested nodes:
4369  * PT_FUNCTION, PT_EXPR, PT_MERGE, PT_INSERT
4370  */
4371 static PT_NODE *
4372 pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
4373 {
4374  PT_NODE *find = NULL;
4375 
4376  if (node == NULL)
4377  {
4378  return NULL;
4379  }
4380 
4381  switch (node->node_type)
4382  {
4383  case PT_DO:
4384  find = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, node->info.do_.expr);
4385  break;
4386 
4387  case PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES:
4388  find = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, node->info.set_variables.assignments);
4389  break;
4390 
4391  case PT_DELETE:
4392  find = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, node->info.delete_.search_cond);
4393  break;
4394 
4395  case PT_SELECT:
4396  find = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, node->info.query.q.select.where);
4397  break;
4398 
4399  case PT_UNION:
4400  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
4401  case PT_INTERSECTION:
4402  /* search in args recursively */
4403  find = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg1);
4404 
4405  if (find)
4406  {
4407  break;
4408  }
4409 
4410  find = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg2);
4411  break;
4412 
4413  case PT_FUNCTION:
4414  if (pt_is_aggregate_function (parser, node) || pt_is_analytic_function (parser, node))
4415  {
4416  find = node;
4417  break;
4418  }
4419 
4420  /* fall through to search nested nodes */
4421 
4422  case PT_EXPR:
4423  case PT_MERGE:
4424  case PT_INSERT:
4425  /* walk tree to search */
4426  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_find_aggregate_analytic_pre, &find, pt_find_aggregate_analytic_post,
4427  &find);
4428  break;
4429 
4430  default:
4431  /* for the rest node types, no need to search */
4432  break;
4433  }
4434 
4435  return find;
4436 }
4437 
4438 /*
4439  * pt_check_attribute_domain () - enforce composition hierarchy restrictions
4440  * on a given list of attribute type definitions
4441  * return: none
4442  * parser(in): the parser context
4443  * attr_defs(in): a list of PT_ATTR_DEF nodes
4444  * class_type(in): class, vclass, or proxy
4445  * self(in): name of new class (for create case) or NULL (for alter case)
4446  * reuse_oid(in): whether the class being created or altered is marked as
4447  * reusable OID (non-referable)
4448  * stmt(in): current statement
4449  *
4450  * Note :
4451  * - enforce the composition hierarchy rules:
4452  * 1. enforce the (temporary?) restriction that no proxy may have an
4453  * attribute whose type is heterogeneous set/multiset/sequence of
4454  * some object and something else (homogeneous sets/sequences are OK)
4455  * 2. no attribute may have a domain of set(vclass), multiset(vclass)
4456  * or sequence(vclass).
4457  * 3. an attribute of a class may NOT have a domain of a vclass or a proxy
4458  * but may still have a domain of another class
4459  * 4. an attribute of a vclass may have a domain of a vclass or class
4460  * 5. an attribute of a proxy may have a domain of another proxy but not
4461  * a class or vclass.
4462  * 6. an attribute cannot have a reusable OID class (a non-referable
4463  * class) as a domain, neither directly nor as the domain of a set
4464  * - 'create class c (a c)' is not an error but a feature.
4465  */
4466 
4467 static void
4468 pt_check_attribute_domain (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * attr_defs, PT_MISC_TYPE class_type, const char *self,
4469  const bool reuse_oid, PT_NODE * stmt)
4470 {
4471  PT_NODE *def, *att, *dtyp, *sdtyp;
4472  DB_OBJECT *cls;
4473  const char *att_nam, *typ_nam, *styp_nam;
4474 
4475  for (def = attr_defs; def != NULL && def->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF; def = def->next)
4476  {
4477  att = def->info.attr_def.attr_name;
4478  att_nam = att->info.name.original;
4479 
4480  /* if it is an auto_increment column, check its domain */
4481  if (def->info.attr_def.auto_increment != NULL)
4482  {
4483  dtyp = def->data_type;
4484  switch (def->type_enum)
4485  {
4486  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
4487  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
4488  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
4489  break;
4490 
4491  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
4492  if (dtyp->info.data_type.dec_precision != 0)
4493  {
4494  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_AUTO_INCREMENT_DOMAIN,
4495  att_nam);
4496  }
4497  break;
4498 
4499  default:
4500  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_AUTO_INCREMENT_DOMAIN,
4501  att_nam);
4502  }
4503  }
4504 
4505  /* we don't allow sets/multisets/sequences of vclasses or reusable OID classes */
4506  if (pt_is_set_type (def))
4507  {
4508  for (dtyp = def->data_type; dtyp != NULL; dtyp = dtyp->next)
4509  {
4510  if ((dtyp->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT) && (sdtyp = dtyp->info.data_type.entity)
4511  && (sdtyp->node_type == PT_NAME) && (styp_nam = sdtyp->info.name.original))
4512  {
4513  cls = db_find_class (styp_nam);
4514  if (cls != NULL)
4515  {
4516  if (db_is_vclass (cls) > 0)
4517  {
4518  PT_ERRORm (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_NO_VOBJ_IN_SETS);
4519  break;
4520  }
4521  if (sm_is_reuse_oid_class (cls))
4522  {
4523  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NON_REFERABLE_VIOLATION,
4524  styp_nam);
4525  break;
4526  }
4527  }
4528  else if (self != NULL && intl_identifier_casecmp (self, styp_nam) == 0)
4529  {
4530  if (reuse_oid)
4531  {
4532  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NON_REFERABLE_VIOLATION,
4533  styp_nam);
4534  break;
4535  }
4536  }
4537  }
4538  }
4539  }
4540 
4541  if (def->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT && def->data_type && def->data_type->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE
4542  && (dtyp = def->data_type->info.data_type.entity) != NULL && dtyp->node_type == PT_NAME
4543  && (typ_nam = dtyp->info.name.original) != NULL)
4544  {
4545  /* typ_nam must be a class in the database */
4546  cls = db_find_class (typ_nam);
4547  if (!cls)
4548  {
4549  if (self != NULL && intl_identifier_casecmp (self, typ_nam) == 0)
4550  {
4551  if (reuse_oid)
4552  {
4553  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NON_REFERABLE_VIOLATION,
4554  typ_nam);
4555  }
4556  }
4557  else
4558  {
4559  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED, typ_nam);
4560  }
4561  }
4562  else
4563  {
4564  /* if dtyp is 'user.class' then check that 'user' owns 'class' */
4565  dtyp->info.name.db_object = cls;
4566  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, dtyp);
4567  if (sm_is_reuse_oid_class (cls))
4568  {
4569  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NON_REFERABLE_VIOLATION,
4570  typ_nam);
4571  }
4572 
4573  switch (class_type)
4574  {
4575  case PT_CLASS:
4576  /* an attribute of a class must be of type class */
4577  if (db_is_vclass (cls) > 0)
4578  {
4579  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CAN_NOT_BE_VCLASS, att_nam);
4580  }
4581  break;
4582  case PT_VCLASS:
4583  /* an attribute of a vclass must be of type vclass or class */
4584  break;
4585  default:
4586  break;
4587  }
4588  }
4589  }
4590 
4591  if (def->type_enum == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
4592  {
4593  (void) pt_check_enum_data_type (parser, def->data_type);
4594  }
4595 
4596 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
4597  /* if a defined attr is TEXT, rewrite the definition */
4598  if (def->info.attr_def.attr_type == PT_NORMAL && PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (att, PT_NAME_INFO_EXTERNAL))
4599  {
4600  if ((class_type != PT_CLASS) || (def->info.attr_def.data_default != NULL)
4601  || (def->info.attr_def.constrain_not_null == 1))
4602  {
4603  /* prevent vclass definition or set default */
4604  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_REGU_NOT_IMPLEMENTED, 1, rel_major_release_string ());
4605  PT_ERROR (parser, stmt, er_msg ());
4606  return;
4607  }
4608  if (stmt->node_type == PT_CREATE_ENTITY)
4609  {
4610  stmt->info.create_entity.internal_stmts =
4611  pt_append_statements_on_add_attribute (parser, stmt->info.create_entity.internal_stmts, stmt, self,
4612  att_nam, def);
4613  if (stmt->info.create_entity.internal_stmts == NULL)
4614  {
4615  return;
4616  }
4617  }
4618  else if (stmt->node_type == PT_ALTER)
4619  {
4620  PT_NODE *entity_nam;
4621  const char *cls_nam;
4622 
4623  entity_nam = stmt->info.alter.entity_name;
4624  cls_nam = entity_nam->info.name.original;
4625  stmt->info.alter.internal_stmts =
4626  pt_append_statements_on_add_attribute (parser, stmt->info.alter.internal_stmts, stmt, cls_nam, att_nam,
4627  def);
4628  if (stmt->info.alter.internal_stmts == NULL)
4629  {
4630  return;
4631  }
4632  }
4633  }
4634 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
4635  }
4636 }
4637 
4638 /*
4639  * pt_check_mutable_attributes () - assert that a given list of attributes are
4640  * indigenous to a given class
4641  * return: none
4642  * parser(in): the parser context
4643  * cls(in): a class object
4644  * attr_defs(in): a list of attribute type definitions
4645  */
4646 
4647 static void
4648 pt_check_mutable_attributes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, DB_OBJECT * cls, PT_NODE * attr_defs)
4649 {
4650  PT_NODE *def, *att;
4651  const char *att_nam, *cls_nam;
4652  DB_ATTRIBUTE *db_att;
4653  DB_OBJECT *super;
4654 
4655  assert (parser != NULL);
4656 
4657  if (!cls || (cls_nam = db_get_class_name (cls)) == NULL)
4658  {
4659  return;
4660  }
4661 
4662  for (def = attr_defs; def != NULL && def->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF; def = def->next)
4663  {
4664  att = def->info.attr_def.attr_name;
4665  att_nam = att->info.name.original;
4666  db_att = db_get_attribute_force (cls, att_nam);
4667  if (!db_att)
4668  {
4669  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_ATTRIBUTE_OF, att_nam, cls_nam);
4670  }
4671  else
4672  {
4673  super = db_attribute_class (db_att);
4674  if (super != cls)
4675  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HEIR_CANT_CHANGE_IT, att_nam,
4676  db_get_class_name (super));
4677  }
4678  }
4679 }
4680 
4681 /*
4682  * pt_check_alter () - semantic check an alter statement
4683  * return: none
4684  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
4685  * alter(in): an alter statement
4686  */
4687 static void
4688 pt_check_alter (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * alter)
4689 {
4690  DB_OBJECT *db, *super;
4691  PT_ALTER_CODE code;
4692  PT_MISC_TYPE type;
4693  PT_NODE *name, *sup, *att, *qry, *attr;
4694  const char *cls_nam, *sup_nam, *att_nam;
4695  DB_ATTRIBUTE *db_att;
4696  DB_METHOD *db_mthd;
4697  int is_meta;
4698  int is_partitioned = 0, ss_partition, trigger_involved = 0;
4699  char keyattr[DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH + 1];
4700 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
4701  DB_OBJECT *dom_cls;
4702  char *drop_name_list = NULL;
4703 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
4704  bool reuse_oid = false;
4705  int collation_id = -1;
4706  bool for_update;
4707 
4708  /* look up the class */
4709  name = alter->info.alter.entity_name;
4710  cls_nam = name->info.name.original;
4711 
4712  if (alter->info.alter.code == PT_CHANGE_ATTR || alter->info.alter.code == PT_ADD_INDEX_CLAUSE)
4713  {
4714  for_update = false;
4715  }
4716  else
4717  {
4718  for_update = true;
4719  }
4720 
4721  db = pt_find_class (parser, name, for_update);
4722  if (!db)
4723  {
4724  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
4725  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_EXIST, cls_nam);
4726  return;
4727  }
4728 
4729  if (sm_get_class_collation (db, &collation_id) != NO_ERROR)
4730  {
4731  PT_ERROR (parser, alter, er_msg ());
4732  return;
4733  }
4734 
4735  reuse_oid = sm_is_reuse_oid_class (db);
4736 
4737  /* attach object */
4738  name->info.name.db_object = db;
4739  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, name);
4740 
4741  /* check that class type is what it's supposed to be */
4742  if (alter->info.alter.entity_type == PT_MISC_DUMMY)
4743  {
4744  alter->info.alter.entity_type = pt_get_class_type (parser, db);
4745  }
4746  else
4747  {
4748  type = alter->info.alter.entity_type;
4749  if ((type == PT_CLASS && db_is_class (db) <= 0) || (type == PT_VCLASS && db_is_vclass (db) <= 0))
4750  {
4751  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_A, cls_nam,
4752  pt_show_misc_type (type));
4753  return;
4754  }
4755  }
4756 
4757  type = alter->info.alter.entity_type;
4758  if (do_is_partitioned_subclass (&is_partitioned, cls_nam, keyattr))
4759  {
4760  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
4761  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST, cls_nam);
4762  return;
4763  }
4764 
4765  code = alter->info.alter.code;
4766  switch (code)
4767  {
4768  case PT_ADD_ATTR_MTHD:
4769  if (type == PT_VCLASS)
4770  {
4771  for (attr = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
4772  {
4773  if (attr->info.attr_def.auto_increment != NULL)
4774  {
4775  PT_ERRORm (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_VCLASS_ATT_CANT_BE_AUTOINC);
4776  }
4777  }
4778  }
4779 
4780  for (attr = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
4781  {
4782  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (attr->type_enum) && attr->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
4783  {
4784  if (pt_attr_check_default_cs_coll (parser, attr, -1, collation_id) != NO_ERROR)
4785  {
4786  return;
4787  }
4788  }
4789  }
4790 
4791  pt_check_attribute_domain (parser, alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list, type, NULL, reuse_oid,
4792  alter);
4793  for (attr = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
4794  {
4795  attr->info.attr_def.data_default = pt_check_data_default (parser, attr->info.attr_def.data_default);
4796  }
4797  break;
4798 
4799  case PT_ALTER_DEFAULT:
4800  for (attr = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.ch_attr_def.attr_name_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
4801  {
4802  att_nam = attr->info.name.original;
4803  is_meta = (attr->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR);
4804  db_att =
4805  (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) (is_meta ? db_get_class_attribute (db, att_nam) : db_get_attribute_force (db, att_nam));
4806  if (db_att != NULL && (db_att->auto_increment != NULL || db_att->header.name_space == ID_SHARED_ATTRIBUTE))
4807  {
4808  PT_ERRORm (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
4809  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_AUTO_INCREMENT_ON_DEFAULT_SHARED);
4810  return;
4811  }
4812  }
4813  alter->info.alter.alter_clause.ch_attr_def.data_default_list =
4814  pt_check_data_default (parser, alter->info.alter.alter_clause.ch_attr_def.data_default_list);
4815  /* fall through, no break */
4816 
4817  case PT_MODIFY_DEFAULT:
4818  pt_resolve_default_external (parser, alter);
4819  break;
4820 
4821  case PT_CHANGE_ATTR:
4822  {
4823  PT_NODE *const att_def = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list;
4824 
4825  if (att_def->next != NULL || att_def->node_type != PT_ATTR_DEF)
4826  {
4827  assert (false);
4828  break;
4829  }
4830 
4831  if (alter->info.alter.entity_type != PT_CLASS)
4832  {
4833  PT_ERRORm (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ALTER_CHANGE_ONLY_TABLE);
4834  break;
4835  }
4836 
4837  for (attr = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
4838  {
4839  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (attr->type_enum) && attr->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
4840  {
4841  if (pt_attr_check_default_cs_coll (parser, attr, -1, collation_id) != NO_ERROR)
4842  {
4843  return;
4844  }
4845  }
4846  }
4847 
4848  pt_check_attribute_domain (parser, att_def, type, NULL, reuse_oid, alter);
4849  for (attr = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
4850  {
4851  attr->info.attr_def.data_default = pt_check_data_default (parser, attr->info.attr_def.data_default);
4852  }
4853  }
4854  break;
4855 
4856  case PT_MODIFY_ATTR_MTHD:
4857  pt_check_attribute_domain (parser, alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list, type, NULL, reuse_oid,
4858  alter);
4859  pt_check_mutable_attributes (parser, db, alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list);
4860  for (attr = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
4861  {
4862  attr->info.attr_def.data_default = pt_check_data_default (parser, attr->info.attr_def.data_default);
4863  }
4864  break;
4865 
4866  case PT_RENAME_ATTR_MTHD:
4867  if (is_partitioned && keyattr[0] && (alter->info.alter.alter_clause.rename.element_type == PT_ATTRIBUTE))
4868  {
4869  if (!strncmp (alter->info.alter.alter_clause.rename.old_name->info.name.original, keyattr,
4870  DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH))
4871  {
4872  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter->info.alter.alter_clause.rename.old_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
4873  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_KEY_COLUMN, keyattr);
4874  }
4875  }
4876  break;
4877 
4878  case PT_DROP_ATTR_MTHD:
4879  for (att = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.attr_mthd.attr_mthd_name_list; att != NULL && att->node_type == PT_NAME;
4880  att = att->next)
4881  {
4882  att_nam = att->info.name.original;
4883  is_meta = (att->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR);
4884  db_att =
4885  (DB_ATTRIBUTE *) (is_meta ? db_get_class_attribute (db, att_nam) : db_get_attribute_force (db, att_nam));
4886  if (db_att)
4887  {
4888  /* an inherited attribute can not be dropped by the heir */
4889  super = (DB_OBJECT *) db_attribute_class (db_att);
4890  if (super != db)
4891  {
4892  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HEIR_CANT_CHANGE_IT, att_nam,
4893  db_get_class_name (super));
4894  }
4895  if (is_partitioned && keyattr[0])
4896  {
4897  if (!strncmp (att_nam, keyattr, DB_MAX_IDENTIFIER_LENGTH))
4898  {
4899  PT_ERRORmf (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_KEY_COLUMN,
4900  att_nam);
4901  }
4902  }
4903 
4904 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
4905  /* if it is TEXT typed attr, collect name of the domain class */
4906  if (sm_has_text_domain (db_att, 0))
4907  {
4908  dom_cls = (DB_OBJECT *) db_domain_class (db_attribute_domain (db_att));
4909  if (drop_name_list != NULL)
4910  {
4911  drop_name_list = pt_append_string (parser, drop_name_list, ",");
4912  }
4913  drop_name_list = pt_append_string (parser, drop_name_list, db_get_class_name (dom_cls));
4914  }
4915 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
4916 
4917  }
4918  else
4919  {
4920  /* perhaps it's a method */
4921  db_mthd = (DB_METHOD *) (is_meta ? db_get_class_method (db, att_nam) : db_get_method (db, att_nam));
4922  if (!db_mthd)
4923  {
4924  if (!is_meta)
4925  {
4926  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_METHOD_OR_ATTR, att_nam,
4927  cls_nam);
4928  }
4929  else
4930  {
4931  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_CLASS_ATTR_MTHD,
4932  att_nam, cls_nam);
4933  }
4934  }
4935  }
4936  }
4937 
4938 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
4939  /* create internal statements to drop the TEXT saving classes */
4940  if (drop_name_list)
4941  {
4942  if ((alter->info.alter.internal_stmts =
4943  pt_append_statements_on_drop_attributes (parser, alter->info.alter.internal_stmts,
4944  drop_name_list)) == NULL)
4945  {
4946  PT_ERRORm (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
4947  return;
4948  }
4949  }
4950 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
4951  break;
4952 
4953  case PT_APPLY_PARTITION:
4954  case PT_REMOVE_PARTITION:
4955  case PT_ANALYZE_PARTITION:
4956  case PT_DROP_PARTITION:
4957  case PT_ADD_PARTITION:
4958  case PT_ADD_HASHPARTITION:
4959  case PT_REORG_PARTITION:
4960  case PT_COALESCE_PARTITION:
4961  case PT_PROMOTE_PARTITION:
4962  if (sm_class_has_triggers (db, &trigger_involved, TR_EVENT_ALL) == NO_ERROR)
4963  {
4964  if (trigger_involved)
4965  {
4966  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
4967  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CANT_PARTITION_MNG_TRIGGERS, cls_nam);
4968  break;
4969  }
4970  }
4971 
4972  if (code == PT_APPLY_PARTITION)
4973  {
4974  if (is_partitioned)
4975  {
4976  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
4977  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ALREADY_PARTITIONED_CLASS, cls_nam);
4978  break;
4979  }
4980  if (alter->info.alter.alter_clause.partition.info)
4981  {
4982  pt_check_partitions (parser, alter, db);
4983  }
4984  }
4985  else
4986  {
4987  if (!is_partitioned)
4988  {
4989  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
4990  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS, cls_nam);
4991  break;
4992  }
4993  if (code != PT_REMOVE_PARTITION)
4994  {
4995  pt_check_alter_partition (parser, alter, db);
4996  }
4997  }
4998  break;
4999 
5000  case PT_ADD_QUERY:
5001  case PT_MODIFY_QUERY:
5002  if (type != PT_CLASS && (qry = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.query.query) != NULL)
5003  {
5004  pt_validate_query_spec (parser, qry, db);
5005  }
5006  /* fall through to next case. do NOT put a break here! */
5007  case PT_DROP_QUERY:
5008  if (type == PT_CLASS)
5009  {
5010  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HAVE_NO_QUERY_SPEC, cls_nam);
5011  }
5012  break;
5013 
5014  case PT_RESET_QUERY:
5015  if (type == PT_CLASS)
5016  {
5017  /* only allow views, not classes here */
5018  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HAVE_NO_QUERY_SPEC, cls_nam);
5019  }
5020  else if (db_get_subclasses (db) != NULL || db_get_superclasses (db) != NULL)
5021  {
5022  /* disallow resetting query for views that have children or parents */
5023  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ALTER_VIEW_IN_HIERARCHY, cls_nam);
5024  }
5025  else if ((qry = alter->info.alter.alter_clause.query.query) == NULL)
5026  {
5027  break;
5028  }
5029  else
5030  {
5031  pt_check_create_view (parser, alter);
5032  }
5033  break;
5034 
5035  case PT_ADD_SUPCLASS:
5036  case PT_DROP_SUPCLASS:
5037  for (sup = alter->info.alter.super.sup_class_list; sup != NULL; sup = sup->next)
5038  {
5039  sup_nam = sup->info.name.original;
5040  super = pt_find_class (parser, sup, true);
5041  if (super == NULL)
5042  {
5043  PT_ERRORmf (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_EXIST, sup_nam);
5044  break;
5045  }
5046  if (sm_partitioned_class_type (super, &ss_partition, NULL, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
5047  {
5048  PT_ERROR (parser, alter, er_msg ());
5049  break;
5050  }
5051  if (ss_partition == DB_PARTITION_CLASS)
5052  {
5053  PT_ERRORm (parser, alter, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST);
5054  break;
5055  }
5056  if (code == PT_ADD_SUPCLASS)
5057  {
5058 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
5059  if (sm_has_text_domain (db_get_attributes (super), 1))
5060  {
5061  /* prevent to define it as a superclass */
5062  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_REGU_NOT_IMPLEMENTED, 1, rel_major_release_string ());
5063  PT_ERROR (parser, alter, er_msg ());
5064  break;
5065  }
5066 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
5067  }
5068  sup->info.name.db_object = super;
5069  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, sup);
5070  if (code == PT_DROP_SUPCLASS)
5071  {
5072  if (db_is_superclass (super, db) <= 0)
5073  {
5074  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, sup, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_SUPERCLASS_OF, sup_nam,
5075  cls_nam);
5076  }
5077  }
5078  else /* PT_ADD_SUPCLASS */
5079  {
5080  switch (type)
5081  {
5082  case PT_CLASS:
5083  if (db_is_class (super) <= 0)
5084  {
5085  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, sup, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NONCLASS_PARENT, cls_nam,
5086  sup_nam);
5087  }
5088  break;
5089  case PT_VCLASS:
5090  if (db_is_vclass (super) <= 0)
5091  {
5092  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, sup, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NONVCLASS_PARENT, cls_nam,
5093  sup_nam);
5094  }
5095  break;
5096  default:
5097  break;
5098  }
5099 
5100  if (db_is_superclass (super, db))
5101  {
5102  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, sup, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ALREADY_SUPERCLASS, sup_nam,
5103  cls_nam);
5104  }
5105  if (db == super)
5106  {
5107  PT_ERRORmf (parser, sup, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SUPERCLASS_CYCLE, sup_nam);
5108  }
5109  if (db_is_subclass (super, db))
5110  {
5111  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, sup, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ALREADY_SUBCLASS, sup_nam,
5112  cls_nam);
5113  }
5114  }
5115  }
5116  break;
5117  default:
5118  break;
5119  }
5120 }
5121 
5122 /*
5123  * attribute_name () - return the name of this attribute
5124  * return: printable name of att
5125  * parser(in): the parser context
5126  * att(in): an attribute
5127  */
5128 static const char *
5129 attribute_name (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * att)
5130 {
5131  if (!att)
5132  {
5133  return NULL;
5134  }
5135 
5136  if (att->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
5137  {
5138  att = att->info.attr_def.attr_name;
5139  }
5140 
5141  if (att->node_type != PT_NAME)
5142  {
5143  return NULL;
5144  }
5145 
5146  return att->info.name.original;
5147 }
5148 
5149 /*
5150  * is_shared_attribute () - is this a shared attribute?
5151  * return: nonzero if att is a shared attribute
5152  * parser(in): the parser context
5153  * att(in): an attribute
5154  */
5155 static int
5156 is_shared_attribute (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * att)
5157 {
5158  if (!att)
5159  {
5160  return 0;
5161  }
5162 
5163  if (att->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
5164  {
5165  if (att->info.attr_def.attr_type == PT_SHARED)
5166  {
5167  return 1;
5168  }
5169 
5170  if (!(att = att->info.attr_def.attr_name))
5171  {
5172  return 0;
5173  }
5174  }
5175 
5176  if (att->node_type != PT_NAME)
5177  {
5178  return 0;
5179  }
5180 
5181  return (att->info.name.meta_class == PT_SHARED);
5182 }
5183 
5184 /*
5185  * pt_find_partition_column_count_func () - find the number of the name node
5186  * which can be used as the partition
5187  * column
5188  * return:
5189  * func(in):
5190  * name_node(in/out):
5191  */
5192 static int
5193 pt_find_partition_column_count_func (PT_NODE * func, PT_NODE ** name_node)
5194 {
5195  int cnt = 0, ret;
5196  PT_NODE *f_arg;
5197 
5198  if (func == NULL)
5199  {
5200  return 0;
5201  }
5202 
5203  if (func->node_type != PT_FUNCTION)
5204  {
5205  return 0;
5206  }
5207 
5208  switch (func->info.function.function_type)
5209  {
5210  case F_INSERT_SUBSTRING:
5211  case F_ELT:
5212  case F_JSON_OBJECT:
5213  case F_JSON_ARRAY:
5214  case F_JSON_INSERT:
5215  case F_JSON_REPLACE:
5216  case F_JSON_SET:
5217  case F_JSON_KEYS:
5218  case F_JSON_REMOVE:
5219  case F_JSON_ARRAY_APPEND:
5220  case F_JSON_MERGE:
5221  case F_JSON_GET_ALL_PATHS:
5222  break;
5223  default:
5224  return 0; /* unsupported function */
5225  }
5226 
5227  f_arg = func->info.function.arg_list;
5228  while (f_arg != NULL)
5229  {
5230  if (f_arg->node_type == PT_NAME)
5231  {
5232  cnt++;
5233  *name_node = f_arg;
5234  }
5235  else if (f_arg->node_type == PT_EXPR)
5236  {
5237  ret = pt_find_partition_column_count (f_arg, name_node);
5238  if (ret > 0)
5239  {
5240  cnt += ret;
5241  }
5242  }
5243  f_arg = f_arg->next;
5244  }
5245 
5246  return cnt;
5247 }
5248 
5249 /*
5250  * pt_find_partition_column_count () - find the number of the name node which
5251  * can be used as the partition column
5252  * return:
5253  * expr(in):
5254  * name_node(in/out):
5255  */
5256 static int
5257 pt_find_partition_column_count (PT_NODE * expr, PT_NODE ** name_node)
5258 {
5259  int cnt = 0, ret;
5260 
5261  if (expr == NULL)
5262  {
5263  return 0;
5264  }
5265 
5266  if (expr->node_type != PT_EXPR)
5267  {
5268  return 0;
5269  }
5270 
5271  switch (expr->info.expr.op)
5272  {
5273  case PT_FUNCTION_HOLDER:
5274  assert (expr->info.expr.arg1 != NULL);
5275  return pt_find_partition_column_count_func (expr->info.expr.arg1, name_node);
5276  case PT_PLUS:
5277  case PT_MINUS:
5278  case PT_TIMES:
5279  case PT_DIVIDE:
5280  case PT_UNARY_MINUS:
5281  case PT_BIT_NOT:
5282  case PT_BIT_AND:
5283  case PT_BIT_OR:
5284  case PT_BIT_XOR:
5285  case PT_BITSHIFT_LEFT:
5286  case PT_BITSHIFT_RIGHT:
5287  case PT_DIV:
5288  case PT_MOD:
5289  case PT_ACOS:
5290  case PT_ASIN:
5291  case PT_ATAN:
5292  case PT_ATAN2:
5293  case PT_COS:
5294  case PT_SIN:
5295  case PT_TAN:
5296  case PT_COT:
5297  case PT_DEGREES:
5298  case PT_RADIANS:
5299  case PT_PI:
5300  case PT_LN:
5301  case PT_LOG2:
5302  case PT_LOG10:
5303  case PT_FORMAT:
5304  case PT_DATE_FORMAT:
5305  case PT_STR_TO_DATE:
5306  case PT_CONCAT:
5307  case PT_CONCAT_WS:
5308  case PT_FIELD:
5309  case PT_LEFT:
5310  case PT_RIGHT:
5311  case PT_LOCATE:
5312  case PT_MID:
5313  case PT_STRCMP:
5314  case PT_REVERSE:
5315  case PT_BIT_COUNT:
5316  case PT_ADDDATE:
5317  case PT_DATE_ADD:
5318  case PT_SUBDATE:
5319  case PT_DATE_SUB:
5320  case PT_DATEF:
5321  case PT_TIMEF:
5322  case PT_DATEDIFF:
5323  case PT_TIMEDIFF:
5324  case PT_MODULUS:
5325  case PT_POSITION:
5326  case PT_FINDINSET:
5327  case PT_SUBSTRING:
5328  case PT_SUBSTRING_INDEX:
5329  case PT_OCTET_LENGTH:
5330  case PT_BIT_LENGTH:
5331  case PT_CHAR_LENGTH:
5332  case PT_LOWER:
5333  case PT_UPPER:
5334  case PT_HEX:
5335  case PT_ASCII:
5336  case PT_CONV:
5337  case PT_BIN:
5338  case PT_MD5:
5339  case PT_TO_BASE64:
5340  case PT_FROM_BASE64:
5341  case PT_TRIM:
5342  case PT_LTRIM:
5343  case PT_RTRIM:
5344  case PT_LIKE_LOWER_BOUND:
5345  case PT_LIKE_UPPER_BOUND:
5346  case PT_LPAD:

5349  case PT_SPACE:
5350  case PT_REPLACE:
5351  case PT_TRANSLATE:
5352  case PT_ADD_MONTHS:
5353  case PT_LAST_DAY:
5354  case PT_MONTHS_BETWEEN:
5355  case PT_SYS_DATE:
5356  case PT_TO_DATE:
5357  case PT_TO_NUMBER:
5358  case PT_SYS_TIME:
5359  case PT_CURRENT_DATE:
5360  case PT_CURRENT_TIME:
5361  case PT_SYS_TIMESTAMP:
5362  case PT_CURRENT_TIMESTAMP:
5363  case PT_SYS_DATETIME:
5364  case PT_CURRENT_DATETIME:
5365  case PT_UTC_TIME:
5366  case PT_UTC_DATE:
5367  case PT_TO_TIME:
5368  case PT_TO_TIMESTAMP:
5369  case PT_TO_DATETIME:
5370  case PT_SCHEMA:
5371  case PT_DATABASE:
5372  case PT_VERSION:
5373  case PT_TIME_FORMAT:
5374  case PT_TIMESTAMP:
5375  case PT_YEARF:
5376  case PT_MONTHF:
5377  case PT_DAYF:
5378  case PT_DAYOFMONTH:
5379  case PT_HOURF:
5380  case PT_MINUTEF:
5381  case PT_SECONDF:
5382  case PT_QUARTERF:
5383  case PT_WEEKDAY:
5384  case PT_DAYOFWEEK:
5385  case PT_DAYOFYEAR:
5386  case PT_TODAYS:
5387  case PT_FROMDAYS:
5388  case PT_TIMETOSEC:
5389  case PT_SECTOTIME:
5390  case PT_WEEKF:
5391  case PT_MAKEDATE:
5392  case PT_MAKETIME:
5393  case PT_ADDTIME:
5394  case PT_UNIX_TIMESTAMP:
5395  case PT_FROM_UNIXTIME:
5396  case PT_EXTRACT:
5397  case PT_TO_CHAR:
5398  case PT_CAST:
5399  case PT_STRCAT:
5400  case PT_FLOOR:
5401  case PT_CEIL:
5402  case PT_POWER:
5403  case PT_ROUND:
5404  case PT_ABS:
5405  case PT_LOG:
5406  case PT_EXP:
5407  case PT_SQRT:
5408  case PT_TRUNC:
5409  case PT_BIT_TO_BLOB:
5410  case PT_BLOB_FROM_FILE:
5411  case PT_BLOB_LENGTH:
5412  case PT_BLOB_TO_BIT:
5413  case PT_CHAR_TO_BLOB:
5414  case PT_CHAR_TO_CLOB:
5415  case PT_CLOB_FROM_FILE:
5416  case PT_CLOB_LENGTH:
5417  case PT_CLOB_TO_CHAR:
5418  case PT_TYPEOF:
5419  case PT_INET_ATON:
5420  case PT_INET_NTOA:
5421  case PT_DBTIMEZONE:
5422  case PT_SESSIONTIMEZONE:
5423  case PT_TZ_OFFSET:
5424  case PT_FROM_TZ:
5425  case PT_NEW_TIME:
5426  case PT_TO_DATETIME_TZ:
5427  case PT_TO_TIMESTAMP_TZ:
5428  case PT_UTC_TIMESTAMP:
5429  case PT_CONV_TZ:
5430  break;
5431 
5432  /* PT_DRAND and PT_DRANDOM are not supported regardless of whether a seed is given or not. because they produce
5433  * random numbers of DOUBLE type. DOUBLE type is not allowed on partition expression. */
5434  case PT_RAND:
5435  case PT_RANDOM:
5436  if (expr->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
5437  {
5438  return -1;
5439  }
5440  break;
5441 
5442  default:
5443  return -1; /* unsupported expression */
5444  }
5445 
5446  if (expr->info.expr.arg1 != NULL)
5447  {
5448  if (expr->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_NAME)
5449  {
5450  *name_node = expr->info.expr.arg1;
5451  cnt++;
5452  }
5453  else if (expr->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_VALUE)
5454  {
5455  if (expr->info.expr.arg1->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
5456  {
5457  return -1;
5458  }
5459  }
5460  else if (expr->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
5461  {
5462  ret = pt_find_partition_column_count (expr->info.expr.arg1, name_node);
5463  if (ret < 0)
5464  {
5465  return -1;
5466  }
5467  cnt += ret;
5468  }
5469  }
5470 
5471  if (expr->info.expr.arg2 != NULL)
5472  {
5473  if (expr->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_NAME)
5474  {
5475  *name_node = expr->info.expr.arg2;
5476  cnt++;
5477  }
5478  else if (expr->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_VALUE)
5479  { /* except default NULL parameter */
5480  if (expr->info.expr.arg2->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL
5481  && ((expr->info.expr.arg2->line_number != expr->info.expr.arg3->line_number)
5482  || (expr->info.expr.arg2->column_number != expr->info.expr.arg3->column_number)))
5483  {
5484  return -1;
5485  }
5486  }
5487  else if (expr->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
5488  {
5489  ret = pt_find_partition_column_count (expr->info.expr.arg2, name_node);
5490  if (ret < 0)
5491  {
5492  return -1;
5493  }
5494  cnt += ret;
5495  }
5496  }
5497 
5498  if (expr->info.expr.arg3 != NULL)
5499  {
5500  if (expr->info.expr.arg3->node_type == PT_NAME)
5501  {
5502  *name_node = expr->info.expr.arg3;
5503  cnt++;
5504  }
5505  else if (expr->info.expr.arg3->node_type == PT_VALUE)
5506  {
5507  if (expr->info.expr.arg3->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
5508  {
5509  return -1;
5510  }
5511  }
5512  else if (expr->info.expr.arg3->node_type == PT_EXPR)
5513  {
5514  ret = pt_find_partition_column_count (expr->info.expr.arg3, name_node);
5515  if (ret < 0)
5516  {
5517  return -1;
5518  }
5519  cnt += ret;
5520  }
5521  }
5522  return cnt;
5523 }
5524 
5525 /*
5526  * pt_value_links_add () -
5527  * return:
5528  * parser(in):
5529  * parts(in):
5530  * val(in):
5531  * ptl(in):
5532  */
5533 static int
5534 pt_value_links_add (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * parts, PT_NODE * val, PT_VALUE_LINKS * ptl)
5535 {
5536  PT_VALUE_LINKS *vblk, *blks;
5537 
5538  vblk = (PT_VALUE_LINKS *) malloc (sizeof (PT_VALUE_LINKS));
5539  if (vblk == NULL)
5540  {
5541  PT_ERRORm (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
5542  return ER_FAILED;
5543  }
5544 
5545  vblk->vallink = val;
5546  vblk->next = ptl->next;
5547  if (ptl->next == NULL)
5548  { /* first item */
5549  ptl->next = vblk;
5550  return 0;
5551  }
5552 
5553  for (blks = ptl->next; blks; blks = blks->next)
5554  {
5555  if (val == NULL)
5556  {
5557  if (blks->vallink == NULL)
5558  {
5559  /* MAXVALUE or NULL duplicate */
5560  goto duplicate_error;
5561  }
5562  }
5563  else if (blks->vallink != NULL)
5564  {
5565  if (db_value_compare (pt_value_to_db (parser, val), pt_value_to_db (parser, blks->vallink)) == DB_EQ)
5566  {
5567  goto duplicate_error;
5568  }
5569  }
5570  }
5571 
5572  ptl->next = vblk;
5573 
5574  return NO_ERROR;
5575 
5576 duplicate_error:
5577  if (vblk != NULL)
5578  {
5579  free_and_init (vblk);
5580  }
5581  PT_ERRORmf (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_PARTITION_DEF,
5582  parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
5583  return ER_FAILED;
5584 }
5585 
5586 /*
5587  * pt_check_partition_values () - perform semantic check on partition
5588  * range/list specification
5589  * return: error code or NO_ERROR
5590  * parser(in) : parser context
5591  * desired_type(in) : desired type for partition values
5592  * data_type(in) : data type for desired_type
5593  * ptl(in) : values context
5594  * parts (in) : node specifying one partition
5595  */
5596 static int
5597 pt_check_partition_values (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_TYPE_ENUM desired_type, PT_NODE * data_type,
5598  PT_VALUE_LINKS * ptl, PT_NODE * parts)
5599 {
5600  int error = NO_ERROR;
5601  PT_NODE *val = NULL;
5602  const char *value_text = NULL;
5603 
5604  if (parts->info.parts.values == NULL)
5605  {
5606  /* MAXVALUE specification */
5607  return pt_value_links_add (parser, parts, NULL, ptl);
5608  }
5609 
5610  for (val = parts->info.parts.values; val != NULL; val = val->next)
5611  {
5612  bool has_different_collation = false;
5613  bool has_different_codeset = false;
5614 
5615  if (val->node_type != PT_VALUE)
5616  {
5617  /* Only values are allowed in partition LIST or RANGE specification. */
5618  assert_release (val->node_type != PT_VALUE);
5619  PT_ERROR (parser, val, er_msg ());
5620  error = ER_FAILED;
5621  break;
5622  }
5623 
5624  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (val->type_enum) && data_type != NULL && PT_HAS_COLLATION (data_type->type_enum))
5625  {
5626  if ((val->data_type != NULL && data_type->info.data_type.units != val->data_type->info.data_type.units)
5627  || (val->data_type == NULL && data_type->info.data_type.units != LANG_SYS_CODESET))
5628  {
5629  has_different_codeset = true;
5630  }
5631 
5632  if ((val->data_type != NULL
5633  && data_type->info.data_type.collation_id != val->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id)
5634  || (val->data_type == NULL && data_type->info.data_type.collation_id != LANG_SYS_COLLATION))
5635  {
5636  has_different_collation = true;
5637  }
5638  }
5639 
5640  if (has_different_codeset == true)
5641  {
5642  int val_codeset;
5643 
5644  val_codeset = (val->data_type != NULL) ? val->data_type->info.data_type.units : LANG_SYS_CODESET;
5645 
5646  error = ER_FAILED;
5647  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, val, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_VAL_CODESET,
5648  lang_charset_introducer ((INTL_CODESET) val_codeset),
5649  lang_charset_introducer ((INTL_CODESET) data_type->info.data_type.units));
5650  break;
5651  }
5652 
5653  if (val->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NULL && (val->type_enum != desired_type || has_different_collation == true))
5654  {
5655  /* Coerce this value to the desired type. We have to preserve the original text of the value for replication
5656  * reasons. The coercion below will either be successful or fail, but it should not alter the way in which
5657  * the original statement is printed */
5658  value_text = val->info.value.text;
5659  val->info.value.text = NULL;
5660  error = pt_coerce_value (parser, val, val, desired_type, data_type);
5661  val->info.value.text = value_text;
5662  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5663  {
5664  break;
5665  }
5666  }
5667 
5668  /* add this value to the values list */
5669  if (val->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
5670  {
5671  error = pt_value_links_add (parser, parts, NULL, ptl);
5672  }
5673  else
5674  {
5675  error = pt_value_links_add (parser, parts, val, ptl);
5676  }
5677 
5678  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5679  {
5680  break;
5681  }
5682  }
5683 
5684  return error;
5685 }
5686 
5687 
5688 /*
5689  * pt_check_partitions () - do semantic checks on a partition clause
5690  * return: none
5691  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
5692  * stmt(in): a create class or alter class statement
5693  * dbobj(in):
5694  *
5695  * Note :
5696  * check that
5697  * - stmt's expression have an attribute
5698  * - expression's attribute is not set nor object type
5699  * - partition type is equals to partition definitions
5700  * - partition max
5701  * - valid hash size
5702  */
5703 
5704 static void
5705 pt_check_partitions (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt, MOP dbobj)
5706 {
5707  PT_NODE *pinfo, *pcol, *attr, *pattr, *parts;
5708  int name_count, valchk, parts_cnt;
5709  PT_VALUE_LINKS vlinks = { NULL, NULL };
5710  PT_VALUE_LINKS *pvl, *delpvl;
5711  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO sc_info = { NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, false, false };
5712  PT_NODE *expr_type;
5713  SM_CLASS *smclass;
5714  SM_ATTRIBUTE *smatt;
5715  bool chkflag = false;
5716  DB_QUERY_TYPE *query_columns = NULL, *column = NULL;
5717  int error = NO_ERROR;
5718 
5719  assert (parser != NULL);
5720 
5721  if (!stmt || (stmt->node_type != PT_CREATE_ENTITY && stmt->node_type != PT_ALTER))
5722  {
5723  return;
5724  }
5725 
5726  if (stmt->node_type == PT_CREATE_ENTITY)
5727  {
5728  pinfo = stmt->info.create_entity.partition_info;
5729  }
5730  else
5731  {
5732  pinfo = stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.partition.info;
5733  }
5734 
5735  if (pinfo == NULL || pinfo->node_type != PT_PARTITION || pinfo->info.partition.type > PT_PARTITION_LIST)
5736  {
5737  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_DEFINITION);
5738  return;
5739  }
5740 
5741  if (0 < parser->host_var_count)
5742  {
5743  PT_ERRORm (parser, pinfo, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HOSTVAR_IN_DDL);
5744  return;
5745  }
5746 
5747  pcol = pinfo->info.partition.expr;
5748  if (pcol->node_type != PT_NAME && pcol->node_type != PT_EXPR)
5749  {
5750  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_PARTITION_COLUMN);
5751  return;
5752  }
5753 
5754  if (pcol->node_type == PT_EXPR)
5755  {
5756  name_count = pt_find_partition_column_count (pcol, &pcol);
5757  if (name_count < 0)
5758  { /* NULL constant exist */
5759  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_DEFINITION);
5760  return;
5761  }
5762  else if (name_count == 0)
5763  {
5764  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_PARTITION_COLUMN);
5765  return;
5766  }
5767  else if (name_count > 1)
5768  {
5769  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ONLYONE_PARTITION_COLUMN);
5770  return;
5771  }
5772  }
5773 
5774  assert (pcol->node_type == PT_NAME);
5775 
5776  if (stmt->node_type == PT_CREATE_ENTITY)
5777  {
5778  for (attr = stmt->info.create_entity.attr_def_list, chkflag = false; attr && attr->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF;
5779  attr = attr->next)
5780  {
5781  pattr = attr->info.attr_def.attr_name;
5782  if (pattr == NULL)
5783  {
5784  continue;
5785  }
5786 
5787  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (pcol->info.name.original, pattr->info.name.original))
5788  {
5789  if (attr->info.attr_def.attr_type != PT_NORMAL)
5790  {
5791  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_COLUMN_TYPE);
5792  return;
5793  }
5794  pcol->type_enum = attr->type_enum;
5795  if (attr->data_type != NULL)
5796  {
5797  assert (pcol->data_type == NULL);
5798  pcol->data_type = parser_copy_tree (parser, attr->data_type);
5799  }
5800  else
5801  {
5802  TP_DOMAIN *d;
5803 
5804  d = pt_type_enum_to_db_domain (pcol->type_enum);
5805  d = tp_domain_cache (d);
5806  pcol->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, d);
5807  }
5808  pinfo->info.partition.keycol = parser_copy_tree (parser, pcol);
5809  chkflag = true;
5810  break;
5811  }
5812  }
5813 
5814  /* check if partitioning is requested by a column in SELECT query */
5815  if (!chkflag && stmt->info.create_entity.create_select != NULL)
5816  {
5817  int error = NO_ERROR;
5818  PT_NODE *qry_select = stmt->info.create_entity.create_select;
5819  /* get columns from SELECT result */
5820 
5821  error = pt_get_select_query_columns (parser, qry_select, &query_columns);
5822  if (error != NO_ERROR)
5823  {
5824  /* error message already set at the above compilation step */
5825  return;
5826  }
5827 
5828  for (column = query_columns; column != NULL; column = db_query_format_next (column))
5829  {
5830  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (column->original_name, pcol->info.name.original))
5831  {
5832  pcol->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (column->db_type);
5833 
5834  assert (column->domain != NULL);
5835  pcol->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, column->domain);
5836  pinfo->info.partition.keycol = parser_copy_tree (parser, pcol);
5837  chkflag = true;
5838  break;
5839  }
5840  }
5841  if (query_columns != NULL)
5842  {
5843  db_free_query_format (query_columns);
5844  query_columns = NULL;
5845  }
5846  assert (NULL == query_columns);
5847  }
5848 
5849  }
5850  else
5851  {
5852  if (au_fetch_class (dbobj, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT) == NO_ERROR)
5853  {
5854  for (smatt = smclass->attributes; smatt != NULL; smatt = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) smatt->header.next)
5855  {
5856  if (SM_COMPARE_NAMES (smatt->header.name, pcol->info.name.original) == 0)
5857  {
5858  if (smatt->class_mop != stmt->info.alter.entity_name->info.name.db_object)
5859  {
5860  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5861  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_INHERITED_ATTR);
5862  }
5863  pcol->type_enum = pt_db_to_type_enum (smatt->type->id);
5864  assert (smatt->domain != NULL);
5865  pcol->data_type = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser, smatt->domain);
5866  pinfo->info.partition.keycol = parser_copy_tree (parser, pcol);
5867  chkflag = true;
5868  break;
5869  }
5870  }
5871  }
5872  }
5873 
5874  if (chkflag)
5875  {
5876  switch (pcol->type_enum)
5877  {
5878  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
5879  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
5880  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
5881  case PT_TYPE_DATE:
5882  case PT_TYPE_TIME:
5883  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
5884  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
5885  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
5886  case PT_TYPE_DATETIME:
5887  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
5888  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
5889  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
5890  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
5891  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
5892  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
5893  break;
5894  default:
5895  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_COLUMN_TYPE);
5896  return;
5897  }
5898  }
5899  else
5900  {
5901  bool found = false;
5902 
5903  if (stmt->node_type == PT_CREATE_ENTITY && stmt->info.create_entity.supclass_list)
5904  {
5905  DB_OBJECT *sup_dbobj = stmt->info.create_entity.supclass_list->info.name.db_object;
5906 
5907  if (au_fetch_class (sup_dbobj, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT) == NO_ERROR)
5908  {
5909  for (smatt = smclass->attributes; smatt != NULL; smatt = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) smatt->header.next)
5910  {
5911  if (SM_COMPARE_NAMES (smatt->header.name, pcol->info.name.original) == 0)
5912  {
5913  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
5914  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_INHERITED_ATTR);
5915  found = true;
5916  }
5917  }
5918  }
5919  }
5920 
5921  if (!found)
5922  {
5923  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_PARTITION_COLUMN);
5924  }
5925  }
5926 
5927  pcol = pinfo->info.partition.expr;
5928  sc_info.top_node = pcol;
5929  sc_info.donot_fold = false;
5930  expr_type = pt_semantic_type (parser, pcol, &sc_info);
5931  if (expr_type)
5932  {
5933  switch (expr_type->type_enum)
5934  {
5935  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
5936  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
5937  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
5938  case PT_TYPE_DATE:
5939  case PT_TYPE_TIME:
5940  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMP:
5941  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPTZ:
5942  case PT_TYPE_TIMESTAMPLTZ:
5943  case PT_TYPE_DATETIME:
5944  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMETZ:
5945  case PT_TYPE_DATETIMELTZ:
5946  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
5947  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
5948  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
5949  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
5950  break;
5951  default:
5952  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_COLUMN_TYPE);
5953  return;
5954  }
5955  }
5956  else
5957  {
5958  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_DEFINITION);
5959  return;
5960  }
5961 
5962  if (pinfo->info.partition.type == PT_PARTITION_HASH)
5963  {
5964  PT_NODE *hashsize_nodep;
5965 
5966  hashsize_nodep = pinfo->info.partition.hashsize;
5967  if (hashsize_nodep == NULL || hashsize_nodep->type_enum != PT_TYPE_INTEGER
5968  || hashsize_nodep->info.value.data_value.i < 1 || hashsize_nodep->info.value.data_value.i > MAX_PARTITIONS)
5969  {
5970  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_SIZE);
5971  }
5972  }
5973  else
5974  { /* RANGE or LIST */
5975  parts = pinfo->info.partition.parts;
5976  if (parts == NULL)
5977  {
5978  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_DEFINITION);
5979  return;
5980  }
5981 
5982  parts_cnt = 0;
5983  for (chkflag = false; parts && parts->node_type == PT_PARTS; parts = parts->next)
5984  {
5985  PT_NODE *fpart;
5986 
5987  if (parts->info.parts.type != pinfo->info.partition.type)
5988  {
5989  chkflag = true;
5990  break;
5991  }
5992  if (parts->info.parts.values != NULL)
5993  {
5994  parts->info.parts.values =
5995  parser_walk_tree (parser, parts->info.parts.values, pt_check_and_replace_hostvar, &valchk, NULL, NULL);
