5996  if ((pinfo->info.partition.type == PT_PARTITION_RANGE)
5997  && parts->info.parts.values->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
5998  {
5999  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CONSTANT_TYPE_MISMATCH,
6000  parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
6001 
6002  goto pvl_free_end;
6003  }
6004  }
6005 
6006  valchk = pt_check_partition_values (parser, expr_type->type_enum, expr_type->data_type, &vlinks, parts);
6007  if (valchk != NO_ERROR)
6008  {
6009  goto pvl_free_end;
6010  }
6011 
6012  for (fpart = parts->next; fpart && fpart->node_type == PT_PARTS; fpart = fpart->next)
6013  {
6014  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original,
6015  fpart->info.parts.name->info.name.original))
6016  {
6017  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_PARTITION_DEF,
6018  fpart->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
6019 
6020  goto pvl_free_end;
6021  }
6022  }
6023 
6024  /* check value increasing for range partition */
6025  if (pinfo->info.partition.type == PT_PARTITION_RANGE)
6026  {
6027  error = pt_check_range_partition_strict_increasing (parser, stmt, parts, parts->next, NULL);
6028  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6029  {
6030  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
6031 
6032  goto pvl_free_end;
6033  }
6034  }
6035 
6036  parts_cnt++;
6037  }
6038 
6039  if (parts_cnt > MAX_PARTITIONS)
6040  {
6041  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_SIZE);
6042  }
6043  else if (chkflag)
6044  {
6045  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_DEFINITION);
6046  }
6047  }
6048 
6049 pvl_free_end:
6050 
6051  pvl = vlinks.next;
6052  while (pvl)
6053  {
6054  delpvl = pvl;
6055  pvl = pvl->next;
6056  free_and_init (delpvl);
6057  }
6058 }
6059 
6060 /*
6061  * partition_range_min_max () - find min/max value
6062  * return: 0-process, 1-duplicate
6063  * dest(in/out): min or max value
6064  * inval(in): input value
6065  * min_max(in): RANGE_MIN, RANGE_MAX
6066  *
6067  * Note :
6068  * check that
6069  * - stmt's expression have an attribute
6070  * - expression's attribute is not set nor object type
6071  * - partition type is equals to partition definitions
6072  * - partition max
6073  * - valid hash size
6074  */
6075 static int
6076 partition_range_min_max (DB_VALUE ** dest, DB_VALUE * inval, int min_max)
6077 {
6078  int op, rst;
6079  DB_VALUE nullval;
6080 
6081  if (dest == NULL)
6082  {
6083  return 0;
6084  }
6085 
6086  if (inval == NULL)
6087  {
6088  db_make_null (&nullval);
6089  inval = &nullval;
6090  }
6091 
6092  if (DB_IS_NULL (inval))
6093  { /* low or high infinite */
6094  if (*dest != NULL)
6095  {
6096  if (DB_IS_NULL (*dest))
6097  {
6098  return 1;
6099  }
6100  pr_free_ext_value (*dest);
6101  }
6102  *dest = db_value_copy (inval);
6103  return 0;
6104  }
6105 
6106  if (*dest == NULL)
6107  {
6108  *dest = db_value_copy (inval);
6109  }
6110  else
6111  {
6112  if (DB_IS_NULL (*dest))
6113  { /* low or high infinite */
6114  if (DB_IS_NULL (inval))
6115  {
6116  return 1;
6117  }
6118  else
6119  {
6120  return 0;
6121  }
6122  }
6123  op = (min_max == RANGE_MIN) ? DB_GT : DB_LT;
6124  rst = db_value_compare (*dest, inval);
6125  if (rst == op)
6126  {
6127  pr_free_ext_value (*dest);
6128  *dest = db_value_copy (inval);
6129  }
6130  else if (rst == DB_EQ)
6131  {
6132  return 1;
6133  }
6134  }
6135 
6136  return 0;
6137 }
6138 
6139 /*
6140  * db_value_list_add () -
6141  * return:
6142  * ptail(out):
6143  * val(in):
6144  */
6145 static int
6146 db_value_list_add (DB_VALUE_PLIST ** ptail, DB_VALUE * val)
6147 {
6148  DB_VALUE_PLIST *tmp_vallist;
6149  DB_VALUE nullval, *chkval;
6150 
6151  if (ptail == NULL)
6152  {
6153  return -1;
6154  }
6155 
6156  if (val == NULL)
6157  {
6158  db_make_null (&nullval);
6159  chkval = &nullval;
6160  }
6161  else
6162  {
6163  chkval = val;
6164  }
6165 
6166  tmp_vallist = (DB_VALUE_PLIST *) malloc (sizeof (DB_VALUE_PLIST));
6167  if (tmp_vallist == NULL)
6168  {
6169  return -1;
6170  }
6171 
6172  if (*ptail == NULL)
6173  {
6174  *ptail = tmp_vallist;
6175  }
6176  else
6177  {
6178  (*ptail)->next = tmp_vallist;
6179  *ptail = tmp_vallist;
6180  }
6181 
6182  (*ptail)->next = NULL;
6183  (*ptail)->val = db_value_copy (chkval);
6184 
6185  return 0;
6186 }
6187 
6188 /*
6189  * db_value_list_find () -
6190  * return:
6191  * phead(in):
6192  * val(in):
6193  */
6194 static int
6195 db_value_list_find (const DB_VALUE_PLIST * phead, const DB_VALUE * val)
6196 {
6197  DB_VALUE_PLIST *tmp;
6198  DB_VALUE nullval, *chkval;
6199 
6200  if (phead == NULL)
6201  {
6202  return 0;
6203  }
6204 
6205  if (val == NULL)
6206  {
6207  db_make_null (&nullval);
6208  chkval = &nullval;
6209  }
6210  else
6211  {
6212  chkval = (DB_VALUE *) val;
6213  }
6214 
6215  for (tmp = (DB_VALUE_PLIST *) phead; tmp; tmp = tmp->next)
6216  {
6217  if ((DB_IS_NULL (tmp->val) && DB_IS_NULL (chkval)) || db_value_compare (tmp->val, chkval) == DB_EQ)
6218  {
6219  return 1;
6220  }
6221  }
6222 
6223  return 0;
6224 }
6225 
6226 /*
6227  * db_value_list_finddel () -
6228  * return:
6229  * phead(in/out):
6230  * val(in):
6231  */
6232 static int
6233 db_value_list_finddel (DB_VALUE_PLIST ** phead, DB_VALUE * val)
6234 {
6235  DB_VALUE_PLIST *tmp, *pre = NULL;
6236  DB_VALUE nullval, *chkval;
6237 
6238  if (phead == NULL)
6239  {
6240  return 0;
6241  }
6242 
6243  if (val == NULL)
6244  {
6245  db_make_null (&nullval);
6246  chkval = &nullval;
6247  }
6248  else
6249  {
6250  chkval = val;
6251  }
6252 
6253  for (tmp = *phead; tmp; tmp = tmp->next)
6254  {
6255  if ((DB_IS_NULL (tmp->val) && DB_IS_NULL (chkval)) || db_value_compare (tmp->val, chkval) == DB_EQ)
6256  {
6257  if (pre == NULL)
6258  {
6259  *phead = tmp->next;
6260  }
6261  else
6262  {
6263  pre->next = tmp->next;
6264  }
6265 
6266  pr_free_ext_value (tmp->val);
6267  free_and_init (tmp);
6268 
6269  return 1;
6270  }
6271  pre = tmp;
6272  }
6273 
6274  return 0;
6275 }
6276 
6277 /*
6278  * pt_check_alter_partition () - do semantic checks on a alter partition clause
6279  * return: none
6280  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
6281  * stmt(in): a alter class statement
6282  * dbobj(in):
6283  *
6284  * Note :
6285  * check that
6286  * - partition type is equals to original partition definitions
6287  * - partition min/max
6288  */
6289 
6290 static void
6291 pt_check_alter_partition (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt, MOP dbobj)
6292 {
6293  PT_NODE *name_list, *part_list;
6294  PT_NODE *names, *parts, *val, *next_parts;
6295  PT_ALTER_CODE cmd;
6296  SM_CLASS *smclass, *subcls;
6297  DB_OBJLIST *objs;
6298  int i, setsize;
6299  int orig_cnt = 0, name_cnt = 0, parts_cnt = 0, chkflag = 0;
6300  DB_VALUE *psize;
6301  char *class_name, *part_name;
6302  DB_VALUE minele, maxele, *minval = NULL, *maxval = NULL;
6303  DB_VALUE *parts_val, *partmin = NULL, *partmax = NULL;
6304  DB_VALUE null_val;
6305  DB_VALUE_PLIST *minmax_head = NULL, *minmax_tail = NULL;
6306  DB_VALUE_PLIST *outlist_head = NULL, *outlist_tail = NULL;
6307  DB_VALUE_PLIST *inlist_head = NULL, *inlist_tail = NULL;
6308  DB_VALUE_PLIST *min_list, *max_list;
6309  DB_VALUE_PLIST *p, *next;
6310  PT_NODE *column_dt = NULL;
6311  PARSER_CONTEXT *tmp_parser = NULL;
6312  PT_NODE **statements = NULL;
6313  const char *expr_sql = NULL;
6314  int error = NO_ERROR;
6315 
6316  assert (parser != NULL);
6317 
6318  if (stmt == NULL)
6319  {
6320  return;
6321  }
6322 
6323  db_make_null (&minele);
6324  db_make_null (&maxele);
6325  db_make_null (&null_val);
6326 
6327  class_name = (char *) stmt->info.alter.entity_name->info.name.original;
6328  cmd = stmt->info.alter.code;
6329  if (cmd == PT_DROP_PARTITION || cmd == PT_ANALYZE_PARTITION || cmd == PT_REORG_PARTITION
6330  || cmd == PT_PROMOTE_PARTITION)
6331  {
6332  name_list = stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.partition.name_list;
6333  }
6334  else
6335  {
6336  name_list = NULL;
6337  }
6338 
6339  if (0 < parser->host_var_count)
6340  {
6341  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HOSTVAR_IN_DDL);
6342  return;
6343  }
6344 
6345  if (cmd == PT_ADD_HASHPARTITION || cmd == PT_COALESCE_PARTITION)
6346  {
6347  psize = pt_value_to_db (parser, stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.partition.size);
6348  }
6349  else
6350  {
6351  psize = NULL;
6352  }
6353 
6354  if (cmd == PT_ADD_PARTITION || cmd == PT_REORG_PARTITION)
6355  {
6356  part_list = stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.partition.parts;
6357  }
6358  else
6359  {
6360  part_list = NULL;
6361  }
6362 
6363  switch (cmd)
6364  { /* parameter check */
6365  case PT_DROP_PARTITION: /* name_list */
6366  case PT_PROMOTE_PARTITION:
6367  if (name_list == NULL)
6368  {
6369  chkflag = 1;
6370  }
6371  break;
6372  case PT_ANALYZE_PARTITION: /* NULL = ALL */
6373  break;
6374  case PT_ADD_PARTITION: /* parts */
6375  if (part_list == NULL)
6376  {
6377  chkflag = 1;
6378  }
6379  break;
6380  case PT_ADD_HASHPARTITION: /* psize */
6381  case PT_COALESCE_PARTITION: /* psize */
6382  if (psize == NULL)
6383  {
6384  chkflag = 1;
6385  }
6386  break;
6387  case PT_REORG_PARTITION: /* name_list, parts */
6388  if (name_list == NULL || part_list == NULL)
6389  {
6390  chkflag = 1;
6391  }
6392  break;
6393  default:
6394  chkflag = 1;
6395  break;
6396  }
6397 
6398  if (chkflag)
6399  {
6400  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
6401  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST, class_name);
6402  return;
6403  }
6404 
6405  /* get partition information : count, name, type */
6406  if (au_fetch_class (dbobj, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT) != NO_ERROR || smclass->partition == NULL)
6407  {
6408  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SELECT_AUTH_FAILURE,
6409  class_name);
6410  return;
6411  }
6412 
6413  if (smclass->partition->partition_type != PT_PARTITION_HASH)
6414  {
6415  PT_NODE *select_list;
6416 
6417  tmp_parser = parser_create_parser ();
6418  if (tmp_parser == NULL)
6419  {
6420  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
6421 
6422  goto check_end;
6423  }
6424 
6425  /* get partition expr */
6426  expr_sql = smclass->partition->expr;
6427 
6428  /* compile the select statement and get the correct data_type */
6429  statements = parser_parse_string (tmp_parser, expr_sql);
6430  if (statements == NULL)
6431  {
6432  if (er_errid () == NO_ERROR)
6433  {
6434  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_INFO);
6435  }
6436 
6437  goto check_end;
6438  }
6439 
6440  statements[0] = pt_compile (tmp_parser, statements[0]);
6441  if (statements[0] == NULL)
6442  {
6443  if (er_errid () == NO_ERROR)
6444  {
6445  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_INFO);
6446  }
6447 
6448  goto check_end;
6449  }
6450 
6451  assert (statements[0]->node_type == PT_SELECT && statements[0]->info.query.q.select.list != NULL);
6452 
6453  select_list = statements[0]->info.query.q.select.list;
6454  if (select_list->data_type != NULL)
6455  {
6456  column_dt = parser_copy_tree (parser, select_list->data_type);
6457  }
6458  else
6459  {
6460  column_dt = pt_domain_to_data_type (parser,
6461  tp_domain_resolve_default (pt_type_enum_to_db (select_list->type_enum)));
6462  }
6463 
6464  parser_free_parser (tmp_parser);
6465  tmp_parser = NULL;
6466  }
6467 
6468  chkflag = 0;
6469  switch (cmd)
6470  { /* possible action check */
6471  case PT_DROP_PARTITION: /* RANGE/LIST */
6472  case PT_ADD_PARTITION:
6473  case PT_REORG_PARTITION:
6474  case PT_PROMOTE_PARTITION:
6475  if (smclass->partition->partition_type == PT_PARTITION_HASH)
6476  {
6477  chkflag = 1;
6478  }
6479  break;
6480 
6481  case PT_ANALYZE_PARTITION: /* ALL */
6482  break;
6483 
6484  case PT_ADD_HASHPARTITION: /* HASH */
6485  case PT_COALESCE_PARTITION:
6486  if (smclass->partition->partition_type != PT_PARTITION_HASH)
6487  {
6488  chkflag = 1;
6489  }
6490  break;
6491 
6492  default:
6493  break;
6494  }
6495 
6496  if (chkflag)
6497  {
6498  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt->info.alter.entity_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
6499  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST, class_name);
6500  goto check_end;
6501  }
6502 
6503  db_make_null (&null_val);
6504  for (objs = smclass->users; objs; objs = objs->next)
6505  {
6506  if (au_fetch_class (objs->op, &subcls, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT) != NO_ERROR)
6507  {
6508  PT_ERRORc (parser, stmt, er_msg ());
6509  goto check_end;
6510  }
6511 
6512  if (!subcls->partition)
6513  {
6514  continue; /* not partitioned */
6515  }
6516 
6517  orig_cnt++;
6518 
6519  db_make_null (&minele);
6520  db_make_null (&maxele);
6521 
6522  if (psize == NULL)
6523  { /* RANGE or LIST */
6524  if (subcls->partition == NULL || subcls->partition->pname == NULL)
6525  {
6526  /* get partition type */
6527  goto invalid_partition_info_fail;
6528  }
6529 
6530  if (smclass->partition->partition_type == DB_PARTITION_RANGE && cmd != PT_DROP_PARTITION
6531  && cmd != PT_PROMOTE_PARTITION)
6532  {
6533  if (set_get_element_nocopy (subcls->partition->values, 0, &minele) != NO_ERROR)
6534  {
6535  goto invalid_partition_info_fail; /* RANGE MIN */
6536  }
6537  if (set_get_element_nocopy (subcls->partition->values, 1, &maxele) != NO_ERROR)
6538  {
6539  goto invalid_partition_info_fail; /* RANGE MAX */
6540  }
6541 
6542  /* MAX VALUE find for ADD PARTITION */
6543  if (cmd == PT_ADD_PARTITION)
6544  {
6545  partition_range_min_max (&maxval, &maxele, RANGE_MAX);
6546  }
6547  }
6548 
6549  for (names = name_list, chkflag = 0; names; names = names->next)
6550  {
6551  if (!names->partition_pruned
6552  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (names->info.name.original, subcls->partition->pname))
6553  {
6554  chkflag = 1;
6555  names->partition_pruned = 1; /* existence marking */
6556  names->info.name.db_object = objs->op;
6557 
6558  if (smclass->partition->partition_type == DB_PARTITION_RANGE && cmd == PT_REORG_PARTITION)
6559  {
6560  partition_range_min_max (&maxval, &maxele, RANGE_MAX);
6561  partition_range_min_max (&minval, &minele, RANGE_MIN);
6562  }
6563 
6564  if (smclass->partition->partition_type == DB_PARTITION_LIST && cmd == PT_REORG_PARTITION)
6565  {
6566  setsize = set_size (subcls->partition->values);
6567  for (i = 0; i < setsize; i++)
6568  { /* in-list old value */
6569  if (set_get_element_nocopy (subcls->partition->values, i, &minele) != NO_ERROR)
6570  {
6571  goto invalid_partition_info_fail;
6572  }
6573 
6574  if (db_value_list_add (&inlist_tail, &minele))
6575  {
6576  goto out_of_mem_fail;
6577  }
6578 
6579  if (inlist_head == NULL)
6580  {
6581  inlist_head = inlist_tail;
6582  }
6583  }
6584  }
6585  }
6586  }
6587 
6588  if (chkflag == 0)
6589  {
6590  if (smclass->partition->partition_type == DB_PARTITION_LIST)
6591  {
6592  setsize = set_size (subcls->partition->values);
6593  for (i = 0; i < setsize; i++)
6594  { /* out-list value */
6595  if (set_get_element_nocopy (subcls->partition->values, i, &minele) != NO_ERROR)
6596  {
6597  goto invalid_partition_info_fail;
6598  }
6599 
6600  if (db_value_list_add (&outlist_tail, &minele))
6601  {
6602  goto out_of_mem_fail;
6603  }
6604 
6605  if (outlist_head == NULL)
6606  {
6607  outlist_head = outlist_tail;
6608  }
6609  }
6610  }
6611  else if (smclass->partition->partition_type == DB_PARTITION_RANGE && cmd == PT_REORG_PARTITION)
6612  {
6613  /* for non-continuous or overlap ranges check */
6614  if (db_value_list_add (&minmax_tail, &minele))
6615  {
6616  goto out_of_mem_fail;
6617  }
6618 
6619  if (minmax_head == NULL)
6620  {
6621  minmax_head = minmax_tail;
6622  }
6623 
6624  if (db_value_list_add (&minmax_tail, &maxele))
6625  {
6626  goto out_of_mem_fail;
6627  }
6628  }
6629  }
6630 
6631 
6632  for (parts = part_list; parts; parts = parts->next)
6633  {
6634  if (!parts->partition_pruned
6635  && !intl_identifier_casecmp (parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original, subcls->partition->pname))
6636  {
6637  parts->partition_pruned = 1; /* existence marking */
6638  }
6639  }
6640  }
6641  }
6642 
6643  if (name_list)
6644  { /* checks unknown partition */
6645  for (names = name_list; names; names = names->next)
6646  {
6647  if (!names->partition_pruned)
6648  {
6649  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_DOES_NOT_EXIST,
6650  names->info.name.original);
6651  goto check_end;
6652  }
6653  name_cnt++;
6654  }
6655  }
6656 
6657  if (part_list)
6658  { /* checks duplicated definition */
6659  for (parts = part_list; parts; parts = parts->next)
6660  {
6661  if (smclass->partition->partition_type != (int) parts->info.parts.type)
6662  {
6663  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_TYPE_MISMATCH,
6664  parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
6665  goto check_end;
6666  }
6667 
6668  /* next part */
6669  next_parts = parts->next;
6670  if (next_parts != NULL && smclass->partition->partition_type != (int) next_parts->info.parts.type)
6671  {
6672  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_TYPE_MISMATCH,
6673  next_parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
6674  goto check_end;
6675  }
6676 
6677  part_name = (char *) parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original;
6678  if (parts->info.parts.values)
6679  {
6680  parts->info.parts.values =
6681  parser_walk_tree (parser, parts->info.parts.values, pt_check_and_replace_hostvar, &chkflag, NULL, NULL);
6682  if (parts->info.parts.type == PT_PARTITION_RANGE && parts->info.parts.values->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
6683  {
6684  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CONSTANT_TYPE_MISMATCH,
6685  part_name);
6686  goto check_end;
6687  }
6688  }
6689 
6690  if (smclass->partition->partition_type == PT_PARTITION_RANGE)
6691  {
6692  /* corece the partition value */
6693  val = parts->info.parts.values;
6694 
6695  if (val != NULL)
6696  {
6697  error = pt_coerce_partition_value_with_data_type (parser, val, column_dt);
6698  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6699  {
6700  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CONSTANT_TYPE_MISMATCH;
6701 
6702  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, part_name);
6703 
6704  goto check_end;
6705  }
6706  }
6707 
6708  /* check strict increasing rule */
6709  error = pt_check_range_partition_strict_increasing (parser, stmt, parts, next_parts, column_dt);
6710  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6711  {
6712  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
6713 
6714  goto check_end;
6715  }
6716 
6717  parts_val = pt_value_to_db (parser, parts->info.parts.values);
6718  if (parts_val == NULL)
6719  {
6720  parts_val = &null_val;
6721  }
6722 
6723  if (db_value_list_find (inlist_head, parts_val))
6724  {
6725  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_PARTITION_DEF,
6726  part_name);
6727  goto check_end;
6728  }
6729 
6730  if (db_value_list_add (&inlist_tail, parts_val))
6731  {
6732  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
6733  goto check_end;
6734  }
6735  if (inlist_head == NULL)
6736  {
6737  inlist_head = inlist_tail;
6738  }
6739 
6740  partition_range_min_max (&partmax, parts_val, RANGE_MAX);
6741  if (!DB_IS_NULL (parts_val))
6742  { /* MAXVALUE */
6743  partition_range_min_max (&partmin, parts_val, RANGE_MIN);
6744  }
6745  }
6746  else
6747  { /* LIST */
6748  for (val = parts->info.parts.values; val && val->node_type == PT_VALUE; val = val->next)
6749  {
6750  error = pt_coerce_partition_value_with_data_type (parser, val, column_dt);
6751  if (error != NO_ERROR)
6752  {
6753  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CONSTANT_TYPE_MISMATCH,
6754  part_name);
6755 
6756  goto check_end;
6757  }
6758 
6759  parts_val = pt_value_to_db (parser, val);
6760  if (parts_val == NULL)
6761  {
6762  parts_val = &null_val;
6763  }
6764 
6765  /* new-list duplicate check */
6766  if (db_value_list_find (minmax_head, parts_val))
6767  {
6768  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_PARTITION_DEF,
6769  part_name);
6770  goto check_end;
6771  }
6772 
6773  if (db_value_list_add (&minmax_tail, parts_val))
6774  {
6775  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
6776  goto check_end;
6777  }
6778  if (minmax_head == NULL)
6779  {
6780  minmax_head = minmax_tail;
6781  }
6782 
6783  /* out-list duplicate check */
6784  if (db_value_list_find (outlist_head, parts_val))
6785  {
6786  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_PARTITION_DEF,
6787  part_name);
6788  goto check_end;
6789  }
6790 
6791  /* in-list delete - lost check */
6792  db_value_list_finddel (&inlist_head, parts_val);
6793  }
6794  }
6795 
6796  /* check if has duplicated name in parts_list of itself */
6797  for (next_parts = parts->next; next_parts; next_parts = next_parts->next)
6798  {
6799  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (next_parts->info.parts.name->info.name.original, part_name))
6800  {
6801  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_PARTITION_DEF,
6802  part_name);
6803  goto check_end;
6804  }
6805  }
6806 
6807  parts_cnt++;
6808  if (parts->partition_pruned)
6809  {
6810  if (name_list)
6811  {
6812  for (names = name_list; names; names = names->next)
6813  {
6814  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (part_name, names->info.name.original))
6815  {
6816  names->partition_pruned = 0;
6817  break; /* REORG partition name reuse */
6818  }
6819  }
6820  if (names != NULL)
6821  {
6822  continue;
6823  }
6824  }
6825 
6826  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_PARTITION_DEF, part_name);
6827  goto check_end;
6828  }
6829  }
6830  }
6831 
6832  if (psize == NULL)
6833  { /* RANGE or LIST */
6834  orig_cnt = orig_cnt - name_cnt + parts_cnt;
6835  if (cmd != PT_PROMOTE_PARTITION)
6836  {
6837  if (orig_cnt < 1 && cmd == PT_DROP_PARTITION)
6838  {
6839  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CANNOT_DROP_ALL_PARTITIONS);
6840  goto check_end;
6841  }
6842 
6843  if (orig_cnt < 1 || orig_cnt > MAX_PARTITIONS)
6844  {
6845  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_SIZE);
6846  goto check_end;
6847  }
6848  }
6849 
6850  if (smclass->partition->partition_type == PT_PARTITION_RANGE)
6851  {
6852  if (cmd == PT_ADD_PARTITION)
6853  {
6854  if (DB_IS_NULL (maxval) || (partmin != NULL && db_value_compare (maxval, partmin) != DB_LT))
6855  {
6856  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_END_OF_PARTITION);
6857  goto check_end;
6858  }
6859 
6860  /* maxval save for do_create_partition */
6861  stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.partition.info = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, maxval);
6862  }
6863  else if (cmd == PT_REORG_PARTITION)
6864  {
6865  if (partmin == NULL)
6866  {
6867  /* reorganizing into one partition with MAXVALUE */
6868  if (parts_cnt != 1)
6869  {
6870  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_RANGE_INVALID,
6871  class_name);
6872  goto check_end;
6873  }
6874  }
6875  else if (!DB_IS_NULL (minval) && db_value_compare (partmin, minval) != DB_GT)
6876  {
6877  range_invalid_error:
6878  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_RANGE_INVALID,
6879  class_name);
6880  goto check_end;
6881  }
6882  if ((DB_IS_NULL (maxval) && !DB_IS_NULL (partmax))
6883  || (!DB_IS_NULL (maxval) && !DB_IS_NULL (partmax) && db_value_compare (maxval, partmax) == DB_GT))
6884  {
6885  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DATA_LOSS_IS_NOT_ALLOWED);
6886  goto check_end;
6887  }
6888 
6889  /* checks non-continuous or overlap ranges */
6890  for (min_list = minmax_head, max_list = (min_list) ? min_list->next : NULL; (min_list && max_list);
6891  min_list = max_list->next, max_list = (min_list) ? min_list->next : NULL)
6892  {
6893  if (DB_IS_NULL (partmax))
6894  { /* new-high infinite */
6895  if (DB_IS_NULL (max_list->val))
6896  {
6897  goto range_invalid_error;
6898  }
6899  continue;
6900  }
6901 
6902  if (DB_IS_NULL (min_list->val))
6903  { /* orig-low infinite */
6904  if (db_value_compare (partmin, max_list->val) != DB_GT)
6905  {
6906  goto range_invalid_error;
6907  }
6908  continue;
6909  }
6910 
6911  if (DB_IS_NULL (max_list->val))
6912  { /* orig-high infinite */
6913  if (db_value_compare (min_list->val, partmax) == DB_LT)
6914  {
6915  goto range_invalid_error;
6916  }
6917  continue;
6918  }
6919 
6920  if ((db_value_compare (minval, min_list->val) != DB_GT
6921  && db_value_compare (min_list->val, partmax) == DB_LT)
6922  || (db_value_compare (minval, max_list->val) == DB_LT
6923  && db_value_compare (max_list->val, partmax) != DB_GT)
6924  || (db_value_compare (min_list->val, minval) != DB_GT
6925  && db_value_compare (minval, max_list->val) == DB_LT)
6926  || (db_value_compare (min_list->val, partmax) == DB_LT
6927  && db_value_compare (partmax, max_list->val) != DB_GT))
6928  {
6929  goto range_invalid_error;
6930  }
6931  }
6932  }
6933  } /* end RANGE */
6934  else
6935  { /* LIST */
6936  if (cmd == PT_REORG_PARTITION && inlist_head != NULL)
6937  {
6938  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DATA_LOSS_IS_NOT_ALLOWED);
6939  goto check_end;
6940  }
6941  }
6942  }
6943  else
6944  { /* HASH */
6945  if (cmd == PT_ADD_HASHPARTITION)
6946  {
6947  orig_cnt += psize->data.i;
6948  }
6949  else
6950  {
6951  orig_cnt -= psize->data.i;
6952  }
6953 
6954  if (orig_cnt < 1 || psize->data.i < 1 || orig_cnt > MAX_PARTITIONS)
6955  {
6956  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_SIZE);
6957  goto check_end;
6958  }
6959  }
6960 
6961 check_end:
6962  if (tmp_parser != NULL)
6963  {
6964  parser_free_parser (tmp_parser);
6965  tmp_parser = NULL;
6966  }
6967 
6968  if (column_dt != NULL)
6969  {
6970  parser_free_tree (parser, column_dt);
6971  column_dt = NULL;
6972  }
6973 
6974  if (maxval)
6975  {
6976  pr_free_ext_value (maxval);
6977  }
6978  if (minval)
6979  {
6980  pr_free_ext_value (minval);
6981  }
6982  if (partmax)
6983  {
6984  pr_free_ext_value (partmax);
6985  }
6986  if (partmin)
6987  {
6988  pr_free_ext_value (partmin);
6989  }
6990 
6991  for (p = minmax_head; p; p = next)
6992  {
6993  next = p->next;
6994  pr_free_ext_value (p->val);
6995  free_and_init (p);
6996  }
6997  for (p = inlist_head; p; p = next)
6998  {
6999  next = p->next;
7000  pr_free_ext_value (p->val);
7001  free_and_init (p);
7002  }
7003  for (p = outlist_head; p; p = next)
7004  {
7005  next = p->next;
7006  pr_free_ext_value (p->val);
7007  free_and_init (p);
7008  }
7009 
7010  return;
7011 
7012 out_of_mem_fail:
7013  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7014  goto out_of_mem;
7015 
7016 invalid_partition_info_fail:
7017  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_INFO);
7018 
7019 out_of_mem:
7020  pr_clear_value (&minele);
7021  pr_clear_value (&maxele);
7022  goto check_end;
7023 }
7024 
7025 /*
7026  * pt_attr_refers_to_self () - is this a self referencing attribute?
7027  * return: 1 if attr refers to self
7028  * parser(in): the parser context
7029  * attr(in): an attribute
7030  * self(in): name of vclass being created/altered
7031  */
7032 static bool
7033 pt_attr_refers_to_self (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * attr, const char *self)
7034 {
7035  PT_NODE *type;
7036  DB_OBJECT *self_obj, *attr_obj;
7037 
7038  if (!attr || attr->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT || !attr->data_type || attr->data_type->node_type != PT_DATA_TYPE
7039  || !self)
7040  {
7041  return false;
7042  }
7043 
7044  for (type = attr->data_type->info.data_type.entity; type && type->node_type == PT_NAME; type = type->next)
7045  {
7046  /* self is a string because in the create case, self does not exist yet */
7047  if (!intl_identifier_casecmp (self, type->info.name.original))
7048  {
7049  return true;
7050  }
7051 
7052  /* an attribute whose type is a subclass of self is also considered a self-referencing attribute */
7053  self_obj = db_find_class (self);
7054  attr_obj = type->info.name.db_object;
7055  if (self_obj && attr_obj && db_is_subclass (attr_obj, self_obj) > 0)
7056  {
7057  return true;
7058  }
7059  }
7060 
7061  return false;
7062 }
7063 
7064 /*
7065  * pt_is_compatible_type () -
7066  * return: true on compatible type
7067  * arg1_type(in):
7068  * arg2_type(in):
7069  */
7070 static bool
7071 pt_is_compatible_type (const PT_TYPE_ENUM arg1_type, const PT_TYPE_ENUM arg2_type)
7072 {
7073  bool is_compatible = false;
7074  if (arg1_type == arg2_type)
7075  {
7076  is_compatible = true;
7077  }
7078  else
7079  switch (arg1_type)
7080  {
7081  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
7082  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
7083  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
7084  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
7085  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
7086  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
7087  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
7088  switch (arg2_type)
7089  {
7090  case PT_TYPE_SMALLINT:
7091  case PT_TYPE_INTEGER:
7092  case PT_TYPE_BIGINT:
7093  case PT_TYPE_FLOAT:
7094  case PT_TYPE_DOUBLE:
7095  case PT_TYPE_NUMERIC:
7096  case PT_TYPE_MONETARY:
7097  case PT_TYPE_LOGICAL: /* logical is compatible with these types */
7098  is_compatible = true;
7099  break;
7100  default:
7101  break;
7102  }
7103  break;
7104  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
7105  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
7106  switch (arg2_type)
7107  {
7108  case PT_TYPE_CHAR:
7109  case PT_TYPE_VARCHAR:
7110  is_compatible = true;
7111  break;
7112  default:
7113  break;
7114  }
7115  break;
7116  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
7117  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
7118  switch (arg2_type)
7119  {
7120  case PT_TYPE_NCHAR:
7121  case PT_TYPE_VARNCHAR:
7122  is_compatible = true;
7123  break;
7124  default:
7125  break;
7126  }
7127  break;
7128  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
7129  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
7130  switch (arg2_type)
7131  {
7132  case PT_TYPE_BIT:
7133  case PT_TYPE_VARBIT:
7134  is_compatible = true;
7135  break;
7136  default:
7137  break;
7138  }
7139  break;
7140  default:
7141  break;
7142  }
7143 
7144  return is_compatible;
7145 }
7146 
7147 /*
7148  * pt_check_vclass_attr_qspec_compatible () -
7149  * return:
7150  * parser(in):
7151  * attr(in):
7152  * col(in):
7153  */
7154 static PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE
7155 pt_check_vclass_attr_qspec_compatible (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * attr, PT_NODE * col)
7156 {
7157  bool is_object_type;
7158  PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE c = pt_union_compatible (parser, attr, col, true, &is_object_type);
7159 
7160  if (c == PT_UNION_INCOMP && pt_is_compatible_type (attr->type_enum, col->type_enum))
7161  {
7162  c = PT_UNION_COMP;
7163  }
7164 
7165  return c;
7166 }
7167 
7168 /*
7169  * pt_check_vclass_union_spec () -
7170  * return:
7171  * parser(in):
7172  * qry(in):
7173  * attrs(in):
7174  */
7175 static PT_NODE *
7176 pt_check_vclass_union_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * qry, PT_NODE * attrds)
7177 {
7178  PT_NODE *attrd = NULL;
7179  PT_NODE *attrs1 = NULL;
7180  PT_NODE *attrs2 = NULL;
7181  PT_NODE *att1 = NULL;
7182  PT_NODE *att2 = NULL;
7183  PT_NODE *result_stmt = NULL;
7184 
7185  /* parser assures us that it's a query but better make sure */
7186  if (!pt_is_query (qry))
7187  {
7188  return NULL;
7189  }
7190 
7191  if (!(qry->node_type == PT_UNION || qry->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE || qry->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION))
7192  {
7193  assert (qry->node_type == PT_SELECT);
7194  return qry;
7195  }
7196 
7197  result_stmt = pt_check_vclass_union_spec (parser, qry->info.query.q.union_.arg1, attrds);
7198  if (pt_has_error (parser) || result_stmt == NULL)
7199  {
7200  return NULL;
7201  }
7202  result_stmt = pt_check_vclass_union_spec (parser, qry->info.query.q.union_.arg2, attrds);
7203  if (pt_has_error (parser) || result_stmt == NULL)
7204  {
7205  return NULL;
7206  }
7207 
7208  attrs1 = pt_get_select_list (parser, qry->info.query.q.union_.arg1);
7209  if (attrs1 == NULL)
7210  {
7211  return NULL;
7212  }
7213  attrs2 = pt_get_select_list (parser, qry->info.query.q.union_.arg2);
7214  if (attrs2 == NULL)
7215  {
7216  return NULL;
7217  }
7218 
7219  for (attrd = attrds, att1 = attrs1, att2 = attrs2;
7220  attrd != NULL && att1 != NULL && att2 != NULL; attrd = attrd->next, att1 = att1->next, att2 = att2->next)
7221  {
7222  /* bypass any class_attribute in the vclass attribute defs */
7223  if (attrd->info.attr_def.attr_type == PT_META_ATTR)
7224  {
7225  continue;
7226  }
7227 
7228  /* we have a vclass attribute def context, so do union vclass compatibility checks where applicable */
7229  if (attrd->type_enum != PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
7230  {
7231  continue;
7232  }
7233 
7234  if (pt_vclass_compatible (parser, attrd->data_type, att1)
7235  && pt_vclass_compatible (parser, attrd->data_type, att2))
7236  {
7237  continue;
7238  }
7239 
7240  if (!pt_class_assignable (parser, attrd->data_type, att1))
7241  {
7242  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_INCOMPATIBLE_COL,
7243  attribute_name (parser, attrd), pt_short_print (parser, att1));
7244  return NULL;
7245  }
7246  if (!pt_class_assignable (parser, attrd->data_type, att2))
7247  {
7248  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att2, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_INCOMPATIBLE_COL,
7249  attribute_name (parser, attrd), pt_short_print (parser, att2));
7250  return NULL;
7251  }
7252  }
7253 
7254  assert (attrd == NULL && att1 == NULL && att2 == NULL);
7255 
7256  return qry;
7257 }
7258 
7259 /*
7260  * pt_check_cyclic_reference_in_view_spec () -
7261  * return:
7262  * parser(in):
7263  * node(in):
7264  * arg(in):
7265  * continue_walk(in):
7266  */
7267 PT_NODE *
7268 pt_check_cyclic_reference_in_view_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
7269 {
7270  const char *spec_name = NULL;
7271  PT_NODE *entity_name = NULL;
7272  DB_OBJECT *class_object;
7273  DB_QUERY_SPEC *db_query_spec;
7274  PT_NODE **result;
7275  PT_NODE *query_spec;
7276  const char *query_spec_string;
7277  const char *self = (const char *) arg;
7278  PARSER_CONTEXT *query_cache;
7279 
7280  if (node == NULL)
7281  {
7282  return node;
7283  }
7284 
7285  switch (node->node_type)
7286  {
7287  case PT_SPEC:
7288 
7289  entity_name = node->info.spec.entity_name;
7290  if (entity_name == NULL)
7291  {
7292  return node;
7293  }
7294  if (entity_name->node_type != PT_NAME)
7295  {
7296  return node;
7297  }
7298 
7299  spec_name = pt_get_name (entity_name);
7300  if (pt_str_compare (spec_name, self, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
7301  {
7302  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CYCLIC_REFERENCE_VIEW_SPEC, self);
7303  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
7304  return node;
7305  }
7306 
7307  class_object = entity_name->info.name.db_object;
7308  if (db_is_vclass (class_object) <= 0)
7309  {
7310  return node;
7311  }
7312 
7313  query_cache = parser_create_parser ();
7314  if (query_cache == NULL)
7315  {
7316  return node;
7317  }
7318 
7319  db_query_spec = db_get_query_specs (class_object);
7320  while (db_query_spec)
7321  {
7322  query_spec_string = db_query_spec_string (db_query_spec);
7323  result = parser_parse_string_use_sys_charset (query_cache, query_spec_string);
7324 
7325  if (result != NULL)
7326  {
7327  query_spec = *result;
7328  parser_walk_tree (query_cache, query_spec, pt_check_cyclic_reference_in_view_spec, arg, NULL, NULL);
7329  }
7330 
7331  if (pt_has_error (query_cache))
7332  {
7333  PT_ERROR (parser, node, query_cache->error_msgs->info.error_msg.error_message);
7334 
7335  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
7336  break;
7337  }
7338 
7339  db_query_spec = db_query_spec_next (db_query_spec);
7340  }
7341  parser_free_parser (query_cache);
7342  break;
7343 
7344  default:
7345  break;
7346  }
7347 
7348  return node;
7349 }
7350 
7351 /*
7352  * pt_check_vclass_query_spec () - do semantic checks on a vclass query spec
7353  * return:
7354  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the qry
7355  * qry(in): a vclass query specification
7356  * attrs(in): the attributes of the vclass
7357  * self(in): name of vclass being created/altered
7358  *
7359  * Note :
7360  * check that query_spec:
7361  * - count(attrs) == count(columns)
7362  * - corresponding attribute and query_spec column match type-wise
7363  * - query_spec column that corresponds to a shared attribute must be NA
7364  */
7365 
7366 static PT_NODE *
7367 pt_check_vclass_query_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * qry, PT_NODE * attrs, const char *self,
7368  const bool do_semantic_check)
7369 {
7370  PT_NODE *columns, *col, *attr;
7371  int col_count, attr_count;
7372 
7373  if (!pt_is_query (qry))
7374  {
7375  return NULL;
7376  }
7377 
7378  if (qry->info.query.into_list != NULL)
7379  {
7380  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_NO_INTO_CLAUSE);
7381  return NULL;
7382  }
7383 
7384  if (do_semantic_check)
7385  {
7386  qry->do_not_replace_orderby = 1;
7387  qry = pt_semantic_check (parser, qry);
7388  if (pt_has_error (parser) || qry == NULL)
7389  {
7390  return NULL;
7391  }
7392  }
7393 
7394  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, qry, pt_check_cyclic_reference_in_view_spec, (void *) self, NULL, NULL);
7395  if (pt_has_error (parser))
7396  {
7397  return NULL;
7398  }
7399 
7400  /* count(attrs) == count(query spec columns) */
7401  columns = pt_get_select_list (parser, qry);
7402  col_count = pt_length_of_select_list (columns, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
7403  attr_count = pt_length_of_list (attrs);
7404  if (attr_count != col_count)
7405  {
7406  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_CNT_NE_COL_CNT, attr_count, col_count);
7407  return NULL;
7408  }
7409 
7410  qry = pt_check_vclass_union_spec (parser, qry, attrs);
7411  if (pt_has_error (parser) || qry == NULL)
7412  {
7413  return NULL;
7414  }
7415 
7416  /* foreach normal/shared attribute and query_spec column do */
7417  for (attr = attrs, col = columns; attr != NULL && col != NULL; attr = attr->next, col = col->next)
7418  {
7419  /* bypass any class_attribute */
7420  if (attr->info.attr_def.attr_type == PT_META_ATTR)
7421  {
7422  attr = attr->next;
7423  continue;
7424  }
7425 
7426  if (col->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR)
7427  {
7428  PT_ERRORm (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HOSTVAR_NOT_ALLOWED_ON_QUERY_SPEC);
7429  }
7430  else if (attr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NONE)
7431  {
7432  if (col->node_type == PT_VALUE && col->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
7433  {
7434  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_INCOMPATIBLE_COL,
7435  attribute_name (parser, attr), pt_short_print (parser, col));
7436  }
7437  else
7438  {
7439  pt_fixup_column_type (col);
7440 
7441  attr->type_enum = col->type_enum;
7442  if (col->data_type)
7443  {
7444  attr->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, col->data_type);
7445  }
7446  }
7447  }
7448  /* attribute and query_spec column must match type-wise */
7449  else if (attr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
7450  {
7451  if (!pt_attr_refers_to_self (parser, attr, self) && !pt_vclass_compatible (parser, attr->data_type, col)
7452  && !pt_class_assignable (parser, attr->data_type, col))
7453  {
7454  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_INCOMPATIBLE_COL,
7455  attribute_name (parser, attr), pt_short_print (parser, col));
7456  }
7457  }
7458  else if (PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (attr->type_enum))
7459  {
7460  if (!pt_collection_assignable (parser, attr, col))
7461  {
7462  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_INCOMPATIBLE_COL,
7463  attribute_name (parser, attr), pt_short_print (parser, col));
7464  }
7465  }
7466  else if (pt_check_vclass_attr_qspec_compatible (parser, attr, col) != PT_UNION_COMP)
7467  {
7468  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_INCOMPATIBLE_COL,
7469  attribute_name (parser, attr), pt_short_print (parser, col));
7470  }
7471 
7472  /* any shared attribute must correspond to NA in the query_spec */
7473  if (is_shared_attribute (parser, attr) && col->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NA && col->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NULL)
7474  {
7475  PT_ERRORmf (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_QSPEC_COL_NOT_NA,
7476  attribute_name (parser, attr));
7477  }
7478  }
7479 
7480  return qry;
7481 }
7482 
7483 /*
7484  * pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec_column () -
7485  * return: current or new column
7486  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the qry
7487  * attr(in): the attributes of the vclass
7488  * col(in): the query_spec column of the vclass
7489  */
7490 
7491 PT_NODE *
7492 pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec_column (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * attr, PT_NODE * col)
7493 {
7494  bool is_object_type;
7495  PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE c;
7496  PT_NODE *new_col, *new_dt, *next_col;
7497 
7498  /* guarantees PT_TYPE_OBJECT and SET types are fully compatible. */
7499  if (attr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT || PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (attr->type_enum))
7500  {
7501  return col;
7502  }
7503 
7504  c = pt_union_compatible (parser, attr, col, true, &is_object_type);
7505  if (((c == PT_UNION_COMP)
7506  && (attr->type_enum == col->type_enum && PT_IS_PARAMETERIZED_TYPE (attr->type_enum) && attr->data_type
7507  && col->data_type)
7508  && ((attr->data_type->info.data_type.precision != col->data_type->info.data_type.precision)
7509  || (attr->data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision != col->data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision)))
7510  || (c == PT_UNION_INCOMP))
7511  {
7512  /* rewrite */
7513  next_col = col->next;
7514  col->next = NULL;
7515  new_col = new_dt = NULL;
7516 
7517  new_col = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
7518  if (new_col == NULL)
7519  {
7520  PT_ERRORm (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7521  return col; /* give up */
7522  }
7523 
7524  new_dt = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_TYPE);
7525  if (new_dt == NULL)
7526  {
7527  PT_ERRORm (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7528  parser_free_tree (parser, new_col);
7529  return col; /* give up */
7530  }
7531 
7532  /* move alias */
7533  new_col->line_number = col->line_number;
7534  new_col->column_number = col->column_number;
7535  new_col->alias_print = col->alias_print;
7536  col->alias_print = NULL;
7537  new_dt->type_enum = attr->type_enum;
7538  if (attr->data_type)
7539  {
7540  new_dt->info.data_type.precision = attr->data_type->info.data_type.precision;
7541  new_dt->info.data_type.dec_precision = attr->data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision;
7542  new_dt->info.data_type.units = attr->data_type->info.data_type.units;
7543  new_dt->info.data_type.collation_id = attr->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id;
7544  assert (new_dt->info.data_type.collation_id >= 0);
7545  new_dt->info.data_type.enumeration =
7546  parser_copy_tree_list (parser, attr->data_type->info.data_type.enumeration);
7547  }
7548  new_col->type_enum = new_dt->type_enum;
7549  new_col->info.expr.op = PT_CAST;
7550  new_col->info.expr.cast_type = new_dt;
7551  new_col->info.expr.arg1 = col;
7552  new_col->next = next_col;
7553  new_col->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, new_dt);
7554  PT_EXPR_INFO_SET_FLAG (new_col, PT_EXPR_INFO_CAST_SHOULD_FOLD);
7555  col = new_col;
7556  }
7557 
7558  return col;
7559 }
7560 
7561 /*
7562  * pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec () -
7563  * return:
7564  * parser(in):
7565  * qry(in):
7566  * attrs(in):
7567  */
7568 static PT_NODE *
7569 pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * qry, PT_NODE * attrs)
7570 {
7571  PT_NODE *columns, *col, *attr;
7572  PT_NODE *new_col, *prev_col;
7573  PT_NODE *node_list;
7574 
7575  /* parser assures us that it's a query but better make sure */
7576  if (!pt_is_query (qry))
7577  {
7578  return NULL;
7579  }
7580 
7581  if (qry->node_type != PT_SELECT)
7582  {
7583  if (!pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec (parser, qry->info.query.q.union_.arg1, attrs) || pt_has_error (parser)
7584  || (!pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec (parser, qry->info.query.q.union_.arg2, attrs)) || pt_has_error (parser))
7585  {
7586  return NULL;
7587  }
7588  }
7589 
7590  if (qry->node_type != PT_SELECT)
7591  {
7592  return qry; /* already done */
7593  }
7594 
7595  if (PT_IS_VALUE_QUERY (qry))
7596  {
7597  for (node_list = qry->info.query.q.select.list; node_list != NULL; node_list = node_list->next)
7598  {
7599  assert (node_list->node_type == PT_NODE_LIST);
7600 
7601  columns = node_list->info.node_list.list;
7602 
7603  col = columns;
7604  attr = attrs;
7605  prev_col = NULL;
7606 
7607  while (attr != NULL && col != NULL)
7608  {
7609  /* skip class attribute */
7610  if (attr->info.attr_def.attr_type == PT_META_ATTR)
7611  {
7612  attr = attr->next;
7613  continue;
7614  }
7615 
7616  new_col = pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec_column (parser, attr, col);
7617  if (new_col != col)
7618  {
7619  if (prev_col == NULL)
7620  {
7621  node_list->info.node_list.list = new_col;
7622  qry->type_enum = new_col->type_enum;
7623  if (qry->data_type)
7624  {
7625  parser_free_tree (parser, qry->data_type);
7626  }
7627  qry->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, new_col->data_type);
7628  }
7629  else
7630  {
7631  prev_col->next = new_col;
7632  }
7633 
7634  col = new_col;
7635  }
7636 
7637  prev_col = col;
7638  col = col->next;
7639  attr = attr->next;
7640  }
7641  }
7642  }
7643  else
7644  {
7645 
7646  columns = pt_get_select_list (parser, qry);
7647 
7648  /* foreach normal/shared attribute and query_spec column do */
7649  attr = attrs;
7650  col = columns;
7651  prev_col = NULL;
7652 
7653  while (attr && col)
7654  {
7655  /* bypass any class_attribute */
7656  if (attr->info.attr_def.attr_type == PT_META_ATTR)
7657  {
7658  attr = attr->next;
7659  continue;
7660  }
7661 
7662  new_col = pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec_column (parser, attr, col);
7663  if (new_col != col)
7664  {
7665  if (prev_col == NULL)
7666  {
7667  qry->info.query.q.select.list = new_col;
7668  qry->type_enum = new_col->type_enum;
7669  if (qry->data_type)
7670  {
7671  parser_free_tree (parser, qry->data_type);
7672  }
7673  qry->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, new_col->data_type);
7674  }
7675  else
7676  {
7677  prev_col->next = new_col;
7678  }
7679 
7680  col = new_col;
7681  }
7682 
7683  /* save previous link */
7684  prev_col = col;
7685  /* advance to next attribute and column */
7686  attr = attr->next;
7687  col = col->next;
7688  }
7689  }
7690 
7691  return qry;
7692 }
7693 
7694 /*
7695  * pt_check_default_vclass_query_spec () -
7696  * return: new attrs node including default values
7697  * parser(in):
7698  * qry(in):
7699  * attrs(in):
7700  *
7701  * For all those view attributes that don't have implicit default values,
7702  * copy the default values from the original table
7703  *
7704  * NOTE: there are two ways attrs is constructed at this point:
7705  * - stmt: create view (attr_list) as select... and the attrs will be created directly from the statement
7706  * - stmt: create view as select... and the attrs will be created from the query's select list
7707  * In both cases, each attribute in attrs will correspond to the column in the select list at the same index
7708  */
7709 static PT_NODE *
7710 pt_check_default_vclass_query_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * qry, PT_NODE * attrs)
7711 {
7712  PT_NODE *attr, *col;
7713  PT_NODE *columns = pt_get_select_list (parser, qry);
7714  PT_NODE *default_data = NULL;
7715  PT_NODE *default_value = NULL, *default_op_value = NULL;
7716  PT_NODE *spec, *entity_name;
7717  DB_OBJECT *obj;
7718  DB_ATTRIBUTE *col_attr;
7719  const char *lang_str;
7720  int flag = 0;
7721  bool has_user_format;
7722 
7723  /* Import default value and on update default expr from referenced table
7724  * for those attributes in the the view that don't have them. */
7725  for (attr = attrs, col = columns; attr && col; attr = attr->next, col = col->next)
7726  {
7727  if (attr->info.attr_def.data_default != NULL && attr->info.attr_def.on_update != DB_DEFAULT_NONE)
7728  {
7729  /* default values are overwritten */
7730  continue;
7731  }
7732  if (col->node_type != PT_NAME)
7733  {
7734  continue;
7735  }
7736  if (col->info.name.spec_id == 0)
7737  {
7738  continue;
7739  }
7740 
7741  spec = (PT_NODE *) col->info.name.spec_id;
7742  entity_name = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
7743  if (entity_name == NULL || !PT_IS_NAME_NODE (entity_name))
7744  {
7745  continue;
7746  }
7747 
7748  obj = entity_name->info.name.db_object;
7749  if (obj == NULL)
7750  {
7751  continue;
7752  }
7753 
7754  col_attr = db_get_attribute_force (obj, col->info.name.original);
7755  if (col_attr == NULL)
7756  {
7757  continue;
7758  }
7759 
7760  if (attr->info.attr_def.on_update == DB_DEFAULT_NONE)
7761  {
7762  attr->info.attr_def.on_update = col_attr->on_update_default_expr;
7763  }
7764 
7765  if (attr->info.attr_def.data_default == NULL)
7766  {
7767  if (DB_IS_NULL (&col_attr->default_value.value)
7768  && (col_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type == DB_DEFAULT_NONE))
7769  {
7770  /* don't create any default node if default value is null unless default expression type is not
7771  * DB_DEFAULT_NONE */
7772  continue;
7773  }
7774 
7775  if (col_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type == DB_DEFAULT_NONE)
7776  {
7777  default_value = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, &col_attr->default_value.value);
7778  if (default_value == NULL)
7779  {
7780  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7781  goto error;
7782  }
7783 
7784  default_data = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_DEFAULT);
7785  if (default_data == NULL)
7786  {
7787  parser_free_tree (parser, default_value);
7788  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7789  goto error;
7790  }
7791  default_data->info.data_default.default_value = default_value;
7792  default_data->info.data_default.shared = PT_DEFAULT;
7793  default_data->info.data_default.default_expr_type = DB_DEFAULT_NONE;
7794  }
7795  else
7796  {
7797  default_op_value = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
7798  if (default_op_value == NULL)
7799  {
7800  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7801  goto error;
7802  }
7803 
7804  default_op_value->info.expr.op =
7805  pt_op_type_from_default_expr_type (col_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type);
7806 
7807  if (col_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_op != T_TO_CHAR)
7808  {
7809  default_value = default_op_value;
7810  }
7811  else
7812  {
7813  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2, *arg3;
7814 
7815  arg1 = default_op_value;
7816  has_user_format = col_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format ? 1 : 0;
7817  arg2 = pt_make_string_value (parser, col_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_format);
7818  if (arg2 == NULL)
7819  {
7820  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value);
7821  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7822  goto error;
7823  }
7824 
7825  arg3 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
7826  if (arg3 == NULL)
7827  {
7828  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value);
7829  parser_free_tree (parser, arg2);
7830  }
7831  arg3->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
7832  lang_str = prm_get_string_value (PRM_ID_INTL_DATE_LANG);
7833  lang_set_flag_from_lang (lang_str, has_user_format, 0, &flag);
7834  arg3->info.value.data_value.i = (long) flag;
7835 
7836  default_value = parser_make_expression (parser, PT_TO_CHAR, arg1, arg2, arg3);
7837  if (default_value == NULL)
7838  {
7839  parser_free_tree (parser, default_op_value);
7840  parser_free_tree (parser, arg2);
7841  parser_free_tree (parser, arg3);
7842  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7843  goto error;
7844  }
7845  }
7846 
7847  default_data = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DATA_DEFAULT);
7848  if (default_data == NULL)
7849  {
7850  parser_free_tree (parser, default_value);
7851  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
7852  goto error;
7853  }
7854 
7855  default_data->info.data_default.default_value = default_value;
7856  default_data->info.data_default.shared = PT_DEFAULT;
7857  default_data->info.data_default.default_expr_type =
7858  col_attr->default_value.default_expr.default_expr_type;
7859  }
7860 
7861  attr->info.attr_def.data_default = default_data;
7862  }
7863  }
7864 
7865  return attrs;
7866 
7867 error:
7868  parser_free_tree (parser, attrs);
7869  return NULL;
7870 }
7871 
7872 /*
7873  * pt_check_create_view () - do semantic checks on a create vclass statement
7874  * or an "ALTER VIEW AS SELECT" statement
7875  *
7876  * return: none
7877  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
7878  * stmt(in): a create vclass statement
7879  *
7880  * Note :
7881  * This function is also called when doing "ALTER VIEW xxx AS SELECT ...",
7882  * which is a simplified case, since it does not support class inheritance.
7883  *
7884  * check that
7885  * - stmt's query_specs are union compatible with each other
7886  * - if no attributes are given, derive them from the query_spec columns
7887  * - if an attribute has no data type then derive it from its
7888  * matching query_spec column
7889  * - corresponding attribute and query_spec column must match type-wise
7890  * - count(attributes) == count(query_spec columns)
7891  * - query_spec column that corresponds to a shared attribute must be NA
7892  * - we allow order by clauses in the queries
7893  */
7894 
7895 static void
7896 pt_check_create_view (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt)
7897 {
7898  PT_NODE *all_attrs = NULL;
7899  PT_NODE *derived_attr = NULL;
7900  PT_NODE *result_stmt = NULL;
7901  PT_NODE **qry_specs_ptr = NULL;
7902  PT_NODE *crt_qry = NULL;
7903  PT_NODE **prev_qry_link_ptr = NULL;
7904  PT_NODE **attr_def_list_ptr = NULL;
7905  PT_NODE *prev_qry;
7906  const char *name = NULL;
7907  int attr_count = 0;
7908 
7909  assert (parser != NULL);
7910 
7911  if (stmt == NULL)
7912  {
7913  return;
7914  }
7915  if (stmt->node_type == PT_CREATE_ENTITY)
7916  {
7917  if (stmt->info.create_entity.entity_type != PT_VCLASS || stmt->info.create_entity.entity_name == NULL)
7918  {
7919  return;
7920  }
7921  }
7922  else if ((stmt->node_type == PT_ALTER) && (stmt->info.alter.code == PT_RESET_QUERY))
7923  {
7924  if (stmt->info.alter.entity_type != PT_VCLASS || stmt->info.alter.entity_name == NULL)
7925  {
7926  return;
7927  }
7928  }
7929  else
7930  {
7931  return;
7932  }
7933 
7934 
7935  if (stmt->node_type == PT_CREATE_ENTITY)
7936  {
7937  name = stmt->info.create_entity.entity_name->info.name.original;
7938  qry_specs_ptr = &stmt->info.create_entity.as_query_list;
7939  attr_def_list_ptr = &stmt->info.create_entity.attr_def_list;
7940  }
7941  else
7942  {
7943  assert ((stmt->node_type == PT_ALTER) && (stmt->info.alter.code == PT_RESET_QUERY));
7944  name = stmt->info.alter.entity_name->info.name.original;
7945  qry_specs_ptr = &stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.query.query;
7946  attr_def_list_ptr = &stmt->info.alter.alter_clause.query.attr_def_list;
7947  }
7948 
7949  if (*qry_specs_ptr == NULL || pt_has_error (parser))
7950  {
7951  return;
7952  }
7953 
7954  prev_qry = NULL;
7955  for (crt_qry = *qry_specs_ptr, prev_qry_link_ptr = qry_specs_ptr; crt_qry != NULL;
7956  prev_qry_link_ptr = &crt_qry->next, crt_qry = crt_qry->next)
7957  {
7958  PT_NODE *const save_next = crt_qry->next;
7959 
7960  crt_qry->next = NULL;
7961 
7962  /* TODO This seems to flag too many queries as view specs because it also traverses the tree to subqueries. It
7963  * might need a pre_function that returns PT_STOP_WALK for subqueries. */
7964  result_stmt = parser_walk_tree (parser, crt_qry, pt_set_is_view_spec, NULL, NULL, NULL);
7965  if (result_stmt == NULL)
7966  {
7967  assert (false);
7968  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_GENERIC_ERROR));
7969  return;
7970  }
7971  crt_qry = result_stmt;
7972 
7973  crt_qry->do_not_replace_orderby = 1;
7974  result_stmt = pt_semantic_check (parser, crt_qry);
7975  if (pt_has_error (parser))
7976  {
7977  if (prev_qry)
7978  {
7979  prev_qry->next = save_next;
7980  }
7981  crt_qry = NULL;
7982  (*prev_qry_link_ptr) = crt_qry;
7983  return;
7984  }
7985 
7986  if (result_stmt == NULL)
7987  {
7988  assert (false);
7989  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_GENERIC_ERROR));
7990  return;
7991  }
7992 
7993  if (pt_has_parameters (parser, result_stmt))
7994  {
7995  PT_ERRORmf (parser, crt_qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_VARIABLE_NOT_ALLOWED, 0);
7996  return;
7997  }
7998 
7999  crt_qry = result_stmt;
8000 
8001  crt_qry->next = save_next;
8002  (*prev_qry_link_ptr) = crt_qry;
8003  prev_qry = crt_qry;
8004  }
8005 
8006  attr_count = pt_number_of_attributes (parser, stmt, &all_attrs);
8007 
8008  /* if no attributes are given, try to derive them from the query_spec columns. */
8009  if (attr_count <= 0)
8010  {
8011  PT_NODE *crt_attr = NULL;
8012  PT_NODE *const qspec_attr = pt_get_select_list (parser, *qry_specs_ptr);
8013 
8014  assert (attr_count == 0);
8015  assert (*attr_def_list_ptr == NULL);
8016 
8017  for (crt_attr = qspec_attr; crt_attr != NULL; crt_attr = crt_attr->next)
8018  {
8019  PT_NODE *s_attr = NULL;
8020 
8021  if (crt_attr->alias_print)
8022  {
8023  s_attr = crt_attr;
8024  }
8025  else
8026  {
8027  /* allow attributes to be derived only from path expressions. */
8028  s_attr = pt_get_end_path_node (crt_attr);
8029  if (s_attr->node_type != PT_NAME)
8030  {
8031  s_attr = NULL;
8032  }
8033  }
8034 
8035  if (s_attr == NULL)
8036  {
8037  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_MISSING_ATTR_NAME,
8038  pt_short_print (parser, crt_attr));
8039  return;
8040  }
8041  else if (s_attr->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR)
8042  {
8043  PT_ERRORm (parser, s_attr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HOSTVAR_NOT_ALLOWED_ON_QUERY_SPEC);
8044  return;
8045  }
8046  else if (s_attr->node_type == PT_VALUE && s_attr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
8047  {
8048  PT_ERRORm (parser, s_attr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NULL_NOT_ALLOWED_ON_QUERY_SPEC);
8049  return;
8050  }
8051 
8052  derived_attr = pt_derive_attribute (parser, s_attr);
8053  if (derived_attr == NULL)
8054  {
8055  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_GENERIC_ERROR));
8056  return;
8057  }
8058 
8059  *attr_def_list_ptr = parser_append_node (derived_attr, *attr_def_list_ptr);
8060  }
8061 
8062  attr_count = pt_number_of_attributes (parser, stmt, &all_attrs);
8063  }
8064 
8065  assert (attr_count >= 0);
8066 
8067  /* do other checks on query specs */
8068  for (crt_qry = *qry_specs_ptr, prev_qry_link_ptr = qry_specs_ptr; crt_qry != NULL;
8069  prev_qry_link_ptr = &crt_qry->next, crt_qry = crt_qry->next)
8070  {
8071  PT_NODE *const save_next = crt_qry->next;
8072 
8073  crt_qry->next = NULL;
8074 
8075  result_stmt = pt_check_vclass_query_spec (parser, crt_qry, all_attrs, name, false);
8076  if (pt_has_error (parser))
8077  {
8078  return;
8079  }
8080  if (result_stmt == NULL)
8081  {
8082  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_GENERIC_ERROR));
8083  return;
8084  }
8085  crt_qry = result_stmt;
8086 
8087  all_attrs = pt_check_default_vclass_query_spec (parser, crt_qry, all_attrs);
8088  if (pt_has_error (parser))
8089  {
8090  return;
8091  }
8092  if (all_attrs == NULL)
8093  {
8094  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_GENERIC_ERROR));
8095  return;
8096  }
8097 
8098  result_stmt = pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec (parser, crt_qry, all_attrs);
8099  if (pt_has_error (parser))
8100  {
8101  return;
8102  }
8103  if (result_stmt == NULL)
8104  {
8105  assert (false);
8106  PT_ERRORm (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_GENERIC_ERROR));
8107  return;
8108  }
8109  crt_qry = result_stmt;
8110 
8111  crt_qry->next = save_next;
8112  (*prev_qry_link_ptr) = crt_qry;
8113  }
8114 }
8115 
8116 /*
8117  * pt_check_create_user () - semantic check a create user statement
8118  * return : none
8119  * parser(in) : the parser context
8120  * node(in) : create user node
8121  */
8122 static void
8123 pt_check_create_user (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8124 {
8125  PT_NODE *user_name;
8126  const char *name;
8127  int name_upper_size;
8128 
8129  if (!node)
8130  {
8131  return;
8132  }
8133  if (node->node_type != PT_CREATE_USER)
8134  {
8135  return;
8136  }
8137 
8138  user_name = node->info.create_user.user_name;
8139  if (user_name->node_type != PT_NAME)
8140  {
8141  return;
8142  }
8143 
8144  name = user_name->info.name.original;
8145  if (name == NULL)
8146  {
8147  return;
8148  }
8149  name_upper_size = intl_identifier_upper_string_size (name);
8150  if (name_upper_size >= DB_MAX_USER_LENGTH)
8151  {
8152  PT_ERRORm (parser, user_name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USER_NAME_TOO_LONG);
8153  }
8154 }
8155 
8156 /*
8157  * pt_check_create_entity () - semantic check a create class/vclass
8158  * return: none
8159  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
8160  * node(in): a create statement
8161  */
8162 
8163 static void
8164 pt_check_create_entity (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8165 {
8166  PT_NODE *parent, *qry_specs, *name, *create_like;
8167  PT_NODE *all_attrs, *r, *resolv_class, *attr;
8168  PT_NODE *tbl_opt_charset, *cs_node, *tbl_opt_coll, *coll_node;
8169  PT_NODE *tbl_opt = NULL;
8170  PT_MISC_TYPE entity_type;
8171  DB_OBJECT *db_obj, *existing_entity;
8172  int found, partition_status = DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
8173  int collation_id, charset;
8174  bool found_reuse_oid = false;
8175  bool found_auto_increment = false;
8176  bool found_tbl_comment = false;
8177  int error = NO_ERROR;
8178 
8179  entity_type = node->info.create_entity.entity_type;
8180 
8181  if (entity_type != PT_CLASS && entity_type != PT_VCLASS)
8182  {
8183  /* control should never reach here if tree is well-formed */
8184  assert (false);
8185  return;
8186  }
8187 
8188  tbl_opt_charset = tbl_opt_coll = NULL;
8189  for (tbl_opt = node->info.create_entity.table_option_list; tbl_opt != NULL; tbl_opt = tbl_opt->next)
8190  {
8191  assert (tbl_opt->node_type == PT_TABLE_OPTION);
8192 
8193  switch (tbl_opt->info.table_option.option)
8194  {
8195  case PT_TABLE_OPTION_REUSE_OID:
8196  {
8197  if (found_reuse_oid)
8198  {
8199  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_TABLE_OPTION,
8200  parser_print_tree (parser, tbl_opt));
8201  return;
8202  }
8203  else
8204  {
8205  found_reuse_oid = true;
8206  }
8207  }
8208  break;
8209 
8210  case PT_TABLE_OPTION_AUTO_INCREMENT:
8211  {
8212  if (found_auto_increment)
8213  {
8214  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_TABLE_OPTION,
8215  parser_print_tree (parser, tbl_opt));
8216  return;
8217  }
8218  else
8219  {
8220  if (tbl_opt->info.table_option.val != NULL)
8221  {
8222  found_auto_increment = true;
8223  assert (tbl_opt->info.table_option.val->node_type == PT_VALUE);
8224  assert (tbl_opt->info.table_option.val->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC);
8225  }
8226  }
8227  }
8228  break;
8229 
8230  case PT_TABLE_OPTION_CHARSET:
8231  {
8232  if (tbl_opt_charset != NULL)
8233  {
8234  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_TABLE_OPTION,
8235  parser_print_tree (parser, tbl_opt));
8236  return;
8237  }
8238  else
8239  {
8240  tbl_opt_charset = tbl_opt;
8241  }
8242  }
8243  break;
8244 
8245  case PT_TABLE_OPTION_COLLATION:
8246  {
8247  if (tbl_opt_coll != NULL)
8248  {
8249  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_TABLE_OPTION,
8250  parser_print_tree (parser, tbl_opt));
8251  return;
8252  }
8253  else
8254  {
8255  tbl_opt_coll = tbl_opt;
8256  }
8257  }
8258  break;
8259  case PT_TABLE_OPTION_COMMENT:
8260  {
8261  if (found_tbl_comment)
8262  {
8263  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DUPLICATE_TABLE_OPTION,
8264  parser_print_tree (parser, tbl_opt));
8265  return;
8266  }
8267  else
8268  {
8269  found_tbl_comment = true;
8270  }
8271  }
8272  break;
8273  default:
8274  /* should never arrive here */
8275  assert (false);
8276  break;
8277  }
8278  }
8279 
8280  /* validate charset and collation options, if any */
8281  cs_node = (tbl_opt_charset) ? tbl_opt_charset->info.table_option.val : NULL;
8282  coll_node = (tbl_opt_coll) ? tbl_opt_coll->info.table_option.val : NULL;
8283  charset = LANG_SYS_CODESET;
8284  collation_id = LANG_SYS_COLLATION;
8285  if ((cs_node != NULL || coll_node != NULL)
8286  && pt_check_grammar_charset_collation (parser, cs_node, coll_node, &charset, &collation_id) != NO_ERROR)
8287  {
8288  return;
8289  }
8290 
8291  /* check name doesn't already exist as a class */
8292  name = node->info.create_entity.entity_name;
8293  existing_entity = pt_find_class (parser, name, false);
8294  if (existing_entity != NULL)
8295  {
8296  if (!(entity_type == PT_VCLASS && node->info.create_entity.or_replace == 1 && db_is_vclass (existing_entity) > 0)
8297  /* If user sets "IF NOT EXISTS", do not throw ERROR if TABLE or VIEW with the same name exists, to stay
8298  * compatible with MySQL. */
8299  && !(entity_type == PT_CLASS && node->info.create_entity.if_not_exists == 1))
8300  {
8301  PT_ERRORmf (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_EXISTS, name->info.name.original);
8302  return;
8303  }
8304  }
8305  else
8306  {
8307  if (er_errid () == ER_LC_UNKNOWN_CLASSNAME && er_get_severity () == ER_WARNING_SEVERITY)
8308  {
8309  /* Because the class is still inexistent, normally, here we will have to encounter some errors/warnings like
8310  * ER_LC_UNKNOWN_CLASSNAME which is unuseful for current context indeed and may disturb other subsequent
8311  * routines. Thus, we can/should clear the errors safely. */
8312  er_clear ();
8313  }
8314  }
8315 
8316  pt_check_user_exists (parser, name);
8317 
8318  /* check uniqueness of non-inherited attribute names */
8319  all_attrs = node->info.create_entity.attr_def_list;
8320  pt_check_unique_attr (parser, name->info.name.original, all_attrs, PT_ATTR_DEF);
8321 
8322  if (entity_type == PT_CLASS)
8323  {
8324  /* for regular classes (no views) set default collation if needed */
8325  for (attr = node->info.create_entity.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
8326  {
8327  if (attr->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF && PT_HAS_COLLATION (attr->type_enum))
8328  {
8329  if (pt_attr_check_default_cs_coll (parser, attr, charset, collation_id) != NO_ERROR)
8330  {
8331  return;
8332  }
8333  }
8334  }
8335  }
8336 
8337  /* enforce composition hierarchy restrictions on attr type defs */
8338  pt_check_attribute_domain (parser, all_attrs, entity_type, name->info.name.original, found_reuse_oid, node);
8339 
8340  /* check that any and all super classes do exist */
8341  for (parent = node->info.create_entity.supclass_list; parent != NULL; parent = parent->next)
8342  {
8343  db_obj = pt_find_class (parser, parent, false);
8344  if (db_obj != NULL)
8345  {
8346  parent->info.name.db_object = db_obj;
8347  error = sm_partitioned_class_type (db_obj, &partition_status, NULL, NULL);
8348  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8349  {
8350  PT_ERROR (parser, node, er_msg ());
8351  break;
8352  }
8353  if (partition_status == DB_PARTITION_CLASS)
8354  {
8355  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_RUNTIME, MSGCAT_RUNTIME_NOT_ALLOWED_ACCESS_TO_PARTITION,
8356  parent->info.name.original);
8357  break;
8358  }
8359  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, parent);
8360 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
8361  if (sm_has_text_domain (db_get_attributes (db_obj), 1))
8362  {
8363  /* prevent to define it as a superclass */
8364  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_REGU_NOT_IMPLEMENTED, 1, rel_major_release_string ());
8365  PT_ERROR (parser, node, er_msg ());
8366  break;
8367  }
8368 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
8369  }
8370  else
8371  {
8372  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, parent, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NONEXISTENT_SUPCLASS,
8373  parent->info.name.original, pt_short_print (parser, node));
8374  return;
8375  }
8376  }
8377 
8378  if (error != NO_ERROR)
8379  {
8380  return;
8381  }
8382 
8383  /* an INHERIT_clause in a create_vclass_stmt without a SUBCLASS_clause is not meaningful. */
8384  if (node->info.create_entity.resolution_list && !node->info.create_entity.supclass_list)
8385  {
8386  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_SUBCLASS_CLAUSE,
8387  pt_short_print_l (parser, node->info.create_entity.resolution_list));
8388  return;
8389  }
8390  else
8391  {
8392  /* the INHERIT_clause can only reference classes that are in the SUBCLASS_clause. */
8393  for (r = node->info.create_entity.resolution_list; r; r = r->next)
8394  {
8395  resolv_class = r->info.resolution.of_sup_class_name;
8396  found = 0;
8397 
8398  for (parent = node->info.create_entity.supclass_list; parent && !found; parent = parent->next)
8399  {
8400  found = !pt_str_compare (resolv_class->info.name.original, parent->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE);
8401  }
8402 
8403  if (!found)
8404  {
8405  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, resolv_class, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_IN_SUBCLASS_LIST,
8406  parser_print_tree (parser, r), pt_short_print_l (parser,
8407  node->info.create_entity.supclass_list));
8408  return;
8409  }
8410  }
8411  }
8412 
8413  if (entity_type == PT_VCLASS)
8414  {
8415  /* The grammar restricts table options to CREATE CLASS / TABLE */
8416  assert (node->info.create_entity.table_option_list == NULL);
8417 
8418  for (attr = all_attrs; attr; attr = attr->next)
8419  {
8420  if (attr->info.attr_def.auto_increment != NULL)
8421  {
8422  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_VCLASS_ATT_CANT_BE_AUTOINC);
8423  return;
8424  }
8425  }
8426  }
8427 
8428  qry_specs = node->info.create_entity.as_query_list;
8429  if (node->info.create_entity.entity_type == PT_CLASS)
8430  {
8431  PT_NODE *select = NULL;
8432  /* simple CLASSes must not have any query specs */
8433  if (qry_specs)
8434  {
8435  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry_specs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_NO_QUERY_SPEC);
8436  return;
8437  }
8438  /* user variables are not allowed in select list for CREATE ... AS SELECT ... */
8439  select = node->info.create_entity.create_select;
8440  if (select != NULL)
8441  {
8442  if (pt_has_parameters (parser, select))
8443  {
8444  PT_ERRORmf (parser, select, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_VARIABLE_NOT_ALLOWED, 0);
8445  return;
8446  }
8447  }
8448  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && node->info.create_entity.partition_info)
8449  {
8450  pt_check_partitions (parser, node, NULL);
8451  }
8452  }
8453  else /* must be a CREATE VCLASS statement */
8454  {
8455  pt_check_create_view (parser, node);
8456  }
8457 
8458  /* check that all constraints look valid */
8459  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
8460  {
8461  (void) pt_check_constraints (parser, node);
8462  }
8463 
8464  /*
8465  * check the auto_increment table option, AND REWRITE IT as
8466  * a constraint for the (single) AUTO_INCREMENT column.
8467  */
8468  if (found_auto_increment)
8469  {
8470  (void) pt_check_auto_increment_table_option (parser, node);
8471  }
8472 
8473  create_like = node->info.create_entity.create_like;
8474  if (create_like != NULL)
8475  {
8476  assert (entity_type == PT_CLASS);
8477 
8478  db_obj = pt_find_class (parser, create_like, false);
8479  if (db_obj == NULL)
8480  {
8481  PT_ERRORmf (parser, create_like, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_DOES_NOT_EXIST,
8482  create_like->info.name.original);
8483  return;
8484  }
8485  else
8486  {
8487  create_like->info.name.db_object = db_obj;
8488  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, create_like);
8489  if (db_is_class (db_obj) <= 0)
8490  {
8491  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_A,
8492  create_like->info.name.original, pt_show_misc_type (PT_CLASS));
8493  return;
8494  }
8495  }
8496  }
8497 
8498  for (attr = node->info.create_entity.attr_def_list; attr; attr = attr->next)
8499  {
8500  attr->info.attr_def.data_default = pt_check_data_default (parser, attr->info.attr_def.data_default);
8501  }
8502 }
8503 
8504 /*
8505  * pt_check_create_index () - semantic check a create index
8506  * return: none
8507  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
8508  * node(in): a create index statement
8509  */
8510 
8511 static void
8512 pt_check_create_index (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8513 {
8514  PT_NODE *name, *prefix_length, *col, *col_expr;
8515  DB_OBJECT *db_obj;
8516  int is_partition = DB_NOT_PARTITIONED_CLASS;
8517 
8518  /* check that there trying to create an index on a class */
8519  name = node->info.index.indexed_class->info.spec.entity_name;
8520  db_obj = db_find_class (name->info.name.original);
8521 
8522  if (db_obj == NULL)
8523  {
8524  PT_ERRORmf (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_A_CLASS, name->info.name.original);
8525  return;
8526  }
8527  else
8528  {
8529  /* make sure it's not a virtual class */
8530  if (db_is_class (db_obj) <= 0)
8531  {
8532  PT_ERRORm (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_INDEX_ON_VCLASS);
8533  return;
8534  }
8535  /* check if this is a partition class */
8536  if (sm_partitioned_class_type (db_obj, &is_partition, NULL, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
8537  {
8538  PT_ERROR (parser, node, er_msg ());
8539  return;
8540  }
8541 
8542  if (is_partition == DB_PARTITION_CLASS)
8543  {
8544  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PARTITION_REQUEST);
8545  return;
8546  }
8547 
8548  /* Check if the columns are valid. We only allow expressions and attribute names. The actual expressions will be
8549  * validated later, we're only interested in the node type */
8550  for (col = node->info.index.column_names; col != NULL; col = col->next)
8551  {
8552  if (col->node_type != PT_SORT_SPEC)
8553  {
8554  assert_release (col->node_type == PT_SORT_SPEC);
8555  return;
8556  }
8557  col_expr = col->info.sort_spec.expr;
8558  if (col_expr == NULL)
8559  {
8560  continue;
8561  }
8562  if (col_expr->node_type == PT_NAME)
8563  {
8564  /* make sure this is not a parameter */
8565  if (col_expr->info.name.meta_class != PT_NORMAL)
8566  {
8567  PT_ERRORmf (parser, col_expr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_INDEX_COLUMN,
8568  pt_short_print (parser, col_expr));
8569  return;
8570  }
8571  }
8572  else if (col_expr->node_type != PT_EXPR)
8573  {
8574  PT_ERRORmf (parser, col_expr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_INDEX_COLUMN,
8575  pt_short_print (parser, col_expr));
8576  return;
8577  }
8578  }
8579  /* make sure we don't mix up index types */
8580 
8581  pt_check_function_index_expr (parser, node);
8582  if (pt_has_error (parser))
8583  {
8584  return;
8585  }
8586 
8587  if (node->info.index.function_expr)
8588  {
8589  if (node->info.index.prefix_length || node->info.index.where)
8590  {
8591  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_CREATE_INDEX);
8592  }
8593  return;
8594  }
8595 
8596  name->info.name.db_object = db_obj;
8597 
8598  /* check that there is only one column to index on */
8599  pt_check_unique_attr (parser, NULL, node->info.index.column_names, PT_SORT_SPEC);
8600  if (pt_has_error (parser))
8601  {
8602  return;
8603  }
8604  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, name);
8605  if (pt_has_error (parser))
8606  {
8607  return;
8608  }
8609 
8610  prefix_length = node->info.index.prefix_length;
8611  if (prefix_length)
8612  {
8613  PT_NODE *index_column;
8614 
8615  if (prefix_length->type_enum != PT_TYPE_INTEGER || prefix_length->info.value.data_value.i == 0)
8616  {
8617  /*
8618  * Parser can read PT_TYPE_BIGINT or PT_TYPE_NUMERIC values
8619  * but domain precision is defined as integer.
8620  * So, we accept only non-zero values of PT_TYPE_INTEGER.
8621  */
8622  PT_ERRORmf (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_PREFIX_LENGTH,
8623  prefix_length->info.value.text);
8624  return;
8625  }
8626 
8627  assert (node->info.index.column_names != NULL);
8628 
8629  /* check if prefix index is allowed for this type of column */
8630  for (index_column = node->info.index.column_names; index_column != NULL; index_column = index_column->next)
8631  {
8632  PT_NODE *col_dt;
8633 
8634  if (index_column->node_type != PT_SORT_SPEC || index_column->info.sort_spec.expr == NULL
8635  || index_column->info.sort_spec.expr->node_type != PT_NAME)
8636  {
8637  continue;
8638  }
8639 
8640  col_dt = index_column->info.sort_spec.expr->data_type;
8641 
8642  if (col_dt != NULL && PT_HAS_COLLATION (col_dt->type_enum))
8643  {
8644  LANG_COLLATION *lc;
8645 
8646  lc = lang_get_collation (col_dt->info.data_type.collation_id);
8647 
8648  assert (lc != NULL);
8649 
8650  if (!(lc->options.allow_prefix_index))
8651  {
8652  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PREFIX_LENGTH_COLLATION,
8653  index_column->info.sort_spec.expr->info.name.original);
8654  return;
8655  }
8656  }
8657  }
8658  }
8659  }
8660 
8661  /* if this is a filter index, check that the filter is a valid filter expression. */
8662  pt_check_filter_index_expr (parser, node->info.index.column_names, node->info.index.where, db_obj);
8663 }
8664 
8665 /*
8666  * pt_check_drop () - do semantic checks on the drop statement
8667  * return: none
8668  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
8669  * node(in): a statement
8670  */
8671 static void
8672 pt_check_drop (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8673 {
8674  PT_NODE *temp;
8675  PT_NODE *name;
8676  DB_OBJECT *db_obj;
8677  DB_ATTRIBUTE *attributes;
8678  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO info;
8679 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
8680  DB_OBJECT *domain_class;
8681  char *drop_name_list = NULL;
8682 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
8683 
8684  if (node->info.drop.if_exists)
8685  {
8686  PT_NODE *prev_node, *free_node, *tmp1, *tmp2;
8687  prev_node = free_node = node->info.drop.spec_list;
8688 
8689  while ((free_node != NULL) && (free_node->node_type == PT_SPEC))
8690  {
8691  const char *cls_name;
8692  /* check if class name exists. if not, we remove the corresponding node from spec_list. */
8693  if ((name = free_node->info.spec.entity_name) != NULL && name->node_type == PT_NAME
8694  && (cls_name = name->info.name.original) != NULL
8695  && (db_obj = db_find_class_with_purpose (cls_name, true)) == NULL)
8696  {
8697  if (free_node == node->info.drop.spec_list)
8698  {
8699  node->info.drop.spec_list = node->info.drop.spec_list->next;
8700  prev_node = free_node->next;
8701  parser_free_node (parser, free_node);
8702  free_node = node->info.drop.spec_list;
8703  }
8704  else
8705  {
8706  prev_node->next = free_node->next;
8707  parser_free_node (parser, free_node);
8708  free_node = prev_node->next;
8709  }
8710  }
8711  else
8712  {
8713  prev_node = free_node;
8714  free_node = free_node->next;
8715  }
8716  }
8717  /* For each class, we check if it has previously been placed in spec_list. We also check if every class has a
8718  * superclass marked with PT_ALL previously placed in spec_list. If any of the two cases above occurs, we mark
8719  * for deletion the corresponding node in spec_list. Marking is done by setting the entity_name as NULL. */
8720
