8721  if (node->info.drop.spec_list && (node->info.drop.spec_list)->next)
8722  {
8723  tmp1 = (node->info.drop.spec_list)->next;
8724  while ((tmp1 != NULL) && (tmp1->node_type == PT_SPEC))
8725  {
8726  tmp2 = node->info.drop.spec_list;
8727  while ((tmp2 != NULL) && (tmp2 != tmp1) && (tmp2->node_type == PT_SPEC))
8728  {
8729  DB_OBJECT *db_obj1, *db_obj2;
8730  PT_NODE *name1, *name2;
8731  const char *cls_name1, *cls_name2;
8732 
8733  name1 = tmp1->info.spec.entity_name;
8734  name2 = tmp2->info.spec.entity_name;
8735  if (name1 && name2)
8736  {
8737  cls_name1 = name1->info.name.original;
8738  cls_name2 = name2->info.name.original;
8739 
8740  db_obj1 = db_find_class_with_purpose (cls_name1, true);
8741  db_obj2 = db_find_class_with_purpose (cls_name2, true);
8742 
8743  if ((db_obj1 == db_obj2)
8744  || ((tmp2->info.spec.only_all == PT_ALL) && db_is_subclass (db_obj1, db_obj2)))
8745  {
8746  parser_free_node (parser, name1);
8747  tmp1->info.spec.entity_name = NULL;
8748  break;
8749  }
8750  }
8751 
8752  tmp2 = tmp2->next;
8753  }
8754 
8755  tmp1 = tmp1->next;
8756  }
8757  }
8758 
8759  /* now we remove the nodes with entity_name NULL */
8760 
8761  prev_node = free_node = node->info.drop.spec_list;
8762 
8763  while ((free_node != NULL) && (free_node->node_type == PT_SPEC))
8764  {
8765 
8766  if ((name = free_node->info.spec.entity_name) == NULL)
8767  {
8768  if (free_node == node->info.drop.spec_list)
8769  {
8770  node->info.drop.spec_list = node->info.drop.spec_list->next;
8771  prev_node = free_node->next;
8772  parser_free_node (parser, free_node);
8773  free_node = node->info.drop.spec_list;
8774  }
8775  else
8776  {
8777  prev_node->next = free_node->next;
8778  parser_free_node (parser, free_node);
8779  free_node = prev_node->next;
8780  }
8781  }
8782  else
8783  {
8784  prev_node = free_node;
8785  free_node = free_node->next;
8786  }
8787  }
8788 
8789  }
8790 
8791  info.spec_parent = NULL;
8792  info.for_update = true;
8793  /* Replace each Entity Spec with an Equivalent flat list */
8794  parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_flat_spec_pre, &info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
8795 
8796  if (node->info.drop.entity_type != PT_MISC_DUMMY || node->info.drop.is_cascade_constraints)
8797  {
8798  const char *cls_nam;
8799  PT_MISC_TYPE typ = node->info.drop.entity_type;
8800 
8801  /* verify declared class type is correct */
8802  for (temp = node->info.drop.spec_list; temp && temp->node_type == PT_SPEC; temp = temp->next)
8803  {
8804  if ((name = temp->info.spec.entity_name) != NULL && name->node_type == PT_NAME
8805  && (cls_nam = name->info.name.original) != NULL && (db_obj = db_find_class (cls_nam)) != NULL)
8806  {
8807  if (typ != PT_MISC_DUMMY)
8808  {
8809  name->info.name.db_object = db_obj;
8810  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, name);
8811  if ((typ == PT_CLASS && db_is_class (db_obj) <= 0)
8812  || (typ == PT_VCLASS && db_is_vclass (db_obj) <= 0))
8813  {
8814  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_A, cls_nam,
8815  pt_show_misc_type (typ));
8816  }
8817  }
8818 
8819  if (node->info.drop.is_cascade_constraints && db_is_vclass (db_obj) > 0)
8820  {
8821  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
8822  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_VIEW_CASCADE_CONSTRAINTS_NOT_ALLOWED, cls_nam);
8823  }
8824  }
8825  }
8826  }
8827 
8828  /* for the classes to drop, check if a TEXT attr is defined on the class, and if defined, drop the reference class
8829  * for the attr */
8830  for (temp = node->info.drop.spec_list; temp && temp->node_type == PT_SPEC; temp = temp->next)
8831  {
8832  const char *cls_nam;
8833 
8834  if ((name = temp->info.spec.entity_name) != NULL && name->node_type == PT_NAME
8835  && (cls_nam = name->info.name.original) != NULL && (db_obj = db_find_class (cls_nam)) != NULL)
8836  {
8837  attributes = db_get_attributes_force (db_obj);
8838  while (attributes)
8839  {
8840  if (db_attribute_type (attributes) == DB_TYPE_OBJECT)
8841  {
8842 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
8843  if (sm_has_text_domain (attributes, 0))
8844  {
8845  domain_class = db_domain_class (db_attribute_domain (attributes));
8846  if (drop_name_list != NULL)
8847  {
8848  drop_name_list = pt_append_string (parser, drop_name_list, ",");
8849  }
8850 
8851  drop_name_list = pt_append_string (parser, drop_name_list, db_get_class_name (domain_class));
8852  }
8853 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
8854  }
8855  attributes = db_attribute_next (attributes);
8856  }
8857  }
8858  }
8859 
8860 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION) /* to disable TEXT */
8861  if (drop_name_list)
8862  {
8863  node->info.drop.internal_stmts =
8864  pt_append_statements_on_drop_attributes (parser, node->info.drop.internal_stmts, drop_name_list);
8865  if (node->info.drop.internal_stmts == NULL)
8866  {
8867  PT_ERRORm (parser, temp, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
8868  return;
8869  }
8870  }
8871 #endif /* ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION */
8872 }
8873 
8874 /*
8875  * pt_check_grant_revoke () - do semantic checks on the grant statement
8876  * return: none
8877  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
8878  * node(in): a statement
8879  */
8880 
8881 static void
8882 pt_check_grant_revoke (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8883 {
8884  PT_NODE *user;
8885  const char *username;
8886  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO info;
8887 
8888  /* Replace each Entity Spec with an Equivalent flat list */
8889  info.spec_parent = NULL;
8890  info.for_update = false;
8891  parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_flat_spec_pre, &info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
8892 
8893  /* make sure the grantees/revokees exist */
8894  for ((user = (node->node_type == PT_GRANT ? node->info.grant.user_list : node->info.revoke.user_list)); user;
8895  user = user->next)
8896  {
8897  if (user->node_type == PT_NAME && (username = user->info.name.original) && !db_find_user (username))
8898  {
8899  PT_ERRORmf (parser, user, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_USER_IS_NOT_IN_DB, username);
8900  }
8901  }
8902 }
8903 
8904 /*
8905  * pt_check_method () - semantic checking for method calls in expressions.
8906  * return: none
8907  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
8908  * node(in): a statement
8909  */
8910 
8911 static void
8912 pt_check_method (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
8913 {
8914  PT_NODE *target;
8915  DB_VALUE val;
8916  const char *method_name;
8917  DB_OBJECT *class_op;
8918  DB_METHOD *method = NULL;
8919 
8920  /* Note: it is possible that an error has been raised eariler. An example is that, method_name is NULL due to a
8921  * connection lost, i.e. db_Connect_status is 0, 'MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_NO_TARGET' is set. So we must check error
8922  * first. */
8923 
8924  assert (parser != NULL);
8925 
8926  if (pt_has_error (parser))
8927  {
8928  return;
8929  }
8930 
8931  assert (node != NULL && node->info.method_call.method_name != NULL);
8932 
8933  db_make_null (&val);
8934 
8935  /* check if call has a target */
8936  target = node->info.method_call.on_call_target;
8937  if (target == NULL)
8938  {
8939  if (jsp_is_exist_stored_procedure (node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original))
8940  {
8941  return;
8942  }
8943  else
8944  {
8945  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_NO_TARGET);
8946  return;
8947  }
8948  }
8949 
8950  /* if we have a null target, constant folding has determined we have no target, there is nothing to check. */
8951  if ((target->node_type == PT_VALUE) && (target->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL))
8952  {
8953  return;
8954  }
8955 
8956  if ((!target->data_type) || (!target->data_type->info.data_type.entity))
8957  {
8958  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_TARGET_NOT_OBJ);
8959  return;
8960  }
8961 
8962  if (!(class_op = target->data_type->info.data_type.entity->info.name.db_object))
8963  {
8964  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "semantic");
8965  return;
8966  }
8967 
8968  method_name = node->info.method_call.method_name->info.name.original;
8969  method = (DB_METHOD *) db_get_method (class_op, method_name);
8970  if (method == NULL)
8971  {
8972  if (er_errid () == ER_OBJ_INVALID_METHOD)
8973  {
8974  er_clear ();
8975  }
8976 
8977  method = (DB_METHOD *) db_get_class_method (class_op, method_name);
8978  if (method == NULL)
8979  {
8980  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_DOESNT_EXIST, method_name);
8981  return;
8982  }
8983  else
8984  {
8985  /* Check to see that they are calling the class method on a class object. We check the initial value if it
8986  * is a parameter knowing that the user could change it at run time. We probably need to add runtime checks
8987  * if we are not already doing this. Also we probably shouldn't get PT_VALUES here now that parameters are
8988  * not bound until runtime (but we'll guard against them anyway). */
8989  if (((target->node_type != PT_NAME) || (target->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER)
8990  || !pt_eval_path_expr (parser, target, &val) || db_is_instance (db_get_object (&val)) <= 0)
8991  && target->node_type != PT_VALUE
8992  && (target->data_type->info.data_type.entity->info.name.meta_class != PT_META_CLASS))
8993  {
8994  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_MIX_CLASS_INST);
8995  return;
8996  }
8997  }
8998  }
8999  else
9000  {
9001  /* Check to see that they are calling the instance method on an instance object. We check the initial value if
9002  * it is a parameter knowing that the user could change it at run time. We probably need to add runtime checks
9003  * if we are not already doing this. Also we probably shouldn't get PT_VALUES here now that parameters are not
9004  * bound until runtime (but we'll guard against them anyway). */
9005  if (((target->node_type != PT_NAME) || (target->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER)
9006  || !pt_eval_path_expr (parser, target, &val) || db_is_instance (db_get_object (&val)) <= 0)
9007  && target->node_type != PT_VALUE
9008  && (target->data_type->info.data_type.entity->info.name.meta_class != PT_CLASS))
9009  {
9010  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_MIX_INST_CLASS);
9011  return;
9012  }
9013  }
9014 
9015  /* check if number of parameters match */
9016  if (db_method_arg_count (method) != pt_length_of_list (node->info.method_call.arg_list))
9017  {
9018  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_METH_ARG_NE_DEFINED);
9019  return;
9020  }
9021 
9022 }
9023 
9024 /*
9025  * pt_check_truncate () - do semantic checks on the truncate statement
9026  * return: none
9027  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
9028  * node(in): a statement
9029  */
9030 static void
9031 pt_check_truncate (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
9032 {
9033  PT_NODE *temp;
9034  PT_NODE *name;
9035  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO info;
9036  DB_OBJECT *db_obj;
9037 
9038  /* replace entity spec with an equivalent flat list */
9039  info.spec_parent = NULL;
9040  info.for_update = false;
9041  parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_flat_spec_pre, &info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
9042 
9043  temp = node->info.truncate.spec;
9044  if (temp && temp->node_type == PT_SPEC)
9045  {
9046  const char *cls_nam;
9047 
9048  if ((name = temp->info.spec.entity_name) != NULL && name->node_type == PT_NAME
9049  && (cls_nam = name->info.name.original) != NULL && (db_obj = db_find_class (cls_nam)) != NULL)
9050  {
9051  name->info.name.db_object = db_obj;
9052  pt_check_user_owns_class (parser, name);
9053  if (db_is_class (db_obj) <= 0)
9054  {
9055  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_A, cls_nam,
9056  pt_show_misc_type (PT_CLASS));
9057  }
9058  }
9059  }
9060 }
9061 
9062 /*
9063  * pt_check_kill () - do semantic checks on the kill statement
9064  * return: none
9065  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
9066  * node(in): a statement
9067  */
9068 static void
9069 pt_check_kill (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
9070 {
9071  PT_NODE *tran_id;
9072 
9073  for (tran_id = node->info.killstmt.tran_id_list; tran_id != NULL; tran_id = tran_id->next)
9074  {
9075  if (tran_id->type_enum != PT_TYPE_INTEGER)
9076  {
9077  PT_ERRORm (parser, tran_id, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_TRANSACTION_ID_WANT_INTEGER);
9078  break;
9079  }
9080  }
9081 }
9082 
9083 /*
9084  * pt_check_single_valued_node () - looks for names outside an aggregate
9085  * which are not in group by list. If it finds one, raises an error
9086  * return:
9087  * parser(in):
9088  * node(in):
9089  * arg(in/out):
9090  * continue_walk(in/out):
9091  */
9092 static PT_NODE *
9093 pt_check_single_valued_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
9094 {
9095  PT_AGG_CHECK_INFO *info = (PT_AGG_CHECK_INFO *) arg;
9096  PT_NODE *spec, *arg2, *group, *expr;
9097  char *node_str;
9098 
9099  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
9100 
9101  if (pt_is_aggregate_function (parser, node))
9102  {
9103  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9104  }
9105  else if (node->node_type == PT_SELECT)
9106  {
9107  /* Can not increment level for list portion of walk. Since those queries are not sub-queries of this query.
9108  * Consequently, we recurse separately for the list leading from a query. Can't just call
9109  * pt_to_uncorr_subquery_list() directly since it needs to do a leaf walk and we want to do a full walk on the
9110  * next list. */
9111  if (node->next)
9112  {
9113  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->next, pt_check_single_valued_node, info,
9114  pt_check_single_valued_node_post, info);
9115  }
9116 
9117  /* don't get confused by uncorrelated, set-derived subqueries. */
9118  if (node->info.query.correlation_level == 0 && (spec = node->info.query.q.select.from)
9119  && spec->info.spec.derived_table && spec->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_SET_EXPR)
9120  {
9121  /* no need to dive into the uncorrelated subquery */
9122  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
9123  }
9124  else
9125  {
9126  *continue_walk = PT_LEAF_WALK;
9127  }
9128 
9129  /* increase query depth as we dive into subqueries */
9130  info->depth++;
9131  }
9132  else
9133  {
9134  switch (node->node_type)
9135  {
9136  case PT_NAME:
9137  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9138 
9139  if (pt_find_spec (parser, info->from, node) && pt_find_attribute (parser, node, info->group_by) < 0)
9140  {
9141  if ((!PT_IS_OID_NAME (node) || parser->oid_included != PT_INCLUDE_OID_TRUSTME)
9142  && !PT_IS_CLASSOID_NAME (node) && node->info.name.meta_class != PT_METHOD
9143  && node->info.name.meta_class != PT_META_ATTR && node->info.name.meta_class != PT_META_CLASS
9144  && node->info.name.meta_class != PT_PARAMETER)
9145  {
9146  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_SINGLE_VALUED,
9147  pt_short_print (parser, node));
9148  }
9149  }
9150  break;
9151 
9152  case PT_DOT_:
9153  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9154 
9155  if ((arg2 = node->info.dot.arg2) && pt_find_spec (parser, info->from, arg2)
9156  && (pt_find_attribute (parser, arg2, info->group_by) < 0))
9157  {
9158  if (!PT_IS_OID_NAME (node->info.dot.arg2) || parser->oid_included != PT_INCLUDE_OID_TRUSTME)
9159  {
9160  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_SINGLE_VALUED,
9161  pt_short_print (parser, node));
9162  }
9163  }
9164  break;
9165 
9166  case PT_VALUE:
9167  /* watch out for parameters of type object--don't walk their data_type list */
9168  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9169  break;
9170 
9171  case PT_EXPR:
9172  if (node->info.expr.op == PT_INST_NUM || node->info.expr.op == PT_ROWNUM || node->info.expr.op == PT_PRIOR
9173  || node->info.expr.op == PT_CONNECT_BY_ROOT || node->info.expr.op == PT_SYS_CONNECT_BY_PATH)
9174  {
9175  if (info->depth == 0)
9176  { /* not in subqueries */
9177  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_SINGLE_VALUED,
9178  pt_short_print (parser, node));
9179  }
9180  }
9181  else if (node->info.expr.op == PT_LEVEL || node->info.expr.op == PT_CONNECT_BY_ISCYCLE
9182  || node->info.expr.op == PT_CONNECT_BY_ISLEAF)
9183  {
9184  if (info->depth == 0)
9185  { /* not in subqueries */
9186  for (group = info->group_by; group; group = group->next)
9187  {
9188  expr = group->info.sort_spec.expr;
9189  if (expr->node_type == PT_EXPR && expr->info.expr.op == node->info.expr.op)
9190  {
9191  break;
9192  }
9193  }
9194  if (group == NULL)
9195  {
9196  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_SINGLE_VALUED,
9197  pt_short_print (parser, node));
9198  }
9199  }
9200  }
9201  else
9202  {
9203  unsigned int save_custom;
9204 
9205  save_custom = parser->custom_print; /* save */
9206 
9207  parser->custom_print |= PT_CONVERT_RANGE;
9208  node_str = parser_print_tree (parser, node);
9209 
9210  for (group = info->group_by; group; group = group->next)
9211  {
9212  expr = group->info.sort_spec.expr;
9213  if (expr->node_type == PT_EXPR && pt_str_compare (node_str, expr->alias_print, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
9214  {
9215  /* find matched expression */
9216  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
9217  break;
9218  }
9219  }
9220 
9221  parser->custom_print = save_custom; /* restore */
9222  }
9223  break;
9224 
9225  default:
9226  break;
9227  }
9228  }
9229 
9230  return node;
9231 }
9232 
9233 /*
9234  * pt_check_single_valued_node_post () -
9235  * return:
9236  * parser(in):
9237  * node(in):
9238  * arg(in/out):
9239  * continue_walk(in/out):
9240  */
9241 static PT_NODE *
9242 pt_check_single_valued_node_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
9243 {
9244  PT_AGG_CHECK_INFO *info = (PT_AGG_CHECK_INFO *) arg;
9245 
9246  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
9247 
9248  if (node->node_type == PT_SELECT)
9249  {
9250  info->depth--; /* decrease query depth */
9251  }
9252 
9253  return node;
9254 }
9255 
9256 /*
9257  * pt_check_into_clause () - check arity of any into_clause
9258  * equals arity of query
9259  * return: none
9260  * parser(in): the parser context used to derive the statement
9261  * qry(in): a SELECT/UNION/INTERSECTION/DIFFERENCE statement
9262  */
9263 static void
9264 pt_check_into_clause (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * qry)
9265 {
9266  PT_NODE *into;
9267  int tgt_cnt, col_cnt;
9268 
9269  assert (parser != NULL);
9270 
9271  if (!qry)
9272  return;
9273 
9274  if (!(into = qry->info.query.into_list))
9275  return;
9276 
9277  if (qry->info.query.is_subquery != 0)
9278  {
9279  /* current query execution mechanism can not handle select_into inside subqueries, since only the results of
9280  * the main query are available on the client, where the select_into assignment is done
9281  */
9282  PT_ERRORm (parser, qry, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SELECT_INTO_IN_SUBQUERY);
9283  }
9284 
9285  tgt_cnt = pt_length_of_list (into);
9286  col_cnt = pt_length_of_select_list (pt_get_select_list (parser, qry), EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
9287  if (tgt_cnt != col_cnt)
9288  {
9289  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, into, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_COL_CNT_NE_INTO_CNT, col_cnt, tgt_cnt);
9290  }
9291 }
9292 
9293 /*
9294  * pt_semantic_check_local () - checks semantics on a particular statement
9295  * return:
9296  * parser(in):
9297  * node(in):
9298  * arg(in):
9299  * continue_walk(in):
9300  */
9301 static PT_NODE *
9302 pt_semantic_check_local (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
9303 {
9304  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO *info = (SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO *) arg;
9305  PT_NODE *next, *top_node = info->top_node;
9306  PT_NODE *orig = node;
9307  PT_NODE *t_node;
9308  PT_NODE *entity, *derived_table;
9309  PT_ASSIGNMENTS_HELPER ea;
9310  STATEMENT_SET_FOLD fold_as;
9311  PT_FUNCTION_INFO *func_info_p = NULL;
9312 
9313  assert (parser != NULL);
9314 
9315  if (!node)
9316  return NULL;
9317 
9318  next = node->next;
9319  node->next = NULL;
9320 
9321  switch (node->node_type)
9322  {
9323  /* Every type of node that can appear at the highest level should be listed here, unless no semantic check is
9324  * required. */
9325  case PT_DELETE:
9326  if (top_node->cannot_prepare == 1)
9327  {
9328  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
9329  }
9330 
9331  entity = NULL;
9332 
9333  /* Make sure that none of the classes that are subject for delete is a derived table */
9334  t_node = node->info.delete_.target_classes;
9335 
9336  if (t_node == NULL)
9337  {
9338  /* this is not a multi-table delete; check all specs for derived tables */
9339  entity = node->info.delete_.spec;
9340 
9341  while (entity)
9342  {
9343  assert (entity->node_type == PT_SPEC);
9344 
9345  if (entity->info.spec.derived_table != NULL)
9346  {
9347  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DELETE_DERIVED_TABLE);
9348  break;
9349  }
9350  }
9351  }
9352  else
9353  {
9354  /* multi-table delete */
9355  while (t_node)
9356  {
9357  entity = pt_find_spec_in_statement (parser, node, t_node);
9358 
9359  if (entity == NULL)
9360  {
9361  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_RESOLUTION_FAILED,
9362  t_node->info.name.original);
9363  break;
9364  }
9365 
9366  if (entity->info.spec.derived_table != NULL)
9367  {
9368  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DELETE_DERIVED_TABLE);
9369  break;
9370  }
9371 
9372  t_node = t_node->next;
9373  }
9374  }
9375 
9376  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9377  break;
9378 
9379  case PT_INSERT:
9380  if (top_node && top_node->cannot_prepare == 1)
9381  {
9382  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
9383  }
9384 
9385  if (node->info.insert.into_var != NULL && node->info.insert.value_clauses->next != NULL)
9386  {
9387  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_DO_INSERT_TOO_MANY, 0);
9388  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
9389  {
9390  PT_ERRORc (parser, node, db_error_string (3));
9391  }
9392  break;
9393  }
9394 
9395  if (node->info.insert.odku_assignments != NULL)
9396  {
9397  node = pt_check_odku_assignments (parser, node);
9398  if (node == NULL || pt_has_error (parser))
9399  {
9400  break;
9401  }
9402  }
9403  /* semantic check value clause for SELECT and INSERT subclauses */
9404  if (node)
9405  {
9406  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9407  }
9408 
9409  /* try to coerce insert_values into types indicated by insert_attributes */
9410  if (node)
9411  {
9412  pt_coerce_insert_values (parser, node);
9413  }
9414  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9415  {
9416  break;
9417  }
9418 
9419  if (node->info.insert.value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type != PT_IS_SUBQUERY)
9420  {
9421  /* Search and check sub-inserts in value list */
9422  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.insert.value_clauses, pt_check_sub_insert, NULL, NULL, NULL);
9423  }
9424  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9425  {
9426  break;
9427  }
9428 
9429  if (top_node && top_node->node_type != PT_INSERT && top_node->node_type != PT_SCOPE)
9430  {
9431  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INS_EXPR_IN_INSERT);
9432  }
9433  break;
9434 
9435  case PT_EVALUATE:
9436  if (node)
9437  {
9438  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9439  }
9440  break;
9441 
9442  case PT_METHOD_CALL:
9443  if (node->info.method_call.call_or_expr == PT_IS_MTHD_EXPR)
9444  {
9445  pt_check_method (parser, node);
9446  }
9447  else if (node->info.method_call.call_or_expr == PT_IS_CALL_STMT)
9448  {
9449  /* Expressions in method calls from a CALL statement need to be typed explicitly since they are not wrapped
9450  * in a query and are not explicitly type-checked via pt_check_method(). This is due to a bad decision which
9451  * allowed users to refrain from fully typing methods before the advent of methods in queries. */
9452  node->info.method_call.arg_list = pt_semantic_type (parser, node->info.method_call.arg_list, info);
9453  node->info.method_call.on_call_target =
9454  pt_semantic_type (parser, node->info.method_call.on_call_target, info);
9455  }
9456  break;
9457 
9458  case PT_FUNCTION:
9459  func_info_p = &node->info.function;
9460 
9461  if (func_info_p->function_type == PT_GENERIC && (pt_length_of_list (func_info_p->arg_list) > NUM_F_GENERIC_ARGS))
9462  {
9463  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GEN_FUNC_TOO_MANY_ARGS,
9464  func_info_p->generic_name, NUM_F_GENERIC_ARGS);
9465  }
9466 
9467  /* check order by for aggregate function */
9468  if (func_info_p->function_type == PT_GROUP_CONCAT)
9469  {
9470  if (pt_check_group_concat_order_by (parser, node) != NO_ERROR)
9471  {
9472  break;
9473  }
9474  }
9475  else if (func_info_p->function_type == PT_CUME_DIST || func_info_p->function_type == PT_PERCENT_RANK)
9476  {
9477  /* for CUME_DIST and PERCENT_RANK aggregate function */
9478  if (pt_check_cume_dist_percent_rank_order_by (parser, node) != NO_ERROR)
9479  {
9480  break;
9481  }
9482  }
9483 
9484  break;
9485 
9486  case PT_UNION:
9487  case PT_INTERSECTION:
9488  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
9489  if (top_node->cannot_prepare == 1)
9490  {
9491  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
9492  }
9493 
9494  /* semantic check {union|intersection|difference} operands */
9495  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9496  {
9497  break;
9498  }
9499 
9500  fold_as = pt_check_union_is_foldable (parser, node);
9501  if (fold_as != STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_NOTHING)
9502  {
9503  node = pt_fold_union (parser, node, fold_as);
9504 
9505  /* don't need do the following steps */
9506  break;
9507  }
9508 
9509  pt_check_into_clause (parser, node);
9510 
9511  /* check the orderby clause if present (all 3 nodes have SAME structure) */
9512  if (pt_check_order_by (parser, node) != NO_ERROR)
9513  {
9514  break; /* error */
9515  }
9516 
9517  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9518  if (node == NULL)
9519  {
9520  break;
9521  }
9522 
9523  /* only root UNION nodes */
9524  if (node->info.query.q.union_.is_leaf_node == false)
9525  {
9526  PT_NODE *attrs = NULL;
9527  int cnt, k;
9528  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *cinfo = NULL;
9529  PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE status;
9530 
9531  /* do collation inference necessary */
9532  attrs = pt_get_select_list (parser, node->info.query.q.union_.arg1);
9533  cnt = pt_length_of_select_list (attrs, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
9534 
9535  cinfo = (SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO *) malloc (cnt * sizeof (SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO));
9536  if (cinfo == NULL)
9537  {
9538  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
9539  break;
9540  }
9541 
9542  for (k = 0; k < cnt; ++k)
9543  {
9544  cinfo[k].idx = -1;
9545  cinfo[k].type_enum = PT_TYPE_NONE;
9546  cinfo[k].prec = DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION;
9547  cinfo[k].scale = DB_DEFAULT_SCALE;
9548  cinfo[k].coll_infer.coll_id = LANG_SYS_COLLATION;
9549  cinfo[k].coll_infer.codeset = LANG_SYS_CODESET;
9550  cinfo[k].coll_infer.coerc_level = PT_COLLATION_NOT_COERC;
9551  cinfo[k].coll_infer.can_force_cs = false;
9552  cinfo[k].ref_att = NULL;
9553  }
9554 
9555  status = pt_get_select_list_coll_compat (parser, node, cinfo, cnt);
9556  if (status == PT_UNION_INCOMP)
9557  {
9558  (void) pt_apply_union_select_list_collation (parser, node, cinfo, cnt);
9559  free (cinfo);
9560  break;
9561  }
9562 
9563  free (cinfo);
9564  }
9565  break;
9566 
9567  case PT_SELECT:
9568  if (top_node->cannot_prepare == 1)
9569  {
9570  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
9571  }
9572 
9573  if (node->info.query.single_tuple == 1)
9574  {
9575  if (pt_length_of_select_list (node->info.query.q.select.list, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS) != 1)
9576  {
9577  /* illegal multi-column subquery */
9578  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_SINGLE_COL);
9579  }
9580  }
9581 
9582  pt_check_into_clause (parser, node);
9583 
9584  if (node->info.query.q.select.with_increment)
9585  {
9586  PT_NODE *select_list = node->info.query.q.select.list;
9587  PT_NODE *hidden_list = node->info.query.q.select.with_increment;
9588 
9589  (void) parser_append_node (hidden_list, select_list);
9590  node->info.query.q.select.with_increment = NULL;
9591  }
9592 
9593  if (pt_has_aggregate (parser, node))
9594  {
9595  PT_AGG_CHECK_INFO info;
9596  PT_NODE *r;
9597  QFILE_TUPLE_VALUE_POSITION pos;
9598  PT_NODE *referred_node;
9599  int max_position;
9600 
9601  /* STEP 1: init agg info */
9602  info.from = node->info.query.q.select.from;
9603  info.depth = 0;
9604  info.group_by = node->info.query.q.select.group_by;
9605 
9606  max_position = pt_length_of_select_list (node->info.query.q.select.list, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
9607 
9608  for (t_node = info.group_by; t_node; t_node = t_node->next)
9609  {
9610  r = t_node->info.sort_spec.expr;
9611  if (r == NULL)
9612  {
9613  continue;
9614  }
9615  /*
9616  * If a position is specified on group by clause,
9617  * we should check its range.
9618  */
9619  if (r->node_type == PT_VALUE && r->alias_print == NULL)
9620  {
9621  if (r->type_enum != PT_TYPE_INTEGER)
9622  {
9623  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_WANT_NUM);
9624  continue;
9625  }
9626  else if (r->info.value.data_value.i == 0 || r->info.value.data_value.i > max_position)
9627  {
9628  PT_ERRORmf (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_RANGE_ERR,
9629  r->info.value.data_value.i);
9630  continue;
9631  }
9632  }
9633  else if (r->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR)
9634  {
9635  PT_ERRORmf (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_GROUPBY_ALLOWED,
9636  pt_short_print (parser, r));
9637  continue;
9638  }
9639 
9640  /* check for after group by position */
9641  pt_to_pos_descr (parser, &pos, r, node, &referred_node);
9642  if (pos.pos_no > 0)
9643  {
9644  /* set after group by position num, domain info */
9645  t_node->info.sort_spec.pos_descr = pos;
9646  }
9647  /*
9648  * If there is a node referred by the position,
9649  * we should rewrite the position to real name or expression
9650  * regardless of pos.pos_no.
9651  */
9652  if (referred_node != NULL)
9653  {
9654  t_node->info.sort_spec.expr = parser_copy_tree (parser, referred_node);
9655  parser_free_node (parser, r);
9656  }
9657  }
9658 
9659  /* STEP 2: check that grouped things are single valued */
9660  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY) || node->info.query.q.select.group_by == NULL)
9661  {
9662  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.list, pt_check_single_valued_node, &info,
9663  pt_check_single_valued_node_post, &info);
9664  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.having, pt_check_single_valued_node, &info,
9665  pt_check_single_valued_node_post, &info);
9666  }
9667  }
9668 
9669  if (pt_has_analytic (parser, node))
9670  {
9671  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.list, pt_check_analytic_function, (void *) node,
9672  NULL, NULL);
9673  }
9674 
9675  /* check the order by */
9676  if (pt_check_order_by (parser, node) != NO_ERROR)
9677  {
9678  break; /* error */
9679  }
9680 
9681  if (node->info.query.q.select.group_by != NULL && node->info.query.q.select.group_by->with_rollup)
9682  {
9683  bool has_gbynum = false;
9684 
9685  /* we do not allow GROUP BY ... WITH ROLLUP and GROUPBY_NUM () */
9686  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.having, pt_check_groupbynum_pre, NULL,
9687  pt_check_groupbynum_post, (void *) &has_gbynum);
9688 
9689  if (has_gbynum)
9690  {
9691  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CANNOT_USE_GROUPBYNUM_WITH_ROLLUP);
9692  }
9693  }
9694 
9695  if (node->info.query.q.select.connect_by)
9696  {
9697  bool has_level_greater, has_level_lesser;
9698  int disallow_ops[] = {
9699  2, /* number of operators */
9700  PT_CONNECT_BY_ISCYCLE,
9701  PT_CONNECT_BY_ISLEAF,
9702  };
9703  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.connect_by, pt_expr_disallow_op_pre, disallow_ops,
9704  NULL, NULL);
9705 
9706  /* check if the LEVEL of connect by is limited */
9707  pt_check_level_expr (parser, node->info.query.q.select.connect_by, &has_level_greater, &has_level_lesser);
9708  if (has_level_lesser)
9709  {
9710  /* override checking cycles to be ignored */
9711  if (node->info.query.q.select.check_cycles == CONNECT_BY_CYCLES_NONE)
9712  {
9713  node->info.query.q.select.check_cycles = CONNECT_BY_CYCLES_NONE_IGNORE;
9714  }
9715  else
9716  {
9717  node->info.query.q.select.check_cycles = CONNECT_BY_CYCLES_IGNORE;
9718  }
9719  }
9720  }
9721 
9722  entity = node->info.query.q.select.from;
9723  if (entity != NULL && entity->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_SHOWSTMT
9724  && (derived_table = entity->info.spec.derived_table) != NULL && derived_table->node_type == PT_SHOWSTMT)
9725  {
9726  SHOWSTMT_TYPE show_type;
9727  SHOW_SEMANTIC_CHECK_FUNC check_func = NULL;
9728 
9729  show_type = derived_table->info.showstmt.show_type;
9730  check_func = showstmt_get_metadata (show_type)->semantic_check_func;
9731  if (check_func != NULL)
9732  {
9733  node = (*check_func) (parser, node);
9734  }
9735  }
9736 
9737  /* check for session variable assignments */
9738  {
9739  int arg[2];
9740 
9741  arg[0] = PT_DEFINE_VARIABLE; /* type */
9742  arg[1] = 0; /* found */
9743 
9744  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.query.q.select.list, pt_find_op_type_pre, arg, NULL, NULL);
9745 
9746  if (arg[1]) /* an assignment was found */
9747  {
9748  PT_SELECT_INFO_SET_FLAG (node, PT_SELECT_INFO_DISABLE_LOOSE_SCAN);
9749  }
9750  }
9751 
9752  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9753  break;
9754 
9755  case PT_DO:
9756  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9757  break;
9758 
9759  case PT_SET_XACTION:
9760  /* Check for multiple isolation settings and multiple timeout settings */
9761  (void) pt_check_xaction_list (parser, node->info.set_xaction.xaction_modes);
9762 
9763  /* Check for mismatch of schema and instance isolation levels */
9764  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node->info.set_xaction.xaction_modes, pt_check_isolation_lvl, NULL, NULL, NULL);
9765  break;
9766 
9767  case PT_UPDATE:
9768  if (top_node->cannot_prepare == 1)
9769  {
9770  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
9771  }
9772 
9773  if (pt_has_aggregate (parser, node))
9774  {
9775  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UPDATE_NO_AGGREGATE);
9776  }
9777 
9778  pt_check_assignments (parser, node);
9779  pt_no_double_updates (parser, node);
9780 
9781  /* cannot update derived tables */
9782  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, node->info.update.assignment);
9783  while ((t_node = pt_get_next_assignment (&ea)) != NULL)
9784  {
9785  entity = pt_find_spec_in_statement (parser, node, t_node);
9786 
9787  if (entity == NULL)
9788  {
9789  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_RESOLUTION_FAILED,
9790  t_node->info.name.original);
9791  break;
9792  }
9793 
9794  if (entity->info.spec.derived_table != NULL || PT_SPEC_IS_CTE (entity))
9795  {
9796  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UPDATE_DERIVED_TABLE);
9797  break;
9798  }
9799 
9800  /* Update of views hierarchies not allowed */
9801  if (db_is_vclass (entity->info.spec.flat_entity_list->info.name.db_object) > 0
9802  && entity->info.spec.only_all == PT_ALL)
9803  {
9804  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UPDATE_SUBVCLASS_NOT_ALLOWED,
9805  t_node->info.name.original);
9806  break;
9807  }
9808  }
9809 
9810  /* Replace left to right attribute references in assignments before doing semantic check. The type checking phase
9811  * might have to perform some coercions on the replaced names. */
9812  node = pt_replace_names_in_update_values (parser, node);
9813 
9814  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9815 
9816  if (node != NULL && node->info.update.order_by != NULL)
9817  {
9818  PT_NODE *order;
9819  for (order = node->info.update.order_by; order != NULL; order = order->next)
9820  {
9821  PT_NODE *r = order->info.sort_spec.expr;
9822  if (r != NULL && r->node_type == PT_VALUE)
9823  {
9824  PT_ERRORmf (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_ORDERBY_ALLOWED,
9825  pt_short_print (parser, r));
9826  break;
9827  }
9828  }
9829  }
9830  break;
9831 
9832  case PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES:
9833  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9834  break;
9835 
9836  case PT_EXPR:
9837  if (node->info.expr.op == PT_CAST)
9838  {
9839  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
9840  if (node == NULL)
9841  {
9842  break;
9843  }
9844 
9845  if (node->node_type == PT_EXPR && node->info.expr.op == PT_CAST)
9846  {
9847  (void) pt_check_cast_op (parser, node);
9848  }
9849  }
9850 
9851  /* check instnum compatibility */
9852  if (pt_is_instnum (node) && PT_EXPR_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_EXPR_INFO_INSTNUM_NC))
9853  {
9854  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INSTNUM_COMPATIBILITY_ERR,
9855  "INST_NUM() or ROWNUM", "INST_NUM() or ROWNUM");
9856  }
9857 
9858  /* check default function */
9859  if (node->info.expr.op == PT_DEFAULTF)
9860  {
9861  pt_check_defaultf (parser, node);
9862  }
9863 
9864  break;
9865 
9866  case PT_SPEC:
9867  {
9868  PT_NODE *derived_table, *a, *b, *select_list;
9869  int attr_cnt, col_cnt, i, j;
9870 
9871  /* check ambiguity in as_attr_list of derived-query */
9872  for (a = node->info.spec.as_attr_list; a && !pt_has_error (parser); a = a->next)
9873  {
9874  for (b = a->next; b && !pt_has_error (parser); b = b->next)
9875  {
9876  if (a->node_type == PT_NAME && b->node_type == PT_NAME
9877  && !pt_str_compare (a->info.name.original, b->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
9878  {
9879  PT_ERRORmf (parser, b, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_AMBIGUOUS_REF_TO,
9880  b->info.name.original);
9881  }
9882  }
9883  }
9884 
9885  /* check hidden column of subquery-derived table */
9886  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && node->info.spec.derived_table_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY
9887  && (derived_table = node->info.spec.derived_table) && derived_table->node_type == PT_SELECT
9888  && derived_table->info.query.order_by && (select_list = pt_get_select_list (parser, derived_table)))
9889  {
9890  attr_cnt = pt_length_of_list (node->info.spec.as_attr_list);
9891  col_cnt = pt_length_of_select_list (select_list, INCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
9892  if (col_cnt - attr_cnt > 0)
9893  {
9894  /* make hidden column attrs */
9895  for (i = attr_cnt, j = attr_cnt; i < col_cnt; i++)
9896  {
9897  t_node = pt_name (parser, mq_generate_name (parser, "ha", &j));
9898  node->info.spec.as_attr_list = parser_append_node (t_node, node->info.spec.as_attr_list);
9899  }
9900  }
9901  }
9902  }
9903  break;
9904 
9905  case PT_NAME:
9906  if (PT_IS_OID_NAME (node) && !PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_NAME_INFO_GENERATED_OID)
9907  && !PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (node, PT_NAME_ALLOW_REUSABLE_OID))
9908  {
9909  PT_NODE *data_type = node->data_type;
9910 
9911  if (data_type != NULL && data_type->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
9912  {
9913  const char *name = data_type->info.data_type.entity->info.name.original;
9914  DB_OBJECT *class_obj = db_find_class (name);
9915 
9916  if (class_obj != NULL && sm_is_reuse_oid_class (class_obj))
9917  {
9918  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NON_REFERABLE_VIOLATION, name);
9919  }
9920  }
9921  }
9922  break;
9923 
9924  case PT_MERGE:
9925  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9926  {
9927  break;
9928  }
9929 
9930  if (top_node->cannot_prepare == 1)
9931  {
9932  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
9933  }
9934 
9935  if (pt_has_aggregate (parser, node))
9936  {
9937  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_NO_AGGREGATE);
9938  break;
9939  }
9940 
9941  pt_check_assignments (parser, node);
9942  pt_no_double_updates (parser, node);
9943 
9944  /* check destination derived table */
9945  entity = node->info.merge.into;
9946  if (entity->info.spec.derived_table != NULL)
9947  {
9948  PT_ERRORm (parser, entity, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_MERGE_DERIVED_TABLE);
9949  break;
9950  }
9951 
9952  /* check update spec */
9953  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, node->info.merge.update.assignment);
9954  while ((t_node = pt_get_next_assignment (&ea)) != NULL)
9955  {
9956  entity = pt_find_spec_in_statement (parser, node, t_node);
9957 
9958  if (entity == NULL)
9959  {
9960  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_RESOLUTION_FAILED,
9961  t_node->info.name.original);
9962  break;
9963  }
9964  /* update assign spec should be merge target */
9965  if (entity->info.spec.id != node->info.merge.into->info.spec.id)
9966  {
9967  PT_ERRORm (parser, t_node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_MERGE_CANT_AFFECT_SOURCE_TABLE);
9968  break;
9969  }
9970  }
9971  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9972  {
9973  break;
9974  }
9975 
9976  if (node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses)
9977  {
9978  if (node->info.merge.insert.value_clauses->next)
9979  {
9980  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_DO_INSERT_TOO_MANY, 0);
9981  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
9982  {
9983  PT_ERRORc (parser, node, db_error_string (3));
9984  }
9985  break;
9986  }
9987  /* check insert attributes list */
9988  for (entity = node->info.merge.insert.attr_list; entity; entity = entity->next)
9989  {
9990  if (entity->info.name.spec_id != node->info.merge.into->info.spec.id)
9991  {
9992  PT_ERRORm (parser, entity, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
9993  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_MERGE_CANT_AFFECT_SOURCE_TABLE);
9994  break;
9995  }
9996  }
9997  if (pt_has_error (parser))
9998  {
9999  break;
10000  }
10001  }
10002 
10003  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
10004 
10005  /* try to coerce insert_values into types indicated by insert_attributes */
10006  if (node)
10007  {
10008  pt_coerce_insert_values (parser, node);
10009  }
10010  break;
10011 
10012  default: /* other node types */
10013  break;
10014  }
10015 
10016  /* Select Aliasing semantic checking of select aliasing, check if it is zero-length string, i.e. "" Only appropriate
10017  * PT_NODE to be check will have 'alias' field as not NULL pointer because the initialized value of 'alias' is NULL
10018  * pointer. So it is safe to do semantic checking of aliasing out of the scope of above 'switch' statement and
10019  * without considering type of the PT_NODE. */
10020  if (node && node->alias_print && *(node->alias_print) == '\0')
10021  {
10022  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_DEFINED, "\"\"");
10023  }
10024 
10025  /* restore list link, if any */
10026  if (node)
10027  {
10028  node->next = next;
10029  }
10030 
10031  if (pt_has_error (parser))
10032  {
10033  if (node)
10034  {
10035  pt_register_orphan (parser, node);
10036  }
10037  else
10038  {
10039  pt_register_orphan (parser, orig);
10040  }
10041  return NULL;
10042  }
10043  else
10044  {
10045  return node;
10046  }
10047 }
10048 
10049 /*
10050  * pt_gen_isnull_preds () - Construct the IS NULL disjuncts for the expanded
10051  * list of path segments
10052  * return:
10053  * parser(in):
10054  * pred(in):
10055  * chain(in):
10056  */
10057 static PT_NODE *
10058 pt_gen_isnull_preds (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * pred, PT_CHAIN_INFO * chain)
10059 {
10060  PT_NODE *disj, *arg1, *next_spec, *conj, *new_path, *new_expr;
10061  PT_NODE *new_pred = NULL;
10062  UINTPTR next_spec_id;
10063  int i;
10064 
10065  /* The algorithm here is that we will incrementally build each new "IS NULL" disjunct. Each successive disjunct will
10066  * contain the previous path expression extended with the next path segment. We will use arg1 to build each
10067  * successive path expression. new_pred will collect the new disjuncts as we build them. */
10068 
10069  arg1 = NULL;
10070  for (i = 0; i < chain->chain_length - 1; i++)
10071  {
10072  /* Remember that the chain was constructed from the end of the path expression to the beginning. Thus, in path
10073  * expr a.b.c.d is null, segment d is in chain[0], c is in chain[1], b is in chain[2], and a is in chain[3].
10074  * Also, by convention, the path conjuncts implied by a path expression segment are hung off the path entity that
10075  * is generated by the path expression segment. In our case, this is the next spec in the chain. */
10076 
10077  next_spec = chain->chain_ptr[chain->chain_length - i - 2];
10078  next_spec_id = next_spec->info.spec.id;
10079  conj = next_spec->info.spec.path_conjuncts;
10080 
10081  /* check for structural errors */
10082  if ((conj->node_type != PT_EXPR) || (!conj->info.expr.arg1) || (!conj->info.expr.arg2)
10083  || (conj->info.expr.arg1->node_type != PT_NAME) || (conj->info.expr.arg2->node_type != PT_NAME)
10084  || (conj->info.expr.arg2->info.name.spec_id != next_spec_id))
10085  {
10086  goto error;
10087  }
10088 
10089  if (arg1 == NULL)
10090  {
10091  /* This is the first segment in the path expression. In this case we want to use the exposed name of the
10092  * spec found in the last chain slot. (i should be 0 here) */
10093  arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, conj->info.expr.arg1);
10094  if (arg1 == NULL)
10095  {
10096  goto out_of_mem;
10097  }
10098  }
10099  else
10100  {
10101  PT_NODE *arg2;
10102 
10103  /* we are building a new segment on the previous path expr */
10104  if (((new_path = parser_new_node (parser, PT_DOT_)) == NULL)
10105  || ((arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, conj->info.expr.arg1)) == NULL))
10106  {
10107  goto out_of_mem;
10108  }
10109 
10110  /* We need to null the resolved field of arg2 according to path expression conventions. This is necessary
10111  * since we copied part of the conjunct which is fully resolved. */
10112  arg2->info.name.resolved = NULL;
10113 
10114  /* attach both arguments to the new path segment */
10115  new_path->info.expr.arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, arg1);
10116  if (new_path->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
10117  {
10118  goto out_of_mem;
10119  }
10120 
10121  new_path->info.expr.arg2 = arg2;
10122 
10123  /* attach the data type */
10124  new_path->line_number = pred->line_number;
10125  new_path->column_number = pred->column_number;
10126  new_path->type_enum = arg2->type_enum;
10127  if (arg2->data_type && ((new_path->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, arg2->data_type)) == NULL))
10128  {
10129  goto out_of_mem;
10130  }
10131 
10132  /* Maintain the loop invariant that arg1 always is the path expression that we build on. */
10133  arg1 = new_path;
10134  }
10135 
10136  /* Link it in with a disjunct. */
10137  disj = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
10138  if (disj == NULL)
10139  {
10140  goto out_of_mem;
10141  }
10142 
10143  disj->line_number = pred->line_number;
10144  disj->column_number = pred->column_number;
10145  disj->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
10146  disj->info.expr.op = PT_IS_NULL;
10147  disj->info.expr.arg1 = arg1;
10148 
10149  if (new_pred == NULL)
10150  {
10151  /* Maintain the loop invariant that new_pred contains the predicate built so far. */
10152  new_pred = disj;
10153  }
10154  else
10155  {
10156  new_expr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
10157  if (new_expr == NULL)
10158  {
10159  goto out_of_mem;
10160  }
10161 
10162  new_expr->line_number = pred->line_number;
10163  new_expr->column_number = pred->column_number;
10164  new_expr->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
10165  new_expr->info.expr.op = PT_OR;
10166  new_expr->info.expr.arg1 = new_pred;
10167  new_expr->info.expr.arg2 = disj;
10168 
10169  /* Maintain the loop invariant that new_pred contains the predicate built so far. */
10170  new_pred = new_expr;
10171  }
10172  }
10173 
10174  new_expr = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
10175  if (new_expr == NULL)
10176  {
10177  goto out_of_mem;
10178  }
10179 
10180  new_expr->line_number = pred->line_number;
10181  new_expr->column_number = pred->column_number;
10182  new_expr->type_enum = PT_TYPE_LOGICAL;
10183  new_expr->info.expr.op = PT_OR;
10184  new_expr->info.expr.arg1 = pred;
10185  new_expr->info.expr.arg2 = new_pred;
10186  new_expr->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
10187 
10188  return new_expr;
10189 
10190 out_of_mem:
10191  PT_ERRORm (parser, pred, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
10192  return NULL;
10193 
10194 error:
10195  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "resolution");
10196  return NULL;
10197 }
10198 
10199 /*
10200  * pt_path_chain () - Construct the list of path entities that are used
10201  * in a path expression
10202  * return:
10203  * parser(in):
10204  * node(in):
10205  * arg(in):
10206  * continue_walk(in):
10207  */
10208 static PT_NODE *
10209 pt_path_chain (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
10210 {
10211  PT_CHAIN_INFO *chain = (PT_CHAIN_INFO *) arg;
10212  PT_NODE *tmp;
10213 
10214  switch (node->node_type)
10215  {
10216  case PT_SPEC:
10217  if (node->info.spec.id == (UINTPTR) chain->spec_id)
10218  {
10219  /* This is the spec to which the final path segment resolves. Start gathering the spec chain. */
10220  chain->chain_ptr[0] = node;
10221  chain->chain_length = 1;
10222  }
10223  else if (chain->chain_length > 0)
10224  {
10225  /* This indicates that we are currently walking up the chain. Need to check if this spec is the parent of the
10226  * last spec. */
10227  for (tmp = node->info.spec.path_entities; tmp != NULL; tmp = tmp->next)
10228  {
10229  if (tmp == chain->chain_ptr[chain->chain_length - 1])
10230  {
10231  /* This is the parent, add it to the list. First check if we have space. */
10232  if (chain->chain_length == chain->chain_size)
10233  {
10234  /* Need to expand, just double the size. */
10235 
10236  chain->chain_size *= 2;
10237  if (chain->chain_ptr == chain->chain)
10238  {
10239  /* This will be the first time we need to alloc. */
10240  chain->chain_ptr = (PT_NODE **) malloc (chain->chain_size * sizeof (PT_NODE *));
10241  if (chain->chain_ptr == NULL)
10242  {
10243  goto out_of_mem;
10244  }
10245  memcpy (chain->chain_ptr, &chain->chain, (chain->chain_length * sizeof (PT_NODE *)));
10246  }
10247  else
10248  {
10249  PT_NODE **tmp;
10250 
10251  tmp = (PT_NODE **) realloc (chain->chain_ptr, (chain->chain_size * sizeof (PT_NODE *)));
10252  if (tmp == NULL)
10253  {
10254  goto out_of_mem;
10255  }
10256  chain->chain_ptr = tmp;
10257  }
10258  }
10259 
10260  /* Add in the parent. */
10261  chain->chain_ptr[chain->chain_length] = node;
10262  chain->chain_length++;
10263  }
10264  }
10265  }
10266  break;
10267 
10268  case PT_SELECT:
10269  case PT_DELETE:
10270  case PT_UPDATE:
10271  case PT_MERGE:
10272  if (chain->chain_length > 0)
10273  {
10274  /* We are about to leave the scope where the chain was found, we can safely stop the walk since we must have
10275  * found the whole chain. */
10276  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
10277  }
10278  break;
10279 
10280  default:
10281  break;
10282  }
10283 
10284  return node;
10285 
10286 out_of_mem:
10287  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
10288 
10289  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
10290  return node;
10291 }
10292 
10293 /*
10294  * pt_expand_isnull_preds_helper () - expand path_expr "IS NULL" predicates to
10295  * include any path segment being NULL
10296  * return:
10297  * parser(in):
10298  * node(in):
10299  * arg(in):
10300  * continue_walk(in):
10301  */
10302 static PT_NODE *
10303 pt_expand_isnull_preds_helper (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
10304 {
10305  PT_NODE *statement = (PT_NODE *) arg;
10306  PT_CHAIN_INFO chain_info;
10307 
10308  if (node->node_type == PT_EXPR && node->info.expr.op == PT_IS_NULL && node->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_DOT_)
10309  {
10310  chain_info.chain_ptr = chain_info.chain;
10311  chain_info.chain_size = PT_CHAIN_LENGTH;
10312  chain_info.chain_length = 0;
10313  chain_info.spec_id = node->info.expr.arg1->info.dot.arg2->info.name.spec_id;
10314 
10315  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, statement, NULL, NULL, pt_path_chain, &chain_info);
10316 
10317  /* now that we have the chain, we need to construct the new "IS NULL" disjuncts. */
10318  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && chain_info.chain_length > 1)
10319  {
10320  node = pt_gen_isnull_preds (parser, node, &chain_info);
10321  }
10322 
10323  /* Free any allocated memory for the spec chain. */
10324  if (chain_info.chain_ptr != chain_info.chain)
10325  {
10326  free_and_init (chain_info.chain_ptr);
10327  }
10328  }
10329 
10330  return node;
10331 }
10332 
10333 /*
10334  * pt_expand_isnull_preds () - expand path_expr "IS NULL" predicates to
10335  * include any path segment being NULL
10336  * return:
10337  * parser(in):
10338  * node(in):
10339  * arg(in):
10340  * continue_walk(in):
10341  */
10342 static PT_NODE *
10343 pt_expand_isnull_preds (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
10344 {
10345  PT_NODE *statement = (PT_NODE *) arg;
10346  PT_NODE **pred = NULL;
10347 
10348  switch (node->node_type)
10349  {
10350  case PT_UPDATE:
10351  pred = &node->info.update.search_cond;
10352  break;
10353 
10354  case PT_DELETE:
10355  pred = &node->info.delete_.search_cond;
10356  break;
10357 
10358  case PT_SELECT:
10359  pred = &node->info.query.q.select.where;
10360  break;
10361 
10362  case PT_MERGE:
10363  pred = &node->info.merge.insert.search_cond;
10364  if (pred)
10365  {
10366  *pred = parser_walk_tree (parser, *pred, NULL, NULL, pt_expand_isnull_preds_helper, statement);
10367  }
10368  pred = &node->info.merge.update.search_cond;
10369  if (pred)
10370  {
10371  *pred = parser_walk_tree (parser, *pred, NULL, NULL, pt_expand_isnull_preds_helper, statement);
10372  }
10373  pred = &node->info.merge.update.del_search_cond;
10374  if (pred)
10375  {
10376  *pred = parser_walk_tree (parser, *pred, NULL, NULL, pt_expand_isnull_preds_helper, statement);
10377  }
10378  pred = &node->info.merge.search_cond;
10379  break;
10380 
10381  default:
10382  break;
10383  }
10384 
10385  if (pred)
10386  {
10387  *pred = parser_walk_tree (parser, *pred, NULL, NULL, pt_expand_isnull_preds_helper, statement);
10388  }
10389 
10390  return node;
10391 }
10392 
10393 /*
10394  * pt_check_and_replace_hostvar () -
10395  * return:
10396  * parser(in):
10397  * node(in):
10398  * arg(in):
10399  * continue_walk(in/out):
10400  */
10401 static PT_NODE *
10402 pt_check_and_replace_hostvar (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
10403 {
10404  PT_NODE *value;
10405  DB_VALUE *dbval;
10406  DB_TYPE type;
10407  int *check = (int *) arg;
10408 
10409  /* do not replace path expression */
10410  if (pt_is_dot_node (node))
10411  {
10412  if (pt_is_input_parameter (node->info.dot.arg1) || pt_is_input_parameter (node->info.dot.arg2))
10413  {
10414  *check = 1; /* this statement cannot be prepared */
10415  }
10416  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
10417  return node;
10418  }
10419 
10420  /* method check */
10421  if (pt_is_method_call (node))
10422  {
10423  *check = 1; /* this statement cannot be prepared */
10424  return node;
10425  }
10426 
10427  /* replace input host var/parameter with its value if given */
10428  if ((pt_is_input_hostvar (node) && parser->host_var_count > node->info.host_var.index && parser->set_host_var == 1)
10429  || pt_is_input_parameter (node))
10430  {
10431  type = pt_node_to_db_type (node);
10432  if (type == DB_TYPE_OBJECT || type == DB_TYPE_VOBJ || TP_IS_SET_TYPE (type))
10433  {
10434  if (pt_is_input_parameter (node))
10435  {
10436  *check = 1; /* this statement cannot be prepared */
10437  }
10438  return node;
10439  }
10440 
10441  dbval = pt_value_to_db (parser, node);
10442  if (dbval && !pr_is_set_type (db_value_type (dbval)))
10443  {
10444  value = pt_dbval_to_value (parser, dbval);
10445  if (value)
10446  {
10447  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (value->type_enum))
10448  {
10449  value->info.value.print_charset = true;
10450  value->info.value.print_collation = true;
10451  value->info.value.is_collate_allowed = true;
10452  }
10453  if (pt_is_input_hostvar (node))
10454  {
10455  /* save host_var index */
10456  value->info.value.host_var_index = node->info.host_var.index;
10457  }
10458  PT_NODE_MOVE_NUMBER_OUTERLINK (value, node);
10459  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
10460  node = value;
10461  }
10462  }
10463  }
10464 
10465  return node;
10466 }
10467 
10468 /*
10469  * pt_check_with_info () - do name resolution & semantic checks on this tree
10470  * return: statement if no errors, NULL otherwise
10471  * parser(in): the parser context
10472  * node(in): a parsed sql statement that needs to be checked.
10473  * info(in): NULL or info->attrdefs is a vclass' attribute defs list
10474  */
10475 
10476 static PT_NODE *
10477 pt_check_with_info (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO * info)
10478 {
10479  PT_NODE *next;
10480  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO sc_info = { NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, false, false };
10481  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO *sc_info_ptr = info;
10482  bool save_donot_fold = false;
10483 
10484  assert (parser != NULL);
10485 
10486  if (!node)
10487  {
10488  return NULL;
10489  }
10490 
10491  /* If it is an internally created statement, set its host variable info again to search host variables at parent
10492  * parser */
10493  SET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT (parser);
10494 
10495  if (sc_info_ptr == NULL)
10496  {
10497  sc_info_ptr = &sc_info;
10498  }
10499  if (info)
10500  {
10501  save_donot_fold = sc_info_ptr->donot_fold; /* save */
10502  }
10503 
10504  sc_info_ptr->top_node = node;
10505  sc_info_ptr->donot_fold = false;
10506  next = node->next;
10507  node->next = NULL;
10508 
10509  switch (node->node_type)
10510  {
10511  case PT_UPDATE:
10512  /*
10513  * If it is an update object, get the object to update, and create an
10514  * entity so that pt_resolve_names will work.
10515  * THIS NEEDS TO BE MOVED INTO RESOLVE NAMES.
10516  */
10517  if (node->info.update.object_parameter != NULL)
10518  {
10519  pt_resolve_object (parser, node);
10520  }
10521 
10522  case PT_HOST_VAR:
10523  case PT_EXPR:
10524  case PT_NAME:
10525  case PT_VALUE:
10526  case PT_FUNCTION:
10527 
10528  case PT_DELETE:
10529  case PT_INSERT:
10530  case PT_METHOD_CALL:
10531  case PT_UNION:
10532  case PT_INTERSECTION:
10533  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
10534  case PT_SELECT:
10535  case PT_EVALUATE:
10536  case PT_SET_XACTION:
10537  case PT_SCOPE:
10538  case PT_DO:
10539  case PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES:
10540  case PT_MERGE:
10541 #if 0 /* to disable TEXT */
10542  /* we postpone TEXT resolution of a insert statement at '*' resolution if (node->node_type == PT_INSERT) {
10543  * pt_resolve_insert_external(parser, node); } else */
10544  if (node->node_type == PT_DELETE)
10545  {
10546  pt_resolve_delete_external (parser, node);
10547  }
10548  else if (node->node_type == PT_UPDATE)
10549  {
10550  pt_resolve_update_external (parser, node);
10551  }
10552 #endif /* 0 */
10553 
10554  sc_info_ptr->system_class = false;
10555  node = pt_resolve_names (parser, node, sc_info_ptr);
10556 
10557  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10558  {
10559  node = pt_check_where (parser, node);
10560  }
10561 
10562  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10563  {
10564  if (sc_info_ptr->system_class && PT_IS_QUERY (node))
10565  {
10566  /* do not cache the result if a system class is involved in the query */
10567  node->info.query.reexecute = 1;
10568  node->info.query.do_cache = 0;
10569  node->info.query.do_not_cache = 1;
10570  node->info.query.has_system_class = 1;
10571  }
10572 
10573  if (node->node_type == PT_UPDATE || node->node_type == PT_DELETE || node->node_type == PT_INSERT
10574  || node->node_type == PT_UNION || node->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION || node->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE
10575  || node->node_type == PT_SELECT || node->node_type == PT_DO || node->node_type == PT_SET_SESSION_VARIABLES
10576  || node->node_type == PT_MERGE)
10577  {
10578  /* may have WHERE clause */
10579  int check = 0;
10580 
10581  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_check_and_replace_hostvar, &check, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
10582  if (check)
10583  {
10584  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
10585  }
10586 
10587  /* because the statement has some object type PT_PARAMETER, it cannot be prepared */
10588  if (parent_parser != NULL)
10589  {
10590  node->cannot_prepare = 1;
10591  }
10592  }
10593 
10594  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_mark_union_leaf_nodes, NULL, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
10595 
10596  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10597  {
10598  /* remove unnecessary variable */
10599  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, NULL, NULL, pt_semantic_check_local, sc_info_ptr);
10600 
10601  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10602  {
10603  /* This must be done before CNF since we are adding disjuncts to the "IS NULL" expression. */
10604  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_expand_isnull_preds, node, NULL, NULL);
10605  }
10606  }
10607  }
10608 
10609  break;
10610 
10611  case PT_CREATE_INDEX:
10612  case PT_ALTER_INDEX:
10613  case PT_DROP_INDEX:
10614  if (parser->host_var_count)
10615  {
10616  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HOSTVAR_IN_DDL);
10617  }
10618  else
10619  {
10620  sc_info_ptr->system_class = false;
10621  node = pt_resolve_names (parser, node, sc_info_ptr);
10622  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && node->node_type == PT_CREATE_INDEX)
10623  {
10624  pt_check_create_index (parser, node);
10625  }
10626 
10627  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && (node->node_type == PT_DROP_INDEX || node->node_type == PT_ALTER_INDEX))
10628  {
10629  pt_check_function_index_expr (parser, node);
10630  }
10631 
10632  if (!pt_has_error (parser) && node->node_type == PT_ALTER_INDEX)
10633  {
10634  DB_OBJECT *db_obj = NULL;
10635  PT_NODE *name = NULL;
10636 
10637  if (node->info.index.indexed_class)
10638  {
10639  name = node->info.index.indexed_class->info.spec.entity_name;
10640  db_obj = db_find_class (name->info.name.original);
10641 
10642  if (db_obj == NULL)
10643  {
10644  PT_ERRORmf (parser, name, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_IS_NOT_A_CLASS,
10645  name->info.name.original);
10646  }
10647  }
10648 
10649  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10650  {
10651  pt_check_filter_index_expr (parser, node->info.index.column_names, node->info.index.where, db_obj);
10652  }
10653  }
10654 
10655  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10656  {
10657  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, info);
10658  }
10659 
10660  if (node && !pt_has_error (parser))
10661  {
10662  if (node->info.index.where && pt_false_search_condition (parser, node->info.index.where))
10663  {
10664  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_FILTER_INDEX,
10665  pt_short_print (parser, node->info.index.where));
10666  }
10667  }
10668 
10669  if (node && !pt_has_error (parser))
10670  {
10671  if (node->info.index.function_expr
10672  && !pt_is_function_index_expr (parser, node->info.index.function_expr->info.sort_spec.expr, true))
10673  {
10674  break;
10675  }
10676  }
10677 
10678  if (node && !pt_has_error (parser))
10679  {
10680  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, NULL, NULL, pt_semantic_check_local, sc_info_ptr);
10681 
10682  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10683  {
10684  /* This must be done before CNF since we are adding disjuncts to the "IS NULL" expression. */
10685  node = parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_expand_isnull_preds, node, NULL, NULL);
10686  }
10687  }
10688  }
10689  break;
10690 
10691  case PT_SAVEPOINT:
10692  if ((node->info.savepoint.save_name) && (node->info.savepoint.save_name->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER))
10693  {
10694  node = pt_resolve_names (parser, node, sc_info_ptr);
10695  }
10696  break;
10697 
10698  case PT_ROLLBACK_WORK:
10699  if ((node->info.rollback_work.save_name)
10700  && (node->info.rollback_work.save_name->info.name.meta_class == PT_PARAMETER))
10701  {
10702  node = pt_resolve_names (parser, node, sc_info_ptr);
10703  }
10704  break;
10705 
10706  case PT_AUTH_CMD:
10707  break; /* see GRANT/REVOKE */
10708 
10709  case PT_DROP:
10710  pt_check_drop (parser, node);
10711  break;
10712 
10713  case PT_VACUUM:
10714  pt_check_vacuum (parser, node);
10715  break;
10716 
10717  case PT_GRANT:
10718  case PT_REVOKE:
10719  pt_check_grant_revoke (parser, node);
10720  break;
10721 
10722  case PT_TRUNCATE:
10723  pt_check_truncate (parser, node);
10724  break;
10725 
10726  case PT_KILL_STMT:
10727  pt_check_kill (parser, node);
10728  break;
10729 
10730  case PT_ALTER:
10731  case PT_ALTER_SERIAL:
10732  case PT_ALTER_TRIGGER:
10733  case PT_ALTER_USER:
10734  case PT_CREATE_ENTITY:
10735  case PT_CREATE_SERIAL:
10736  case PT_CREATE_TRIGGER:
10737  case PT_CREATE_USER:
10738  case PT_DROP_SERIAL:
10739  case PT_DROP_TRIGGER:
10740  case PT_DROP_USER:
10741  case PT_RENAME:
10742  case PT_RENAME_TRIGGER:
10743  case PT_UPDATE_STATS:
10744  switch (node->node_type)
10745  {
10746  case PT_ALTER:
10747  pt_check_alter (parser, node);
10748 
10749  if (node->info.alter.code == PT_ADD_ATTR_MTHD || node->info.alter.code == PT_ADD_INDEX_CLAUSE)
10750  {
10751  if (parser->host_var_count)
10752  {
10753  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_HOSTVAR_IN_DDL);
10754  break;
10755  }
10756  }
10757 
10758  if (node->info.alter.code == PT_ADD_INDEX_CLAUSE)
10759  {
10760  /* apply typechecking on ALTER TABLE ADD INDEX statements, to check the expression in the WHERE clause of
10761  * a partial index */
10762  PT_NODE *p = node->info.alter.create_index;
10763  assert (p != NULL);
10764 
10765  while (p)
10766  {
10767  sc_info_ptr->system_class = false;
10768  p = pt_resolve_names (parser, p, sc_info_ptr);
10769  if (p && !pt_has_error (parser))
10770  {
10771  pt_check_create_index (parser, p);
10772  }
10773 
10774  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
10775  {
10776  p = pt_semantic_type (parser, p, info);
10777  }
10778 
10779  if (p && !pt_has_error (parser))
10780  {
10781  p = parser_walk_tree (parser, p, NULL, NULL, pt_semantic_check_local, sc_info_ptr);
10782 
10783  if (p && !pt_has_error (parser))
10784  {
10785  /* This must be done before CNF since we are adding disjuncts to the "IS NULL" expression. */
10786  p = parser_walk_tree (parser, p, pt_expand_isnull_preds, p, NULL, NULL);
10787  }
10788  }
10789 
10790  if (p != NULL && !pt_has_error (parser) && p->info.index.function_expr != NULL
10791  && !pt_is_function_index_expr (parser, p->info.index.function_expr->info.sort_spec.expr, true))
10792  {
10793  break;
10794  }
10795  if (p && !pt_has_error (parser))
10796  {
10797  p = p->next;
10798  }
10799  else
10800  {
10801  break;
10802  }
10803  }
10804  }
10805  break;
10806 
10807  case PT_CREATE_ENTITY:
10808  pt_check_create_entity (parser, node);
10809  break;
10810 
10811  case PT_CREATE_USER:
10812  pt_check_create_user (parser, node);
10813  break;
10814 
10815  default:
10816  break;
10817  }
10818  break;
10819 
10820  default:
10821  break;
10822  }
10823 
10824  /* restore list link, if any */
10825  if (node)
10826  {
10827  node->next = next;
10828  }
10829 
10830  if (info)
10831  {
10832  sc_info_ptr->donot_fold = save_donot_fold; /* restore */
10833  }
10834 
10835  RESET_HOST_VARIABLES_IF_INTERNAL_STATEMENT (parser);
10836 
10837  if (er_errid () == ER_LK_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED)
10838  {
10839  PT_ERRORc (parser, node, db_error_string (3));
10840  }
10841 
10842  if (pt_has_error (parser))
10843  {
10844  pt_register_orphan (parser, node);
10845  return NULL;
10846  }
10847  else
10848  {
10849  return node;
10850  }
10851 }
10852 
10853 /*
10854  * pt_semantic_quick_check_node () - perform semantic validation on a
10855  * node that is not necessarily part of a
10856  * statement
10857  * return : modified node or NULL on error
10858  * parser (in) : parser context
10859  * entity_name (in) : PT_NAME of the class containing attributes from node
10860  * node (in) : node to check
10861  *
10862  * Note: Callers of this function need both the spec and the node after
10863  * the call. This is why we have to pass pointers to PT_NODE*
10864  */
10865 PT_NODE *
10866 pt_semantic_quick_check_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE ** spec_p, PT_NODE ** node_p)
10867 {
10868  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO sc_info = { NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, false, false };
10869  int error = NO_ERROR;
10870  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
10871 
10872  /* resolve names */
10873  error = pt_quick_resolve_names (parser, spec_p, node_p, &sc_info);
10874  if (error != NO_ERROR || pt_has_error (parser))
10875  {
10876  return NULL;
10877  }
10878 
10879  node = *node_p;
10880 
10881  /* perform semantic check */
10882  node = pt_semantic_type (parser, node, &sc_info);
10883  if (node == NULL)
10884  {
10885  return NULL;
10886  }
10887  node_p = &node;
10888  return node;
10889 }
10890 
10891 /*
10892  * pt_semantic_check () -
10893  * return: PT_NODE *(modified) if no errors, else NULL if errors
10894  * parser(in):
10895  * node(in): statement a parsed sql statement that needs to be checked
10896  */
10897 
10898 PT_NODE *
10899 pt_semantic_check (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
10900 {
10901  return pt_check_with_info (parser, node, NULL);
10902 }
10903 
10904 /*
10905  * pt_find_class () -
10906  * return: DB_OBJECT * for the class whose name is in p,
10907  * NULL if not a class name
10908  * parser(in):
10909  * p(in): a PT_NAME node
10910  *
10911  * Note :
10912  * Finds CLASS VCLASS VIEW only
10913  */
10914 static DB_OBJECT *
10915 pt_find_class (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * p, bool for_update)
10916 {
10917  if (!p)
10918  return 0;
10919 
10920  if (p->node_type != PT_NAME)
10921  return 0;
10922 
10923  return db_find_class_with_purpose (p->info.name.original, for_update);
10924 }
10925 
10926 
10927 /*
10928  * pt_check_unique_attr () - check that there are no duplicate attr
10929  * in given list
10930  * return: none
10931  * parser(in): the parser context
10932  * entity_name(in): class name or index name
10933  * att(in): an attribute definition list
10934  * att_type(in): an attribute definition type list
10935  */
10936 static void
10937 pt_check_unique_attr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *entity_name, PT_NODE * att, PT_NODE_TYPE att_type)
10938 {
10939  PT_NODE *p, *q, *p_nam, *q_nam;
10940 
10941  assert (parser != NULL);
10942  if (!att)
10943  {
10944  return;
10945  }
10946 
10947  for (p = att; p; p = p->next)
10948  {
10949  if (p->node_type != att_type)
10950  {
10951  continue; /* give up */
10952  }
10953 
10954  p_nam = NULL; /* init */
10955  if (att_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
10956  {
10957  p_nam = p->info.attr_def.attr_name;
10958  }
10959  else if (att_type == PT_SORT_SPEC)
10960  {
10961  p_nam = p->info.sort_spec.expr;
10962  }
10963 
10964  if (p_nam == NULL || p_nam->node_type != PT_NAME)
10965  {
10966  continue; /* give up */
10967  }
10968 
10969  for (q = p->next; q; q = q->next)
10970  {
10971  if (q->node_type != att_type)
10972  {
10973  continue; /* give up */
10974  }
10975 
10976  q_nam = NULL; /* init */
10977  if (att_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
10978  {
10979  q_nam = q->info.attr_def.attr_name;
10980  }
10981  else if (att_type == PT_SORT_SPEC)
10982  {
10983  q_nam = q->info.sort_spec.expr;
10984  }
10985 
10986  if (q_nam == NULL || q_nam->node_type != PT_NAME)
10987  {
10988  continue; /* give up */
10989  }
10990 
10991  /* a class attribute and a normal attribute can have identical names */
10992  if (att_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
10993  {
10994  if (p->info.attr_def.attr_type != q->info.attr_def.attr_type)
10995  {
10996  continue; /* OK */
10997  }
10998  }
10999 
11000  if (!pt_str_compare (p_nam->info.name.original, q_nam->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
11001  {
11002  if (att_type == PT_ATTR_DEF) /* is class entity */
11003  {
11004  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, q_nam, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CLASS_ATTR_DUPLICATED,
11005  q_nam->info.name.original, entity_name);
11006  }
11007  else /* is index entity */
11008  {
11009  PT_ERRORmf (parser, q_nam, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INDEX_ATTR_DUPLICATED,
11010  q_nam->info.name.original);
11011  }
11012  }
11013  }
11014  }
11015 }
11016 
11017 /*
11018  * pt_assignment_class_compatible () - Make sure that the rhs is a valid
11019  * candidate for assignment into the lhs
11020  * return: error_code
11021  * parser(in): handle to context used to parse the insert statement
11022  * lhs(in): the AST form of an attribute from the namelist part of an insert
11023  * rhs(in): the AST form of an expression from the values part of an insert
11024  */
11025 static int
11026 pt_assignment_class_compatible (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * lhs, PT_NODE * rhs)
11027 {
11028  assert (parser != NULL);
11029  assert (lhs != NULL);
11030  assert (lhs->node_type == PT_NAME);
11031  assert (lhs->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NONE);
11032  assert (rhs != NULL);
11033 
11034  if (lhs->node_type == PT_NAME)
11035  {
11036  if (lhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
11037  {
11038  if (!pt_class_assignable (parser, lhs->data_type, rhs))
11039  {
11040  /* incompatible object domains */
11041  PT_ERRORmf (parser, rhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INCOMP_TYPE_ON_ATTR,
11042  lhs->info.name.original);
11043  return ER_FAILED;
11044  }
11045  }
11046  }
11047 
11048  return NO_ERROR;
11049 }
11050 
11051 /*
11052  * pt_assignment_compatible () - Make sure that the rhs is a valid candidate
11053  * for assignment into the lhs
11054  * return: the rhs node if compatible, NULL for errors
11055  * parser(in): handle to context used to parse the insert statement
11056  * lhs(in): the AST form of an attribute from the namelist part of an insert
11057  * rhs(in): the AST form of an expression from the values part of an insert
11058  */
11059 static PT_NODE *
11060 pt_assignment_compatible (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * lhs, PT_NODE * rhs)
11061 {
11062  assert (parser != NULL);
11063  assert (lhs != NULL);
11064  assert (lhs->node_type == PT_NAME);
11065  assert (rhs != NULL);
11066 
11067  if (lhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_OBJECT)
11068  {
11069  if (rhs->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR && (rhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NONE || rhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MAYBE))
11070  {
11071  rhs->type_enum = lhs->type_enum;
11072  rhs->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, lhs->data_type);
11073  return rhs;
11074  }
11075 
11076  if (pt_assignment_class_compatible (parser, lhs, rhs) != NO_ERROR)
11077  {
11078  return NULL;
11079  }
11080  }
11081  else
11082  {
11083  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO sci = {
11084  0, PT_TYPE_NONE, 0, 0, false,
11085  {0, INTL_CODESET_NONE, PT_COLLATION_NOT_COERC, false}
11086  ,
11087  NULL
11088  };
11089  bool is_cast_allowed = true;
11090 
11091  sci.type_enum = lhs->type_enum;
11092  if (lhs->data_type)
11093  {
11094  sci.prec = lhs->data_type->info.data_type.precision;
11095  sci.scale = lhs->data_type->info.data_type.dec_precision;
11096  if (lhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_JSON && lhs->data_type->info.data_type.json_schema != NULL)
11097  {
11098  sci.force_cast = true;
11099  }
11100  }
11101 
11102  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (lhs->type_enum))
11103  {
11104  (void) pt_get_collation_info (lhs, &(sci.coll_infer));
11105  }
11106 
11107  if (pt_is_compatible_without_cast (parser, &sci, rhs, &is_cast_allowed))
11108  {
11109  return rhs;
11110  }
11111 
11112  if (!is_cast_allowed)
11113  {
11114  return NULL;
11115  }
11116 
11117  if (rhs->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NULL)
11118  {
11119  if (rhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MAYBE)
11120  {
11121  TP_DOMAIN *d;
11122 
11123  if (lhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_ENUMERATION)
11124  {
11125  d = pt_data_type_to_db_domain (parser, lhs->data_type, NULL);
11126  d = tp_domain_cache (d);
11127  }
11128  else
11129  {
11130  DB_TYPE lhs_dbtype;
11131 
11132  assert_release (!(PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (lhs->type_enum) || lhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC)
11133  || lhs->data_type != NULL);
11134  lhs_dbtype = pt_type_enum_to_db (lhs->type_enum);
11135 
11136  if (rhs->node_type != PT_HOST_VAR)
11137  {
11138  d = tp_domain_resolve_default (lhs_dbtype);
11139  }
11140  else
11141  {
11142  TP_DOMAIN *hv_domain = NULL;
11143 
11144  /* node_type is PT_HOST_VAR set host var's expected domain with next order of priority. 1.
11145  * host_var->host_var_expected_domains[index] 2. lhs's expected domain 3. default domain of lhs
11146  * type */
11147  if (rhs->info.host_var.index < parser->host_var_count && parser->host_var_expected_domains)
11148  {
11149  hv_domain = parser->host_var_expected_domains[rhs->info.host_var.index];
11150  }
11151 
11152  if (hv_domain && hv_domain->type->id != DB_TYPE_UNKNOWN)
11153  {
11154  /* host var's expected domain is already set */
11155  d = hv_domain;
11156  if (TP_TYPE_HAS_COLLATION (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (d)))
11157  {
11158  d->codeset = sci.coll_infer.codeset;
11159  d->collation_id = sci.coll_infer.coll_id;
11160  }
11161  }
11162  else
11163  {
11164  /* use lhs's expected_domain */
11165  if (lhs->expected_domain != NULL)
11166  {
11167  d = lhs->expected_domain;
11168  }
11169  else
11170  {
11171  d = tp_domain_resolve_default (lhs_dbtype);
11172  }
11173 
11174  if (PT_HAS_COLLATION (lhs->type_enum))
11175  {
11176  d = tp_domain_copy (d, false);
11177  d->codeset = sci.coll_infer.codeset;
11178  d->collation_id = sci.coll_infer.coll_id;
11179  d = tp_domain_cache (d);
11180  }
11181  }
11182  }
11183  }
11184 
11185  pt_set_expected_domain (rhs, d);
11186  if (rhs->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR)
11187  {
11188  pt_preset_hostvar (parser, rhs);
11189  }
11190  }
11191  else
11192  {
11193  bool rhs_is_collection_with_str = false;
11194  PT_NODE *cast_dt = NULL;
11195 
11196  assert_release (!(PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (lhs->type_enum) || lhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NUMERIC)
11197  || lhs->data_type != NULL);
11198 
11199  if (PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (rhs->type_enum) && lhs->data_type == NULL && rhs->data_type != NULL)
11200  {
11201  PT_NODE *dt_element;
11202 
11203  dt_element = rhs->data_type;
11204 
11205  while (dt_element != NULL)
11206  {
11207  if (PT_IS_CHAR_STRING_TYPE (dt_element->type_enum))
11208  {
11209  rhs_is_collection_with_str = true;
11210  break;
11211  }
11212  dt_element = dt_element->next;
11213  }
11214  }
11215 
11216  if (PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (lhs->type_enum) && PT_IS_COLLECTION_TYPE (rhs->type_enum)
11217  && lhs->data_type == NULL && rhs_is_collection_with_str == true)
11218  {
11219  PT_NODE *dt_element;
11220 
11221  /* create a data type for lhs with with string having DB charset */
11222  cast_dt = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, rhs->data_type);
11223 
11224  dt_element = cast_dt;
11225 
11226  while (dt_element != NULL)
11227  {
11228  if (PT_IS_CHAR_STRING_TYPE (dt_element->type_enum))
11229  {
11230  dt_element->info.data_type.collation_id = LANG_SYS_COLLATION;
11231  dt_element->info.data_type.units = lang_charset ();
11232  dt_element->info.data_type.collation_flag = TP_DOMAIN_COLL_NORMAL;
11233  }
11234  dt_element = dt_element->next;
11235  }
11236  }
11237  else
11238  {
11239  cast_dt = lhs->data_type;
11240  }
11241 
11242  rhs = pt_wrap_with_cast_op (parser, rhs, lhs->type_enum, 0, 0, cast_dt);
11243  if (cast_dt != NULL && cast_dt != lhs->data_type)
11244  {
11245  parser_free_tree (parser, cast_dt);
11246  cast_dt = NULL;
11247  }
11248  /* the call to pt_wrap_with_cast_op might fail because a call to allocate memory failed. In this case,
11249  * the error message is set by the calls inside pt_wrap_with_cast_op and we just return NULL */
11250  }
11251  }
11252  }
11253 
11254  return rhs;
11255 }
11256 
11257 /*
11258  * pt_check_assignments () - assert that the lhs of the set clause are
11259  * all pt_name nodes.
11260  * This will guarantee that there are no complex path expressions.
11261  * Also asserts that the right hand side is assignment compatible.
11262  * return: none
11263  * parser(in): the parser context
11264  * stmt(in): an update or merge statement
11265  */
11266 
11267 static void
