11268 pt_check_assignments (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt)
11269 {
11270  PT_NODE *a, *next, *lhs, *rhs, *list, *rhs_list;
11271  PT_NODE *assignment_list;
11272 
11273  assert (parser != NULL);
11274 
11275  assignment_list = pt_get_assignments (stmt);
11276  if (assignment_list == NULL)
11277  {
11278  return;
11279  }
11280 
11281  for (a = assignment_list; a; a = next)
11282  {
11283  next = a->next; /* save next link */
11284  if (a->node_type == PT_EXPR && a->info.expr.op == PT_ASSIGN && (lhs = a->info.expr.arg1) != NULL
11285  && (rhs = a->info.expr.arg2) != NULL)
11286  {
11287  if (lhs->node_type == PT_NAME)
11288  {
11289  if (pt_is_query (rhs))
11290  {
11291  /* check select list length */
11292  rhs_list = pt_get_select_list (parser, rhs);
11293  assert (rhs_list != NULL);
11294  if (pt_length_of_select_list (rhs_list, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS) != 1)
11295  {
11296  /* e.g., a = (select 1, 2 from ...) */
11297  PT_ERRORm (parser, lhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ILLEGAL_RHS);
11298  }
11299  else
11300  {
11301  (void) pt_assignment_class_compatible (parser, lhs, rhs_list);
11302  }
11303  }
11304  else
11305  {
11306  /* Not a query, just check if assignment is possible. The call below will wrap the rhs node with a
11307  * cast to the type of the lhs_node */
11308  (void) pt_assignment_class_compatible (parser, lhs, rhs);
11309  }
11310  }
11311  else if (lhs->node_type == PT_EXPR && PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (lhs) && (list = lhs->info.expr.arg1))
11312  {
11313  /* multi-column update with subquery CASE1: always-false subquery is already converted NULL. so, change
11314  * NULL into NULL paren-expr (a) = NULL -> a = NULL (a, b) = NULL -> a = NULL, b = NULL CASE2: (a, b) =
11315  * subquery */
11316 
11317  if (rhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NA || rhs->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
11318  {
11319  /* CASE 1: flatten multi-column assignment expr */
11320  PT_NODE *e1, *e1_next, *e2, *tmp;
11321 
11322  a->next = NULL; /* cut-off expr link */
11323  lhs->info.expr.arg1 = NULL; /* cut-off lhs link */
11324 
11325  parser_free_tree (parser, lhs); /* free exp, arg1 */
11326  parser_free_tree (parser, rhs); /* free exp, arg1 */
11327 
11328  e2 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
11329  if (e2 == NULL)
11330  {
11331  PT_ERRORm (parser, a, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
11332  return;
11333  }
11334 
11335  e2->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NULL;
11336  a->info.expr.arg1 = list;
11337  a->info.expr.arg2 = e2;
11338  e1 = list->next;
11339  list->next = NULL;
11340  tmp = NULL; /* init */
11341 
11342  for (; e1; e1 = e1_next)
11343  {
11344  e1_next = e1->next;
11345  e1->next = NULL;
11346 
11347  e2 = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
11348  if (e2 == NULL)
11349  {
11350  PT_ERRORm (parser, a, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
11351  return;
11352  }
11353  e2->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NULL;
11354 
11355  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
11356  if (tmp == NULL)
11357  {
11358  PT_ERRORm (parser, a, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
11359  return;
11360  }
11361 
11362  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_ASSIGN;
11363  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = e1;
11364  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = e2;
11365  parser_append_node (tmp, a);
11366  }
11367 
11368  if (tmp == NULL)
11369  {
11370  a->next = next; /* (a) = NULL */
11371  }
11372  else
11373  {
11374  tmp->next = next; /* (a, b) = NULL */
11375  }
11376  }
11377  else if (pt_is_query (rhs))
11378  {
11379  /* check select list length */
11380  rhs_list = pt_get_select_list (parser, rhs);
11381  assert (rhs_list != NULL);
11382  if (pt_length_of_list (list) != pt_length_of_select_list (rhs_list, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS))
11383  {
11384  PT_ERRORm (parser, lhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ILLEGAL_LHS);
11385  }
11386  else
11387  {
11388  for (; list && rhs_list; rhs_list = rhs_list->next)
11389  {
11390  if (rhs_list->is_hidden_column)
11391  {
11392  /* skip hidden column */
11393  continue;
11394  }
11395 
11396  (void) pt_assignment_class_compatible (parser, list, rhs_list);
11397  list = list->next;
11398  }
11399  assert (list == NULL);
11400  assert (rhs_list == NULL);
11401  }
11402  }
11403  }
11404  else
11405  {
11406  PT_ERRORm (parser, lhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ILLEGAL_LHS);
11407  }
11408  }
11409  else
11410  {
11411  /* malformed assignment list */
11412  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "semantic");
11413  }
11414  }
11415 }
11416 
11417 /*
11418  * pt_replace_names_in_update_values () - Walk through update assignments and
11419  * replace references to attributes
11420  * with assignments for those
11421  * attributes
11422  * return : UPDATE statement or NULL
11423  * parser (in) : parser context
11424  * update (in) : UPDATE parse tree
11425  *
11426  * Note: Update assignments are considered to be evaluate left to right.
11427  * For each attribute referenced on the right side of an assignment, if the
11428  * attribute was referenced in an assignment which appears in the UPDATE
11429  * statement before this assignment (i.e.: to the left of this assigment)
11430  * replace the value with that assignment.
11431  */
11432 static PT_NODE *
11433 pt_replace_names_in_update_values (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * update)
11434 {
11435  PT_NODE *attr = NULL, *val = NULL;
11436  PT_NODE *node = NULL, *prev = NULL;
11437 
11438  if (!prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_UPDATE_USE_ATTRIBUTE_REFERENCES))
11439  {
11440  /* Use SQL standard approach which always uses the existing value for an attribute rather than the updated value */
11441  return update;
11442  }
11443 
11444  if (update == NULL)
11445  {
11446  return NULL;
11447  }
11448 
11449  prev = update->info.update.assignment;
11450  if (prev == NULL)
11451  {
11452  return NULL;
11453  }
11454 
11455  if (prev->next == NULL)
11456  {
11457  /* only one assignment, nothing to be done */
11458  return update;
11459  }
11460 
11461  for (node = prev->next; node != NULL; prev = node, node = node->next)
11462  {
11463  if (!PT_IS_EXPR_NODE (node) || node->info.expr.op != PT_ASSIGN)
11464  {
11465  /* this is probably an error but it will be caught later */
11466  continue;
11467  }
11468 
11469  attr = node->info.expr.arg1;
11470  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (attr))
11471  {
11472  /* Cannot reference other assignments in N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR */
11473  continue;
11474  }
11475 
11476  val = node->info.expr.arg2;
11477  if (val == NULL || PT_IS_CONST (val))
11478  {
11479  /* nothing to be done for constants */
11480  continue;
11481  }
11482 
11483  /* This assignment is attr = expr. Walk expr and replace all occurrences of attributes with previous assignments.
11484  * Set prev->next to NULL so that we only search in assignments to the left of the current one. */
11485  prev->next = NULL;
11486 
11487  val =
11488  parser_walk_tree (parser, val, pt_replace_referenced_attributes, update->info.update.assignment, NULL, NULL);
11489 
11490  if (val != NULL && val != node->info.expr.arg2)
11491  {
11492  parser_free_tree (parser, node->info.expr.arg2);
11493  node->info.expr.arg2 = val;
11494  }
11495 
11496  /* repair node and list */
11497  prev->next = node;
11498  }
11499 
11500  return update;
11501 }
11502 
11503 /*
11504  * pt_replace_referenced_attributes () - replace an attributes with
11505  * expressions from previous assignments
11506  * return : node or NULL
11507  * parser (in) :
11508  * node (in) :
11509  * arg (in) :
11510  * continue_walk (in) :
11511  */
11512 static PT_NODE *
11513 pt_replace_referenced_attributes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
11514 {
11515  PT_NODE *assignment = NULL, *val = NULL;
11516  PT_NODE *assignments = (PT_NODE *) arg;
11517 
11518  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
11519 
11520  if (!pt_is_attr (node))
11521  {
11522  return node;
11523  }
11524 
11525  if (node->node_type != PT_NAME)
11526  {
11527  /* this is a PT_DOT, we don't have to go further */
11528  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
11529  }
11530 
11531  if (assignments == NULL)
11532  {
11533  assert_release (assignments != NULL);
11534  return node;
11535  }
11536 
11537  /* search for name in assignments */
11538  for (assignment = assignments; assignment != NULL; assignment = assignment->next)
11539  {
11540  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (assignment))
11541  {
11542  continue;
11543  }
11544 
11545  if (pt_name_equal (parser, assignment->info.expr.arg1, node))
11546  {
11547  /* Found the attribute we're looking for */
11548  break;
11549  }
11550  }
11551 
11552  if (assignment == NULL)
11553  {
11554  /* Did not find the attribute. This means that UPDATE should use the existing value */
11555  return node;
11556  }
11557 
11558  /* Replace node with rhs from the assignment. Notice that we're stopping at the first encounter of this attribute.
11559  * Normally, we should find the last assignment (from left to right), but, since CUBRID does not allow multiple
11560  * assignments to the same attribute, the first occurrence is the only one. */
11561  val = parser_copy_tree (parser, assignment->info.expr.arg2);
11562 
11563  if (val == NULL)
11564  {
11565  /* set error and return original node */
11566  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11567  return node;
11568  }
11569 
11570  /* do not recurse into this node */
11571  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
11572 
11573  return val;
11574 }
11575 
11576 /*
11577  * pt_no_attr_and_meta_attr_updates () - check for mixed (class, non-class)
11578  * assignments in the same update/merge statement
11579  * return: none
11580  * parser(in): the parser context
11581  * stmt(in): an update/merge statement
11582  */
11583 void
11584 pt_no_attr_and_meta_attr_updates (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * statement)
11585 {
11586  bool has_attrib = false, has_meta_attrib = false;
11587  PT_ASSIGNMENTS_HELPER ea;
11588  PT_NODE *assignments;
11589 
11590  assignments = pt_get_assignments (statement);
11591  if (assignments == NULL)
11592  {
11593  return;
11594  }
11595 
11596  pt_init_assignments_helper (parser, &ea, assignments);
11597  while (pt_get_next_assignment (&ea) && (!has_attrib || !has_meta_attrib))
11598  {
11599  if (ea.lhs->info.name.meta_class == PT_META_ATTR)
11600  {
11601  has_meta_attrib = true;
11602  }
11603  else
11604  {
11605  has_attrib = true;
11606  }
11607  }
11608  if (has_attrib && has_meta_attrib)
11609  {
11610  PT_ERRORm (parser, statement, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UPDATE_MIX_CLASS_NON_CLASS);
11611  }
11612 }
11613 
11614 /*
11615  * pt_node_double_insert_assignments () - Check if an attribute is assigned
11616  * more than once.
11617  *
11618  * return : Void.
11619  * parser (in) : Parser context.
11620  * stmt (in) : Insert statement.
11621  */
11622 void
11623 pt_no_double_insert_assignments (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt)
11624 {
11625  PT_NODE *attr = NULL, *spec = NULL;
11626  PT_NODE *entity_name;
11627 
11628  if (stmt == NULL || stmt->node_type != PT_INSERT)
11629  {
11630  return;
11631  }
11632 
11633  spec = stmt->info.insert.spec;
11634  entity_name = spec->info.spec.entity_name;
11635  if (entity_name == NULL)
11636  {
11637  assert (false);
11638  PT_ERROR (parser, stmt,
11639  "The parse tree of the insert statement is incorrect." " entity_name of spec must be set.");
11640  return;
11641  }
11642 
11643  if (entity_name->info.name.original == NULL)
11644  {
11645  assert (false);
11646  PT_ERROR (parser, entity_name, er_msg ());
11647  return;
11648  }
11649 
11650  /* check for duplicate assignments */
11651  for (attr = stmt->info.insert.attr_list; attr != NULL; attr = attr->next)
11652  {
11653  PT_NODE *attr2;
11654  for (attr2 = attr->next; attr2 != NULL; attr2 = attr2->next)
11655  {
11656  if (pt_name_equal (parser, attr, attr2))
11657  {
11658  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, attr2, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GT_1_ASSIGNMENT_TO,
11659  entity_name->info.name.original, attr2->info.name.original);
11660  return;
11661  }
11662  }
11663  }
11664 }
11665 
11666 /*
11667  * pt_no_double_updates () - assert that there are no multiple assignments to
11668  * the same attribute in the given update or merge statement
11669  * return: none
11670  * parser(in): the parser context
11671  * stmt(in): an update or merge statement
11672  */
11673 
11674 void
11675 pt_no_double_updates (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt)
11676 {
11677  PT_NODE *a, *b, *att_a, *att_b;
11678  PT_NODE *assignment_list;
11679 
11680  assert (parser != NULL);
11681 
11682  assignment_list = pt_get_assignments (stmt);
11683  if (assignment_list == NULL)
11684  {
11685  return;
11686  }
11687 
11688  for (a = assignment_list; a; a = a->next)
11689  {
11690  if (!(a->node_type == PT_EXPR && a->info.expr.op == PT_ASSIGN && (att_a = a->info.expr.arg1)))
11691  {
11692  goto exit_on_error;
11693  }
11694 
11695  if (att_a->node_type != PT_NAME)
11696  {
11697  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (att_a))
11698  {
11699  att_a = att_a->info.expr.arg1;
11700  }
11701  else
11702  {
11703  goto exit_on_error;
11704  }
11705  }
11706 
11707  for (; att_a; att_a = att_a->next)
11708  {
11709  /* first, check current node */
11710  for (att_b = att_a->next; att_b; att_b = att_b->next)
11711  {
11712  if (att_b->node_type != PT_NAME || att_b->info.name.original == NULL)
11713  {
11714  goto exit_on_error;
11715  }
11716  /* for multi-table we must check name and spec id */
11717  if (!pt_str_compare (att_a->info.name.original, att_b->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE)
11718  && att_a->info.name.spec_id == att_b->info.name.spec_id)
11719  {
11720  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att_a, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GT_1_ASSIGNMENT_TO,
11721  att_a->info.name.resolved, att_a->info.name.original);
11722  return;
11723  }
11724  }
11725 
11726  /* then, check the following node */
11727  for (b = a->next; b; b = b->next)
11728  {
11729  if (!(b->node_type == PT_EXPR && b->info.expr.op == PT_ASSIGN && (att_b = b->info.expr.arg1)))
11730  {
11731  goto exit_on_error;
11732  }
11733 
11734  if (att_b->node_type != PT_NAME)
11735  {
11736  if (PT_IS_N_COLUMN_UPDATE_EXPR (att_b))
11737  {
11738  att_b = att_b->info.expr.arg1;
11739  }
11740  else
11741  {
11742  goto exit_on_error;
11743  }
11744  }
11745 
11746  for (; att_b; att_b = att_b->next)
11747  {
11748  if (att_b->node_type != PT_NAME || att_b->info.name.original == NULL)
11749  {
11750  goto exit_on_error;
11751  }
11752  /* for multi-table we must check name and spec id */
11753  if (!pt_str_compare (att_a->info.name.original, att_b->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE)
11754  && att_a->info.name.spec_id == att_b->info.name.spec_id)
11755  {
11756  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att_a, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GT_1_ASSIGNMENT_TO,
11757  att_a->info.name.resolved, att_a->info.name.original);
11758  return;
11759  }
11760  }
11761  }
11762  }
11763  }
11764 
11765  return;
11766 
11767 exit_on_error:
11768  /* malformed assignment list */
11769  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "semantic");
11770  return;
11771 }
11772 
11773 /*
11774  * pt_invert () -
11775  * return:
11776  * parser(in):
11777  * name_expr(in): an expression from a select list
11778  * result(out): written in terms of the same single variable or path-expr
11779  *
11780  * Note :
11781  * Given an expression p that involves only:
11782  * + - / * ( ) constants and a single variable (which occurs only once).
11783  *
11784  * Find the functional inverse of the expression.
11785  * [ f and g are functional inverses if f(g(x)) == x ]
11786  *
11787  * function inverse
11788  * -------- --------
11789  * -x -x
11790  * 4*x x/4
11791  * 4*x+10 (x-10)/4
11792  * 6+x x-6
11793  *
11794  * Can't invert: x+y; x+x; x*x; constants ; count(*); f(x) ;
11795  */
11796 PT_NODE *
11797 pt_invert (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * name_expr, PT_NODE * result)
11798 {
11799  int result_isnull = 0;
11800  PT_NODE *tmp;
11801  PT_NODE *msgs;
11802  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO sc_info = { NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, false, false };
11803 
11804  assert (parser != NULL);
11805  msgs = parser->error_msgs;
11806 
11807  /* find the variable and return if none */
11808  if (pt_find_var (name_expr, &tmp) != 1 || tmp == NULL)
11809  {
11810  return NULL;
11811  }
11812 
11813  /* walk through the expression, inverting as you go */
11814  while (name_expr)
11815  {
11816  /* Got a path expression, you're done. ( result = path expr ) */
11817  if (name_expr->node_type == PT_NAME)
11818  break;
11819 
11820  /* not an expression? then can't do it */
11821  if (name_expr->node_type != PT_EXPR)
11822  {
11823  result = 0;
11824  break;
11825  }
11826 
11827  /* the inverse of any expression involving NULL is NULL */
11828  result_isnull = result->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL;
11829  switch (name_expr->info.expr.op)
11830  {
11831  case PT_UNARY_MINUS:
11832  /* ( result = -expr ) <=> ( -result = expr ) */
11833  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
11834  if (!result_isnull)
11835  {
11836  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
11837  if (tmp == NULL)
11838  {
11839  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11840  return NULL;
11841  }
11842 
11843  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_UNARY_MINUS;
11844  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = result;
11845  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
11846  {
11847  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
11848  }
11849  result = tmp;
11850  }
11851  break;
11852 
11853  case PT_PLUS:
11854  /* ( result = A + B ) <=> ( result - A = B ) */
11855  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg1, 0))
11856  {
11857  if (result_isnull)
11858  {
11859  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
11860  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
11861  }
11862  else
11863  {
11864  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
11865  if (tmp == NULL)
11866  {
11867  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11868  return NULL;
11869  }
11870 
11871  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_MINUS;
11872  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = result;
11873  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg2);
11874 
11875  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
11876  {
11877  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
11878  return NULL;
11879  }
11880 
11881  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
11882  {
11883  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
11884  }
11885  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
11886  {
11887  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
11888  }
11889  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
11890  result = tmp;
11891  }
11892  break;
11893  }
11894 
11895  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg2, 0))
11896  {
11897  if (result_isnull)
11898  {
11899  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
11900  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
11901  }
11902  else
11903  {
11904  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
11905  if (tmp == NULL)
11906  {
11907  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11908  return NULL;
11909  }
11910 
11911  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_MINUS;
11912  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = result;
11913  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg1);
11914  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
11915  {
11916  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
11917  return NULL;
11918  }
11919 
11920  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
11921  {
11922  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
11923  }
11924  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
11925  {
11926  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
11927  }
11928  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
11929  result = tmp;
11930  }
11931  break;
11932  }
11933 
11934  return NULL;
11935 
11936  case PT_MINUS:
11937  /* ( result = A-B ) <=> ( result+B = A ) ( result = A-B ) <=> ( A-result = B ) */
11938  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg1, 0))
11939  {
11940  if (result_isnull)
11941  {
11942  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
11943  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
11944  }
11945  else
11946  {
11947  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
11948  if (tmp == NULL)
11949  {
11950  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11951  return NULL;
11952  }
11953 
11954  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_PLUS;
11955  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = result;
11956  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg2);
11957  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
11958  {
11959  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
11960  return NULL;
11961  }
11962 
11963  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
11964  {
11965  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
11966  }
11967  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
11968  {
11969  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
11970  }
11971  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
11972  result = tmp;
11973  }
11974  break;
11975  }
11976 
11977  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg2, 0))
11978  {
11979  if (result_isnull)
11980  {
11981  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
11982  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
11983  }
11984  else
11985  {
11986  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
11987  if (tmp == NULL)
11988  {
11989  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
11990  return NULL;
11991  }
11992 
11993  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_MINUS;
11994  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = result;
11995  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg1);
11996  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
11997  {
11998  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
11999  return NULL;
12000  }
12001 
12002  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12003  {
12004  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12005  }
12006  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12007  {
12008  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12009  }
12010  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
12011  result = tmp;
12012  }
12013  break;
12014  }
12015 
12016  return NULL;
12017 
12018  case PT_DIVIDE:
12019  /* ( result = A/B ) <=> ( result*B = A ) ( result = A/B ) <=> ( A/result = B ) */
12020  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg1, 0))
12021  {
12022  if (result_isnull)
12023  {
12024  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
12025  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
12026  }
12027  else
12028  {
12029  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
12030  if (tmp == NULL)
12031  {
12032  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
12033  return NULL;
12034  }
12035 
12036  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_TIMES;
12037  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = result;
12038  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg2);
12039  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
12040  {
12041  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
12042  return NULL;
12043  }
12044 
12045  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12046  {
12047  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12048  }
12049  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12050  {
12051  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12052  }
12053  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
12054  result = tmp;
12055  }
12056  break;
12057  }
12058 
12059  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg2, 0))
12060  {
12061  if (result_isnull)
12062  {
12063  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
12064  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
12065  }
12066  else
12067  {
12068  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
12069  if (tmp == NULL)
12070  {
12071  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
12072  return NULL;
12073  }
12074 
12075  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_DIVIDE;
12076  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = result;
12077  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg1);
12078  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1 == NULL)
12079  {
12080  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
12081  return NULL;
12082  }
12083 
12084  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12085  {
12086  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12087  }
12088  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12089  {
12090  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12091  }
12092  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
12093  result = tmp;
12094  }
12095  break;
12096  }
12097 
12098  return NULL;
12099 
12100  case PT_TIMES:
12101  /* ( result = A*B ) <=> ( result/A = B ) */
12102  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg1, 0))
12103  {
12104  if (result_isnull)
12105  {
12106  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
12107  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
12108  }
12109  else
12110  {
12111  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
12112  if (tmp == NULL)
12113  {
12114  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
12115  return NULL;
12116  }
12117 
12118  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_DIVIDE;
12119  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = result;
12120  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg2);
12121  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
12122  {
12123  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
12124  return NULL;
12125  }
12126 
12127  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12128  {
12129  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12130  }
12131  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12132  {
12133  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12134  }
12135  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
12136  result = tmp;
12137  }
12138  break;
12139  }
12140 
12141  if (pt_find_var (name_expr->info.expr.arg2, 0))
12142  {
12143  if (result_isnull)
12144  {
12145  /* no need to invert result because result already has a null */
12146  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
12147  }
12148  else
12149  {
12150  tmp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_EXPR);
12151  if (tmp == NULL)
12152  {
12153  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
12154  return NULL;
12155  }
12156 
12157  tmp->info.expr.op = PT_DIVIDE;
12158  tmp->info.expr.arg1 = result;
12159  tmp->info.expr.arg2 = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr->info.expr.arg1);
12160  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2 == NULL)
12161  {
12162  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "parser_copy_tree");
12163  return NULL;
12164  }
12165 
12166  if (tmp->info.expr.arg1->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12167  {
12168  tmp->info.expr.arg1->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12169  }
12170  if (tmp->info.expr.arg2->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12171  {
12172  tmp->info.expr.arg2->info.expr.paren_type = 1;
12173  }
12174  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg2;
12175  result = tmp;
12176  }
12177  break;
12178  }
12179 
12180  return NULL;
12181 
12182  case PT_CAST:
12183  /* special case */
12184  name_expr = name_expr->info.expr.arg1;
12185  break;
12186 
12187  default:
12188  return NULL;
12189  }
12190  }
12191 
12192  /* set type of expression */
12193  if (!result_isnull)
12194  {
12195  sc_info.top_node = name_expr;
12196  sc_info.donot_fold = false;
12197  result = pt_semantic_type (parser, result, &sc_info);
12198  }
12199 
12200  if (result)
12201  {
12202  /* return name and resulting expression */
12203  result->next = parser_copy_tree (parser, name_expr);
12204  }
12205 
12206  if (pt_has_error (parser))
12207  {
12208  /* if we got an error just indicate not-invertible, end return with previous error state. */
12209  parser->error_msgs = msgs;
12210  return NULL;
12211  }
12212 
12213  return result;
12214 }
12215 
12216 /*
12217  * pt_find_var () - Explores an expression looking for a path expr.
12218  * Count these and return the count
12219  * return: number of path (PT_NAME node) expressions in the tree
12220  * p(in): an parse tree representing the syntactic
12221  * result(out): for returning a result expression pointer
12222  */
12223 
12224 int
12225 pt_find_var (PT_NODE * p, PT_NODE ** result)
12226 {
12227  if (!p)
12228  return 0;
12229 
12230  /* got a name expression */
12231  if (p->node_type == PT_NAME || (p->node_type == PT_DOT_))
12232  {
12233  if (result)
12234  *result = p;
12235  return 1;
12236  }
12237 
12238  /* if an expr (binary op) count both paths */
12239  if (p->node_type == PT_EXPR)
12240  {
12241  return (pt_find_var (p->info.expr.arg1, result) + pt_find_var (p->info.expr.arg2, result));
12242  }
12243 
12244  return 0;
12245 }
12246 
12247 /*
12248  * pt_remove_from_list () -
12249  * return: PT_NODE* to the list without "node" in it
12250  * parser(in):
12251  * node(in/out):
12252  * list(in/out):
12253  */
12254 PT_NODE *
12255 pt_remove_from_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, PT_NODE * list)
12256 {
12257  PT_NODE *temp;
12258 
12259  if (!list)
12260  return list;
12261 
12262  if (node == list)
12263  {
12264  temp = node->next;
12265  node->next = NULL;
12266  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
12267  return temp;
12268  }
12269 
12270  temp = list;
12271  while (temp && temp->next != node)
12272  {
12273  temp = temp->next;
12274  }
12275 
12276  if (temp)
12277  {
12278  temp->next = node->next;
12279  node->next = NULL;
12280  parser_free_tree (parser, node);
12281  }
12282 
12283  return list;
12284 }
12285 
12286 /*
12287  * pt_find_order_value_in_list () - checking an ORDER_BY list for a node with
12288  * the same value as sort_spec
12289  * return: PT_NODE* the found match or NULL
12290  * parser(in):
12291  * sort_value(in):
12292  * order_list(in):
12293  */
12294 
12295 PT_NODE *
12296 pt_find_order_value_in_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * sort_value, const PT_NODE * order_list)
12297 {
12298  PT_NODE *match = NULL;
12299 
12300  match = (PT_NODE *) order_list;
12301 
12302  while (match && sort_value && match->info.sort_spec.expr)
12303  {
12304  if (sort_value->node_type == PT_VALUE && match->info.sort_spec.expr->node_type == PT_VALUE
12305  && (match->info.sort_spec.expr->info.value.data_value.i == sort_value->info.value.data_value.i))
12306  {
12307  break;
12308  }
12309  else if (sort_value->node_type == PT_NAME && match->info.sort_spec.expr->node_type == PT_NAME
12310  && (pt_check_path_eq (parser, sort_value, match->info.sort_spec.expr) == 0))
12311  {
12312  /* when create/alter view, columns which are not in select list will not be replaced as value type. */
12313  break;
12314  }
12315  else
12316  {
12317  match = match->next;
12318  }
12319  }
12320 
12321  return match;
12322 }
12323 
12324 /*
12325  * pt_check_order_by () - checking an ORDER_BY clause
12326  * return:
12327  * parser(in):
12328  * query(in): query node has ORDER BY
12329  *
12330  * Note :
12331  * If it is an INTEGER, make sure it does not exceed the number of items
12332  * in the select list.
12333  * If it is a path expression, match it with an item in the select list and
12334  * replace it with the corresponding INTEGER.
12335  * IF not match, add hidden_column to select_list.
12336  * For the order-by clause of a UNION/INTERSECTION type query,
12337  * simply check that the items are ALL INTEGERS and it does not
12338  * exceed the number of items in the select list..
12339  */
12340 
12341 int
12342 pt_check_order_by (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query)
12343 {
12344  PT_NODE *select_list, *order_by, *col, *r, *temp, *order, *match;
12345  int n, i, select_list_len, select_list_full_len;
12346  bool ordbynum_flag;
12347  char *r_str = NULL;
12348  int error;
12349  bool skip_orderby_num = false;
12350 
12351  /* initinalize local variables */
12352  error = NO_ERROR;
12353  select_list = order_by = NULL;
12354 
12355  /* get select_list */
12356  switch (query->node_type)
12357  {
12358  case PT_SELECT:
12359  select_list = query->info.query.q.select.list;
12360  break;
12361 
12362  case PT_UNION:
12363  case PT_INTERSECTION:
12364  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
12365  {
12366  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2;
12367 
12368  /* traverse through nested union */
12369  temp = query;
12370  while (1)
12371  {
12372  arg1 = temp->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
12373  arg2 = temp->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
12374 
12375  if (PT_IS_QUERY (arg1))
12376  {
12377  if (arg1->node_type == PT_SELECT)
12378  { /* found, exit loop */
12379  select_list = arg1->info.query.q.select.list;
12380  break;
12381  }
12382  else
12383  {
12384  temp = arg1; /* continue */
12385  }
12386  }
12387  else
12388  {
12389  /* should not get here, that is an error! */
12390  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNION_INCOMPATIBLE;
12391  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, arg1, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, pt_short_print (parser, arg1),
12392  pt_short_print (parser, arg2));
12393  break;
12394  }
12395  }
12396  }
12397  break;
12398 
12399  default:
12400  break;
12401  }
12402 
12403  /* not query statement or error occurs */
12404  if (select_list == NULL)
12405  {
12406  return error;
12407  }
12408 
12409  if (query->node_type == PT_SELECT && pt_is_single_tuple (parser, query))
12410  {
12411  /*
12412  * This case means "select count(*) from athlete order by code"
12413  * we will remove order by clause to avoid error message
12414  * but, "select count(*) from athlete order by 2" should make out of range err
12415  */
12416  if (query->info.query.order_by != NULL)
12417  {
12418  PT_NODE head;
12419  PT_NODE *last = &head;
12420  PT_NODE *order_by = query->info.query.order_by;
12421 
12422  last->next = NULL;
12423  while (order_by != NULL)
12424  {
12425  PT_NODE *next = order_by->next;
12426  order_by->next = NULL;
12427 
12428  if (order_by->info.sort_spec.expr->node_type == PT_NAME)
12429  {
12430  parser_free_node (parser, order_by);
12431  skip_orderby_num = true;
12432  }
12433  else
12434  {
12435  last->next = order_by;
12436  last = order_by;
12437  }
12438 
12439  order_by = next;
12440  }
12441 
12442  query->info.query.order_by = head.next;
12443  }
12444 
12445  /*
12446  * This case means "select count(*) from athlete limit ?"
12447  * This limit clause should be evaluated after "select count(*) from athlete"
12448  * So we will change it as subquery.
12449  */
12450  if (query->info.query.limit != NULL)
12451  {
12452  SEMANTIC_CHK_INFO sc_info = { NULL, NULL, 0, 0, 0, false, false };
12453  PT_NODE *limit = query->info.query.limit;
12454  query->info.query.limit = NULL;
12455 
12456  /* rewrite as derived table */
12457  query = mq_rewrite_aggregate_as_derived (parser, query);
12458  if (query == NULL || pt_has_error (parser))
12459  {
12460  return ER_FAILED;
12461  }
12462 
12463  /* clear spec_ids of names referring derived table and re-run name resolving; their types are not resolved
12464  * and, since we're on the post stage of the tree walk, this will not happen naturally; */
12465  query->info.query.q.select.list =
12466  mq_clear_ids (parser, query->info.query.q.select.list, query->info.query.q.select.from);
12467 
12468  /* re-resolve names */
12469  sc_info.donot_fold = true;
12470  sc_info.top_node = query;
12471  query = pt_resolve_names (parser, query, &sc_info);
12472  if (pt_has_error (parser) || !query)
12473  {
12474  return ER_FAILED;
12475  }
12476 
12477  query->info.query.limit = limit;
12478  }
12479  }
12480 
12481  /* get ORDER BY clause */
12482  order_by = query->info.query.order_by;
12483  if (order_by == NULL)
12484  {
12485  if (query->node_type == PT_SELECT)
12486  {
12487  /* need to check select_list */
12488  goto check_select_list;
12489  }
12490 
12491  /* union has not ORDER BY */
12492  return error;
12493  }
12494 
12495  /* save original length of select_list */
12496  select_list_len = 0;
12497  select_list_full_len = pt_length_of_select_list (select_list, INCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
12498 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
12499  select_list_len = pt_length_of_select_list (select_list, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
12500 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
12501 
12502  for (order = order_by; order; order = order->next)
12503  {
12504  /* get the EXPR */
12505  r = order->info.sort_spec.expr;
12506  if (r == NULL)
12507  { /* impossible case */
12508  continue;
12509  }
12510 
12511  /* if a good integer, done */
12512  if (r->node_type == PT_VALUE)
12513  {
12514  if (r->type_enum == PT_TYPE_INTEGER)
12515  {
12516  n = r->info.value.data_value.i;
12517  /* check size of the integer */
12518  if (select_list_full_len < n || n < 1)
12519  {
12520  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_RANGE_ERR;
12521  PT_ERRORmf (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, n);
12522  /* go ahead */
12523  }
12524  else
12525  {
12526  /* the following invalid query cause error in here SELECT orderby_num() FROM t ORDER BY 1; */
12527  for (col = select_list, i = 1; i < n; i++)
12528  {
12529  col = col->next;
12530  }
12531 
12532  /* sorting node should be either an existing select node or an hidden column added by system */
12533  assert (n <= select_list_len || col->is_hidden_column);
12534 
12535  if (col->node_type == PT_EXPR && col->info.expr.op == PT_ORDERBY_NUM)
12536  {
12537  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_NAN_PATH;
12538  PT_ERRORmf (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, "ORDERBY_NUM()");
12539  /* go ahead */
12540  }
12541  }
12542  }
12543  else
12544  {
12545  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_WANT_NUM;
12546  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
12547  /* go ahead */
12548  }
12549  }
12550  else if (r->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR)
12551  {
12552  PT_ERRORmf (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_ORDERBY_ALLOWED,
12553  pt_short_print (parser, r));
12554  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_ORDERBY_ALLOWED;
12555  }
12556  else
12557  {
12558  /* not an integer value. Try to match with something in the select list. */
12559 
12560  n = 1; /* a counter for position in select_list */
12561  if (r->node_type != PT_NAME && r->node_type != PT_DOT_)
12562  {
12563  r_str = parser_print_tree (parser, r);
12564  }
12565 
12566  for (col = select_list; col; col = col->next)
12567  {
12568  /* if match, break; */
12569  if (r->node_type == col->node_type)
12570  {
12571  if (r->node_type == PT_NAME || r->node_type == PT_DOT_)
12572  {
12573  if (pt_check_path_eq (parser, r, col) == 0)
12574  {
12575  break; /* match */
12576  }
12577  }
12578  else
12579  {
12580  if (pt_str_compare (r_str, parser_print_tree (parser, col), CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
12581  {
12582  break; /* match */
12583  }
12584  }
12585  }
12586  else if (pt_check_compatible_node_for_orderby (parser, r, col))
12587  {
12588  break;
12589  }
12590  n++;
12591  }
12592 
12593  /* if end of list, no match create a hidden column node and append to select_list */
12594  if (col == NULL)
12595  {
12596  if (query->node_type != PT_SELECT)
12597  {
12598  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ORDERBY_IS_NOT_INT;
12599  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
12600  }
12601  else if (query->info.query.all_distinct == PT_DISTINCT)
12602  {
12603  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_ORDERBY_WITH_DISTINCT;
12604  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
12605  }
12606  else
12607  {
12608  /* when check order by clause in create/alter view, do not change order_by and select_list. The order
12609  * by clause will be replaced in mq_translate_subqueries() again. */
12610  if (query->do_not_replace_orderby)
12611  {
12612  continue;
12613  }
12614 
12615  col = parser_copy_tree (parser, r);
12616  if (col == NULL)
12617  {
12618  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
12619  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
12620  return error; /* give up */
12621  }
12622  else
12623  {
12624  /* mark as a hidden column */
12625  col->is_hidden_column = 1;
12626  parser_append_node (col, select_list);
12627  }
12628  }
12629  }
12630 
12631  /* we got a match=n, Create a value node and replace expr with it */
12632  temp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
12633  if (temp == NULL)
12634  {
12635  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
12636  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
12637  }
12638  else
12639  {
12640  temp->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
12641  temp->info.value.data_value.i = n;
12642  pt_value_to_db (parser, temp);
12643  parser_free_tree (parser, r);
12644  order->info.sort_spec.expr = temp;
12645  }
12646  }
12647 
12648  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12649  { /* something wrong */
12650  continue; /* go ahead */
12651  }
12652 
12653  /* set order by position num */
12654  order->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.pos_no = n;
12655  if (query->node_type != PT_SELECT)
12656  {
12657  continue; /* OK */
12658  }
12659 
12660  /* at here, query->node_type == PT_SELECT set order_by domain info */
12661  if (col->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NONE && col->type_enum != PT_TYPE_MAYBE)
12662  { /* is resolved */
12663  order->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.dom = pt_xasl_node_to_domain (parser, col);
12664  }
12665  } /* for (order = order_by; ...) */
12666 
12667  /* now check for duplicate entries. - If they match on ascending/descending, remove the second. - If they do not,
12668  * generate an error. */
12669  for (order = order_by; order; order = order->next)
12670  {
12671  while ((match = pt_find_order_value_in_list (parser, order->info.sort_spec.expr, order->next)))
12672  {
12673  if ((order->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc != match->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc)
12674  || (pt_to_null_ordering (order) != pt_to_null_ordering (match)))
12675  {
12676  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_DIR_CONFLICT;
12677  PT_ERRORmf (parser, match, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, pt_short_print (parser, match));
12678  break;
12679  }
12680  else
12681  {
12682  order->next = pt_remove_from_list (parser, match, order->next);
12683  }
12684  }
12685  }
12686 
12687  if (error != NO_ERROR)
12688  { /* give up */
12689  return error;
12690  }
12691 
12692 check_select_list:
12693 
12694  /* orderby_num() in select list restriction check */
12695  for (col = select_list; col; col = col->next)
12696  {
12697  if (PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (col->node_type))
12698  {
12699  /* skip orderby_num() expression in subqueries */
12700  continue;
12701  }
12702 
12703  if (col->node_type == PT_EXPR && col->info.expr.op == PT_ORDERBY_NUM)
12704  {
12705  if (!order_by && !skip_orderby_num)
12706  {
12707  /* the following invalid query cause error in here; SELECT orderby_num() FROM t; */
12708  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_NOT_EXIST;
12709  PT_ERRORmf (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, "ORDERBY_NUM()");
12710  break;
12711  }
12712  }
12713  else
12714  {
12715  /* the following query cause error in here; SELECT orderby_num()+1 FROM t; SELECT orderby_num()+1, a FROM t
12716  * ORDER BY 2; SELECT {orderby_num()} FROM t; SELECT {orderby_num()+1}, a FROM t ORDER BY 2; */
12717  ordbynum_flag = false;
12718  (void) parser_walk_leaves (parser, col, pt_check_orderbynum_pre, NULL, pt_check_orderbynum_post,
12719  &ordbynum_flag);
12720  if (ordbynum_flag)
12721  {
12722  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ORDERBYNUM_SELECT_LIST_ERR;
12723  PT_ERRORm (parser, col, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
12724  break;
12725  }
12726  }
12727  }
12728 
12729  return error;
12730 }
12731 
12732 /*
12733  * pt_check_path_eq () - determine if two path expressions are the same
12734  * return: 0 if two path expressions are the same, else non-zero.
12735  * parser(in):
12736  * p(in):
12737  * q(in):
12738  */
12739 int
12740 pt_check_path_eq (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * p, const PT_NODE * q)
12741 {
12742  PT_NODE_TYPE n;
12743 
12744  if (p == NULL && q == NULL)
12745  {
12746  return 0;
12747  }
12748 
12749  if (p == NULL || q == NULL)
12750  {
12751  return 1;
12752  }
12753 
12754  /* check node types are same */
12755  if (p->node_type != q->node_type)
12756  {
12757  return 1;
12758  }
12759 
12760  n = p->node_type;
12761  switch (n)
12762  {
12763  /* if a name, the original and resolved fields must match */
12764  case PT_NAME:
12765  if (pt_str_compare (p->info.name.original, q->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
12766  {
12767  return 1;
12768  }
12769  if (pt_str_compare (p->info.name.resolved, q->info.name.resolved, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
12770  {
12771  return 1;
12772  }
12773  if (p->info.name.spec_id != q->info.name.spec_id)
12774  {
12775  return 1;
12776  }
12777  break;
12778 
12779  /* EXPR must be X.Y.Z. */
12780  case PT_DOT_:
12781  if (pt_check_path_eq (parser, p->info.dot.arg1, q->info.dot.arg1))
12782  {
12783  return 1;
12784  }
12785 
12786  /* A recursive call on arg2 should work, except that we have not yet recognised common sub-path expressions
12787  * However, it is also sufficient and true that the left path be strictly equal and arg2's names match. That even
12788  * allows us to use this very function to implement recognition of common path expressions. */
12789  if (p->info.dot.arg2 == NULL || q->info.dot.arg2 == NULL)
12790  {
12791  return 1;
12792  }
12793 
12794  if (p->info.dot.arg2->node_type != PT_NAME || q->info.dot.arg2->node_type != PT_NAME)
12795  {
12796  return 1;
12797  }
12798 
12799  if (pt_str_compare (p->info.dot.arg2->info.name.original, q->info.dot.arg2->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
12800  {
12801  return 1;
12802  }
12803 
12804  break;
12805 
12806  default:
12807  PT_ERRORmf (parser, p, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_NAN_PATH,
12808  pt_short_print (parser, p));
12809  return 1;
12810  }
12811 
12812  return 0;
12813 }
12814 
12815 /*
12816  * pt_check_class_eq () - determine if two class name expressions are the same
12817  * return: 0 if two class name expressions are the same, else non-zero
12818  * parser(in):
12819  * p(in):
12820  * q(in):
12821  */
12822 int
12823 pt_check_class_eq (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * p, PT_NODE * q)
12824 {
12825  PT_NODE_TYPE n;
12826 
12827  if (p == NULL && q == NULL)
12828  {
12829  return 0;
12830  }
12831 
12832  if (p == NULL || q == NULL)
12833  {
12834  return 1;
12835  }
12836 
12837  /* check if node types are same */
12838  if (p->node_type != q->node_type)
12839  {
12840  return 1;
12841  }
12842 
12843  n = p->node_type;
12844  switch (n)
12845  {
12846  /* if a name, the resolved (class name) fields must match */
12847  case PT_NAME:
12848  if (pt_str_compare (p->info.name.resolved, q->info.name.resolved, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
12849  {
12850  return 1;
12851  }
12852  if (p->info.name.spec_id != q->info.name.spec_id)
12853  {
12854  return 1;
12855  }
12856  break;
12857 
12858  default:
12859  PT_ERRORmf (parser, p, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_NAN_PATH,
12860  pt_short_print (parser, p));
12861  return 1;
12862  }
12863 
12864  return 0;
12865 }
12866 
12867 /*
12868  * pt_coerce_insert_values () - try to coerce the insert values to the types
12869  * indicated by the insert attributes
12870  * return:
12871  * parser(in): handle to context used to parse the insert/merge statement
12872  * stmt(in): the AST form of an insert/merge statement
12873  */
12874 static PT_NODE *
12875 pt_coerce_insert_values (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt)
12876 {
12877  PT_NODE *v = NULL, *a = NULL, *crt_list = NULL;
12878  int a_cnt = 0, v_cnt = 0;
12879  PT_NODE *prev = NULL;
12880  PT_NODE *attr_list = NULL;
12881  PT_NODE *value_clauses = NULL;
12882 
12883  /* preconditions are not met */
12884  if (stmt->node_type != PT_INSERT && stmt->node_type != PT_MERGE)
12885  {
12886  return NULL;
12887  }
12888 
12889 #if 0 /* to disable TEXT */
12890  pt_resolve_insert_external (parser, ins);
12891 #endif /* 0 */
12892 
12893  if (stmt->node_type == PT_INSERT)
12894  {
12895  attr_list = stmt->info.insert.attr_list;
12896  value_clauses = stmt->info.insert.value_clauses;
12897  }
12898  else
12899  {
12900  attr_list = stmt->info.merge.insert.attr_list;
12901  value_clauses = stmt->info.merge.insert.value_clauses;
12902  }
12903 
12904  a_cnt = pt_length_of_list (attr_list);
12905 
12906  for (crt_list = value_clauses; crt_list != NULL; crt_list = crt_list->next)
12907  {
12908  if (crt_list->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_DEFAULT_VALUE)
12909  {
12910  v = NULL;
12911  }
12912  else if (crt_list->info.node_list.list_type == PT_IS_SUBQUERY)
12913  {
12914  /* this sort of nods at union queries */
12915  v = pt_get_select_list (parser, crt_list->info.node_list.list);
12916  v_cnt = pt_length_of_select_list (v, EXCLUDE_HIDDEN_COLUMNS);
12917  if (a_cnt != v_cnt)
12918  {
12919  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_CNT_COL_CNT_NE, a_cnt, v_cnt);
12920  }
12921  else
12922  {
12923  continue;
12924  }
12925  }
12926  else
12927  {
12928  v = crt_list->info.node_list.list;
12929  v_cnt = pt_length_of_list (v);
12930  if (a_cnt != v_cnt)
12931  {
12932  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ATT_CNT_VAL_CNT_NE, a_cnt, v_cnt);
12933  }
12934  }
12935  prev = NULL;
12936  for (a = attr_list; v != NULL && a != NULL; prev = v, v = v->next, a = a->next)
12937  {
12938  /* test assignment compatibility. This sets parser->error_msgs */
12939  PT_NODE *new_node;
12940 
12941  new_node = pt_assignment_compatible (parser, a, v);
12942  if (new_node == NULL)
12943  {
12944  /* this in an error and the message was set by the call to pt_assignment_compatible. Just continue */
12945  continue;
12946  }
12947 
12948  if (new_node != v)
12949  {
12950  v = new_node;
12951  if (prev == NULL)
12952  {
12953  /* first node in the list */
12954  crt_list->info.node_list.list = v;
12955  }
12956  else
12957  {
12958  /* relink list to the wrapped node */
12959  prev->next = v;
12960  }
12961  }
12962 
12963  if (v->node_type == PT_HOST_VAR && v->type_enum == PT_TYPE_MAYBE && v->expected_domain == NULL
12964  && (PT_IS_NUMERIC_TYPE (a->type_enum) || PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (a->type_enum)))
12965  {
12966  TP_DOMAIN *d;
12967 
12968  d = pt_node_to_db_domain (parser, a, NULL);
12969  d = tp_domain_cache (d);
12970  v->expected_domain = d;
12971  }
12972  }
12973  }
12974  return stmt;
12975 }
12976 
12977 /*
12978  * pt_check_sub_insert () - Checks if sub-inserts are semantically correct
12979  *
12980  * return : Unchanged node argument.
12981  * parser (in) : Parser context.
12982  * node (in) : Parse tree node.
12983  * void_arg (in) : Unused argument.
12984  * continue_walk (in) : Continue walk.
12985  */
12986 static PT_NODE *
12987 pt_check_sub_insert (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *void_arg, int *continue_walk)
12988 {
12989  PT_NODE *entity_name = NULL, *value_clauses = NULL;
12990 
12991  if (*continue_walk == PT_STOP_WALK)
12992  {
12993  return node;
12994  }
12995 
12996  switch (node->node_type)
12997  {
12998  case PT_INSERT:
12999  /* continue to checks */
13000  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
13001  break;
13002  case PT_SELECT:
13003  case PT_INTERSECTION:
13004  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
13005  case PT_UNION:
13006  /* stop advancing into this node */
13007  *continue_walk = PT_LIST_WALK;
13008  return node;
13009  default:
13010  /* do nothing */
13011  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
13012  return node;
13013  }
13014  /* Check current insert node */
13015  value_clauses = node->info.insert.value_clauses;
13016  if (value_clauses->next)
13017  {
13018  /* Only one row is allowed for sub-inserts */
13019  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_DO_INSERT_TOO_MANY, 0);
13020  if (!pt_has_error (parser))
13021  {
13022  PT_ERRORc (parser, node, db_error_string (3));
13023  }
13024  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
13025  return node;
13026  }
13027  entity_name = node->info.insert.spec->info.spec.entity_name;
13028  if (entity_name == NULL || entity_name->info.name.db_object == NULL)
13029  {
13030  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "Unresolved insert spec");
13031  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
13032  return node;
13033  }
13034  if (sm_is_reuse_oid_class (entity_name->info.name.db_object))
13035  {
13036  /* Inserting Reusable OID is not allowed */
13037  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NON_REFERABLE_VIOLATION,
13038  entity_name->info.name.original);
13039  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
13040  return node;
13041  }
13042 
13043  /* check sub-inserts for this sub-insert */
13044  if (value_clauses->info.node_list.list_type != PT_IS_SUBQUERY)
13045  {
13046  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, value_clauses, pt_check_sub_insert, NULL, NULL, NULL);
13047  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13048  {
13049  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
13050  }
13051  }
13052  return node;
13053 }
13054 
13055 /*
13056  * pt_count_input_markers () - If the node is a input host variable marker,
13057  * compare its index+1 against *num_ptr and record the bigger of
13058  * the two into *num_ptr
13059  * return:
13060  * parser(in):
13061  * node(in): the node to check
13062  * arg(in/out):
13063  * continue_walk(in):
13064  */
13065 
13066 PT_NODE *
13067 pt_count_input_markers (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13068 {
13069  int *num_markers;
13070 
13071  num_markers = (int *) arg;
13072 
13073  if (pt_is_input_hostvar (node))
13074  {
13075  if (*num_markers < node->info.host_var.index + 1)
13076  {
13077  *num_markers = node->info.host_var.index + 1;
13078  }
13079  }
13080 
13081  return node;
13082 }
13083 
13084 /*
13085  * pt_count_output_markers () - If the node is a output host variable marker,
13086  * compare its index+1 against *num_ptr and record the bigger of
13087  * the two into *num_ptr
13088  * return:
13089  * parser(in):
13090  * node(in): the node to check
13091  * arg(in/out):
13092  * continue_walk(in):
13093  */
13094 PT_NODE *
13095 pt_count_output_markers (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13096 {
13097  int *num_markers;
13098 
13099  num_markers = (int *) arg;
13100 
13101  if (pt_is_output_hostvar (node))
13102  {
13103  if (*num_markers < node->info.host_var.index + 1)
13104  {
13105  *num_markers = node->info.host_var.index + 1;
13106  }
13107  }
13108 
13109  return node;
13110 }
13111 
13112 /*
13113  * pt_has_using_index_clause () -
13114  * return:
13115  * parser(in):
13116  * node(in):
13117  * arg(in):
13118  * continue_walk(in):
13119  */
13120 PT_NODE *
13121 pt_has_using_index_clause (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13122 {
13123  bool *found = (bool *) arg;
13124  PT_NODE *ui_node;
13125 
13126  switch (node->node_type)
13127  {
13128  case PT_DELETE:
13129  ui_node = node->info.delete_.using_index;
13130  break;
13131 
13132  case PT_UPDATE:
13133  ui_node = node->info.update.using_index;
13134  break;
13135 
13136  case PT_SELECT:
13137  ui_node = node->info.query.q.select.using_index;
13138  break;
13139 
13140  default:
13141  ui_node = NULL;
13142  break;
13143  }
13144 
13145  if (ui_node)
13146  {
13147  *found = true;
13148  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
13149  }
13150 
13151  return node;
13152 }

13154 /*
13155  * pt_validate_query_spec () - check if a query_spec is compatible with a
13156  * given {vclass} object
13157  * return: an error code if checking found an error, NO_ERROR otherwise
13158  * parser(in): handle to context used to parse the query_specs
13159  * s(in): a query_spec in parse_tree form
13160  * c(in): a vclass object
13161  */
13162 
13163 int
13164 pt_validate_query_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * s, DB_OBJECT * c)
13165 {
13166  PT_NODE *attrs = NULL;
13167  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
13168 
13169  assert (parser != NULL && s != NULL && c != NULL);
13170 
13171  /* a syntax error for query_spec */
13172  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13173  {
13174  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_SYNTAX);
13175  error_code = er_errid ();
13176  goto error_exit;
13177  }
13178 
13179  if (db_is_vclass (c) <= 0)
13180  {
13181  error_code = ER_OBJ_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
13182  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 0);
13183  goto error_exit;
13184  }
13185 
13186  s = parser_walk_tree (parser, s, pt_set_is_view_spec, NULL, NULL, NULL);
13187  assert (s != NULL);
13188 
13189  attrs = pt_get_attributes (parser, c);
13190 
13191  /* apply semantic checks to query_spec */
13192  s = pt_check_vclass_query_spec (parser, s, attrs, db_get_class_name (c), true);
13193  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13194  {
13195  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_SEMANTIC);
13196  error_code = er_errid ();
13197  goto error_exit;
13198  }
13199  if (s == NULL)
13200  {
13201  error_code = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
13202  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 0);
13203  goto error_exit;
13204  }
13205 
13206  s = pt_type_cast_vclass_query_spec (parser, s, attrs);
13207  if (pt_has_error (parser))
13208  {
13209  pt_report_to_ersys (parser, PT_SEMANTIC);
13210  error_code = er_errid ();
13211  goto error_exit;
13212  }
13213  if (s == NULL)
13214  {
13215  error_code = ER_GENERIC_ERROR;
13216  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 0);
13217  goto error_exit;
13218  }
13219 
13220  return error_code;
13221 
13222 error_exit:
13223  return error_code;
13224 }
13225 
13226 
13227 /*
13228  * pt_check_xaction_list () - Checks to see if there is more than one
13229  * isolation level clause or more than one timeout value clause
13230  * return:
13231  * parser(in):
13232  * node(in): the node to check
13233  */
13234 
13235 static void
13236 pt_check_xaction_list (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
13237 {
13238  int num_iso_nodes = 0;
13239  int num_time_nodes = 0;
13240 
13241  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_count_iso_nodes, &num_iso_nodes, NULL, NULL);
13242 
13243  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_count_time_nodes, &num_time_nodes, NULL, NULL);
13244 
13245  if (num_iso_nodes > 1)
13246  {
13247  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GT_1_ISOLATION_LVL);
13248  }
13249 
13250  if (num_time_nodes > 1)
13251  {
13252  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GT_1_TIMEOUT_CLAUSES);
13253  }
13254 }
13255 
13256 /*
13257  * pt_count_iso_nodes () - returns node unchanged, count by reference
13258  * return:
13259  * parser(in):
13260  * node(in): the node to check
13261  * arg(in/out): count of isolation level nodes
13262  * continue_walk(in):
13263  */
13264 
13265 static PT_NODE *
13266 pt_count_iso_nodes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13267 {
13268  int *cnt = (int *) arg;
13269 
13270  if (node->node_type == PT_ISOLATION_LVL)
13271  {
13272  (*cnt)++;
13273  }
13274 
13275  return node;
13276 }
13277 
13278 /*
13279  * pt_count_time_nodes () - returns node timeouted, count by reference
13280  * return:
13281  * parser(in):
13282  * node(in): the node to check
13283  * arg(in/out): count of timeout nodes
13284  * continue_walk(in):
13285  */
13286 static PT_NODE *
13287 pt_count_time_nodes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13288 {
13289  int *cnt = (int *) arg;
13290 
13291  if (node->node_type == PT_TIMEOUT)
13292  {
13293  (*cnt)++;
13294  }
13295 
13296  return node;
13297 }
13298 
13299 /*
13300  * pt_check_isolation_lvl () - checks isolation level node
13301  * return:
13302  * parser(in):
13303  * node(in/out): the node to check
13304  * arg(in):
13305  * continue_walk(in):
13306  *
13307  * Note :
13308  * checks
13309  * 1) if isolation levels for schema & instances are compatible.
13310  * 2) if isolation number entered, check to see if it is valid.
13311  */
13312 
13313 static PT_NODE *
13314 pt_check_isolation_lvl (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
13315 {
13316  DB_TRAN_ISOLATION cur_lvl;
13317  int dummy;
13318 
13319  if (node->node_type == PT_ISOLATION_LVL)
13320  {
13321  if (node->info.isolation_lvl.level != NULL)
13322  {
13323  /* assume correct type, value checking will be done at run-time */
13324  return node;
13325  }
13326 
13327  /* check to make sure an isolation level has been given */
13328  if ((node->info.isolation_lvl.schema == PT_NO_ISOLATION_LEVEL)
13329  && (node->info.isolation_lvl.instances == PT_NO_ISOLATION_LEVEL)
13330  && (node->info.isolation_lvl.async_ws == false))
13331  {
13332  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_ISOLATION_LVL_MSG);
13333  }
13334 
13335  /* get the current isolation level in case user is defaulting either the schema or the instances level. */
13336  (void) db_get_tran_settings (&dummy, &cur_lvl);
13337 
13338  if (node->info.isolation_lvl.schema == PT_NO_ISOLATION_LEVEL)
13339  {
13340  switch (cur_lvl)
13341  {
13342  case TRAN_UNKNOWN_ISOLATION:
13343  /* in this case, the user is specifying only the instance level when there was not a previous isolation
13344  * level set. Default the schema isolation level to the instance isolation level. */
13345  node->info.isolation_lvl.schema = node->info.isolation_lvl.instances;
13346  break;
13347 
13348  case TRAN_READ_COMMITTED:
13349  case TRAN_REPEATABLE_READ:
13350  node->info.isolation_lvl.schema = PT_REPEATABLE_READ;
13351  break;
13352 
13353  case TRAN_SERIALIZABLE:
13354  node->info.isolation_lvl.schema = PT_SERIALIZABLE;
13355  break;
13356  }
13357  }
13358 
13359  if (node->info.isolation_lvl.instances == PT_NO_ISOLATION_LEVEL)
13360  {
13361  switch (cur_lvl)
13362  {
13363  case TRAN_UNKNOWN_ISOLATION:
13364  /* in this case, the user is specifying only the schema level when there was not a previous isolation
13365  * level set. Default the instances isolation level to the schema isolation level. */
13366  node->info.isolation_lvl.instances = node->info.isolation_lvl.schema;
13367  break;
13368 
13369  case TRAN_READ_COMMITTED:
13370  node->info.isolation_lvl.instances = PT_READ_COMMITTED;
13371  break;
13372 
13373  case TRAN_REPEATABLE_READ:
13374  node->info.isolation_lvl.instances = PT_REPEATABLE_READ;
13375  break;
13376 
13377  case TRAN_SERIALIZABLE:
13378  node->info.isolation_lvl.instances = PT_SERIALIZABLE;
13379  break;
13380  }
13381  }
13382 
13383  /* coercing/correcting of incompatible level happens in do_set_xaction() */
13384  }
13385 
13386  return node;
13387 }
13388 
13389 #if defined (ENABLE_UNUSED_FUNCTION)
13390 /*
13391  * pt_find_attr_def () - Finds the PT_NODE in attr_def_list with the same
13392  * original_name as the given name
13393  * return: db_user instance if user exists, NULL otherwise.
13394  * attr_def_list(in): the list of attr_def's in a CREATE_ENTITY node
13395  * name(in): a PT_NAME node
13396  */
13397 
13398 PT_NODE *
13399 pt_find_attr_def (const PT_NODE * attr_def_list, const PT_NODE * name)
13400 {
13401  PT_NODE *p;
13402 
13403  for (p = (PT_NODE *) attr_def_list; p; p = p->next)
13404  {
13405  if (intl_identifier_casecmp (p->info.attr_def.attr_name->info.name.original, name->info.name.original) == 0)
13406  {
13407  break;
13408  }
13409  }
13410 
13411  return p;
13412 }

13415  * pt_find_cnstr_def () - Finds the PT_NODE in cnstr_def_list with the same
13416  * original_name as the given name
13417  * return: attribute instance iff attribute exists, NULL otherwise.
13418  * cnstr_def_list(in): the list of constraint elements
13419  * name(in): a PT_NAME node
13420  */
13421 PT_NODE *
13422 pt_find_cnstr_def (const PT_NODE * cnstr_def_list, const PT_NODE * name)
13423 {

13425 
13426  for (p = (PT_NODE *) cnstr_def_list; p; p = p->next)
13427  {
13428  if (intl_identifier_casecmp (p->info.name.original, name->info.name.original) == 0)
13429  {
13430  break;
13431  }
13432  }
13433 
13434  return p;
13435 }
