13437 
13438 /*
13439  * pt_check_constraint () - Checks the given constraint appears to be valid
13440  * return: the constraint node
13441  * parser(in): the current parser context
13442  * create(in): a CREATE_ENTITY node
13443  * constraint(in): a CONSTRAINT node, assumed to have come from the
13444  * constraint_list of "create"
13445  *
13446  * Note :
13447  * Right now single-column UNIQUE and NOT NULL constraints are the only
13448  * ones that are understood. All others are ignored (with a warning).
13449  * Unfortunately, this can't do the whole job because at this point we know
13450  * nothing about inherited attributes, etc. For example, someone could be
13451  * trying to add a UNIQUE constraint to an inherited attribute, but we won't
13452  * be able to handle it because we'll be unable to resolve the name. Under
13453  * the current architecture the template stuff will need to be extended to
13454  * understand constraints.
13455  */
13456 
13457 static PT_NODE *
13458 pt_check_constraint (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * create, const PT_NODE * constraint)
13459 {
13460  switch (constraint->info.constraint.type)
13461  {
13462  case PT_CONSTRAIN_UNKNOWN:
13463  goto warning;
13464 
13465  case PT_CONSTRAIN_NULL:
13466  case PT_CONSTRAIN_NOT_NULL:
13467  case PT_CONSTRAIN_UNIQUE:
13468  break;
13469 
13470  case PT_CONSTRAIN_PRIMARY_KEY:
13471  case PT_CONSTRAIN_FOREIGN_KEY:
13472  case PT_CONSTRAIN_CHECK:
13473  if (create->info.create_entity.entity_type != PT_CLASS)
13474  {
13475  goto error;
13476  }
13477  else
13478  {
13479  goto warning;
13480  }
13481  }
13482 
13483  return (PT_NODE *) constraint;
13484 
13485 warning:
13486  PT_WARNINGmf (parser, constraint, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNIMPLEMENTED_CONSTRAINT,
13487  parser_print_tree (parser, constraint));
13488  return (PT_NODE *) constraint;
13489 
13490 error:
13491  PT_ERRORm (parser, constraint, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_WANT_NO_CONSTRAINTS);
13492  return NULL;
13493 }
13494 
13495 /*
13496  * pt_check_constraints () - Checks all of the constraints given in
13497  * this CREATE_ENTITY node
13498  * return: the CREATE_ENTITY node
13499  * parser(in): the current parser context
13500  * create(in): a CREATE_ENTITY node
13501  */
13502 static PT_NODE *
13503 pt_check_constraints (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const PT_NODE * create)
13504 {
13505  PT_NODE *constraint;
13506 
13507  for (constraint = create->info.create_entity.constraint_list; constraint; constraint = constraint->next)
13508  {
13509  (void) pt_check_constraint (parser, create, constraint);
13510  }
13511 
13512  return (PT_NODE *) create;
13513 }
13514 
13515 /*
13516  * pt_find_class_of_index () - Find the name of the class that has a given
13517  * index (specified by its name and type)
13518  * return: a PT_NAME node with the class name or NULL on error
13519  * parser(in):
13520  * index_name(in):
13521  * index_type(in):
13522  *
13523  * Note:
13524  * Only constraint types that satisfy the DB_IS_CONSTRAINT_INDEX_FAMILY
13525  * condition will be searched for.
13526  */
13527 PT_NODE *
13528 pt_find_class_of_index (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, const char *const index_name, const DB_CONSTRAINT_TYPE index_type)
13529 {
13530  PT_NODE *node = NULL;
13531  DB_OBJECT *const class_ = db_find_class_of_index (index_name, index_type);
13532 
13533  if (class_ == NULL)
13534  {
13535  return NULL;
13536  }
13537  node = pt_name (parser, db_get_class_name (class_));
13538  if (node == NULL)
13539  {
13540  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
13541  return NULL;
13542  }
13543  return node;
13544 }
13545 
13546 /*
13547  * pt_check_defaultf () - Checks to see if default function is well-formed
13548  * return: none
13549  * parser(in):
13550  * node(in): the node to check
13551  */
13552 static int
13553 pt_check_defaultf (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
13554 {
13555  PT_NODE *arg;
13556 
13557  assert (node != NULL && node->node_type == PT_EXPR && node->info.expr.op == PT_DEFAULTF);
13558  if (node == NULL || node->node_type != PT_EXPR || node->info.expr.op != PT_DEFAULTF)
13559  {
13560  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "bad node type");
13561  return ER_FAILED;
13562  }
13563 
13564  arg = node->info.expr.arg1;
13565 
13566  /* OIDs don't have default value */
13567  if (arg == NULL || arg->node_type != PT_NAME || arg->info.name.meta_class == PT_OID_ATTR
13568  || !PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (arg, PT_NAME_REAL_TABLE))
13569  {
13570  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_DEFAULT_JUST_COLUMN_NAME);
13571  return ER_FAILED;
13572  }
13573 
13574  /* Argument of DEFAULT function should be given. So, PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT bit might be always set when
13575  * expression node was created. The following assertion and defensive code will be used to handle unexpected
13576  * situation. */
13577  assert (PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (arg, PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT) && arg->info.name.default_value != NULL);
13578  if (!PT_NAME_INFO_IS_FLAGED (arg, PT_NAME_INFO_FILL_DEFAULT) || arg->info.name.default_value == NULL)
13579  {
13580  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "bad DEFAULTF node");
13581  return ER_FAILED;
13582  }
13583 
13584  /* In case of no default value defined on an attribute: DEFAULT function returns NULL when the attribute given as
13585  * argument has UNIQUE or no constraint, but it returns a semantic error for PRIMARY KEY or NOT NULL constraint. This
13586  * function does not return a semantic error for attributes with auto_increment because, regardless of the default
13587  * value, NULL will not be inserted there. */
13588  if (arg->info.name.resolved && arg->info.name.original)
13589  {
13590  DB_ATTRIBUTE *db_att = NULL;
13591  db_att = db_get_attribute_by_name (arg->info.name.resolved, arg->info.name.original);
13592 
13593  if (db_att && !db_attribute_is_auto_increment (db_att))
13594  {
13595  if ((db_attribute_is_primary_key (db_att) || db_attribute_is_non_null (db_att))
13596  && arg->info.name.default_value->node_type == PT_VALUE
13597  && DB_IS_NULL (&(arg->info.name.default_value->info.value.db_value)))
13598  {
13599  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OBJ_ATTRIBUTE_CANT_BE_NULL, 1, arg->info.name.original);
13600  PT_ERRORc (parser, arg, er_msg ());
13601  return ER_FAILED;
13602  }
13603  }
13604  }
13605  return NO_ERROR;
13606 }
13607 
13608 
13609 /*
13610  * pt_check_auto_increment_table_option () - Checks that the AUTO_INCREMENT
13611  * table option has a non-ambiguous field to apply to and that
13612  * the respective field does not have an explicit auto_increment start
13613  * value.
13614  *
13615  * NOTE: the function also modifies the parse tree by rewriting the
13616  * table option as an AUTO_INCREMENT constraint for the respective field.
13617  *
13618  * return: error code
13619  * parser(in): the current parser context
13620  * create(in): a CREATE_ENTITY node
13621  */
13622 static int
13623 pt_check_auto_increment_table_option (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * create)
13624 {
13625  PT_NODE *attr = NULL;
13626  PT_NODE *auto_inc_attr = NULL;
13627  PT_NODE *start_val = NULL;
13628  PT_NODE *increment_val = NULL;
13629  PT_NODE *tbl_opt = NULL;
13630  PT_NODE *prev_tbl_opt = NULL;
13631 
13632  /* do we have EXACTLY ONE auto_increment node in our attr list? */
13633  for (attr = create->info.create_entity.attr_def_list; attr != NULL; attr = attr->next)
13634  {
13635  if (attr->info.attr_def.auto_increment != NULL)
13636  {
13637  if (auto_inc_attr != NULL)
13638  {
13639  /* we already found an auto increment attr! */
13640  PT_ERRORm (parser, create, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_SINGLE_COL_AMBIGUITY));
13641  return ER_FAILED;
13642  }
13643  auto_inc_attr = attr;
13644  }
13645  }
13646 
13647  if (auto_inc_attr == NULL)
13648  {
13649  PT_ERRORm (parser, create, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_SINGLE_COL_AMBIGUITY));
13650  return ER_FAILED;
13651  }
13652 
13653  /* here we have exactly ONE attribute with auto_increment */
13654 
13655  if (auto_inc_attr->info.attr_def.auto_increment->info.auto_increment.start_val != NULL)
13656  {
13657  /* does it already have a start value? this is not good */
13658  PT_ERRORm (parser, create, MSGCAT_SET_ERROR, -(ER_AUTO_INCREMENT_SINGLE_COL_AMBIGUITY));
13659  return ER_FAILED;
13660  }
13661 
13662  /* alter the tree */
13663 
13664  /* locate the tbl opt, save its numeric value and destroy it */
13665 
13666  prev_tbl_opt = NULL;
13667  tbl_opt = create->info.create_entity.table_option_list;
13668  while (tbl_opt != NULL)
13669  {
13670  if (tbl_opt->info.table_option.option == PT_TABLE_OPTION_AUTO_INCREMENT)
13671  {
13672  start_val = parser_copy_tree (parser, tbl_opt->info.table_option.val);
13673  if (prev_tbl_opt != NULL)
13674  {
13675  prev_tbl_opt->next = tbl_opt->next;
13676  }
13677  else
13678  {
13679  create->info.create_entity.table_option_list = tbl_opt->next;
13680  }
13681 
13682  tbl_opt->next = NULL;
13683  parser_free_tree (parser, tbl_opt);
13684  break;
13685 
13686  }
13687 
13688  prev_tbl_opt = tbl_opt;
13689  tbl_opt = tbl_opt->next;
13690  }
13691 
13692  /* add the two nodes to the attribute definition */
13693  increment_val = pt_make_integer_value (parser, 1);
13694 
13695  if (start_val == NULL || increment_val == NULL)
13696  {
13697  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "allocate new node");
13698  return NO_ERROR;
13699  }
13700 
13701  auto_inc_attr->info.attr_def.auto_increment->info.auto_increment.start_val = start_val;
13702  auto_inc_attr->info.attr_def.auto_increment->info.auto_increment.increment_val = increment_val;
13703 
13704  return NO_ERROR;
13705 }
13706 
13707 /*
13708  * pt_check_group_concat_order_by () - checks an ORDER_BY clause of a
13709  * GROUP_CONCAT aggregate function;
13710  * if the expression or identifier from
13711  * ORDER BY clause matches an argument of function,
13712  * the ORDER BY item is converted into associated
13713  * number.
13714  * return:
13715  * parser(in):
13716  * query(in): query node has ORDER BY
13717  *
13718  *
13719  * Note :
13720  *
13721  * Only one order by item is supported :
13722  * - if it is an INTEGER, make sure it does not exceed the number of items
13723  * in the argument list.
13724  * - if it is a path expression, match it with an argument in the
13725  * function's argument list and replace the node with a PT_VALUE
13726  * with corresponding number.
13727  * - if it doesn't match, an error is issued.
13728  */
13729 static int
13730 pt_check_group_concat_order_by (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * func)
13731 {
13732  PT_NODE *arg_list = NULL;
13733  PT_NODE *order_by = NULL;
13734  PT_NODE *arg = NULL;
13735  PT_NODE *temp, *order;
13736  int n, i, arg_list_len;
13737  int error = NO_ERROR;
13738  PT_NODE *group_concat_sep_node_save = NULL;
13739 
13740  assert (func->info.function.function_type == PT_GROUP_CONCAT);
13741 
13742  /* get ORDER BY clause */
13743  order_by = func->info.function.order_by;
13744  if (order_by == NULL)
13745  {
13746  goto error_exit;
13747  }
13748 
13749  arg_list = func->info.function.arg_list;
13750  if (arg_list == NULL)
13751  {
13752  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_INTERNAL_FUNCTION, "GROUP_CONCAT");
13753  goto error_exit;
13754  }
13755 
13756  /* remove separator from list of arguments */
13757  group_concat_sep_node_save = func->info.function.arg_list->next;
13758  func->info.function.arg_list->next = NULL;
13759 
13760  /* save original length of select_list */
13761  arg_list_len = pt_length_of_list (arg_list);
13762  for (order = order_by; order != NULL; order = order->next)
13763  {
13764  /* get the EXPR */
13765  PT_NODE *r = order->info.sort_spec.expr;
13766  if (r == NULL)
13767  { /* impossible case */
13768  continue;
13769  }
13770 
13771  if (PT_IS_LOB_TYPE (r->type_enum))
13772  {
13773  PT_ERRORmf (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_ORDERBY_ALLOWED,
13774  pt_short_print (parser, r));
13775  goto error_exit;
13776  }
13777 
13778  /* if a good integer, done */
13779  if (r->node_type == PT_VALUE)
13780  {
13781  if (r->type_enum == PT_TYPE_INTEGER)
13782  {
13783  n = r->info.value.data_value.i;
13784  /* check size of the integer */
13785  if (n > arg_list_len || n < 1)
13786  {
13787  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_RANGE_ERR;
13788  PT_ERRORmf (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, n);
13789  /* go ahead */
13790  }
13791  else
13792  {
13793  /* goto associated argument: */
13794  for (arg = arg_list, i = 1; i < n; i++)
13795  {
13796  arg = arg->next;
13797  }
13798  }
13799  }
13800  else
13801  {
13802  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_WANT_NUM;
13803  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
13804  /* go ahead */
13805  }
13806  }
13807  else
13808  {
13809  char *r_str = NULL;
13810  /* not an integer value. Try to match with something in the select list. */
13811 
13812  n = 1; /* a counter for position in select_list */
13813  if (r->node_type != PT_NAME && r->node_type != PT_DOT_)
13814  {
13815  r_str = parser_print_tree (parser, r);
13816  }
13817 
13818  for (arg = arg_list; arg != NULL; arg = arg->next)
13819  {
13820  /* if match, break; */
13821  if (r->node_type == arg->node_type)
13822  {
13823  if (r->node_type == PT_NAME || r->node_type == PT_DOT_)
13824  {
13825  if (pt_check_path_eq (parser, r, arg) == 0)
13826  {
13827  break; /* match */
13828  }
13829  }
13830  else
13831  {
13832  if (pt_str_compare (r_str, parser_print_tree (parser, arg), CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
13833  {
13834  break; /* match */
13835  }
13836  }
13837  }
13838  n++;
13839  }
13840 
13841  /* if end of list -> error : currently aggregate functions don't support other order by expression than
13842  * arguments */
13843  if (arg == NULL)
13844  {
13845  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_GROUP_CONCAT_ORDERBY_SAME_EXPR;
13846  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
13847  /* go ahead */
13848  }
13849  else
13850  {
13851  /* we got a match=n, Create a value node and replace expr with it */
13852  temp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
13853  if (temp == NULL)
13854  {
13855  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY;
13856  PT_ERRORm (parser, r, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error);
13857  }
13858  else
13859  {
13860  temp->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
13861  temp->info.value.data_value.i = n;
13862  pt_value_to_db (parser, temp);
13863  parser_free_tree (parser, r);
13864  order->info.sort_spec.expr = temp;
13865  }
13866  }
13867  }
13868 
13869  if (error != NO_ERROR)
13870  { /* something wrong, exit */
13871  goto error_exit;
13872  }
13873 
13874  /* at this point <n> contains the sorting position : either specified in statement or computed, and <arg> is the
13875  * corresponding function argument */
13876  assert (arg != NULL);
13877  assert (n > 0 && n <= arg_list_len);
13878 
13879  /* set order by position num */
13880  order->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.pos_no = n;
13881 
13882  /* set order_by domain info */
13883  if (arg->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NONE && arg->type_enum != PT_TYPE_MAYBE)
13884  { /* is resolved */
13885  order->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.dom = pt_xasl_node_to_domain (parser, arg);
13886  }
13887  }
13888 
13889  assert (func->info.function.order_by->next == NULL);
13890 
13891 error_exit:
13892  if (group_concat_sep_node_save != NULL)
13893  {
13894  func->info.function.arg_list->next = group_concat_sep_node_save;
13895  }
13896 
13897  return error;
13898 }
13899 
13900 /*
13901  * pt_check_cume_dist_percent_rank_order_by () - checks an ORDER_BY clause of a
13902  * CUME_DIST aggregate function;
13903  * if the expression or identifier from
13904  * ORDER BY clause matches an argument of function,
13905  * the ORDER BY item is converted into associated
13906  * number.
13907  * return: NO_ERROR or error_code
13908  * parser(in):
13909  * func(in):
13910  *
13911  *
13912  * Note :
13913  * We need to check arguments and order by,
13914  * because the arguments must be constant expression and
13915  * match the ORDER BY clause by position.
13916  */
13917 
13918 static int
13919 pt_check_cume_dist_percent_rank_order_by (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * func)
13920 {
13921  PT_NODE *arg_list = NULL;
13922  PT_NODE *order_by = NULL;
13923  PT_NODE *arg = NULL;
13924  PT_NODE *order = NULL;
13925  PT_NODE *order_expr = NULL;
13926  DB_OBJECT *obj = NULL;
13927  DB_ATTRIBUTE *att = NULL;
13928  TP_DOMAIN *dom = NULL;
13929  DB_VALUE *value = NULL;
13930  int i, arg_list_len, order_by_list_len;
13931  int error = NO_ERROR;
13932  const char *func_name;
13933 
13934  /* get function name for ERROR message */
13935  if (func->info.function.function_type == PT_CUME_DIST)
13936  {
13937  func_name = "CUME_DIST";
13938  }
13939  else if (func->info.function.function_type == PT_PERCENT_RANK)
13940  {
13941  func_name = "PERCENT_RANK";
13942  }
13943  else
13944  {
13945  assert (false);
13946  return ER_FAILED;
13947  }
13948 
13949  /* first check if the arguments are constant */
13950  arg_list = func->info.function.arg_list;
13951  order_by = func->info.function.order_by;
13952 
13953  /* for analytic function */
13954  if (func->info.function.analytic.is_analytic)
13955  {
13956  if (arg_list != NULL || order_by != NULL)
13957  {
13958  error = ER_FAILED;
13959  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_INTERNAL_FUNCTION, func_name);
13960  }
13961  goto error_exit;
13962  }
13963 
13964  /* aggregate function */
13965  if (arg_list == NULL || order_by == NULL)
13966  {
13967  error = ER_FAILED;
13968  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_INTERNAL_FUNCTION, func_name);
13969  goto error_exit;
13970  }
13971 
13972  /* save original length of select_list */
13973  arg_list_len = pt_length_of_list (arg_list);
13974  order_by_list_len = pt_length_of_list (order_by);
13975  if (arg_list_len != order_by_list_len)
13976  {
13977  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNMACHTED_ARG_ORDER, func_name);
13978  goto error_exit;
13979  }
13980 
13981  arg = arg_list;
13982  order = order_by;
13983  for (i = 0; i < arg_list_len; i++)
13984  {
13985  /* check argument type: arguments must be constant */
13986  if (!pt_is_const_expr_node (arg))
13987  {
13988  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_CONSTANT_PARAMETER, func_name);
13989  goto error_exit;
13990  }
13991 
13992  /* check order by */
13993  order_expr = order->info.sort_spec.expr;
13994  if (order->node_type != PT_SORT_SPEC || (order_expr->node_type != PT_NAME && order_expr->node_type != PT_VALUE)
13995  || PT_IS_LOB_TYPE (order_expr->type_enum))
13996  {
13997  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_FUNCTION_ORDERBY, func_name);
13998  goto error_exit;
13999  }
14000 
14001  if (order_expr->node_type == PT_NAME)
14002  {
14003  /* check if the arg matches order by clause by position */
14004  dom = NULL;
14005  obj = db_find_class (order_expr->info.name.resolved);
14006  if (obj != NULL)
14007  {
14008  att = db_get_attribute (obj, order_expr->info.name.original);
14009  if (att != NULL)
14010  {
14011  dom = att->domain;
14012  }
14013  }
14014 
14015  /* Note: it is possible that class is not found. i.e. 'select PERCENT_RANK(null,3) within group (order by
14016  * score,score1) from (select NULL score,'00001' score1 from db_root) S;' We just let it go if an attribute
14017  * could not be found. */
14018 
14019  /* for common values */
14020  if (arg->node_type == PT_VALUE && dom != NULL)
14021  {
14022  value = &arg->info.value.db_value;
14023  error = db_value_coerce (value, value, dom);
14024  if (error != NO_ERROR)
14025  {
14026  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CANT_COERCE_TO,
14027  pt_short_print (parser, arg), pt_show_type_enum (order_expr->type_enum));
14028  goto error_exit;
14029  }
14030  }
14031  }
14032 
14033  /* to next */
14034  order->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.pos_no = i + 1;
14035  arg = arg->next;
14036  order = order->next;
14037  }
14038 
14039 error_exit:
14040 
14041  return error;
14042 }
14043 
14044 
14045 /*
14046  * pt_has_parameters () - check if a statement uses session variables
14047  * return : true if the statement uses session variables
14048  * parser (in) : parser context
14049  * stmt (in) : statement
14050  */
14051 static bool
14052 pt_has_parameters (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt)
14053 {
14054  bool has_paramenters = false;
14055 
14056  parser_walk_tree (parser, stmt, pt_is_parameter_node, &has_paramenters, NULL, NULL);
14057 
14058  return has_paramenters;
14059 }
14060 
14061 /*
14062  * pt_is_parameter_node () - check if a node is a session variable
14063  * return : node
14064  * parser (in) : parser context
14065  * node (in) : node
14066  * arg (in) :
14067  * continue_walk (in) :
14068  */
14069 static PT_NODE *
14070 pt_is_parameter_node (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
14071 {
14072  bool *is_parameter = (bool *) arg;
14073  *continue_walk = PT_CONTINUE_WALK;
14074 
14075  if (*is_parameter)
14076  {
14077  /* stop checking, there already is a parameter in the statement */
14078  return node;
14079  }
14080 
14081  if (node->node_type == PT_EXPR)
14082  {
14083  if (node->info.expr.op == PT_EVALUATE_VARIABLE || node->info.expr.op == PT_DEFINE_VARIABLE)
14084  {
14085  *is_parameter = true;
14086  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
14087  }
14088  }
14089 
14090  return node;
14091 }
14092 
14093 /*
14094  * pt_resolve_sort_spec_expr - resolves a sort spec expression
14095  * returns: parser node or NULL on error
14096  * sort_spec(in): PT_SORT_SPEC node whose expression must be resolved
14097  * select_list(in): statement's select list for PT_VALUE lookup
14098  */
14099 static PT_NODE *
14100 pt_resolve_sort_spec_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * sort_spec, PT_NODE * select_list)
14101 {
14102  PT_NODE *expr, *resolved;
14103 
14104  if (parser == NULL || sort_spec == NULL)
14105  {
14106  /* nothing to do */
14107  return NULL;
14108  }
14109 
14110  if (sort_spec->node_type != PT_SORT_SPEC)
14111  {
14112  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "expecting a sort spec");
14113  return NULL;
14114  }
14115 
14116  expr = sort_spec->info.sort_spec.expr;
14117  if (expr == NULL)
14118  {
14119  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "null sort expression");
14120  return NULL;
14121  }
14122 
14123  if (expr->node_type == PT_EXPR && expr->info.expr.op == PT_UNARY_MINUS)
14124  {
14125  PT_ERRORm (parser, sort_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_WANT_NUM);
14126  return NULL;
14127  }
14128  else if (expr->node_type != PT_VALUE)
14129  {
14130  return expr;
14131  }
14132 
14133  /* we have a PT_VALUE sort expression; look it up in select list */
14134  if (expr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_INTEGER)
14135  {
14136  int index = expr->info.value.data_value.i;
14137  resolved = pt_get_node_from_list (select_list, index - 1);
14138 
14139  if (resolved != NULL)
14140  {
14141  return resolved;
14142  }
14143  else
14144  {
14145  PT_ERRORmf (parser, sort_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_RANGE_ERR, index);
14146  return NULL;
14147  }
14148  }
14149  else
14150  {
14151  PT_ERRORm (parser, sort_spec, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_SPEC_WANT_NUM);
14152  return NULL;
14153  }
14154 }
14155 
14156 /*
14157  * pt_compare_sort_spec_expr - compare two sort expressions
14158  * returns: true if expressions are the same, false otherwise
14159  * expr1(in): first expression
14160  * expr2(in): second expression
14161  */
14162 static bool
14163 pt_compare_sort_spec_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * expr1, PT_NODE * expr2)
14164 {
14165  if (parser == NULL || expr1 == NULL || expr2 == NULL)
14166  {
14167  return false;
14168  }
14169 
14170  if ((expr1->node_type == PT_NAME || expr1->node_type == PT_DOT_)
14171  && (expr2->node_type == PT_NAME || expr2->node_type == PT_DOT_))
14172  {
14173  /* we have comparable names */
14174  if (pt_check_path_eq (parser, expr1, expr2) == 0)
14175  {
14176  /* name match */
14177  return true;
14178  }
14179  }
14180  else
14181  {
14182  /* brute method, compare printed trees */
14183  char *str_expr = parser_print_tree (parser, expr1);
14184  char *str_spec_expr = parser_print_tree (parser, expr2);
14185 
14186  if (pt_str_compare (str_expr, str_spec_expr, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
14187  {
14188  /* match */
14189  return true;
14190  }
14191  }
14192 
14193  /* no match */
14194  return false;
14195 }
14196 
14197 /*
14198  * pt_find_matching_sort_spec - find a matching sort spec in a spec list
14199  * return: match or NULL
14200  * parser(in): parser context
14201  * spec(in): sort spec to look for
14202  * spec_list(in): sort spec list to look into
14203  * select_list(in): statement's select list, for PT_VALUE lookup
14204  */
14205 static PT_NODE *
14206 pt_find_matching_sort_spec (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * spec, PT_NODE * spec_list, PT_NODE * select_list)
14207 {
14208  PT_NODE *spec_expr, *expr;
14209 
14210  if (parser == NULL || spec == NULL || spec_list == NULL)
14211  {
14212  /* nothing to do here */
14213  return NULL;
14214  }
14215 
14216  /* fetch sort expression */
14217  spec_expr = pt_resolve_sort_spec_expr (parser, spec, select_list);
14218  if (spec_expr == NULL)
14219  {
14220  return NULL;
14221  }
14222 
14223  /* iterate list and check for match */
14224  while (spec_list)
14225  {
14226  /* fetch sort expression */
14227  expr = pt_resolve_sort_spec_expr (parser, spec_list, select_list);
14228  if (expr == NULL)
14229  {
14230  return NULL;
14231  }
14232 
14233  /* compare */
14234  if (pt_compare_sort_spec_expr (parser, expr, spec_expr))
14235  {
14236  /* found match */
14237  return spec_list;
14238  }
14239 
14240  /* advance */
14241  spec_list = spec_list->next;
14242  }
14243 
14244  /* nothing was found */
14245  return NULL;
14246 }
14247 
14248 /*
14249  * pt_remove_unusable_sort_specs () - remove unusable sort specs
14250  * return: new list, after filtering sort specs
14251  * parser(in): parser context
14252  * list(in): spec list
14253  * Note:
14254  * This call remove useless sort specs like NULL and constant expressions
14255  * (e.g.: order by null, order by 1 + 5, etc)
14256  */
14257 static PT_NODE *
14258 pt_remove_unusable_sort_specs (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * list)
14259 {
14260  PT_NODE *item, *expr, *save_next;
14261 
14262  /* check nulls */
14263  if (parser == NULL)
14264  {
14265  assert (false);
14266  return NULL;
14267  }
14268 
14269  if (list == NULL)
14270  {
14271  return NULL;
14272  }
14273 
14274  /* remove nulls */
14275  item = list;
14276  list = NULL;
14277  while (item)
14278  {
14279  /* unlink */
14280  save_next = item->next;
14281  item->next = NULL;
14282 
14283  if (item->node_type != PT_SORT_SPEC || item->info.sort_spec.expr == NULL)
14284  {
14285  assert (false);
14286  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "invalid sort spec");
14287  }
14288 
14289  expr = item->info.sort_spec.expr;
14290  if (expr->node_type == PT_VALUE && expr->type_enum == PT_TYPE_NULL)
14291  {
14292  /* NULL spec, get rid of it */
14293  parser_free_tree (parser, item);
14294  }
14295  else if (expr->node_type == PT_EXPR && pt_is_const_expr_node (expr))
14296  {
14297  /* order by constant which is not place holder, get rid of it */
14298  parser_free_tree (parser, item);
14299  }
14300  else
14301  {
14302  /* normal spec, keep it */
14303  list = parser_append_node (item, list);
14304  }
14305 
14306  /* continue */
14307  item = save_next;
14308  }
14309 
14310  /* list contains only normal specs */
14311  return list;
14312 }
14313 
14314 /*
14315  * pt_check_analytic_function () -
14316  * return:
14317  * parser(in):
14318  * func(in): Function node
14319  * arg(in): SELECT node
14320  * continue_walk(in):
14321  *
14322  */
14323 static PT_NODE *
14324 pt_check_analytic_function (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * func, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
14325 {
14326  PT_NODE *arg_list, *partition_by, *order_by, *select_list;
14327  PT_NODE *order, *query;
14328  PT_NODE *link = NULL, *order_list = NULL, *match = NULL;
14329  PT_NODE *new_order = NULL;
14330 
14331  if (func->node_type != PT_FUNCTION || !func->info.function.analytic.is_analytic)
14332  {
14333  return func;
14334  }
14335 
14336  query = (PT_NODE *) arg;
14337  if (query->node_type != PT_SELECT)
14338  {
14339  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NOT_ALLOWED_HERE,
14340  pt_short_print (parser, func));
14341  return func;
14342  }
14343 
14344  arg_list = func->info.function.arg_list;
14345  if (arg_list == NULL && func->info.function.function_type != PT_COUNT_STAR
14346  && func->info.function.function_type != PT_ROW_NUMBER && func->info.function.function_type != PT_RANK
14347  && func->info.function.function_type != PT_DENSE_RANK && func->info.function.function_type != PT_CUME_DIST
14348  && func->info.function.function_type != PT_PERCENT_RANK)
14349  {
14350  PT_ERRORmf (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_FUNCTION_NO_ARGS,
14351  pt_short_print (parser, func));
14352  return func;
14353  }
14354 
14355  /* median doesn't support over(order by ...) */
14356  if (func->info.function.function_type == PT_MEDIAN)
14357  {
14358  if (func->info.function.analytic.order_by != NULL)
14359  {
14360  PT_ERRORm (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_MEDIAN_FUNC_NOT_ALLOW_ORDER_BY);
14361  return func;
14362  }
14363  else if (!PT_IS_CONST (arg_list))
14364  {
14365  /* only sort data when arg is not constant */
14366  new_order = parser_new_node (parser, PT_SORT_SPEC);
14367  if (new_order == NULL)
14368  {
14369  PT_ERRORm (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
14370  return func;
14371  }
14372 
14373  new_order->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc = PT_ASC;
14374  new_order->info.sort_spec.nulls_first_or_last = PT_NULLS_DEFAULT;
14375  new_order->info.sort_spec.expr = parser_copy_tree (parser, arg_list);
14376  if (new_order->info.sort_spec.expr == NULL)
14377  {
14378  PT_ERRORm (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
14379  return func;
14380  }
14381 
14382  func->info.function.analytic.order_by = new_order;
14383  }
14384  }
14385 
14386  /* remove NULL specs */
14387  func->info.function.analytic.partition_by =
14388  pt_remove_unusable_sort_specs (parser, func->info.function.analytic.partition_by);
14389  func->info.function.analytic.order_by = pt_remove_unusable_sort_specs (parser, func->info.function.analytic.order_by);
14390 
14391  partition_by = func->info.function.analytic.partition_by;
14392  order_by = func->info.function.analytic.order_by;
14393  select_list = query->info.query.q.select.list;
14394 
14395  /* order_by sort direction has priority over partition_by direction */
14396  if (order_by != NULL && partition_by != NULL)
14397  {
14398  PT_NODE *part, *match;
14399 
14400  /* iterate partition_by nodes */
14401  for (part = partition_by; part; part = part->next)
14402  {
14403  /* find matching sort spec in order_by list and copy direction */
14404  match = pt_find_matching_sort_spec (parser, part, order_by, select_list);
14405 
14406  if (match != NULL)
14407  {
14408  part->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc = match->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc;
14409  part->info.sort_spec.nulls_first_or_last = match->info.sort_spec.nulls_first_or_last;
14410  }
14411  }
14412  }
14413 
14414  /* link partition and order lists together */
14415  for (link = partition_by; link && link->next; link = link->next)
14416  {
14417  ;
14418  }
14419  if (link)
14420  {
14421  order_list = partition_by;
14422  link->next = order_by;
14423  }
14424  else
14425  {
14426  order_list = order_by;
14427  }
14428 
14429  /* check for nested analytic functions */
14430  if (pt_has_analytic (parser, order_list))
14431  {
14432  PT_ERRORm (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NESTED_ANALYTIC_FUNCTIONS);
14433  goto error_exit;
14434  }
14435 
14436  /* replace names/exprs with positions in select list where possible; this also re-processes PT_VALUE sort expressions
14437  * so we can identify and reduce cases like: SELECT a, b, a, AVG(b) OVER (PARTITION BY A ORDER BY 1 asc, 3 asc) */
14438  for (order = order_list; order; order = order->next)
14439  {
14440  PT_NODE *expr, *col, *temp;
14441  int index;
14442 
14443  /* resolve sort spec */
14444  expr = pt_resolve_sort_spec_expr (parser, order, select_list);
14445  if (expr == NULL)
14446  {
14447  goto error_exit;
14448  }
14449 
14450  /* try to match with something in the select list */
14451  for (col = select_list, index = 1; col; col = col->next, index++)
14452  {
14453  if (col->is_hidden_column)
14454  {
14455  /* skip hidden columns; they might disappear later on */
14456  continue;
14457  }
14458 
14459  if (pt_compare_sort_spec_expr (parser, expr, col))
14460  {
14461  /* found a match in select list */
14462  break;
14463  }
14464  }
14465 
14466  /* if we have a match in the select list, we can replace it on the spot; otherwise, wait for XASL generation */
14467  if (col != NULL)
14468  {
14469  PT_NODE *save_next = col->next;
14470 
14471  col->next = NULL;
14472  if (pt_has_analytic (parser, col))
14473  {
14474  col->next = save_next;
14475 
14476  /* sort expression contains analytic function */
14477  PT_ERRORm (parser, func, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NESTED_ANALYTIC_FUNCTIONS);
14478  goto error_exit;
14479  }
14480  else
14481  {
14482  col->next = save_next;
14483  }
14484 
14485  /* create a value node and replace expr with it */
14486  temp = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
14487  if (temp == NULL)
14488  {
14489  PT_ERRORm (parser, expr, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
14490  goto error_exit;
14491  }
14492  else
14493  {
14494  temp->type_enum = PT_TYPE_INTEGER;
14495  temp->info.value.data_value.i = index;
14496  (void) pt_value_to_db (parser, temp);
14497  parser_free_tree (parser, order->info.sort_spec.expr);
14498  order->info.sort_spec.expr = temp;
14499  }
14500 
14501  /* set position descriptor and resolve domain */
14502  order->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.pos_no = index;
14503  if (col->type_enum != PT_TYPE_NONE && col->type_enum != PT_TYPE_MAYBE)
14504  { /* is resolved */
14505  order->info.sort_spec.pos_descr.dom = pt_xasl_node_to_domain (parser, col);
14506  }
14507  }
14508  }
14509 
14510  /* check for duplicate entries */
14511  for (order = order_list; order; order = order->next)
14512  {
14513  PT_NODE *temp;
14514 
14515  while ((match = pt_find_matching_sort_spec (parser, order, order->next, select_list)))
14516  {
14517  if ((order->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc != match->info.sort_spec.asc_or_desc)
14518  || (pt_to_null_ordering (order) != pt_to_null_ordering (match)))
14519  {
14520  PT_ERRORmf (parser, match, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_SORT_DIR_CONFLICT,
14521  pt_short_print (parser, match));
14522  goto error_exit;
14523  }
14524  else
14525  {
14526  /* check if we are going to remove the link */
14527  if (link && match == link)
14528  {
14529  temp = order_list;
14530  while (temp->next != match)
14531  {
14532  temp = temp->next;
14533  }
14534  link = temp;
14535  }
14536 
14537  /* check if we are going to remove the first ORDER BY node */
14538  if (link && match == link->next)
14539  {
14540  /* func may be printed again by pt_find_matching_sort_spec, make sure we don't reference garbage in
14541  * order_by */
14542  func->info.function.analytic.order_by = match->next;
14543  }
14544 
14545  /* remove match */
14546  order->next = pt_remove_from_list (parser, match, order->next);
14547  }
14548  }
14549  }
14550 
14551 error_exit:
14552  /* un-link partition and order lists */
14553  if (link)
14554  {
14555  func->info.function.analytic.order_by = link->next;
14556  link->next = NULL;
14557  }
14558 
14559  return func;
14560 }
14561 
14562 /* pt_check_function_index_expr () - check if there is at most one expression
14563  * in the index definition and , if one
14564  * expression does exist, it is checked to
14565  * see if it meets the constraints of being
14566  * part of an index
14567  * return :
14568  * parser(in) : parser context
14569  * node (in) : node - PT_CREATE_INDEX
14570  */
14571 static void
14572 pt_check_function_index_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
14573 {
14574  PT_NODE *col, *rem = NULL;
14575  int fnc_cnt = 0;
14576  int i = 0;
14577 
14578  for (col = node->info.index.column_names, i = 0; col != NULL; col = col->next, i++)
14579  {
14580  if (col->info.sort_spec.expr->node_type != PT_NAME)
14581  {
14582  if (pt_is_function_index_expr (parser, col->info.sort_spec.expr, true))
14583  {
14584  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, col->info.sort_spec.expr, pt_check_function_index_expr_pre, NULL, NULL,
14585  NULL);
14586  if (pt_has_error (parser))
14587  {
14588  /* Stop. */
14589  return;
14590  }
14591  node->info.index.function_expr = parser_copy_tree (parser, col);
14592  node->info.index.func_pos = i;
14593  rem = col;
14594  }
14595  else
14596  {
14597  return;
14598  }
14599  fnc_cnt++;
14600  }
14601  }
14602  if (fnc_cnt > 1)
14603  {
14604  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_FUNCTION_INDEX);
14605  }
14606  else if (fnc_cnt > 0 && rem)
14607  {
14608  PT_NODE *list, *arg, *n;
14609  node->info.index.column_names = pt_remove_from_list (parser, rem, node->info.index.column_names);
14610  list = pt_expr_to_sort_spec (parser, node->info.index.function_expr->info.sort_spec.expr);
14611 
14612  for (arg = list; arg != NULL; arg = arg->next)
14613  {
14614  for (n = node->info.index.column_names; n != NULL; n = n->next)
14615  {
14616  if (!pt_str_compare (arg->info.sort_spec.expr->info.name.original,
14617  n->info.sort_spec.expr->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
14618  {
14619  break;
14620  }
14621  }
14622  if (n == NULL)
14623  {
14624  PT_NODE *new_node = parser_copy_tree (parser, arg);
14625  new_node->next = NULL;
14626  node->info.index.column_names = parser_append_node (new_node, node->info.index.column_names);
14627  node->info.index.func_no_args++;
14628  }
14629  }
14630  }
14631 }
14632 
14633 /*
14634  * pt_check_function_index_expr_pre () - Helper function to check function
14635  * index semantic correctness.
14636  *
14637  * return : Current node.
14638  * parser (in) : Parser context.
14639  * node (in) : Current node.
14640  * arg (in/out) : Not used.
14641  * continue_walk (in/out) : Walker argument to know when to stop advancing.
14642  */
14643 static PT_NODE *
14644 pt_check_function_index_expr_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
14645 {
14646  assert (continue_walk != NULL);
14647 
14648  if (*continue_walk == PT_STOP_WALK || node == NULL)
14649  {
14650  return node;
14651  }
14652  if (node->node_type == PT_NAME && PT_IS_LTZ_TYPE (node->type_enum))
14653  {
14654  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_LTZ_IN_FUNCTION_FILTER_INDEX);
14655  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
14656  }
14657  return node;
14658 }
14659 
14660 /*
14661  * pt_check_filter_index_expr () - verify if an expression tree is allowed
14662  * to be used in the filter expression of an
14663  * index
14664  * return : true if expression tree is valid, false otherwise
14665  * parser (in) : parser context
14666  * atts (in): an attribute definition list
14667  * node (in) : root node of expression tree
14668  * db_obj (in) : class mop
14669  */
14670 static void
14671 pt_check_filter_index_expr (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * atts, PT_NODE * node, MOP db_obj)
14672 {
14673  PT_FILTER_INDEX_INFO info;
14674  int atts_count = 0, i = 0;
14675 
14676  if (node == NULL)
14677  {
14678  /* null node; nothing to check */
14679  return;
14680  }
14681 
14682  info.atts = atts;
14683  while (atts)
14684  {
14685  atts_count++;
14686  atts = atts->next;
14687  }
14688 
14689  info.atts_count = atts_count;
14690  info.is_null_atts = (bool *) malloc (atts_count * sizeof (bool));
14691  if (info.is_null_atts == NULL)
14692  {
14693  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
14694  return;
14695  }
14696  for (i = 0; i < atts_count; i++)
14697  {
14698  info.is_null_atts[i] = false;
14699  }
14700  info.is_valid_expr = true;
14701  info.is_constant_expression = true;
14702  info.has_keys_in_expression = false;
14703  info.depth = 0;
14704  info.has_not = false;
14705 
14706  (void) parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_check_filter_index_expr_pre, &info, pt_check_filter_index_expr_post, &info);
14707 
14708  /* at least one key must be contained in filter expression (without IS_NULL operator, or variations like "not a is
14709  * not null") or at least one key must be not null constrained */
14710  if (info.is_valid_expr == true && info.is_constant_expression == false && info.has_keys_in_expression == false)
14711  {
14712  PT_NODE *attr = NULL, *p_nam = NULL;
14713  SM_CLASS *smclass = NULL;
14714  SM_ATTRIBUTE *smatt = NULL;
14715  int i;
14716  bool has_not_null_constraint;
14717 
14718  /* search for null constraints */
14719  i = 0;
14720  has_not_null_constraint = false;
14721  for (attr = info.atts; attr != NULL && has_not_null_constraint == false; attr = attr->next, i++)
14722  {
14723  if (attr->node_type == PT_SORT_SPEC)
14724  {
14725  p_nam = attr->info.sort_spec.expr;
14726  }
14727  else if (attr->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
14728  {
14729  p_nam = attr->info.attr_def.attr_name;
14730  }
14731 
14732  if (p_nam == NULL || p_nam->node_type != PT_NAME)
14733  {
14734  continue; /* give up */
14735  }
14736 
14737  if (smclass == NULL)
14738  {
14739  assert (db_obj != NULL);
14740  if (au_fetch_class (db_obj, &smclass, AU_FETCH_READ, AU_SELECT) != NO_ERROR)
14741  {
14742  info.is_valid_expr = false;
14743  break;
14744  }
14745  }
14746 
14747  for (smatt = smclass->attributes; smatt != NULL; smatt = (SM_ATTRIBUTE *) smatt->header.next)
14748  {
14749  if (SM_COMPARE_NAMES (smatt->header.name, p_nam->info.name.original) == 0)
14750  {
14751  if (db_attribute_is_non_null (smatt))
14752  {
14753  has_not_null_constraint = true;
14754  }
14755  break;
14756  }
14757  }
14758  }
14759 
14760  if (has_not_null_constraint == false)
14761  {
14762  info.is_valid_expr = false;
14763  }
14764  }
14765  if (info.is_valid_expr == false)
14766  {
14767  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_FILTER_INDEX,
14768  pt_short_print (parser, node));
14769  }
14770 
14771  if (info.is_null_atts)
14772  {
14773  free_and_init (info.is_null_atts);
14774  }
14775 }
14776 
14777 /*
14778  * pt_check_filter_index_expr_post ()
14779  *
14780  * return : current node
14781  * parser (in) : parser context
14782  * node (in) : node
14783  * arg (in/out) : (is_valid_expr, expression depth)
14784  * continue_walk (in) : continue walk
14785  */
14786 static PT_NODE *
14787 pt_check_filter_index_expr_post (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
14788 {
14789  PT_FILTER_INDEX_INFO *info = (PT_FILTER_INDEX_INFO *) arg;
14790  assert (info != NULL);
14791 
14792  switch (node->node_type)
14793  {
14794  case PT_EXPR:
14795  info->depth--;
14796  switch (node->info.expr.op)
14797  {
14798  case PT_NOT:
14799  info->has_not = !(info->has_not);
14800  break;
14801 
14802  default:
14803  break;
14804  }
14805  break;
14806 
14807  case PT_FUNCTION:
14808  info->depth--;
14809  break;
14810 
14811  default:
14812  break;
14813  }
14814 
14815  return node;
14816 }
14817 
14818 /*
14819  * pt_check_filter_index_expr () - verify if a node is allowed to be used
14820  * in the filter expression of an index
14821  * return : current node
14822  * parser (in) : parser context
14823  * node (in) : node
14824  * arg (in/out) : PT_FILTER_INDEX_INFO *
14825  * continue_walk (in) : continue walk
14826  */
14827 static PT_NODE *
14828 pt_check_filter_index_expr_pre (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
14829 {

14831  assert (info != NULL);
14832 
14833  if (node == NULL || info->is_valid_expr == false)
14834  {
14835  return node;

14839  switch (node->node_type)

14841  case PT_EXPR:

14844  switch (node->info.expr.op)

14846  case PT_AND:

14848  case PT_NOT_BETWEEN:

14851  case PT_IS_IN:

14860  case PT_LE_SOME:
14861  case PT_EQ_ALL:
14862  case PT_NE_ALL:
14863  case PT_GE_ALL:
14864  case PT_GT_ALL:
14865  case PT_LT_ALL:
14866  case PT_LE_ALL:
14867  case PT_EQ:
14868  case PT_NE:
14869  case PT_GE:
14870  case PT_GT:
14871  case PT_LT:
14872  case PT_LE:
14873  case PT_NULLSAFE_EQ:
14874  case PT_PLUS:
14875  case PT_MINUS:
14876  case PT_TIMES:

14878  case PT_UNARY_MINUS:

14883  case PT_BIT_COUNT:
14884  case PT_BITSHIFT_LEFT:
14885  case PT_BITSHIFT_RIGHT:
14886  case PT_DIV:
14887  case PT_MOD:
14888  case PT_XOR:
14889  case PT_BETWEEN_AND:
14890  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LE:
14891  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_LT:
14892  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LE:
14893  case PT_BETWEEN_GT_LT:
14894  case PT_BETWEEN_EQ_NA:
14895  case PT_BETWEEN_INF_LE:
14896  case PT_BETWEEN_INF_LT:
14897  case PT_BETWEEN_GE_INF:

14899  case PT_RANGE:
14900  case PT_MODULUS:

14902  case PT_SUBSTRING:
14903  case PT_OCTET_LENGTH:
14904  case PT_BIT_LENGTH:
14905  case PT_SUBSTRING_INDEX:

14916  case PT_TRANSLATE:
14917  case PT_REPEAT:

14951  case PT_LOCATE:

14960  case PT_SIN:

14963  case PT_DEGREES:
14964  case PT_RADIANS:
14965  case PT_PI:
14966  case PT_FORMAT:
14967  case PT_LN:
14968  case PT_LOG2:
14969  case PT_LOG10:
14970  case PT_TIME_FORMAT:
14971  case PT_TIMESTAMP:
14972  case PT_FROM_UNIXTIME:
14973  case PT_ADDDATE:
14974  case PT_DATE_ADD:
14975  case PT_SUBDATE:
14976  case PT_DATE_SUB:
14977  case PT_DATE_FORMAT:
14978  case PT_DATEF:
14979  case PT_TIMEF:
14980  case PT_YEARF:
14981  case PT_MONTHF:
14982  case PT_DAYF:
14983  case PT_HOURF:
14984  case PT_MINUTEF:
14985  case PT_SECONDF:
14986  case PT_DAYOFMONTH:
14987  case PT_WEEKDAY:
14988  case PT_DAYOFWEEK:
14989  case PT_DAYOFYEAR:
14990  case PT_QUARTERF:
14991  case PT_TODAYS:
14992  case PT_FROMDAYS:
14993  case PT_TIMETOSEC:
14994  case PT_SECTOTIME:
14995  case PT_MAKEDATE:
14996  case PT_MAKETIME:
14997  case PT_WEEKF:
14998  case PT_USER:
14999  case PT_DATEDIFF:
15000  case PT_TIMEDIFF:
15001  case PT_STR_TO_DATE:
15002  case PT_DEFAULTF:
15003  case PT_LIKE_LOWER_BOUND:
15004  case PT_LIKE_UPPER_BOUND:
15005  case PT_BLOB_LENGTH:
15006  case PT_BLOB_TO_BIT:
15007  case PT_CLOB_LENGTH:
15008  case PT_CLOB_TO_CHAR:
15009  case PT_RLIKE:
15010  case PT_RLIKE_BINARY:
15011  case PT_NOT_RLIKE:
15012  case PT_NOT_RLIKE_BINARY:
15013  case PT_HEX:
15014  case PT_ADDTIME:
15015  case PT_ASCII:
15016  case PT_CONV:
15017  case PT_BIN:
15018  case PT_FINDINSET:
15019  case PT_INET_ATON:
15020  case PT_INET_NTOA:
15021  case PT_TZ_OFFSET:
15022  case PT_NEW_TIME:
15023  case PT_FROM_TZ:
15024  case PT_TO_DATETIME_TZ:
15025  case PT_TO_TIMESTAMP_TZ:
15026  case PT_CONV_TZ:
15027  /* valid expression, nothing to do */
15028  break;
15029  case PT_NOT:
15030  info->has_not = !(info->has_not);
15031  break;
15032  case PT_IS_NULL:
15033  case PT_IS_NOT_NULL:
15034  {
15035  PT_NODE *attr = NULL, *p_nam = NULL;
15036  PT_NODE *arg1 = NULL;
15037  int i = 0, j = 0;
15038 
15039  if (node->info.expr.op == PT_IS_NULL)
15040  {
15041  if (info->has_not == true)
15042  {
15043  /* not expression is null case */
15044  break;
15045  }
15046  }
15047  else if (info->has_not == false)
15048  {
15049  /* expression is not null case */
15050  break;
15051  }
15052 
15053  arg1 = node->info.expr.arg1;
15054  if (arg1 == NULL || info->atts == NULL)
15055  {
15056  break;
15057  }
15058 
15059  if (arg1->node_type != PT_NAME)
15060  {
15061  /* do not allow expression is null do not allow not expression is not null */
15062  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15063 
15064  break;
15065  }
15066 
15067  /* arg1 is PT_NAME node */
15068  if (arg1->info.name.original == NULL)
15069  {
15070  break;
15071  }
15072 
15073  i = 0;
15074  for (attr = info->atts; attr != NULL; attr = attr->next, i++)
15075  {
15076  if (attr->node_type == PT_SORT_SPEC)
15077  {
15078  p_nam = attr->info.sort_spec.expr;
15079  }
15080  else if (attr->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
15081  {
15082  p_nam = attr->info.attr_def.attr_name;
15083  }
15084 
15085  if (p_nam == NULL || p_nam->node_type != PT_NAME)
15086  {
15087  continue; /* give up */
15088  }
15089 
15090  if (!pt_str_compare (p_nam->info.name.original, arg1->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE))
15091  {
15092  info->is_null_atts[i] = true;
15093  for (j = 0; j < info->atts_count; j++)
15094  {
15095  if (info->is_null_atts[j] == false)
15096  {
15097  break;
15098  }
15099  }
15100  if (j == info->atts_count)
15101  {
15102  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15103  }
15104 
15105  break;
15106  }
15107  }
15108  }
15109  break;
15110 
15111  case PT_FUNCTION_HOLDER:
15112  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
15113  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_FUNCTION_CANNOT_BE_USED_FOR_FILTER_INDEX,
15114  pt_show_function (node->info.expr.arg1->info.function.function_type));
15115  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15116  break;
15117 
15118  default:
15119  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
15120  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_FUNCTION_CANNOT_BE_USED_FOR_FILTER_INDEX, pt_show_binopcode (node->info.expr.op));
15121  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15122  break;
15123  }
15124  break;
15125 
15126  case PT_FUNCTION:
15127  info->depth++;
15128  /* do not allow aggregates and analytic functions */
15129  switch (node->info.function.function_type)
15130  {
15131  case F_SET:
15132  case F_MULTISET:
15133  case F_SEQUENCE:
15134  /* the functions above are used in the argument IN (values list) expression */
15135  case F_ELT:
15136  case F_INSERT_SUBSTRING:
15137  case F_JSON_OBJECT:
15138  case F_JSON_ARRAY:
15139  case F_JSON_INSERT:
15140  case F_JSON_REPLACE:
15141  case F_JSON_SET:
15142  case F_JSON_KEYS:
15143  case F_JSON_REMOVE:
15144  case F_JSON_ARRAY_APPEND:
15145  case F_JSON_MERGE:
15146  case F_JSON_GET_ALL_PATHS:
15147  /* valid expression, nothing to do */
15148  break;
15149  default:
15150  PT_ERRORmf (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC,
15151  MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_FUNCTION_CANNOT_BE_USED_FOR_FILTER_INDEX,
15152  pt_show_function (node->info.function.function_type));
15153  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15154  break;
15155  }
15156  break;
15157 
15158  case PT_NAME:
15159  /* only allow attribute names */
15160  info->is_constant_expression = false;
15161  if (node->info.name.meta_class != PT_META_ATTR && node->info.name.meta_class != PT_NORMAL)
15162  {
15163  /* valid expression, nothing to do */
15164  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15165  }
15166  else if (PT_IS_LTZ_TYPE (node->type_enum))
15167  {
15168  PT_ERRORm (parser, node, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NO_LTZ_IN_FUNCTION_FILTER_INDEX);
15169  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15170  }
15171  else if (info->has_keys_in_expression == false)
15172  {
15173  PT_NODE *attr = NULL, *p_nam = NULL;
15174  int i;
15175  i = 0;
15176  for (attr = info->atts; attr != NULL; attr = attr->next, i++)
15177  {
15178  if (attr->node_type == PT_SORT_SPEC)
15179  {
15180  p_nam = attr->info.sort_spec.expr;
15181  }
15182  else if (attr->node_type == PT_ATTR_DEF)
15183  {
15184  p_nam = attr->info.attr_def.attr_name;
15185  }
15186 
15187  if (p_nam == NULL || p_nam->node_type != PT_NAME)
15188  {
15189  continue; /* give up */
15190  }
15191 
15192  if ((pt_str_compare (p_nam->info.name.original, node->info.name.original, CASE_INSENSITIVE) == 0)
15193  && (info->is_null_atts[i] == 0))
15194  {
15195  info->has_keys_in_expression = true;
15196  break;
15197  }
15198  }
15199  }
15200  break;
15201 
15202  case PT_VALUE:
15203  if (info->depth == 0)
15204  {
15205  if (node->info.value.db_value_is_initialized && DB_VALUE_TYPE (&node->info.value.db_value) == DB_TYPE_INTEGER)
15206  {
15207  if (db_get_int (&node->info.value.db_value) == 0)
15208  {
15209  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15210  }
15211  }
15212  }
15213  break;
15214  case PT_DATA_TYPE:
15215  /* valid expression, nothing to do */
15216  break;
15217 
15218  default:
15219  info->is_valid_expr = false;
15220  break;
15221  }
15222 
15223  if (info->is_valid_expr == false)
15224  {
15225  *continue_walk = PT_STOP_WALK;
15226  }
15227 
15228  return node;
15229 }
15230 
15231 /*
15232  * pt_get_assignments () - get assignment list for INSERT/UPDATE/MERGE
15233  * statements
15234  * return : assignment list or NULL
15235  * node (in): statement node
15236  */
15237 static PT_NODE *
15238 pt_get_assignments (PT_NODE * node)
15239 {
15240  if (node == NULL)
15241  {
15242  return NULL;
15243  }
15244 
15245  switch (node->node_type)
15246  {
15247  case PT_UPDATE:
15248  return node->info.update.assignment;
15249  case PT_MERGE:
15250  return node->info.merge.update.assignment;
15251  case PT_INSERT:
15252  return node->info.insert.odku_assignments;
15253  default:
15254  return NULL;
15255  }
15256 }
15257 
15258 /*
15259  * pt_check_odku_assignments () - check ON DUPLICATE KEY assignments of an
15260  * INSERT statement
15261  * return : node
15262  * parser (in) : parser context
15263  * insert (in) : insert statement
15264  *
15265  * Note: this function performs the following validations:
15266  * - there are no double assignments
15267  * - assignments are only performed to columns belonging to the insert spec
15268  * - only instance attributes are updated
15269  */
15270 PT_NODE *
15271 pt_check_odku_assignments (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * insert)
15272 {
15273  PT_NODE *assignment, *spec, *lhs;
15274  if (insert == NULL || insert->node_type != PT_INSERT)
15275  {
15276  return insert;
15277  }
15278 
15279  if (insert->info.insert.odku_assignments == NULL)
15280  {
15281  return insert;
15282  }
15283 
15284  pt_no_double_updates (parser, insert);
15285  if (pt_has_error (parser))
15286  {
15287  return NULL;
15288  }
15289  pt_check_assignments (parser, insert);
15290  if (pt_has_error (parser))
15291  {
15292  return NULL;
15293  }
15294 
15295  spec = insert->info.insert.spec;
15296  for (assignment = insert->info.insert.odku_assignments; assignment != NULL; assignment = assignment->next)
15297  {
15298  if (assignment->node_type != PT_EXPR || assignment->info.expr.op != PT_ASSIGN)
15299  {
15300  assert (false);
15301  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "semantic");
15302  return NULL;
15303  }
15304  lhs = assignment->info.expr.arg1;
15305  if (lhs == NULL || lhs->node_type != PT_NAME)
15306  {
15307  assert (false);
15308  PT_INTERNAL_ERROR (parser, "semantic");
15309  return NULL;
15310  }
15311  if (lhs->info.name.spec_id != spec->info.spec.id)
15312  {
15313  PT_ERRORm (parser, lhs, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_ILLEGAL_LHS);
15314  return NULL;
15315  }
15316  }
15317  return insert;
15318 }
15319 
15320 /*
15321  * pt_check_vacuum () - Check VACUUM statement.
15322  *
15323  * return : Void.
15324  * parser (in) : Parser context.
15325  * node (in) : VACUUM parse tree node.
15326  */
15327 static void
15328 pt_check_vacuum (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
15329 {
15330  PT_FLAT_SPEC_INFO info;
15331 
15332  assert (parser != NULL);
15333  if (!PT_IS_VACUUM_NODE (node))
15334  {
15335  /* Not the scope of this function */
15336  return;
15337  }
15338 
15339  info.spec_parent = NULL;
15340  info.for_update = false;
15341  /* Replace each Entity Spec with an Equivalent flat list */
15342  parser_walk_tree (parser, node, pt_flat_spec_pre, &info, pt_continue_walk, NULL);
15343 }
15344 
15345 /*
15346  * pt_get_select_list_coll_compat () - scans a UNION parse tree and retains
15347  * for each column with collation the node
15348  * (and its compatibility info) having the
15349  * least (collation) coercible level
15350  *
15351  * return: compatibility status
15352  * parser(in): the parser context
15353  * query(in): query node
15354  * cinfo(in/out): compatibility info array structure
15355  * num_cinfo(in): number of elements in cinfo
15356  */
15357 static PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE
15358 pt_get_select_list_coll_compat (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo, int num_cinfo)
15359 {
15360  PT_NODE *attrs, *att;
15361  int i;
15362  PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE status = PT_UNION_COMP, status2;
15363 
15364  assert (query != NULL);
15365 
15366  switch (query->node_type)
15367  {
15368  case PT_SELECT:
15369 
15370  attrs = pt_get_select_list (parser, query);
15371 
15372  for (att = attrs, i = 0; i < num_cinfo && att != NULL; ++i, att = att->next)
15373  {
15374  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO cinfo_att;
15375 
15376  if (!PT_HAS_COLLATION (att->type_enum))
15377  {
15378  continue;
15379  }
15380 
15381  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (att, &cinfo_att);
15382 
15383  if (cinfo[i].type_enum == PT_TYPE_NONE)
15384  {
15385  /* first query, init this column */
15386  memcpy (&(cinfo[i]), &cinfo_att, sizeof (cinfo_att));
15387  }
15388  else if (cinfo_att.coll_infer.coerc_level < cinfo[i].coll_infer.coerc_level)
15389  {
15390  assert (PT_HAS_COLLATION (cinfo[i].type_enum));
15391 
15392  memcpy (&(cinfo[i].coll_infer), &(cinfo_att.coll_infer), sizeof (cinfo_att.coll_infer));
15393  cinfo[i].ref_att = att;
15394  status = PT_UNION_INCOMP;
15395  }
15396  else if (cinfo_att.coll_infer.coll_id != cinfo[i].coll_infer.coll_id)
15397  {
15398  status = PT_UNION_INCOMP;
15399  }
15400  }
15401  break;
15402  case PT_UNION:
15403  case PT_INTERSECTION:
15404  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
15405  status = pt_get_select_list_coll_compat (parser, query->info.query.q.union_.arg1, cinfo, num_cinfo);
15406 
15407  if (status != PT_UNION_COMP && status != PT_UNION_INCOMP)
15408  {
15409  break;
15410  }
15411 
15412  status2 = pt_get_select_list_coll_compat (parser, query->info.query.q.union_.arg2, cinfo, num_cinfo);
15413  if (status2 != PT_UNION_COMP)
15414  {
15415  status = status2;
15416  }
15417  break;
15418  default:
15419  break;
15420  }
15421 
15422  return status;
15423 }
15424 
15425 /*
15426  * pt_apply_union_select_list_collation () - scans a UNION parse tree and
15427  * sets for each node with collation the collation corresponding
15428  * of the column in 'cinfo' array
15429  *
15430  * return: union compatibility status
15431  * parser(in): the parser context
15432  * query(in): query node
15433  * cinfo(in): compatibility info array structure
15434  * num_cinfo(in): number of elements in cinfo
15435  */
15436 static PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE
15437 pt_apply_union_select_list_collation (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query, SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO * cinfo,
15438  int num_cinfo)
15439 {
15440  PT_NODE *attrs, *att, *prev_att, *next_att, *new_att;
15441  int i;
15442  PT_UNION_COMPATIBLE status = PT_UNION_COMP, status2;
15443 
15444  assert (query != NULL);
15445 
15446  switch (query->node_type)
15447  {
15448  case PT_SELECT:
15449 
15450  attrs = pt_get_select_list (parser, query);
15451 
15452  prev_att = NULL;
15453  next_att = NULL;
15454 
15455  for (att = attrs, i = 0; i < num_cinfo && att != NULL; ++i, prev_att = att, att = next_att)
15456  {
15457  SEMAN_COMPATIBLE_INFO cinfo_att;
15458 
15459  next_att = att->next;
15460 
15461  if (!PT_HAS_COLLATION (att->type_enum))
15462  {
15463  continue;
15464  }
15465 
15466  assert (PT_HAS_COLLATION (cinfo[i].type_enum));
15467 
15468  pt_get_compatible_info_from_node (att, &cinfo_att);
15469 
15470  if (cinfo_att.coll_infer.coll_id != cinfo[i].coll_infer.coll_id)
15471  {
15472  bool new_cast_added = false;
15473 
15474  if (pt_common_collation (&cinfo_att.coll_infer, &(cinfo[i].coll_infer), NULL, 2, false,
15475  &cinfo_att.coll_infer.coll_id, &cinfo_att.coll_infer.codeset) != 0)
15476  {
15477  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNION_INCOMPATIBLE,
15478  pt_short_print (parser, att), pt_short_print (parser, cinfo[i].ref_att));
15479  return PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX;
15480  }
15481 
15482  new_att = pt_make_cast_with_compatible_info (parser, att, next_att, &cinfo_att, &new_cast_added);
15483  if (new_att == NULL)
15484  {
15485  PT_ERRORmf2 (parser, att, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_UNION_INCOMPATIBLE,
15486  pt_short_print (parser, att), pt_short_print (parser, cinfo[i].ref_att));
15487  return PT_UNION_INCOMP_CANNOT_FIX;
15488  }
15489 
15490  att = new_att;
15491 
15492  if (new_cast_added)
15493  {
15494  if (prev_att == NULL)
15495  {
15496  query->info.query.q.select.list = att;
15497  query->type_enum = att->type_enum;
15498  if (query->data_type)
15499  {
15500  parser_free_tree (parser, query->data_type);
15501  }
15502 
15503  query->data_type = parser_copy_tree_list (parser, att->data_type);
15504  }
15505  else
15506  {
15507  prev_att->next = att;
15508  }
15509  }
15510 
15511  status = PT_UNION_INCOMP;
15512  }
15513  }
15514  break;
15515  case PT_UNION:
15516  case PT_INTERSECTION:
15517  case PT_DIFFERENCE:
15518  status = pt_apply_union_select_list_collation (parser, query->info.query.q.union_.arg1, cinfo, num_cinfo);
15519  if (status != PT_UNION_COMP && status != PT_UNION_INCOMP)
15520  {
15521  return status;
15522  }
15523 
15524  status2 = pt_apply_union_select_list_collation (parser, query->info.query.q.union_.arg2, cinfo, num_cinfo);
15525 
15526  if (status2 != PT_UNION_COMP && status2 != PT_UNION_INCOMP)
15527  {
15528  return status;
15529  }
15530 
15531  if (status2 != PT_UNION_COMP)
15532  {
15533  status = status2;
15534  }
15535 
15536  if (status == PT_UNION_INCOMP)
15537  {
15538  if (query->data_type != NULL)
15539  {
15540  parser_free_tree (parser, query->data_type);
15541  }
15542 
15543  query->data_type = parser_copy_tree (parser, query->info.query.q.union_.arg1->data_type);
15544  }
15545  break;
15546  default:
15547  break;
15548  }
15549 
15550  return status;
15551 }
15552 
15553 /*
15554  * pt_mark_union_leaf_nodes () - walking function for setting for each UNION
15555  * DIFFERENCE/INTERSECTION query if it is a root
15556  * of a leaf node.
15557  * return:
15558  * parser(in):
15559  * node(in):
15560  * arg(in):
15561  * continue_walk(in/out):
15562  */
15563 static PT_NODE *
15564 pt_mark_union_leaf_nodes (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node, void *arg, int *continue_walk)
15565 {
15566  if (PT_IS_UNION (node) || PT_IS_INTERSECTION (node) || PT_IS_DIFFERENCE (node))
15567  {
15568  PT_NODE *arg;
15569 
15570  arg = node->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
15571  if (PT_IS_UNION (arg) || PT_IS_INTERSECTION (arg) || PT_IS_DIFFERENCE (arg))
15572  {
15573  arg->info.query.q.union_.is_leaf_node = 1;
15574  }
15575 
15576  arg = node->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
15577  if (PT_IS_UNION (arg) || PT_IS_INTERSECTION (arg) || PT_IS_DIFFERENCE (arg))
15578  {
15579  arg->info.query.q.union_.is_leaf_node = 1;
15580  }
15581  }
15582 
15583  return node;
15584 }

15586 /*
15587  * pt_check_where () - do semantic checks on a node's where clause
15588  * return:
15589  * parser(in): the parser context
15590  * node(in): the node to check
15591  */
15592 static PT_NODE *
15593 pt_check_where (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * node)
15594 {
15595  PT_NODE *function = NULL;
15596 
15597  /* check if exists aggregate/analytic functions in where clause */
15598  function = pt_find_aggregate_analytic_in_where (parser, node);
15599  if (function != NULL)
15600  {
15601  if (pt_is_aggregate_function (parser, function))
15602  {
15603  PT_ERRORm (parser, function, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_INVALID_AGGREGATE);
15604  }
15605  else
15606  {
15607  PT_ERRORm (parser, function, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_NESTED_ANALYTIC_FUNCTIONS);
15608  }
15609  }
15610 
15611  return node;
15612 }
15613 
15614 /*
15615  * pt_check_range_partition_strict_increasing () -
15616  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
15617  * parser(in): the parser context
15618  * stmt(in): the top statement
15619  * part(in): current partition
15620  * part_next(in): the next partition
15621  * column_dt(in): data type
15622  *
15623  */
15624 static int
15625 pt_check_range_partition_strict_increasing (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * stmt, PT_NODE * part,
15626  PT_NODE * part_next, PT_NODE * column_dt)
15627 {
15628  int error = NO_ERROR;
15629  PT_NODE *pt_val1 = NULL, *pt_val2 = NULL;
15630  DB_VALUE *db_val1 = NULL, *db_val2 = NULL;
15631  DB_VALUE null_val;
15632  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT compare_result;
15633 
15634  assert (parser != NULL && stmt != NULL && part != NULL && part->node_type == PT_PARTS);
15635  assert (part_next == NULL || part_next->node_type == PT_PARTS);
15636  assert (column_dt == NULL || column_dt->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE);
15637 
15638  /* make sure value1 is the same type described by column_dt */
15639  pt_val1 = part->info.parts.values;
15640  assert (pt_val1 == NULL || column_dt == NULL
15641  || (pt_val1->type_enum == column_dt->type_enum
15642  && (!PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (pt_val1->type_enum)
15643  || (pt_val1->data_type == NULL
15644  || (pt_val1->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id ==
15645  column_dt->info.data_type.collation_id)))));
15646 
15647  db_make_null (&null_val);
15648 
15649  /* next value */
15650  if (part_next != NULL)
15651  {
15652  /* the first value */
15653  db_val1 = pt_value_to_db (parser, pt_val1);
15654  if (db_val1 == NULL)
15655  {
15656  if (pt_has_error (parser))
15657  {
15658  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_RANGE_INVALID;
15659 
15660  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, part->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
15661 
15662  goto end;
15663  }
15664 
15665  db_val1 = &null_val;
15666  }
15667 
15668  pt_val2 = part_next->info.parts.values;
15669 
15670  /* if column_dt is not null, do the cast if needed */
15671  if (pt_val2 != NULL && column_dt != NULL)
15672  {
15673  error = pt_coerce_partition_value_with_data_type (parser, pt_val2, column_dt);
15674 
15675  if (error != NO_ERROR)
15676  {
15677  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_CONSTANT_TYPE_MISMATCH;
15678 
15679  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error,
15680  part_next->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
15681 
15682  goto end;
15683  }
15684  }
15685 
15686  db_val2 = pt_value_to_db (parser, pt_val2);
15687  if (db_val2 == NULL)
15688  {
15689  if (pt_has_error (parser))
15690  {
15691  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_RANGE_INVALID;
15692 
15693  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error,
15694  part_next->info.parts.name->info.name.original);
15695 
15696  goto end;
15697  }
15698 
15699  db_val2 = &null_val;
15700  }
15701 
15702  /* check the strict increasing */
15703  if (DB_IS_NULL (db_val1))
15704  {
15705  /* this is an error */
15706  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_RANGE_ERROR;
15707 
15708  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, part);
15709 
15710  goto end;
15711  }
15712  else if (!DB_IS_NULL (db_val2))
15713  {
15714  compare_result = (DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT) db_value_compare (db_val1, db_val2);
15715  if (compare_result != DB_LT)
15716  {
15717  /* this is an error */
15718  error = MSGCAT_SEMANTIC_PARTITION_RANGE_ERROR;
15719 
15720  PT_ERRORmf (parser, stmt, MSGCAT_SET_PARSER_SEMANTIC, error, part_next);
15721 
15722  goto end;
15723  }
15724  }
15725  }
15726 
15727 end:
15728 
15729  return error;
15730 }
15731 
15732 /*
15733  * pt_coerce_partition_value_with_data_type () - do the cast
15734  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
15735  * parser(in):
15736  * value(in):
15737  * data_type(in):
15738  *
15739  */
15740 static int
15741 pt_coerce_partition_value_with_data_type (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * value, PT_NODE * data_type)
15742 {
15743  int error = NO_ERROR;
15744 
15745  assert (value != NULL && data_type != NULL && data_type->node_type == PT_DATA_TYPE);
15746 
15747  if (value->type_enum != data_type->type_enum
15748  || (PT_IS_STRING_TYPE (value->type_enum) && value->data_type != NULL
15749  && value->data_type->info.data_type.collation_id != data_type->info.data_type.collation_id))
15750  {
15751  error = pt_coerce_value (parser, value, value, data_type->type_enum, data_type);
15752  }
15753 
15754  return error;
15755 }
15756 
15757 /*
15758  * pt_try_remove_order_by - verify and remove order_by clause after it has been decided it is unnecessary
15759  * return: void
15760  * parser(in): Parser context
15761  * query(in/out): Processed query
15762  */
15763 void
15764 pt_try_remove_order_by (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * query)
15765 {
15766  PT_NODE *col, *next;
15767 
15768  assert (PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (query->node_type));
15769 
15770  if (query->info.query.order_by == NULL || query->info.query.orderby_for != NULL || query->info.query.limit != NULL)
15771  {
15772  /* order_by can not be removed when query has orderby_for or limit */
15773  return;
15774  }
15775 
15776  /* if select list has orderby_num(), can not remove ORDER BY clause for example:
15777  * (i, j) = (select i, orderby_num() from t order by i)
15778  */
15779  for (col = pt_get_select_list (parser, query); col; col = col->next)
15780  {
15781  if (col->node_type == PT_EXPR && col->info.expr.op == PT_ORDERBY_NUM)
15782  {
15783  break; /* can not remove ORDER BY clause */
15784  }
15785  }
15786 
15787  if (!col)
15788  {
15789  /* no column is ORDERBY_NUM, order_by can be removed */
15790  parser_free_tree (parser, query->info.query.order_by);
15791  query->info.query.order_by = NULL;
15792  query->info.query.order_siblings = 0;
15793 
15794  for (col = pt_get_select_list (parser, query); col && col->next; col = next)
15795  {
15796  next = col->next;
15797  if (next->is_hidden_column)
15798  {
15799  parser_free_tree (parser, next);
15800  col->next = NULL;
15801  break;
15802  }
15803  }
15804  }
15805 }
15806 
15807 
15808 /*
15809  * pt_check_union_is_foldable - decide if union can be folded
15810  *
15811  * return : union foldability
15812  * parser(in) : Parser context.
15813  * union_node(in) : Union node.
15814  */
15815 STATEMENT_SET_FOLD
15816 pt_check_union_is_foldable (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * union_node)
15817 {
15818  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2;
15819  bool arg1_is_null, arg2_is_null;
15820  STATEMENT_SET_FOLD fold_as;
15821 
15822  assert (union_node->node_type == PT_UNION || union_node->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION
15823  || union_node->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE || union_node->node_type == PT_CTE);
15824 
15825  if (union_node->node_type == PT_CTE)
15826  {
15827  /* A CTE is a union between the non_recursive and recursive parts */
15828  return STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_NOTHING;
15829  }
15830 
15831  arg1 = union_node->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
15832  arg2 = union_node->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
15833 
15834  arg1_is_null = pt_false_where (parser, arg1);
15835  arg2_is_null = pt_false_where (parser, arg2);
15836 
15837  if (!arg1_is_null && !arg2_is_null)
15838  {
15839  /* nothing to fold at this moment. */
15840  fold_as = STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_NOTHING;
15841  }
15842  else if (arg1_is_null && arg2_is_null)
15843  {
15844  /* fold the entire node as null */
15845  fold_as = STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_NULL;
15846  }
15847  else if (arg1_is_null && !arg2_is_null)
15848  {
15849  if (union_node->node_type == PT_UNION)
15850  {
15851  fold_as = STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG2;
15852  }
15853  else
15854  {
15855  fold_as = STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_NULL;
15856  }
15857  }
15858  else
15859  {
15860  assert (!arg1_is_null && arg2_is_null);
15861 
15862  if (union_node->node_type == PT_UNION || union_node->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE)
15863  {
15864  fold_as = STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG1;
15865  }
15866  else
15867  {
15868  assert (union_node->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION);
15869  fold_as = STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_NULL;
15870  }
15871  }
15872 
15873  /* check if folding would require merging WITH clauses; in this case we give up folding */
15874  if (fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG1 || fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG2)
15875  {
15876  PT_NODE *active = (fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG1 ? arg1 : arg2);
15877 
15878  if (PT_IS_QUERY_NODE_TYPE (active->node_type) && active->info.query.with != NULL
15879  && union_node->info.query.with != NULL)
15880  {
15881  fold_as = STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_NOTHING;
15882  }
15883  }
15884 
15885  return fold_as;
15886 }
15887 
15888 /*
15889  * pt_fold_union - fold union node following indicated method
15890  *
15891  * return : union node folded
15892  * parser (in) : Parser context.
15893  * union_node (in) : Union node.
15894  * fold_as (in) : indicated folding method
15895  */
15896 PT_NODE *
15897 pt_fold_union (PARSER_CONTEXT * parser, PT_NODE * union_node, STATEMENT_SET_FOLD fold_as)
15898 {
15899  PT_NODE *arg1, *arg2, *new_node, *next;
15900  int line, column;
15901  const char *alias_print;
15902 
15903  assert (union_node->node_type == PT_UNION || union_node->node_type == PT_INTERSECTION
15904  || union_node->node_type == PT_DIFFERENCE);
15905 
15906  arg1 = union_node->info.query.q.union_.arg1;
15907  arg2 = union_node->info.query.q.union_.arg2;
15908 
15909  line = union_node->line_number;
15910  column = union_node->column_number;
15911  alias_print = union_node->alias_print;
15912  next = union_node->next;
15913  union_node->next = NULL;
15914 
15915  if (fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_NULL)
15916  {
15917  /* fold the statement set as null, we don't need to fold orderby clause because we return null. */
15918  parser_free_tree (parser, union_node);
15919  new_node = parser_new_node (parser, PT_VALUE);
15920  new_node->type_enum = PT_TYPE_NULL;
15921  }
15922  else if (fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG1 || fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG2)
15923  {
15924  PT_NODE *active;
15925  PT_NODE *union_orderby, *union_orderby_for, *union_limit, *union_with_clause;
15926  unsigned int union_rewrite_limit;
15927 
15928  if (fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG1)
15929  {
15930  active = arg1;
15931  }
15932  else
15933  {
15934  active = arg2;
15935  }
15936 
15937  /* to save union's orderby or limit clause to arg1 or arg2 */
15938  union_orderby = union_node->info.query.order_by;
15939  union_orderby_for = union_node->info.query.orderby_for;
15940  union_limit = union_node->info.query.limit;
15941  union_rewrite_limit = union_node->info.query.rewrite_limit;
15942  union_with_clause = union_node->info.query.with;
15943 
15944  /* When active node has a limit or orderby_for clause and union node has a limit or ORDERBY clause, need a
15945  * derived table to keep both conflicting clauses. When a subquery has orderby clause without
15946  * limit/orderby_for, it may be ignored for meaningless cases. */
15947  if ((active->info.query.limit || active->info.query.orderby_for) && (union_limit || union_orderby))
15948  {
15949  PT_NODE *derived;
15950 
15951  derived = mq_rewrite_query_as_derived (parser, active);
15952  if (derived == NULL)
15953  {
15954  assert (pt_has_error (parser));
15955  return NULL;
15956  }
15957 
15958  new_node = derived;
15959  }
15960  else
15961  {
15962  /* just use active node */
15963  new_node = active;
15964  }
15965 
15966  /* unlink and free union node */
15967  union_node->info.query.order_by = NULL;
15968  union_node->info.query.orderby_for = NULL;
15969  union_node->info.query.limit = NULL;
15970  if (fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_AS_ARG1)
15971  {
15972  union_node->info.query.q.union_.arg1 = NULL; /* to save arg1 to fold */
15973  }
15974  else
15975  {
15976  union_node->info.query.q.union_.arg2 = NULL; /* to save arg2 to fold */
15977  }
15978  union_node->info.query.with = NULL;
15979 
15980  parser_free_tree (parser, union_node);
15981 
15982  /* to fold the query with remaining parts */
15983  if (union_orderby != NULL)
15984  {
15985  new_node->info.query.order_by = union_orderby;
15986  new_node->info.query.orderby_for = union_orderby_for;
15987  }
15988  if (union_limit != NULL)
15989  {
15990  new_node->info.query.limit = union_limit;
15991  new_node->info.query.rewrite_limit = union_rewrite_limit;
15992  }
15993  if (union_with_clause)
15994  {
15995  assert (new_node->info.query.with == NULL);
15996  new_node->info.query.with = union_with_clause;
15997  }
15998 
15999  /* check the union's orderby or limit clause if present */
16000  pt_check_order_by (parser, new_node);
16001  }
16002  else
16003  {
16004  assert (fold_as == STATEMENT_SET_FOLD_NOTHING);
16005 
16006  /* do nothing */
16007  new_node = union_node;
16008  }
16009 
16010  new_node->line_number = line;
16011  new_node->column_number = column;
16012  new_node->alias_print = alias_print;
16013  new_node->next = next;
16014 
16015  return new_node;
16016 }
